(271, 'Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016', '', 'Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016: Innovate. Invest. Impact. Integrate', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Sankalp%20SE%20Asia%20Summit%202016.jpg\" style=\"height:378px; width:380px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016, platform multi-stakeholder kewirausahaan sosial terbesar di Asia Tenggara akan kembali digelar untuk kedua kalinya di Indonesia. Menyadari peran penting dari perusahaan sosial di ASEAN, Summit ini akan diselenggarakan pada 25 &ndash; 26 Oktober 2016 di Hotel Bidakara, Jakarta, bertujuan untuk membangun ekosistem yang lebih inklusif seiring dengan pesatnya pertumbuhan kewirausahaan sosial di Asia Tenggara, terutama Indonesia dengan semangat besarnya dalam membangun kewirausahaan. Summit ini diselenggarakan oleh Sankalp Forum, sebuah inisiatif dari Intellecap Advisory Services yang berbasis di India dan Kenya yang telah aktif menunjukkan komitmen jangka panjang dalam membangun koridor kewirausahaan sosial di India, Afrika, dan Asia Tenggara, di mana diproyeksikan mempunyai iklim investasi yang kuat.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Sankalp Summit akan berfokus pada tiga hal: Pengetahuan, Modal dan Jaringan&mdash;jaringan untuk berkolaborasi, akses ke modal, pengetahuan dan bimbingan untuk para peserta, karena hal ini merupakan fondasi dasar bagi UKM di daerah-daerah&mdash;khususnya Indonesia, dengan keunikannya dan ekosistem kewirausahaan yang semakin berkembang.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Edisi ke-2 Sankalp Summit di Asia Tenggara ini bertujuan menemukan strategi-strategi baru untuk <strong>innovate, invest, integrate and impact. </strong>Acara ini akan mempertemukan lebih dari 500 pemangku kepentingan dari berbagai wilayah termasuk 10+ finalis dari Southeast Asia Awards yang akan diselenggarakan bersamaan dengan Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016, dengan menghadirkan pameran 20+ booth, 30+ sesi acara, 40+ speaker yang berpengalaman dalam inovasi dan investasi produk atau jasa yang memiliki dampak positif pada ekosistem kewirausahaan sosial di wilayah tersebut. Di summit ini, berbagai pemangku kepentingan akan membahas topik pembangunan ekonomi dan inovasi yang terpimpin dan bagaimana mereka bersama-sama dapat mencapai tujuan pertumbuhan yang inklusif. Tahun ini, Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016 berfokus pada sektor: air, kesehatan, inklusi keuangan, pertanian, dan pendidikan.</p>\n\n<p>Daftar sekarang dan <strong>dapatkan diskon 50% untuk kategori tiket non-enterprise khusus</strong> untuk rekan-rekan pengurus dan anggota Filantropi Indonesia.</p>\n', 'b2d89901602b0b6efde9241c42b9fb34.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-10-24 04:01:17', '2016-10-26 09:51:57', 5, 'sankalp-southeast-asia-summit-2016', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'vlb0IzfWgf88hKm', 'N', '', '', '2016-10-25 00:00:00', '2016-10-26 23:59:59'),
(272, 'Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016', '', 'Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016: Innovate. Invest. Impact. Integrate', '<pre>\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Sankalp%20SE%20Asia%20Summit%202016%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:378px; width:380px\" />\nJoin us at the 2nd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2016 in Indonesia at Hotel Bidakara, Jakarta (See location below). Sankalp Forum is the leading common-action platform for entrepreneurship and innovation. In continuation to the inaugural Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2015, the 2nd edition of the Summit aims to connect entrepreneurs from the region with investors, corporates, service providers, enablers and policy makers, to facilitate their growth strategies.   \n\nThis is an exciting time for innovation, entrepreneurship and inclusive growth in Southeast Asia region. All set on the path of market integration, the region is poised for growth led by technology, financial integration and physical connectivity. The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) countries&ndash; Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, and Vietnam, viewed as a single entity, would rank as the world&rsquo;s seventh-largest economy and home to more than 600 million people. The region is at a critical juncture with the formation of the ASEAN Economic Community (AEC).  \n\nSoutheast Asia projects a strong investment climate &ndash; macro strategies like ASEAN and AEC ushering in a single economic market will allow free movement of goods, services, skilled labor, and capital, which are expected to boost investments, create jobs and increase incomes. The number of consuming households in ASEAN is expected nearly double by 2025, with around 40 percent of the population in the low and low-middle income groups. This demographic shift and the opportunities it presents indicate a blurring of lines between mainstream businesses and those targeted towards social impact, where Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (SMEs) will have to innovate with solutions to ensure inclusive growth.   \n\nThe journey promises to be eventful as the region attempts to leverage its diversity in culture and political structures to build a common institutional fabric by bringing down non-tariff barriers, structuring labor movement, bridging the development divide between the economically advanced ASEAN six and the four newer countries. The AEC can potentially boost the region&rsquo;s growth from 5.4 percent (2004 to 2014) to 7.1 percent (2016 to 2025).  \n\nEntrepreneurs and SMEs already play a huge role in the region. Networks for collaboration, access to capital, knowledge and mentorship will form the basic building blocks of SME growth in the region. At the ecosystem level, new players will emerge while existing catalysts will have to rethink their capacity building strategies to ensure that entrepreneurs and SMEs scale up.   \n\nThe 2nd edition of Sankalp Summit in Southeast Asia aims at discovering these new strategies to innovate, invest, integrate and impact. It will connect entrepreneurs, investors, corporates and policy makers towards unlikely alliances and collaborations in the region. At the summit, these diverse stakeholders will deliberate on the building blocks of an integrated and innovation-led economy and how they can together achieve the goal of inclusive growth. The three pillars driving these conversations will be Knowledge, Capital and Networks.</pre>\n', 'b2d89901602b0b6efde9241c42b9fb34.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-10-24 04:01:17', '2016-10-26 09:51:57', 5, 'sankalp-southeast-asia-summit-2016', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'vlb0IzfWgf88hKm', 'N', '', '', '2016-10-25 00:00:00', '2016-10-26 23:59:59'),
(273, 'Tampilan baru situs resmi Filantropi Indonesia', '', 'Perubahan baru situs Filantropi Indonesia', '<p>Filantropi Indonesia (FI) sekarang memiliki tampilan dan fitur-fitur baru pada situs resmi organisasi, <a href=\"http://www.filantropi-indonesia.org\">www.filantropi-indonesia.org</a>. Sebagai organisasi payung lembaga filantropi se-Indonesia, situs resmi Filantropi Indonesia bertujuan untuk menjadi wadah dan pusat informasi bagi anggota dan publik mengenai sektor filantropi. Selain itu sebagai asosiasi berbasis keanggotaan, situs baru ini memiliki laman khusus Anggota yang berisi profil masing-masing organisasi. Anggota pun dapat memiliki akses eksklusif pada laman Standar &amp; Pedoman di mana beberapa e-book, jurnal dan artikel lainnya hanya dapat di-download oleh anggota.</p>\n\n<p>Fitur tambahan lain adalah di halaman Beranda ada bagian khusus pemberitaan filantropi untuk Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (SDGs). Di situ ada berita dari mancanegara dan Indonesia, serta beberapa sumber informasi lainnya yang berguna bagi anggota dan publik terkait SDGs. Pengunjung situs juga dapat berlangganan e-newsletter FI, Kabar Filantropi, langsung dengan memasukkan alamat surat elektronik. Bagi organisasi yang ingin mendaftar jadi anggota juga langsung dapat menekan tombol Registrasi dan selanjutnya melakukan proses pendaftaran secara online.</p>\n\n<p>Harapan kami adalah dengan tampilan dan tambahan fitur-fitur baru ini, Filantropi Indonesia dapat melayani mitra, anggota dan publik di dalam maupun luar negeri dengan lebih baik lagi di dunia yang semakin terhubung secara online. Semua untuk kemandirian yang berkelanjutan bagi Indonesia.</p>\n', 'f759203829edf60e09a1f8df3d95ee18.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-10-26 03:25:29', '2018-02-19 14:10:11', 5, 'tampilan-baru-situs-resmi-filantropi-indonesia', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '0Z6YW47a0m5zoTq', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(274, 'A new look for the official website of Indonesia Philanthropy Association', '', 'Upgrade on Filantropi Indonesia website', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Indonesia Philanthropy Association (Filantropi Indonesia or FI) now has a new look and additional features on the official website of the organization: www.filantropi.or.id. As an umbrella organization encompassing philanthropic institutions in Indonesia, the official website of FI aims to be a hub and an information centre for members and the public on the philanthropy sector. As a membership-based association, the new site also has a special page that contains the Members profile. Members also have exclusive access to the Standards &amp; Guidelines page where some e-books, journals and other articles can be downloaded.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another feature now available is a special section for Philanthropy for Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) news. There is news from abroad and Indonesia, as well as several other useful sources of information for our members and the public on SDGs. Visitors can also subscribe to the e-newsletter,&nbsp;<em>Kabar Filantropi</em>&nbsp;or Philanthropy News, directly from the home page. For organizations that want to register as a member, they can also click on the registration button to undertake the registration process online.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With this new look and additional features, we hope to better serve our partners, members and the public at home and abroad in a world that is increasingly connected. Our mission remains the achievement of sustainable development for Indonesia and we hope this resource will facilitate a meaningful dialogue towards this goal.</p>\n', 'f759203829edf60e09a1f8df3d95ee18.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-10-26 03:25:30', '2018-02-19 14:10:11', 5, 'a-new-look-for-the-official-website-of-indonesia-philanthropy-association', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '0Z6YW47a0m5zoTq', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(285, 'UNDP - Philanthropy as an Emerging Contributor to Development Cooperation', '', '', '', 'a886bd67ef5fc44761774a680e68b264.png', '', 0, 'N', 'M', '2016-10-26 05:32:05', '2016-11-07 14:26:19', 5, 'undp-philanthropy-as-an-emerging-contributor-to-development-cooperation', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'UNDP_-_Philanthropy_as_an_Emerging_Contributor_to_Development_Cooperation.pdf', '', '', '', 'Jruio420ewi4uIU', 'EOiTOxnEXhqFbB1', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
