(318, 'Philanthropists are looking into start-ups', '', 'Bali, Indonesia CNN - The development startup in Indonesia is emerging. The industry is projected to be backed by funding from the generous philanthropic alias country.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali, Indonesia CNN</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The start-up culture in Indonesia is emerging. The industry is projected to be backed by funding from philanthropic organisations of from generous Indonesians themselves.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Chairman of the Executive Board of the Indonesian Philanthropy Association, Timotheus Lesmana, said philanthropy can act as venture capital for start-ups in need of funds.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Based on&nbsp;the amount of funds that is projected to be invested,&nbsp;philanthropy should be wise in managing it however: In 2014, the association recorded 12.5 trillion funds coming from philanthropy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;We want to change the concept of giving into investments that can make an impact. Many Indonesian philanthropists&nbsp;choose to give aid to other countries because they don&#39;t understand the concept of donating to a start-up well enough,&quot; said Timotheus to&nbsp;CNNIndonesia.com during&nbsp;the Start-up Pitch Day in Sanur, Bali.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is&nbsp;the duty of all philanthropic actors to encourage&nbsp;the generous to give and share. Just to illustrate, the Indonesian diaspora community in the United States managed to raise US $ 3 million in 2014.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With estimated per person donations amounting to IDR 320.000 per year, Timotheus was optimistic that the numbers could exceed&nbsp;the value of the amount collected from the Indonesian diaspora in the US.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Philanthropy is often synonymous with generous people who are in&nbsp;the elite group&nbsp;and&nbsp;like&nbsp;to give and want to change people for the better.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So far, the money collected has usually been used for the provision of social assistance for people in need.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;Donations often create dependence, we want the funds collected to be beneficial. To avoid misunderstanding, later there will be&nbsp;an option for donors who are willing to give the money&nbsp;to fund a start-up,&quot; he said.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Indonesia Philanthropy Association noted that there are three philanthropic focus groups in Indonesia, there are the family foundations, celebrity/conglomerate&nbsp;philanthropists, and corporate and community-based foundations.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In early October, Indonesia Philanthropy Association plans to start raising funds to support start-ups, particularly those who focus in&nbsp;art, culture, and performances.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;We saw very few people who were willing to give initial funding for graphic design and film production. Philanthropy is expected to be an alternative financing for start-ups&quot; he concluded.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Source:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.cnnindonesia.com/teknologi/20161107155412-185-170940/kaum-dermawan-mulai-lirik-startup/\">http://www.cnnindonesia.com/teknologi/20161107155412-185-170940/kaum-dermawan-mulai-lirik-startup/</a></p>\n', '6aedc205679a3d52d373b2c579162ef9.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-11-08 08:15:31', '2018-02-23 09:47:51', 5, 'philanthropists-are-looking-into-start-ups', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '3OxZIEgKWc77DZG', 'N', '', 'CNNIndonesia.com', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(319, 'Eliminate Dengue Project Yogya ', '', 'Yayasan Tahija Memerangi Demam Berdarah secara Alami ala Eliminate Dengue Project Jogya', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Upaya pengendalian demam berdarah dengue (DBD) dengan menggunakan nyamuk <em>aedes aegypti</em> yang membawa bakteri <em>Wolbachia</em>, yang akan menahan perkembangan virus <em>dengue</em> di dalam tubuh nyamuk, kini diujicobakan di Kota Yogyakarta, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta (DIY).</p>\n\n<p>Penelitian ini dibiayai sepenuhnya oleh Yayasan Tahija sesuai dengan visi Yayasan untuk mewujudkan Indonesia yang lebih baik dengan membangun kemitraan untuk prakarsa yang berkesinambungan dalam bidang kesehatan masyarakat, pendidikan, kebudayaan, pelestarian lingkungan hidup dan pelayanan sosial.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Penelitian yang dimulai sejak 2011 direncanakan akan berlanjut hingga 2019. Metode penyebaran nyamuk ber-<em>Wolbachia</em> ini awalnya diterapkan dalam skala kecil di Kabupaten Sleman (Kronggahan dan Nogotirto) Januari &ndash; Juni 2014 dan Kabupaten Bantul (Jomblangan dan Singosaren) Desember 2014 &ndash; Mei 2015 menunjukkan hasil yang cukup memuaskan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pengalaman penelitian skala kecil di Sleman dan Bantul menunjukkan bahwa pada wilayah dimana jumlah <em>Wolbachia</em> sudah tinggi, mampu melindungi warga dari penularan lokal DBD.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Setelah pengujian dengan metode <em>Wolabchia</em> di Sleman dan Bantul menunjukkan hasil yang menjanjikan, maka penelitian dilanjutkan dalam skala yang lebih besar di kota Yogyakarta dimulai pada pertengahan tahun ini. &nbsp;Metode ini menjadi pelengkap upaya mencegah dan menanggulangi penularan DBD.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Peluncuran program ini di kota Yogyakarta ditandai dengan peletakan perdana ember berisi telur nyamuk <em>aedes aegypti</em> ber-<em>Wolbachia</em> di depan rumah warga di RT18/RW5 Keluruhan Tegalrejo oleh Dirjen Riset dan Pengembangan Kementrian Riset dan Teknologi Pendidikan Tinggi, Muhammad Dimyati dan Ketua Pembina Yayasan Tahija, Dr. Sjakon G. Tahija pada tanggal 31 Agustus 2016.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Peletakan ember perdana ini dilanjutkan dengan penitipan sekitar 1.000 ember mulai Agustus 2016. &nbsp;EDP-Yogya berencana menyebar sekitar 6.000 ember yang masing-masing berisi 100 telur nyamuk ber-<em>Wolbachia</em> di pemukiman warga secara bertahap sampai tahun 2017.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Diharapkan dalam kurun waktu tertentu, nyamuk ber-<em>Wolbachia</em> akan berkembang biak secara alami dengan nyamuk setempat dan menghasilkan keturunan ber-<em>Wolbachia</em> sehingga menghambat penularan virus DBD ke manusia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dirjen Penguatan Riset dan Pengembangan Kementrian Riset dan Teknologi Pendidikan Tinggi Republik Indonesia dalam sambutannya menilai bahwa pengujian metode <em>Wolbachia</em> merupakan inovasi untuk mencari upaya terbaik dalam menangani kasus DBD.&nbsp; Beliau juga mengapresiasi kontribusi Filantropi mengingat alokasi dana pemerintah untuk penelitian belum memadai sehingga memerlukan kerja sama dari berbagai pihak.</p>\n', 'fcc2d1b414c8cc40b96fce80f1adc561.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-11-11 03:06:25', '2018-02-23 09:47:04', 5, 'eliminate-dengue-project-yogya-', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'fc4Cq73lk4MEpz6', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Tahija', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(320, 'Eliminate Dengue Project – Yogyakarta', '', 'Tahija Foundation Fights Dengue Naturally ala Eliminate Dengue Project Jogya', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Efforts to control dengue haemorrhagic fever (DHF), with the help of&nbsp;<strong>Wolbachia</strong>, a common bacterium that stops the virus from replicating inside the mosquitoes that transmit the disease, are now being tested in the city of Yogyakarta Special Region (DIY).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This research was funded entirely by the Tahija Foundation in accordance with the Foundation&#39;s vision&nbsp;to achieve a&nbsp;better Indonesia by building partnerships for sustainable initiatives in the field of public health, education, culture, environmental protection and social services.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The study, which began in 2011 is planned to continue until 2019. The method for distributing mosquitoes carrying&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;was initially piloted on a small scale in Sleman (Kronggahan and Nogotirto) from January to June 2014, and Bantul (Jomblangan and Singosaren) from December 2014 - May 2015, have shown quite satisfactory results.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Small-scale research experience in Sleman and Bantul shows that in areas where the number of&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;is already high, it is able to protect the citizens from local dengue transmission.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After the test in Sleman and Bantul&nbsp;<em>Wolabchia</em>&nbsp;showed promising results, the study continued in a larger scale in the city of Yogyakarta which began in mid-year.&nbsp;This method complements efforts to prevent and combat the transmission of dengue.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The launch of this program in the city of Yogyakarta was marked by laying a bucket of&nbsp;<em>aedes aegypti</em>&nbsp;eggs carrying&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;in front of houses in RT18 / RW5 Kelurahan Tegalrejo by the Director General of Research and Development from the Ministry of Research, Technology and Higher Education, Muhammad Dimyati, and Chairman of the Tahija Foundation Trustees, Dr.&nbsp;Sjakon G. Tahija on August 31, 2016.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This launch was followed by depositing about 1,000 buckets of eggs from August 2016. EDP-Yogya plans to deploy about 6,000 buckets, each containing 100 eggs of&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;mosquitoes in residential areas gradually until 2017.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is expected that within a certain time,&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;mosquitoes will breed naturally with the local mosquito and&nbsp;produce&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;offspring thereby inhibiting dengue virus transmission to humans.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Directorate General of Research Strengthening and Development, from the Ministry of Research, Technology and Higher Education of the Republic of Indonesia said in a speech that testing the&nbsp;<em>Wolbachia</em>&nbsp;methods is an innovative approach in handling dengue cases.&nbsp;He also appreciated the contribution of Philanthropy considering that the allocation of government funds for research has not been adequate, requiring the cooperation of various parties.</p>\n', 'fcc2d1b414c8cc40b96fce80f1adc561.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-11-11 03:06:25', '2018-02-23 09:47:04', 5, 'eliminate-dengue-project-yogyakarta', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'fc4Cq73lk4MEpz6', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Tahija', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(325, 'Plan International Indonesia: Girls Leadership in Indonesia 2016', '', 'Laporan berupa video program \"Because I am a Girl\" 2016', '<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Rj_oxOpYiI&amp;feature=youtu.be\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Plan%20Intl%20Indonesia_IDG-Girl%202016%282%29.jpg\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></a></p>\n', '', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-11-11 04:11:30', '2016-11-11 11:11:30', 5, 'plan-international-indonesia-girls-leadership-in-indonesia-2016', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '9XsyP4BQ97EuD1y', 'N', '', 'Plan International Indonesia', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(326, 'Plan International Indonesia: Girls Leadership in Indonesia 2016', '', 'Video of \"Because I am a Girl\" program report', '<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Rj_oxOpYiI&amp;feature=youtu.be\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Plan%20Intl%20Indonesia_IDG-Girl%202016%283%29.jpg\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></a></p>\n', '', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-11-11 04:11:30', '2016-11-11 11:11:30', 5, 'plan-international-indonesia-girls-leadership-in-indonesia-2016', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '9XsyP4BQ97EuD1y', 'N', '', 'Plan International Indonesia', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(327, 'Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016', '', 'Laporan pelaksanaan Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016 yang telah sukses diselenggarakan untuk masyarakat yang berada di wilayah operasional PT. Adaro Indonesia sebagai wujud persaudaraan Adaro dan masyarakat sekitar. Festival Dangsanak Adaro tahun 2016, merupakan event tahunan CSR yang ketiga kalinya dilaksanakan oleh CSR Adaro Grup dan Komunitas Dangsanak Adaro.\n', '<p>&ldquo;<em>Wan Dangsanak Gawi Sabumi Maharung Banua</em>.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Bersama Saudara Bergotong Royong Memelihara Banua.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kalimat di atas merupakan <em>tagline</em> acara Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016. Festival Dangsanak Adaro merupakan kegiatan yang dipersembahkan untuk masyarakat yang berada di wilayah operasional PT. Adaro Indonesia sebagai wujud persaudaraan Adaro dengan masyarakat sekitar.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tujuan dari acara yang sudah ketiga kalinya diadakan ini adalah <em>pertama</em>, untuk memperkuat ikatan persaudaraan Adaro dengan masyarakat di wilayah operasional PT. Adaro Indonesia. <em>Kedua</em>, untuk meningkatkan wawasan dan partisipasi masyarakat dalam program pemberdayaan masyarakat dengan fokus utama pada bidang lingkungan melalui kampanye <em>Reduce, Reuse dan Recycle </em>(3R). <em>Ketiga,</em> untuk mempublikasikan hasil karya mitra binaan <em>Corporate Social Responsibility</em> (CSR) PT. Adaro Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Festival yang berlangsung dari tanggal 30 Oktober sampai 4 November 2016 ini mengambil tema tentang lingkungan. Tema lingkungan dipilih karena sesuai dengan perhatian dan sasaran CSR dan QHSE PT. Adaro Indonesia selama ini.&nbsp; Sejalan dengan tema yang dipilih, Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016 diawali dengan Clean Up Tabalong Day (CUTD), yaitu kegiatan yang mengajak masyarakat kabupaten Tabalong dan sekitarnya untuk terjun langsung ke lingkungan tempat tinggal dan melakukan aksi kebersihan dalam satu hari.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai sebuah acara kolaborasi, Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016 melibatkan berbagai pihak, seperti jajaran staf PT. Adaro Indonesia, pemerintah daerah kabupaten Tabalong, komunitas setempat, relawan, dan mitra pendukung acara. Keterlibatan dan kolaborasi berbagai pihak terlihat dari semaraknya rangkaian acara mulai dari pembukaan, acara inti, sampai penutupan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara pembukaan Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016 berlangsung pada tanggal 30 Oktober 2016. Pembukaan dimulai dengan acara teatrikal persembahan siswa-siswa SMK N 1 Murungpudak. Dilanjutkan dengan acara peresmian yang dipimpin oleh manajemen Adaro dan&nbsp; Bupati Tabalong.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai sebuah festival, Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016, mempunyai berbagai rangkaian acara dengan mengusung tema lingkungan, pendidikan, ekonomi, kesehatan, dan sosial budaya.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara puncak program lingkungan diisi oleh sekolah-sekolah Adiwiyata binaan CSR PT. Adaro Indonesia.<br />\nDengan tema 3R <em>Care </em>(<em>Reduce, Reuse </em>dan<em> Recycle</em>), acara ini dikemas dalam bentuk kampanye ramah lingkungan seperti program pengolahan sampah menjadi berkah, pantomim dan <em>mural art competition</em>.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara puncak bidang pendidikan digelar dengan penyelenggaraan Olimpiade Proyek Sains<br />\ntingkat SD dan SMP se-Kalselteng di Gedung Informasi Tanjung. Dalam acara ini juga, berbagai hasil proyek sains siswa dipamerkan kepada pengunjung. Selain itu, ada juga atraksi permainan sains yang dipersembahkan oleh guru-guru dari Kelas Lentera.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara puncak program ekonomi dengan tema <em>Agribisnis Day</em> dikemas dalam bentuk Kelompencapir dengan sasaran seluruh mitra binaan dari program CSR ekonomi Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri (YABN). Acara Kelompencapir diisi dengan cerdas cermat dan permainan <em>team building</em>. Sebagai motivasi, dalam acara ini ditayangkan video yang menceritakan <em>success story</em> petani karet yang berhasil melakukan panen perdana hasil binaan YABN.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara puncak program kesehatan diselenggarakan dengan tema <em>STBM Awards</em>, yaitu penyerahan penghargaan terhadap desa ODF terbaik. Acara dibuka dengan persembahan hiburan dari kader-kader STBM. Acara dilanjutkan dengan deklarasi ODF yang diikuti seluruh desa yang berhasil ODF dan &nbsp;penyerahan piagam.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sedangkan, &ldquo;Tutus Adat Maruwat Adat Yang Tersisa&rdquo; merupakan acara puncak program sosial budaya yang menampilkan <em>History and Success Story </em>PT. Adaro Indonesia selama ini dalam membina hubungan baik dengan masyarakat Dayak, baik yang berada di Kabupaten Tabalong maupun Kabupaten Balangan.<br />\nSeluruh hasil karya berupa kesenian dan bentuk pembinaan yang ditujukan kepada para tamu undangan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Demikian kilasan acara Festival Dangsanak Adaro yang berlangsung selama enam hari. Dengan adanya festival maupun rangkaian acara yang mengikutinya, termasuk penyelenggaraan pameran, PT. Adaro Indonesia berharap acara ini dapat terus rutin diselenggarakan setiap tahun serta menjadi ajang ruang kolaborasi antara berbagai pihak yang mendukung keberadaan PT. Adaro Indonesia di daerah operasinya.</p>\n', '59edd0f0c674d73844be34599733fc61.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', '', '2016-11-14 05:55:16', '2018-02-23 09:46:00', 5, 'festival-dangsanak-adaro-2016', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'O4sLmeTyrlSir7L', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(328, 'Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016', '', 'The report of Dangsanak Adaro Festival 2016 that has been successfully held for the communities in the operational area of PT Adaro Indonesia as an expression of unity with the communities. Dangsanak Adaro Festival is an annual event, and 2016 marks the third time of the event presented by the Adaro Group CSR and Dangsanak Adaro Community.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>&quot;Wan Dangsanak Gawi sabumi Maharung BANUA.&quot;</em></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;Together we work side by side to maintain Banua&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The above sentence is the&nbsp;tagline&nbsp;of Dangsanak Adaro Festival 2016, the third in its history. Dangsanak Adaro Festival is an event dedicated to the public involved in the operation areas of PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia, as an engagement with the surrounding community.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The purpose of the event is, firstly,&nbsp;to strengthen the bonds of brotherhood between Adaro and the community in PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia&rsquo;s areas of operations.&nbsp;Secondly,&nbsp;to improve the knowledge and participation of the community in community development programs with a primary focus on the environment through the campaign&nbsp;Reduce, Reuse and Recycle (3R).&nbsp;Finally, the event seeks to publicize PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia&rsquo;s partner institutions engaged in Corporate Social Responsibility&nbsp;(CSR) programs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The festival was held from the 30<sup>th</sup> of October until the 4<sup>th</sup> of November 2016 with an environmental theme.&nbsp;Environment was chosen because it is in accordance with the CSR and QHSE concerns held by PT. Adaro Indonesia.&nbsp; Dangsanak Adaro Festival 2016 began with a Clean Up Tabalong Day (CUTD), an activity which invited the public of Tabalong and its surrounding counties to go out and work together to clean-up their local environment.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As a collaborative event, Dangsanak Adaro Festival 2016 also involved various other parties, such as the staff of PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia, the district government of Tabalong, local communities, volunteers, and supporters of the event.&nbsp;The involvement and collaboration of various parties can be seen from the festivity of the events ranging from the opening, peak events, until closing.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dangsanak Adaro Festival opening ceremony in 2016 took place on the 30<sup>th</sup> of October. The opening ceremony began with a theatrical performance by students of SMKN 1 Murungpudak.&nbsp;Following this was the inauguration address led by Adaro management and the governor of Tabalong.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Festival Dangsanak Adaro 2016 had a variety of individual events with specific themes such as environment, education, economy, health, and social culture.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main event for the environmental program was presented by Adiwiyata schools under PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia CSR program.&nbsp;With the theme 3R&nbsp;Care&nbsp;(Reduce, Reuse&nbsp;and&nbsp;Recycle)<em>,</em>&nbsp;the event was held in the form of environmentally friendly campaigns such as waste management programs, and pantomime and&nbsp;mural art competitions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main event for the education portion was the Science Project Olympics for both primary and junior high school level in the Kalselteng region, taking place in the Informasi Tanjung Building.&nbsp;At this event, a variety of student science projects were on display to visitors.&nbsp;In addition, there were also numerous science games presented by the teachers of Kelas Lentera.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main event of the economics program with the theme of&nbsp;Agribusiness Day&nbsp;was delivered in the form Kelompencapir (complexes) targeting the CSR economy program partners of Adaro Bangun Negeri Foundation (YABN).&nbsp;At the Kelompencapir event there were quizzes and&nbsp;team building&nbsp;games.&nbsp;They also aired a video that detailed the&nbsp;success story&nbsp;of rubber farmers who successfully had their first harvest under YABN&rsquo;s program.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main event for the health program was the&nbsp;Community-Based Total Sanitation (STBM) Awards<em>,</em>&nbsp;which awarded the best open defecation free (ODF) villages.&nbsp;The event was opened by entertainment offerings from STBM teams.&nbsp;The event was followed by the declaration of ODF followed by all successful ODF villages and awarding of the certificate.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Meanwhile, &quot;Tutus Maruwat &ndash; The Remaining Indigenous Culture&quot; is the peak of the social and cultural programs featuring&nbsp;the history and success story&nbsp;of PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia, who has been fostering good relations with the Dayak community, located in both Tabalong and Balangan. The results of all the art and development works were on display for the invited guests.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Those are just some of the highlights of Dangsanak Adaro Festival.&nbsp;Through this festival, as well as the series of events that followed, PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia hopes that the event will continue to be held regularly every year, as well as continue to exist as a collaboration arena between the various parties that support the existence of PT.&nbsp;Adaro Indonesia in its areas of operations.</p>\n', '59edd0f0c674d73844be34599733fc61.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', '', '2016-11-14 05:55:17', '2018-02-23 09:46:00', 5, 'festival-dangsanak-adaro-2016', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'O4sLmeTyrlSir7L', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
