(357, '[Event] Expert Group Meeting on Developing Partnerships for SDGs – Asia and Pacific', '', 'Laporan pelaksanaan pertemuan tingkat Asia Pasifik mengenai kemitraan, dalam rangka United Nations Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) SDG Week', '<p>Divisi Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (Division of Sustainable Development) dari United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs (UN-DESA) mengadakan Pertemuan Kelompok Ahli yang membahas tentang &ldquo;<em>Mengembangkan Kemitraaan untuk mendukung peninjauan Forum Politis Level Tinggi &ndash; Asia dan Pasifik</em>&rdquo;, pada hari Senin, 28 November 2016 yang lalu di United Nations Conference Centre, Bangkok, Thailand.</p>\n\n<p>Pertemuan ini termasuk dalam rangkaian United Nations Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) SDG Week, yang berlangsung dari tanggal 28 November &ndash; 2 Desember. Filantropi Indonesia mendapat undangan sebagai aktor dari sektor swasta di Indonesia yang aktif melakukan dan mendorong kemitraan antar sektor untuk pencapaian SDGs. Pertemuan ini mengundang juga perwakilan dari berbagai sektor dan bidang, termasuk akademisi, lembaga PBB, pemerintahan, dan NGO. Tujuannya adalah untuk melihat berbagai elemen dari kemitraan, menelaah model kemitraan yang sukses, serta tantangan-tantangan dari tahapan pengembangan kemitraan.</p>\n\n<p>Struktur dari pertemuan dibagi menjadi empat sesi yang saling berkaitan, di tiap sesi ada panelis pembicara yang membagikan pengalaman mereka di bidang dan organisasi masing-masing tentang kemitraan untuk SDGs. Setelah itu ada diskusi interaktif untuk membahas isu-isu yang dibahas dengan lebih dalam dari para peserta yang lain.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Sesi 1 &ndash; Pendekatan inovatif dari kemitraan dalam menjalankan SDGs</h2>\n\n<p>Dalam sesi ini pembicara dan peserta forum diajak untuk melihat beberapa pendekatan kemitraan yang sudah ada, yang sedang bertumbuh dan inovatif menuju pencapaian tujuan pembangunan berkelanjutan. Ada lima pembicara dan diskusi sesi dipimpin oleh moderator. Dari diskusi di sesi ini peserta pertemuan membahas beberapa temuan dan tantangan ke depan mengenai model kemitraan antar sektor: Bahwa kemitraan memiliki peran sebagai <em>conveyor role</em> yang menhubungkan antar titik atau aktor yang memiliki tujuan dan visi yang sama, kemitraan harus memberdayakan komunitas yang ingin dibangun, perlu ada insentif untuk pihak-pihak yang menjadi pelopor kemitraan di bidang masing-masing (seperti hibah atau sistem penghargaan), dan penekanan akan peran iptek dalam membentuk kemitraan justru dapat berdampak buruk terhadap prinsip &ldquo;leaving no one behind&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Sesi 2 - Model tata kelola kemitraan, akuntabilitas dan keterlibatan pemangku kepentingan</h2>\n\n<p>Sesi kedua pada hari itu berbicara mengenai bermacam-macam model tata kelola kemitraan, termasuk bagaimana melibatkan pemangku kepentingan dari beragam perspektif dengan cara-cara yang efektif. Beberapa pembicara menyampaikan tantangan dan isu yang hampir sama mengenai topik ini, yaitu isu kepercayaan dan minimnya keterlibatan pihak penerima bantuan. Dipercaya bahwa agar kemitraan antar sektor dan pemangku kepentingan dapat berjalan baik, harus ada pendekatan inklusif, komunikasi yang terbuka, serta komitmen dari semua pihak. Dengan adanya kepercayaan dari pihak pemerintah, swasta maupun masyarakat sipil, maka bentuk <em>governance</em> (tata kelola) bagi kemitraan yang ideal dapat tercipta. Selain itu, kemitraan juga harus berani merangkul kontradiksi yang akan muncul dan bisa mengatasi ketimpangan kekuatan antar pemangku kepentingan.</p>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Sesi 3 &ndash; Lingkungan yang kondusif di tingkat nasional untuk membina kemitraan yang efektif</h2>\n\n<p>Setelah makan siang dan istirahat, peserta kembali mengikuti sesi ketiga di hari itu, mengenai lingkungan yang kondusif untuk kemitraan di suatu negara dapat tumbuh subur dan terjalin erat antar sektor. Dalam sesi kali ini diharapkan dapat terungkap aspek-aspek eksternal apa saja yang mendukung kemitraan dan apa yang justru menghambatnya. Faktor penting untuk menciptakan lingkungan yang kondusif adalah <em>national ownership</em> atau sejauh mana pemerintah di negara tersebut merasa bahwa SDGs adalah agenda nasional. Lalu pentingnya keselarasan dengan program pembangunan pemerintah, ketersediaan data, keterlibatan masyarakat lokal, serta perencanaan yang strategis. Tiap negara memiliki kondisi sosial, ekonomi dan politik yang berbeda, karena itu tantangan selanjutnya adalah agar pemerintah maupun swasta untuk tidak &ldquo;pilih kasih&rdquo; terhadap bidang-bidang yang tidak banyak pelakunya (seperti tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan nomor 10 dan 16).</p>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">Sesi 4 &ndash; Keterlibatan kemitraan dengan 2030 Agenda tindak lanjut dan review proses</h2>\n\n<p>Sesi penutup dalam pertemuan ini memberikan gambaran dari perwakilan pemerintah serta praktisi kemitraan untuk meningkatkan dialog agar kemitraan lintas sektor dapat berkontribusi dan terlibat dalam pembahasan perencanaan pembangunan di tingkat nasional, regional maupun internasional. Sesi ini terkait pelaksanaan High-level Political Forum tentang SDG pada pertengahan tahun 2017 yang akan datang, untuk memberikan masukan dan rekomendasi terhadap forum tersebut. Dalam bahasan topik ini, terungkap bahwa setelah melewati tahun pertama pelaksanaan SDG, masih banyak pekerjaan rumah yang harus dikerjakan. Salah satunya sinergi antara aktor besar, seperti lembaga bantuan internasional (ODA), sektor swasta, dan pemerintah dengan organisasi masyarakat sipil dan penerima bantuan.</p>\n', '0b8434e1374ba9eec00ed7a81b8fe014.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-07 09:15:36', '2018-02-19 14:42:12', 5, '-event-expert-group-meeting-on-developing-partnerships-for-sdgs-asia-and-pacific', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'K15QtpdXIge2wg4', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(358, '[Event] Expert Group Meeting on Developing Partnerships for SDGs – Asia and Pacific', '', 'Report on Asia-Pacific level meeting about partnerships, during the United Nations Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) SDG Week', '<p>The Division of Sustainable Development of United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs (UN-DESA) organized a Group Meeting with the theme of&nbsp;<em>&ldquo;Developing Partnerships for the Sustainable Development Goals in support of the reviews of the High-level Political Forum - Asia and Pacific&quot;,</em>&nbsp;on 28<sup>th</sup> November 2016 at the United Nations Conference Centre, Bangkok, Thailand.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting was a part of the United Nations Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific&rsquo;s (ESCAP) SDG Week, which ran from November 28<sup>th</sup> to December 2<sup>nd</sup>. The&nbsp;Indonesia Philanthropy Association was invited to represent the private sector in Indonesia who are actively engaged in fostering multi-sector partnerships to aid in achieving the SDGs.&nbsp;This meeting also included representatives from various other sectors, including academia, UN agencies, governments, and NGOs.&nbsp;The aim was to look at the various elements of the partnership, to examine successful models, and to identify challenges in different phases of a partnership.</p>\n\n<p>The full day meeting included four interrelated sessions, with each session comprised of a panellist of 5-6 speakers who shared their organisation&rsquo;s experiences in SDG partnerships.&nbsp;Following the presentations, there was an interactive discussion led by a moderator to discuss the issues raised within the forum.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2><strong><em>Session 1 - The innovative approach of partnership in running the SDGs</em></strong></h2>\n\n<p>In this session, speakers and participants of the forum looked at some of the existing and emerging approaches to partnerships supporting the achievement of the sustainable development goals.&nbsp; From this session, participants discussed some findings and challenges ahead regarding specific models of partnership across sectors. The most important considerations discussed were the &ldquo;conveyor role&rdquo;&nbsp;of partnerships which connects actors who share the same goal and vision, that partnerships should empower the individuals and communities involved, the necessity for incentivising parties to form pioneer partnership in their respective fields (such as grants or awards system), and the role of science and technology in forming a partnership if it could adversely affect the principle of &quot;leaving no one behind&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2><strong><em>Session 2 - Governance models of partnerships, accountability and stakeholder engagement</em></strong></h2>\n\n<p>The second session of the day discussed the various governance models shaping partnerships, including how to most effectively involve stakeholders and beneficiaries.&nbsp;Most speakers identified similar challenges and issues on this topic, for example the issue of trust and lack of beneficiaries&rsquo; involvement in the decision-making process.&nbsp;In order for multi-sector and multi-stakeholder partnerships to work well, there must be an inclusive approach, open communication, and commitment from all parties involved.&nbsp;With trust and confidence from the government, private sector and civil society, an ideal governance model for partnerships can be created.&nbsp;Additionally, partnership must be able to embrace contradictions that will emerge and overcome power inequalities between stakeholders.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2><strong><em>Session 3 &ndash; National enabling environment for fostering effective partnerships</em></strong></h2>\n\n<p>After lunch, the participants returned for the third session which discussed enabling conducive environments so that partnerships may flourish across sectors.&nbsp;In this session, it was expected to reveal which aspects support partnerships and which prevent their effective operation.&nbsp;One of the most important factors in creating an enabling environment is national ownership, or how governments incorporate SDGs into their national agenda.&nbsp;Also identified was the importance of alignment with government&#39;s development strategies, the availability of data, the involvement of local communities, and the need for strategic planning.&nbsp;Each country has a different social, economic and political context, which is why the next challenge for the government and private sectors is not to &quot;cherry-pick&quot; which SDGs or areas they want to support because there are some less glamourous goals such as SDG number 10 (equality between countries) and 16 (creating peaceful and inclusive societies).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2><strong><em>Session 4 - Partnership engagement with 2030 Agenda follow-up and review processes</em></strong></h2>\n\n<p>This last session of the meeting provided an overview from government representatives, as well as the partnership practitioners, aimed at fostering a dialogue on how multi-stakeholder partnerships can best contribute and engage in the national review process at the national, regional and global levels.&nbsp;This session included a brief look ahead at the upcoming High-level Political Forum centring around SDGs in mid-2017, especially to provide input and recommendation to the Forum.&nbsp;During the discussion, it was revealed that after the first year of SDGs implementation, there is still a lot of work&nbsp;to be done.&nbsp;One pressing goal is to create synergy between the big &ldquo;P&rdquo;, such as international aid agencies (ODA), the private sector, and the government, with the small &ldquo;p&rdquo; which includes civil society organizations and beneficiaries.</p>\n', '0b8434e1374ba9eec00ed7a81b8fe014.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-07 09:15:36', '2018-02-19 14:42:12', 5, '-event-expert-group-meeting-on-developing-partnerships-for-sdgs-asia-and-pacific', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'K15QtpdXIge2wg4', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(361, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 12', '', 'PLF ke-12 akan membahas mengenai berbagai upaya yang dilakukan lembaga filantropi untuk mengatasi beragam persoalan nutrisi di Indonesia dengan pendekatan program yang kreatif dan inovatif.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/PLF%2012%20poster.jpeg\" style=\"height:672px; width:480px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">PLF ke-12 akan membahas mengenai berbagai upaya yang dilakukan lembaga filantropi untuk mengatasi beragam persoalan nutrisi di Indonesia dengan pendekatan program yang kreatif dan inovatif.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nutrisi merupakan hal penting bagi manusia dan memiliki manfaat begitu banyak, tidak hanya bagi kesehatan tetapi juga terhadap perkembangan otak. Dalam masa pertumbuhannya, anak yang mengalami ketidakseimbangan nutrisi atau malnutrisi akan mengakibatkan&nbsp;disfungsi perkembangan.<br />\n<br />\nMalnutrisi sendiri merupakan permasalahan yang sangat kompleks bagi suatu bangsa. Ketidakmampuan untuk mengatasi isu malnutrisi akan berdampak besar bagi pertumbuhan ekonomi. Seseorang yang mengalami kekurangan nutrisi akan memiliki tingkat produktivitas dan penghasilan yang lebih rendah sehigga tidak akan mampu memberikan kontribusi bagi pertumbuhan ekonomi. Jika malnutrisi dialami penduduk dalam jumlah besar tentunya akan berpengaruh pada penurunan pendapatan negara.<br />\n<br />\nApabila dikaitkan dengan <em>Sustainable Developmet Goals</em> (SDGs), program peningkatan kesejahteraan global, maka penuntasan malnutrisi berkontribusi ke dalam 5 goals dari 17 goals, yaitu: Tanpa Kemiskinan, Tanpa Kelaparan, Kehidupan Sehat dan Sejahtera, Pendidikan Berkualitas, serta Kemitraan dalam menyelesaikan tantangan-tantangan bangsa terkait nutrisi.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nDalam tujuan untuk mengoptimalkan peran lembaga atau komunitas filantropi dalam pengentasan malnutrisi di Indonesia, maka Filantropi Indonesia menghadirkan&nbsp;<strong>Philanthropy Learning Forum ke-12&nbsp;</strong>dengan tema <strong>&ldquo;Peran Filantropi Dalam Penanganan Nutrisi Bangsa&rdquo; </strong>yang akan diadakan pada:</p>\n\n<p>Hari/tanggal &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: <strong>Selasa, 20 Desember</strong><strong> 2016</strong></p>\n\n<p>Pukul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : <strong>12.00 </strong><strong>&ndash; 1</strong><strong>6.00</strong> <strong>WIB&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tempat&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : <strong>Ruang Annex Building,&nbsp;Wisma Indocement lantai dasar, Jl. Jend. Sudirman Kav. 70-71, Jakarta Pusat</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Silakan buka tautan berikut untuk mendaftar:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/JY2qiL2ARwlB3Yrj2\">https://goo.gl/forms/JY2qiL2ARwlB3Yrj2</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong><u>KUOTA TERBATAS, pendaftaran akan ditutup saat jumlah peserta sudah memenuhi kuota</u></strong></span></p>\n', 'e3f2131c9c6ae23c73b0763555451ddc.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-08 04:32:48', '2016-12-16 15:49:53', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-12', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'nnS3jl7tEPrE3Ba', 'N', '', '', '2016-12-20 00:00:00', '2016-12-20 23:59:59'),
(362, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 12', '', 'The 12th PLF will discuss the various efforts from philanthropy organizations and actors to address various issues of nutrition in Indonesia with creative and innovative programs.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/PLF%2012%20poster%20EN.jpeg\" style=\"height:672px; width:480px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nutrition is important for humans and it has many benefits, not only for health but also for brain development. In infancy, children who experience malnutrition or nutritional imbalance will experience dysfunctional developments.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Malnutrition itself is a very complex problem on national level. The inability to address the issue of malnutrition will have a major impact on economic growth. Someone who lacks of&nbsp;nutrition&nbsp;will have a low level of productivity and lower income therefore he/she will not be able to contribute to economic growth. If malnutrition is experienced by a large number of people then it will&nbsp;certainly affect the decrease on national&nbsp;revenue.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When linked with the Sustainable Developmet Goals (SDGs), a global welfare improvement program, then the eradication of malnutrition contributes to 5 goals out of 17 goals, namely: No Poverty, Zero Hunger, Good Health and Well-being, Quality Education and Partnership for the Goals in solving nation challenges related to nutrition.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To optimize the role of philanthropy&nbsp;institutions and community to alleviate malnutrition in Indonesia, the Indonesian Philanthropy Association presents the 12th Philanthropy Learning Forum with the theme &quot;The Role of Philanthropy in&nbsp;Developing National Nutrition&quot; which will be held:</p>\n\n<p>Date &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : <strong>Tuesday, 20 December</strong><strong> 2016</strong></p>\n\n<p>Time &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : <strong>12.00 </strong><strong>&ndash; 1</strong><strong>6.00</strong> <strong>WIB&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Location&nbsp; : <strong>Annex Building,&nbsp;Wisma Indocement ground floor, Jl. Jend. Sudirman Kav. 70-71, Jakarta Pusat</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Please RSVP here:<strong>&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/JY2qiL2ARwlB3Yrj2\">https://goo.gl/forms/JY2qiL2ARwlB3Yrj2</a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><u><strong>LIMITED SEAT, we will close registration when we have reached the quota</strong></u></span></p>\n', 'e3f2131c9c6ae23c73b0763555451ddc.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-08 04:32:49', '2016-12-16 15:49:53', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-12', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'nnS3jl7tEPrE3Ba', 'N', '', '', '2016-12-20 00:00:00', '2016-12-20 23:59:59'),
(363, '[Siaran Pers] Aksi Kerelawanan di Indonesia Menuju Era Digital', '', 'Siaran pers dari launching bulan relawan nasional, yang diadakan pada Senin, 5 Desember 2016', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Empat puluh tujuh organisasi, dua startup berbasis teknologi dan perubahan sosial, serta dua sektor swasta bergabung bersama &ndash; sama meningkatkan kesadaran masyarakat akan kerelawanan, meluncurkan Bulan Relawan Nasional yang pertama di Indonesia. Bertepatan dengan Hari Relawan Internasional pada 5 Desember, rangkaian Bulan Relawan Nasional akan dimulai pada tanggal 5 Desember 2016 sampai 20 Desember 2016, menggabungkan kampanye digital dengan kegiatan &ndash; kegiatan kreatif yang mengajak masyarakat untuk menjadi bagian di dalamnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Inisiatif ini digagas oleh Tim Aksi Baik, yang terdiri dari 2 startup berbasis teknologi dan perubahan sosial (Campaign.com dan Indorelawan.org) dan komunitas Indonesian Future Leaders (IFL)</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ilman Dzikri, Programme Manager IFL mengatakan, &ldquo;Tujuan kami menginisiasi kegiatan ini yakni mengajak lebih banyak anak muda untuk melakukan kegiatan kerelawanan dan semoga mereka bisa melihat hal tersebut menjadi salah satu pilihan lain untuk pengembangan diri.&rdquo; &ldquo;Sebagai Negara yang didirikan berdasarkan nilai &ndash; nilai gotong royong, aksi kerelawanan merupakan kunci penting untuk merevitalisasi nilai &ndash; nilai zaman modern.&rdquo; Tambah Marsya Anggia Natashahta, Direktur Indorelawan.org.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rangkaian Bulan Relawan Nasional ini didukung oleh Kemenpora, Kemdikbud, Kemensos dan United Nations Volunteers Program (UNV). &ldquo;Relawan merupakan bagian penting untuk mengajak lebih banyak orang untuk terlibat dalam 17 tujuan pembangunan berkelanjutan di level masyarakat. Mereka adalah jembatan yang diperlukan antara komunitas dan masyarakat sebagaimana kontribusi mereka sangat penting dalam memenuhi tujuan &ndash; tujuan tersebut untuk Indonesia.&rdquo; Kata Perwakilan dari UNV Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Berdasarkan survei online yang diikuti oleh lebih dari 3000 responden di Indonesia pada bulan November 2016, salah satu alasan umum mengapa orang tidak melakukan aksi kerelawanan adalah kesulitan mereka untuk menemukan informasi dari organisasi terkait dan kegiatan yang dilakukannya. Selain itu, banyak juga responden yang merasa bahwa mereka tidak memiliki keahlian atau keterampilan yang sesuai dengan kegiatan kerelawanan yang akan dilakukan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Untuk mengatasi masalah tersebut, selama Bulan Relawan ini masyarakat dianjurkan mengunjungi pusat informasi di website (<a href=\"http://bulanrelawannasional.com/\">http://bulanrelawannasional.com/</a>) untuk mengetahui lebih banyak tentang aksi kerelawanan dan memilih berbagai macam kegiatan kerelawanan yang bisa mereka lakukan selama sebulan ini.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Melengkapi hal tersebut, masyarakat diminta untuk menandatangani janji online di change.org (<a href=\"http://change.org/bulanrelawannasional\">http://change.org/bulanrelawannasional</a>) dalam memberikan kontribusi waktu mereka untuk menciptakan aksi sosial yang lebih besar.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sebuah kampanye media sosial yang menargetkan anak muda, juga diluncurkan oleh Campaign.com (<a href=\"http://www.campaign.com/10JamAksiBaik\">http://www.campaign.com/10JamAksiBaik</a>), mendorong mereka untuk membagikan ide &ndash; ide apa saja yang akan mereka lakukan dengan waktu 10 jam di tahun 2017 untuk perubahan sosial dengan tagar #10JamAksiBaik.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;Ini adalah sebuah langkah yang sangat dibutuhkan untuk ke depannya, dimana startup berbasis teknologi dan kelompok masyarakat bersama &ndash; sama mendorong keterlibatan yang lebih besar dan merayakan kontribusi yang diberikan oleh relawan di Indonesia. Ini adalah contoh yang sangat baik dari apa yang bisa dicapai jika ada kemitraan yang setara antara sektor swasta dan public masyarakat,&rdquo; kata Benjamin Xue Chief Engagement Officer Campaign.com</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Untuk mengakhiri Bulan Relawan, sebuah Festival Relawan akan diadakan di bulan Desember. Acara tersebut akan menjadi acara gabungan yang terdiri dari talkshow, penghargaan kerelawanan dan booth yang menarik yang melibatkan berbagai organisasi masyarakat. Lebih lanjut mengenai acara tersebut akan diinformasikan kepada public dalam beberapa hari mendatang.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Untuk mendukung Bulan Relawan Nasional:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Website: http://bulanrelawannasional.com/</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Online pledge: http://change.org/bulanrelawannasional</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Campaign Page: http://www.campaign.com/10JamAksiBaik</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Officiall Hashtag: #BulanRelawanNasional #10JamAksiBaik</p>\n', '5d72ea9346f24f52b624a37b72421263.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-08 04:47:19', '2016-12-08 11:47:19', 5, '-siaran-pers-aksi-kerelawanan-di-indonesia-menuju-era-digital', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '3B1RY5ZryrUbEsw', 'N', '', 'Indorelawan, Campaign.com, Indonesi', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(364, '[Press Release] Volunteerism in Indonesia moves forward by going digital', '', 'Press release of the launching of national volunteer month on Monday, December 5 2016', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Forty seven organisations, two social change tech startups and two private sector companies have come together to raise awareness of volunteerism, launching Indonesia&rsquo;s first ever National Volunteer Month. Coinciding with World Volunteer Day on 5<sup>th</sup> December, National Volunteer Month will take place from 5 December 2016 to 20 December 2016, combining the dynamism of digital awareness with creative offline activities for the public to take part in.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This first &ndash; of &ndash; its &ndash; kind initiative is jointly organised by Team Aksi Baik, a collective of 2 social &ndash; good startups (Campaign.com and Indorelawan.org) with community group Indonesian Future Leaders (IFL).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ilman Dzikri, Programme Manager of IFL said &ldquo;Our aim in co &ndash; initiating this event is to invite more youths to be involved in volunteering activities and hopefully they can view it as an additional option for self &ndash; development.&rdquo; &ldquo;As a country Founded on values of mutual cooperation, volunteerism is a vital key to revitalizing the values of modern times.&rdquo; Added Marsya Anggia Nashahta, Director for Indorelawan.org</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The entire Volunteer Month is supported by Kemenpora, Kemdikbud, Kemensos and United Nations Volunteers Programme Indonesia (UNV). &ldquo;Volunteers are vital in engaging people to be involved with the various 17 sustainable development goals at a community level. They are the indispensable bridge between the community groups and public as their contributions are critical in meeting these goals for Indonesia,&rdquo; a representative from UNV Indonesia said.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During an online survey done by over 3000 respondents in Indonesia in November 2016, one of the common cited reasons why people do not volunteer their time was that it was hard to find relevant information about the respective organisations and their activities. To add to that difficulty, a lot of respondents feel that they do not have the appropriate expertise or skills when it came to volunteering.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To address these concerns and more, during this Volunteer Month the public are encouraged to visit a central information website (<a href=\"http://bulanrelawannasional.com/\">http://bulanrelawannasional.com/</a>) to find out more about volunteerism and choose a whole range of activities that they can volunteer in during this month.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Complementing it, the public are asked to sign an online pledge on change.org (<a href=\"http://change.org/bulanrelawannasional\">http://change.org/bulanrelawannasional</a>) to use their time for the create bigger social good.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A social media campaign, targeted at youths, have also been rolled aout by Campaign.com (<a href=\"http://www.campaign.com/10JamAksiBaik\">http://www.campaign.com/10JamAksiBaik</a>), encouraging them to share their ideas on what they will do with 10 hours in 2017 for social change with the hashtag #10JamAksiBaik.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;This is a much needed step forward with tech &ndash; startups and community groups coming together to push for a greater involvement and celebrate contributions by volunteers here in Indonesia. It is a very good example of what can be achieved if there is equal partnerships made between the private and public sector of society,&rdquo; said Benjamin Xue, Chief Engagement Officer of Campaign.com</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To cap off the exciting Volunteer Month, a Volunteer Festival will be held later in December. The event will be a mix of educational talks, an award ceremony and exciting booth spaces involving various community organisations. More details of the event will be shared with the public in the coming days.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To support National Volunteer Month:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Website: http://bulanrelawannasional.com/</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Online pledge: http://change.org/bulanrelawannasional</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Campaign Page: http://www.campaign.com/10JamAksiBaik</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Officiall Hashtag: #BulanRelawanNasional #10JamAksiBaik</p>\n', '5d72ea9346f24f52b624a37b72421263.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-08 04:47:22', '2016-12-08 11:47:19', 5, '-press-release-volunteerism-in-indonesia-moves-forward-by-going-digital', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '3B1RY5ZryrUbEsw', 'N', '', 'Indorelawan, Campaign.com, Indonesi', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(373, 'WINGS Forum 2017 ', '', 'WINGSForum, WINGS’ flagship event, brings together a globally diverse group of senior staff of philanthropy support organizations and leaders in philanthropy to share knowledge, network, and advance effective philanthropy worldwide.', '<p>WINGSForum, WINGS&rsquo; flagship event, brings together a globally diverse group of senior staff of philanthropy support organizations and leaders in philanthropy to share knowledge, network, and advance effective philanthropy worldwide.Held every three years, WINGSForum has become the premier event in the global philanthropy community. Focused on identifying new innovations in the sector, WINGSForum was designed as a peer learning experience where philanthropy leaders could share practical lessons and inspiration from their work.</p>\n\n<table style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>WINGSForum 2017 will provide an opportunity for reflection on the state of affairs in our field and on the dynamics of power, money and participation. Given the urgency of global crises and challenges to civil society, we must harness the potential of philanthropy, in all its diversity, for a more inclusive, equitable world. The upcoming forum will set the stage and provide an environment that helps facilitate, support, and encourage innovative and thoughtful discussions on recognising the potential to influence social change; challenging current models and practices of philanthropy; creating the conditions for philanthropy to thrive.WINGSForum 2017 will be held from 22-24 February 2017 in Mexico City at the Hilton Mexico City Reforma. A primary financial, political and cultural center of Latin America, Mexico City will be a wonderful backdrop for our global community of philanthropy influencers.</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Untuk informasi selengkapnya silakan buka website WINGS Forum 2017 di <a href=\"http://wingsforum.org/\">www.wingsforum.org</a></p>\n', '95b05371a7fffd30db4766f35f48a1fc.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-21 03:56:43', '2016-12-21 10:59:08', 5, 'wings-forum-2017-critical-philanthropy-addressing-complexity-challenging-ourselves-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'RZjuUJECOz0uJMf', 'N', '', '', '2017-02-22 00:00:00', '2017-02-24 23:59:59'),
(374, 'WINGS Forum 2017 ', '', 'WINGSForum, WINGS’ flagship event, brings together a globally diverse group of senior staff of philanthropy support organizations and leaders in philanthropy to share knowledge, network, and advance effective philanthropy worldwide.', '<p>WINGSForum, WINGS&rsquo; flagship event, brings together a globally diverse group of senior staff of philanthropy support organizations and leaders in philanthropy to share knowledge, network, and advance effective philanthropy worldwide.Held every three years, WINGSForum has become the premier event in the global philanthropy community. Focused on identifying new innovations in the sector, WINGSForum was designed as a peer learning experience where philanthropy leaders could share practical lessons and inspiration from their work.</p>\n\n<table style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>WINGSForum 2017 will provide an opportunity for reflection on the state of affairs in our field and on the dynamics of power, money and participation. Given the urgency of global crises and challenges to civil society, we must harness the potential of philanthropy, in all its diversity, for a more inclusive, equitable world. The upcoming forum will set the stage and provide an environment that helps facilitate, support, and encourage innovative and thoughtful discussions on recognising the potential to influence social change; challenging current models and practices of philanthropy; creating the conditions for philanthropy to thrive.WINGSForum 2017 will be held from 22-24 February 2017 in Mexico City at the Hilton Mexico City Reforma. A primary financial, political and cultural center of Latin America, Mexico City will be a wonderful backdrop for our global community of philanthropy influencers.</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>To read more about the WINGS Forum 2017, visit their official website <a href=\"http://wingsforum.org/\">www.wingsforum.org</a></p>\n', '95b05371a7fffd30db4766f35f48a1fc.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-21 03:56:43', '2016-12-21 10:59:08', 5, 'wings-forum-2017-critical-philanthropy-addressing-complexity-challenging-ourselves-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'RZjuUJECOz0uJMf', 'N', '', '', '2017-02-22 00:00:00', '2017-02-24 23:59:59'),
(375, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 13 ', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan Baznas untuk mengadakan seminar dan lokakarya mengenai zakat untuk pencapaian SDGs', '<h2><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/tcgFqO2VVrGwFtFF3\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20PLF%2013%281%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:991px; width:700px\" /></a></h2>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6suRU5yLVBrQUZMOFk?usp=sharing\">UNDUH MATERI PRESENTASI NARASUMBER</a></p>\n', '6fa681f072049900756d5c0cec27b1f7.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-22 08:32:32', '2017-01-27 14:13:16', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-13-zakat-on-sdgs-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'ue5mYyroc8A8jcJ', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-26 00:00:00', '2017-01-26 23:59:59'),
(376, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 13 ', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia together with Baznas will co-host a full day seminar and workshop about zakat on SDGs achievement', '<h2><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/tcgFqO2VVrGwFtFF3\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20PLF%2013%282%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:991px; width:700px\" /></a></h2>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6suRU5yLVBrQUZMOFk?usp=sharing\">DOWNLOAD PRESENTATION FROM SPEAKERS</a></p>\n', '6fa681f072049900756d5c0cec27b1f7.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-22 08:32:32', '2017-01-27 14:13:16', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-13-zakat-on-sdgs-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'ue5mYyroc8A8jcJ', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-26 00:00:00', '2017-01-26 23:59:59'),
(379, 'Kiprah Filantropi Indonesia Selama 2016 Diapresiasi Oleh Anggotanya', '', 'Tahun 2016 menjadi tahun di mana Filantropi Indonesia mengalami banyak perubahan dan penambahan aktivitas serta pencapaian.  ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada penghujung tahun, lebih tepatnya Selasa, 20 Desember 2016, Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan Rapat Umum Anggota yang merupakan agenda tahunan dengan tujuan sebagai pertanggungjawaban program yang telah dilaksanakan sepanjang tahun 2016, termasuk laporan keuangan dan pemaparan rencana program tahun 2017. Ada empat hal utama yang dibahas dalam RUA ini yaitu, perihal organisasi, keanggotaan, pelaksanaan program kerja serta keuangan 2015-2016, dan penyampaian rencana kerja serta keuangan tahun 2017.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_101052.jpg\" style=\"height:338px; width:600px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Perihal organisasi, Filantropi Indonesia sedang mengupayakan untuk mendapatkan status legal dan meminta waktu perpanjangan selama satu tahun untuk proses pengurusan akta. Tidak hanya itu, di tahun 2016 terjadi perubahan nama dan logo resmi organisasi, yang sebelumnya Perhimpunan Filantropi Indonesia menjadi Filantropi Indonesia, demikian pula dengan logo baru dengan tiga lingkaran yang melambangkan tiga aktor filantropi&nbsp;(donatur, perantara dan pelaksana program)&nbsp;telah ditetapkan untuk menggantikan logo lama.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sejak awal tahun 2016, ada&nbsp;18 anggota organisasi baru yang bergabung, sehingga total keseluruhan anggota FI hingga sekarang berjumlah 40 organisasi. Di sesi diskusi, beberapa anggota memberikan tanggapan agar ada kriteria dalam penerimaan anggota. Hal ini ditanggapi oleh Timotheus Lesmana sebagai Ketua Badan Pengurus yang mengatakan bahwa FI sudah memiliki kriteria penerimaan dan pengeluaran anggota.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_110110.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk peningkatan kapasitas anggota, pada tahun 2017 FI akan memiliki tiga program rutin, yaitu&nbsp;Philanthropy Learning Forum, Philanthropy Skill Share Forum, dan Philanthropy Executive Development Program, yang tujuannya untuk penguatan kapasitas lembaga.&nbsp;Dalam kesempatan ini, beberapa anggota mengusulkan agar ke depannya FI berani untuk mengangkat isu &ndash; isu sosial yang sedang populer dan strategis, seperti isu toleransi antar umat beragama.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selain itu kegiatan <em>roadshow </em>SDGs ke 8 (delapan) kota di Indonesia juga akan mulai berjalan di 2017. Kegiatan ini sebenarnya bertujuan untuk mengenalkan SDGs kepada para pelaku filantropi di daerah. Pelaksanaan <em>roadshow </em>ini&nbsp;tertunda karena Perpres SDGs yang belum ditandatangani oleh Presiden dan dokumen SDG belum diterjemahkan oleh Bappenas, oleh karenanya baru dapat dilaksanakan mulai awal 2017&nbsp;dan bekerja sama dengan lembaga filantropi dan nirlaba di daerah.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_110242.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalam bidang riset dan pengembangan, direncanakan pada Januari 2017 FI sudah menerbitkan lima buku dan kajian yaitu <em><strong>Filantropi di Indonesia: Mengapa bukan untuk Kesenian</strong></em>&nbsp;(sudah terbit), <em><strong>Kesiapan Filantropi dalam mendukung Pencapaian SDGs</strong></em>, <strong><em>Profil dan Peran Yayasan Perusahaan</em></strong>, <strong><em>Profil dan Peran Yayasan Keluarga</em></strong>, dan buku saku <strong><em>Mengapa Filantropi Perlu Mendukung SDGs</em></strong>.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalam tuturannya, Timotheus berharap agar di tahun 2017 dan seterusnya, anggota-anggota FI dapat lebih aktif lagi terutama dalam mendukung advokasi serta pencapaian SDGs. Akhirnya RUA Filantropi Indonesia di tahun 2016 ditutup oleh Erna Witoelar, selaku Ketua Badan Pengarah, yang mengatakan bahwa semua anggota dan pegiat filantropi harus berkontribusi pada pencapaian semua goals di 17 SDGs, baik yang kurang populer maupun yang sudah banyak pelakunya.</p>\n', 'f9b7c059288f8b0b7d3d1ba447eb1963.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-23 07:48:46', '2018-02-19 14:44:35', 5, 'kiprah-filantropi-indonesia-selama-2016-diapresiasi-oleh-anggotanya', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'AgeyAUtEX8O1XlG', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(380, 'Indonesia Philanthropy Association\'s Achievement During 2016 is appreciated by its Members', '', '2016 is the year where Filantropi Indonesia experienced positive changes, added more activities and reached many achievements   ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On Tuesday, December 20<sup>th</sup>, 2016, Philanthropy Indonesia held its annual General Meeting of Members with the objectives of discussing accountability programs that have been implemented throughout 2016, financial statements and the reveal of the 2017 program plan. Topics discussed were the organization itself, membership, implementation of work programs and finances for 2015-2016, and the delivery of work plans and finances for 2017.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_101052%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Regarding the organization, Philanthropy Indonesia is working on obtaining legal status and requesting a one-year extension for the deed process. In 2016, there was a change of the official name and logo of the organization. Previously the Philanthropy Association of Indonesia, the organization is currently operating under the name of Indonesian Philanthropy with the new logo depicting three circles representing the three philanthropic actors (donors, intermediaries and program implementers).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Since the beginning of 2016, there have been 18 new member organizations to join, bringing the total number of FI members up to 40 organizations. In the discussion session, some members asked questions regarding the criteria for the acceptance of new members. This was elaborated upon by Timotheus Lesmana, Chairman of the Governing Body, who said that FI already has set criteria for the acceptance and expenditure of members.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_110110%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In 2017 FI will have three regular programs, the Philanthropy Learning Forum, the Philanthropy Skill Share Forum, and the Philanthropy Executive Development Program, with the aim of strengthening institutional capacity. At the event, some members suggested that in the future, FI raised more social issues that are popular and strategic, such as the issue of tolerance among religious people.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In addition, the Indonesian philanthropy roadshow will also commence in 2017. This event is aimed at introducing SDGs to the philanthropic actors in the regions visited. The implementation of the roadshow was previously delayed because the Presidential Regulation on SDGs had not been signed by the President, while the SDG documents had not been translated by Bappenas. Therefore, implementation will officially start in early 2017, in collaboration with local philanthropic and non-profit institutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_110153.jpg\" style=\"width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the field of research and development, FI is currently in the various stages of publishing five books and studies of Philanthropy in Indonesia: Why not for Arts, Philanthropy Readiness in support of Achievement of SDGs, the Profile and Role of Corporate Foundation, the Profile and Role of Family Foundation, and a pocket book: Why Philanthropy Needs to Support SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In his speech, Timotheus expressed his desire that in 2017 and beyond, FI members can be more active, especially in supporting advocacy and the achievement of SDGs. Finally, RUA Philanthropy Indonesia in 2016 was closed by Erna Witoelar, Chairperson of the Steering Committee, who said that all members and activists of philanthropy should contribute to the achievement of the 17 SDGs.</p>\n', 'f9b7c059288f8b0b7d3d1ba447eb1963.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-23 07:48:46', '2018-02-19 14:44:35', 5, '', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'AgeyAUtEX8O1XlG', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(381, '[Philanthropy Skill Share Forum] Teknik Memikat Jurnalis Media', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia menggelar workshop pertama untuk pengembangan kapasitas lembaga', '<p>Sebagai salah satu wujud dukungan dan fasilitas kepada para anggota, Filantropi Indonesia menyelenggarakan <em>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum</em>. <em>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum</em> merupakan sebuah pelatihan selama satu hari penuh yang bertujuan untuk mengembangkan kapasitas dan keahlian para profesional dan pegiat filantropi. Pada bulan Desember 2016 ini, untuk pertama kalinya <em>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum</em> diadakan di kantor Filantropi Indonesia, kawasan Gunung Sahari, Jakarta Pusat.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/PSSF1-4.jpeg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Topik yang diangkat pada <em>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum</em> kali ini adalah &lsquo;Teknik Memikat Jurnalis Media&rsquo;. Topik ini dipilih karena lembaga filantropi atau organisasi sosial mempunyai hubungan yang tidak lepas begitu saja dengan media massa dalam hal publisitas program serta kegiatan yang dilakukan. Walaupun pada dasarnya, lembaga filantropi atau organisasi sosial itu juga memiliki kanal-kanal media komunikasi sendiri seperti situs (<em>website</em>) organisasi maupun akun media sosial untuk mempublikasikan program maupun kegiatannya.</p>\n\n<p>Ada dua narasumber yang memberikan paparan pada acara yang berlangsung pada hari Kamis (15/12) ini. Narasumber pertama adalah Ahmad Husein, <em>Senior Communication Manager</em> di International Federation of Red Cross (IFRC) dan mantan jurnalis/redaktur di beberapa media nasional. Beliau menyampaikan strategi dan kiat dalam memikat jurnalis media yang dapat dilakukan oleh lembaga filantropi. Narasumber kedua adalah Hamid Abidin, Direktur Eksekutif Filantropi Indonesia yang dulu juga pernah menjadi jurnalis di media nasional. Beliau menyampaikan studi kasus penulisan undangan dan rilis media (<em>press release</em>) oleh lembaga filantropi sekaligus mengajak peserta untuk praktik langsung.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/PSSF1-6.jpeg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Walaupun baru pertama kali diadakan, <em>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum </em>mendapat sambutan yang baik. Hal ini dapat dibuktikan dari jumlah peserta yang hadir. Ada dua puluh orang yang hadir dan berasal dari berbagai lembaga filantropi maupun organisasi sosial. Organisasi yang sudah menjadi anggota Filantropi Indonesia dapat mengikuti pelatihan ini secara cuma-cuma, sedangkan nonanggota Filantropi Indonesia dikenakan biaya. Hal ini merupakan itikad baik Filantropi Indonesia untuk memfasilitasi anggotanya dalam menyelesaikan tantangan yang dihadapi, khususnya di bidang publisitas di media massa.</p>\n\n<p>Sampai jumpa lagi di Philanthropy Skill Share Forum kedua di&nbsp;2017!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'ba0c7b790b0b0cd0893d576578407d82.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-23 08:21:41', '2018-02-19 14:45:56', 5, '-philanthropy-skill-share-forum-teknik-memikat-jurnalis-media', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'ZKBcb7ECSOEE3dG', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(382, '[Philanthropy Skill Share Forum] How to Attract Media Journalists', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia held its first workshop for members\' capacity building', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To provide support for, and as a service to our members, Philanthropy Indonesia organizes the Philanthropy Skill Share Forum. The Philanthropy Skill Share Forum is a full-day training exercise aimed at developing the capacity and expertise of professionals and philanthropic activists. In December 2016, for the first time, Philanthropy Skill Share Forum was held at the Indonesian Philanthropy office, Gunung Sahari area, Central Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The topic raised in the Philanthropy Skill Share Forum this time was &#39;Techniques for attracting Media Journalists&#39;. This topic was chosen because philanthropic and social organizations require coverage in mass media to facilitate program publicity and knowledge of activities undertaken. Although philanthropy or social organizations have their own communication media channels such as the organization&#39;s website or social media accounts to publish its programs and activities, mass media provides wide-spread advertisement not achievable with smaller-scale media accounts. There were two speakers for the event which took place on Thursday 15th of December. The first speakers were Ahmad Husein, Senior Communication Manager at the International Federation of Red Cross (IFRC) and former journalist / editor of several national-wide media companies. He conveyed strategies and tips essential for attracting media journalist&rsquo;s attention which can be employed by philanthropic institutions. The second speaker was Hamid Abidin, Executive Director of Philanthropy Indonesia who has also worked as a journalist in national media organisations. He delivered a case study on writing invitations and press releases for philanthropic institutions before inviting participants to practice directly.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Philanthropy Skill Share Forum received good reception, as evidenced by both the number of participants present and their participation over the course of the event. There were twenty people present, all coming from various philanthropic institutions as well as social organizations. Organizations that are already members of Philanthropy Indonesia can attend this training free of charge, while non-members of Philanthropy Indonesia are charged a small operational fee. Philanthropy Indonesian conducts many events aimed at assisting its members in solving the challenges the face, especially in the field of publicity in mass media. See you again at the second Philanthropy Skill Share Forum in 2017!</p>\n', 'ba0c7b790b0b0cd0893d576578407d82.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2016-12-23 08:21:41', '2018-02-19 14:45:56', 5, '-philanthropy-skill-share-forum-how-to-attract-media-journalists', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'ZKBcb7ECSOEE3dG', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(383, 'Corporate Philosophy in Promoting the Support of Arts and Culture - Future Business and Art Partnership for Indonesian and Malaysian Corporations', '', 'Tokyo Forum memaparkan berbagai bentuk dukungan dari perusahaan Jepang untuk bidang kesenian dan membahas model-model pembangunan untuk mempromosikan seni dan budaya pada sektor swasta di negara-negara ASEAN ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Association for Corporate Support of the Arts (Kigoyo Mecenat Kyogikai: KMK) has been conducting the project which is a continuos series of implementing research, mutual exchanges and conferences in collaboration with Southeast Asian countries; &#39;Research and Conference in Facilitating Corporate Mecenat (corporate support of the arts and culture) Activities and Establishing Network in ASEAN countries&#39;. Since its start in early 2015, KMK has conducted this project in Indonesia, Tokyo and Malaysia. In recent years in Indonesia and Malaysia, there have been accelerating movements towards the establishment of intermediate sectors for corporate support of the arts.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tokyo Forum introduces a wide range of Japanese corporate support for the arts that are deeply rooted in the corporate history and philosophy, and at the same time, discusses the possible development models of arts and cultural promotion within private sectors in ASEAN countries by inviting KMK&#39;s ASEAN partners in order to encourage the establishment of intermediate support sectors that will promote corporate support for the arts, as well as to promote multidirectional cultural exchange and collaboration at more practical level.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Tokyo%20Forum%202%282%29.jpg\" style=\"height:989px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Tokyo%20Forum%201.jpg\" style=\"height:971px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', '9b94300d0143f78a625880aecbd9ba3b.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-03 04:06:28', '2017-01-03 13:02:18', 5, 'corporate-philosophy-in-promoting-the-support-of-arts-and-culture-future-business-and-art-partnership-for-indonesian-and-malaysian-corporations', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'A2UO9sFdL8jxdFe', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-26 00:00:00', '2017-01-26 23:59:59'),
(384, 'Corporate Philosophy in Promoting the Support of Arts and Culture - Future Business and Art Partnership for Indonesian and Malaysian Corporations', '', 'Tokyo Forum introduces a wide range of Japanese corporate support for the arts and discusses the possible development models of arts and cultural promotion within private sectors in ASEAN countries', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Association for Corporate Support of the Arts (Kigoyo Mecenat Kyogikai: KMK) has been conducting the project which is a continuos series of implementing research, mutual exchanges and conferences in collaboration with Southeast Asian countries; &#39;Research and Conference in Facilitating Corporate Mecenat (corporate support of the arts and culture) Activities and Establishing Network in ASEAN countries&#39;. Since its start in early 2015, KMK has conducted this project in Indonesia, Tokyo and Malaysia. In recent years in Indonesia and Malaysia, there have been accelerating movements towards the establishment of intermediate sectors for corporate support of the arts.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tokyo Forum introduces a wide range of Japanese corporate support for the arts that are deeply rooted in the corporate history and philosophy, and at the same time, discusses the possible development models of arts and cultural promotion within private sectors in ASEAN countries by inviting KMK&#39;s ASEAN partners in order to encourage the establishment of intermediate support sectors that will promote corporate support for the arts, as well as to promote multidirectional cultural exchange and collaboration at more practical level.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Tokyo%20Forum%202%283%29.jpg\" style=\"height:989px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Tokyo%20Forum%201%281%29.jpg\" style=\"width:700px\" /></p>\n', '9b94300d0143f78a625880aecbd9ba3b.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-03 04:06:28', '2017-01-03 13:02:18', 5, 'corporate-philosophy-in-promoting-the-support-of-arts-and-culture-future-business-and-art-partnership-for-indonesian-and-malaysian-corporations', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'A2UO9sFdL8jxdFe', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-26 00:00:00', '2017-01-26 23:59:59'),
(385, 'Converging Interests: How governments and the philanthropy sector are collaborating to achieve the SDGs', '', '', '', '8ab39fa581edc9fcb5e6275841fe4182.png', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-01-03 06:56:29', '2017-04-13 11:37:28', 5, 'converging-interests-how-governments-and-the-philanthropy-sector-are-collaborating-to-achieve-the-sdgs', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'SDGfunders_25675.pdf', '', '', '', 'Jruio420ewi4uIU', 'yftiEiWnE5xn7Uc', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(386, 'Converging Interests: How governments and the philanthropy sector are collaborating to achieve the SDGs', '', '', '', '8ab39fa581edc9fcb5e6275841fe4182.png', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-01-03 06:56:29', '2017-04-13 11:37:28', 5, 'converging-interests-how-governments-and-the-philanthropy-sector-are-collaborating-to-achieve-the-sdgs', 'download', 0, '', 'en', 'SDGfunders_25675.pdf', '', '', '', 'Jruio420ewi4uIU', 'yftiEiWnE5xn7Uc', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(387, '[Event] Global Summit on Community Philanthropy', '', 'Laporan singkat dari pelaksanaan Global Summit on Community Philanthropy di Johannesburg, Afrika Selatan di bulan Desember kemarin', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Pada tanggal 1-2 Desember yang lalu, Filantropi Indonesia berkesempatan untuk mengikuti <em>Global Summit on Community Philanthropy</em> di Johannesburg, Afrika Selatan. Selain Filantropi Indonesia, delegasi Indonesia yang hadir adalah Indonesia Untuk Kemanusiaan (IKA). Konferensi yang berlangsung selama dua hari itu dihadiri oleh kurang lebih 300 delegasi dari 50 negara. Masing-masing peserta berasal dari berbagai organisasi filantropi maupun komunitas, baik <em>private funders</em>, <em>public funders</em>, maupun Lembaga Swadaya Masyarakat (<em>Non-Government Organizations</em>/NGOs) atau Organisasi Masyarakat Sipil (<em>Civil Society Organizations</em>/CSOs).</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Mengangkat tema &lsquo;<em>Shift the Power</em>&rsquo;, konferensi ini menjadi angin segar dalam dunia NGOs maupun organisasi sosial berbasis komunitas (selanjutnya disebut dengan istilah &lsquo;<em>community foundations</em>&rsquo;). Konferensi ini menjadi gerakan global yang menyuarakan kesetaraan dalam menyikapi kegiatan filantropi maupun bantuan internasional, baik dari segi pemberi maupun penerima hibah. Selain itu, konferensi ini juga menjunjung tinggi lokalitas yang berasal dari komunitas atau NGOs di suatu daerah.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Inisiasi &lsquo;<em>Shift the Power</em>&rsquo; didukung oleh apa yang disebut sebagai <em>8 pillars of good development</em>, yaitu: (1)&nbsp;Partisipasi dan mobilisasi massa (<em>participation and mobilizing people</em>), (2)&nbsp;Nilai tambah (<em>value added</em>), (3) Sumber daya (<em>resources</em>), (4)&nbsp;Data dan fakta (<em>evidence and data</em>), (5) Pemerintah (<em>governance</em>), (6) Intervensi yang efektif (<em>effective intervention</em>), (7)&nbsp;Narasi dan komumikasi (<em>narration and communication</em>), and (8)&nbsp;<em>Architecture &amp; hybridity</em>.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161201_091352.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></span></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><em>Plenary Session</em></strong></span></h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><em>Plenary Session</em> hari pertama mengangkat topik &lsquo;<em>What Needs to Happen to Shift the Power</em>&rsquo; menghadirkan narasumber Ambassador James Joseph (<em>keynote speaker</em>), Sibongile Mkhabela, Hilary Pennington, dan Gerry Salole (moderator).</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Plenary Session hari kedua mengangkat tema &lsquo;Rethinking the Resourcing of Civil Society&rsquo;&nbsp;menghadirkan narasumber <a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/degan-ali\">Degan Ali</a>, Annabel Cruz,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/lucia-dellagnelo\">Lucia Dellagnelo</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/janet-mawiyoo\">Janet Mawiyoo</a>, <a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/littleton-tazewell\">Littleton Tazewell</a>, dan <a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/dhananjayan-sriskandarajah\">Dhananjayan (Danny) Sriskandarajah</a> (moderator).</span></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><em>Concurrent Session </em></strong></span></h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><em>Concurrent Session</em> atau sesi paralel hari pertama menghadirkan lima topik yang dapat dipilih oleh peserta untuk diikuti.</span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&lsquo;<em>Tactics or Design Elements&nbsp;in the Structure of Community Grantmaking Work to&nbsp;Strengthen the Local Capacity, Influence, Trust, Relationships and Resources Needed For Community Change to Stick and Keep Moving Forward</em>&rsquo; oleh The Aspen Institute dan Segal Family Foundation.</span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&lsquo;<em>Network Effects</em>&rsquo; oleh Civicus, Community Foundation of Canada, dan Council of Foundations.</span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&lsquo;<em>How Data Can Drive, Inform and Grow a Locally Owned Development Agenda</em>&rsquo; oleh Foundation Center, Keystone, dan LIN.</span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&lsquo;<em>Shifting Decision Making Power to the People: Models of Participatory Grantmaking</em>&rsquo; oleh African Women&rsquo;s Development Fund (AWDF), Dalia, dan Mama Cash.</span></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&lsquo;<em>Addicted to Scale? What It Really Means to Make an Impact</em>&rsquo; oleh Global Fund for Community Foundations dan Community Foundation of Canada.</span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161201_093203.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Sesi paralel hari kedua menghadirkan empat topik yang dapat dipilih oleh peserta untuk diikuti.</span></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">1.&lsquo;<em>Preaching the Practice and Practicing What We Preach</em>&rsquo;&nbsp;oleh KCDF, Philanthropy for Social Justice and Peace, dan Rockefeller Brothers Fund.</span></h3>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">2.&lsquo;<em>How Do We Maintain Good Governance - and</em> <em>Shift the Power</em>?&rsquo; oleh Global Fund for Community Foundations dan Partnership &ndash; Broker Association.</span></h3>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">3.&lsquo;<em>Exploring How Language Can Shift the Power</em>&lsquo; oleh Comunalia dan Ellas</span></h3>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">4.&lsquo;<em>What Happens When Everyone Is a Donor</em>?&rsquo;&nbsp;oleh Ford Foundation dan ICOM.</span></h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Sketches.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></span></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><em>Lightening Talks</em></strong></span></h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Acara pidato singkat ini disampaikan oleh <a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/victoria-grant\">Victoria Grant</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/felecia-lucky\">Felicia Lucky</a>, dan&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/jiangangzhu\">Jiangang Zhu</a> secara bergantian di atas panggung. Victoria Grant dari Community Foundations of Canada menyampaikan pidato terkait keanekaragaman yang merupakan sesuatu yang alami. Keanekaragaman tidak perlu menjadi sebuah kendala yang harus diatasi oleh sebuah lembaga sosial di suatu wilayah. Victoria Grant mencontohkan, dengan banyaknya <em>indegeneous people</em> di Kanada. Felicia Lucky dari Black Belt Commmunity Foundation menyampaikan hal terkait pemanfaatan sumber daya yang dimiliki oleh suatu yayasan, termasuk membuat narasai-narasi yang unik terkait program dan dampak yang dikerjakan oleh yayasan. Terakhir, Jiangang Zhu yang menyampaikan topik tentang Community Foundation di Cina.</span></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><em>Open Session</em></strong></span></h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><em>Open Session</em> merupakan forum sukarela yang bisa diinisiasi oleh setiap peserta yang memiliki isu khusus dalam dunia filantropi. Sedangkan, para peserta lainnya dapat mengikuti diskusi ini selama satu jam sesuai dengan isu yang diminati. Beberapa organisasi yang berpartisipasi dalam Open Session antara lain Foundations for Peace, Southern Africa Trust, WITS University, Global Fund for Community Foundations, <a href=\"http://www.racialequity.org/\">Philanthropic Initiative for Racial Equity</a>&nbsp;(PRE), Ibero-American Network of Community Foundations, ICOM, dan Zambian Governance Foundation.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Selain itu, dalam konferensi itu juga diselipkan acara penganugerahan Olga Alexeeva Memorial Prize keempat. Nominasi penghargaan tersebut adalah orang-orang yang dianggap memiliki kontribusi di dunia filantropi di masing-masing negara, antara lain Paul Bacher, Artemisa Castro Felix, Audrey Elster, Neville Gabriel, Laurence Lien, Bhekinkosi Moyo, dan Maria Amalia Souza. Akhirnya, yang berhasil meraih penghargaan adalah Bhekinkosi Moyo, Direktur Eksekutif Southern Africa Trust dan ketua (<em>chair</em>) Africa Philanthropy Network.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Finalists.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Di media sosial, khususnya Twitter, konferensi ini dapat disimak kembali dengan tanda pagar (tagar) #ShiftThePower atau di akun resmi penyelenggara Global Summit on Community Philanthropy, Global Fund for Community Foundations @Globalfundcf.</span></p>\n', 'c64884280b3d06c3ac74e4f58476bdc0.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-04 08:13:34', '2018-02-19 14:49:01', 5, '-event-global-summit-on-community-philanthropy', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'OUyUiUnUvIgKVDu', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(388, '[Event] Global Summit on Community Philanthropy', '', 'Short report on the Global Summit on Community Philanthropy event in Johannesburg, South Africa last December', '<p>On December 1<sup>st</sup> and 2nd 2016, Filantropi Indonesia attended the Global Summit on Community Philanthropy in Johannesburg, South Africa. Another delegation from Indonesia was Indonesia Untuk Kemanusiaan (IKA/Indonesia for Humanity). This 2-days conference was attended by 300 delegations from 50 countries. The participants represented various philanthropic organizations or actors, such as private funders, public funders, Non-Government Organizations (NGOs) and Civil Society Organizations (CSOs).</p>\n\n<p>The theme of the Summit was &lsquo;Shift the Power&rsquo; and it was a breath of fresh air for many community-based organizations (generally abbreviated to &lsquo;community foundations&rsquo;). This conference initiated a social movement that emphasized equity in philanthropy activities and international aid, for both the grant-making and grantee organizations. The conference also highlighted the importance of local communities or NGOs in the region.</p>\n\n<p>The &lsquo;Shift the Power&rsquo; initiative is supported by the 8 pillars of good development, which are:</p>\n\n<p>(1) participation and mobilizing people,</p>\n\n<p>(2) value adding,</p>\n\n<p>(3) resources,</p>\n\n<p>(4) evidence and data,</p>\n\n<p>(5) governance,</p>\n\n<p>(6) effective intervention,</p>\n\n<p>(7)&nbsp;narrative and communications,</p>\n\n<p>(8)&nbsp;architecture &amp; hybridity.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161201_091352%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Plenary Session</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>The topic on the first day of Plenary Session was &lsquo;What Needs to Happen to Shift the Power&rsquo;. The speakers were Ambassador James Joseph (keynote speaker), Sibongile Mkhabela, Hilary Pennington, and Gerry Salole (moderator).</p>\n\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">The topic on the second day of Plenary Session was &lsquo;Rethinking the Resourcing of Civil Society&rsquo;. The speakers were&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/degan-ali\">Degan Ali</a>, Annabel Cruz,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/lucia-dellagnelo\">Lucia Dellagnelo</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/janet-mawiyoo\">Janet Mawiyoo</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/littleton-tazewell\">Littleton Tazewell</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/dhananjayan-sriskandarajah\">Dhananjayan (Danny) Sriskandarajah</a>&nbsp;(moderator).</span></h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Concurrent Session </strong></span></p>\n\n<p>There were 5 topics on the first day:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>&lsquo;Tactics or Design Elements&nbsp;in the Structure of Community Grant-making Work to&nbsp;Strengthen the Local Capacity, Influence, Trust, Relationships and Resources Needed for Community Change to Stick and Keep Moving Forward&rsquo; by The Aspen Institute and Segal Family Foundation.</li>\n	<li>&lsquo;Network Effects&rsquo; by Civicus, Community Foundation of Canada, and Council of Foundations.</li>\n	<li>&lsquo;How Data Can Drive, Inform and Grow a Locally Owned Development Agenda&rsquo; by Foundation Center, Keystone, and LIN.</li>\n	<li>&lsquo;Shifting Decision Making Power to the People: Models of Participatory Grantmaking&rsquo; by African Women&rsquo;s Development Fund (AWDF), Dalia, and Mama Cash.</li>\n	<li>&lsquo;Addicted to Scale? What It Really Means to Make an Impact&rsquo; by Global Fund for Community Foundations and Community Foundation of Canada.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161201_093203%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">On the second day, there were 4 topics in the parallel session.</span></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">1.&lsquo;Preaching the Practice and Practicing What We Preach&rsquo; by KCDF, Philanthropy for Social Justice and Peace, and Rockefeller Brothers Fund.</span></h3>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">2.&lsquo;How Do We Maintain Good Governance - and Shift the Power?&rsquo; by Global Fund for Community Foundations and Partnership &ndash; Broker Association.</span></h3>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">3.&lsquo;Exploring How Language Can Shift the Power&lsquo; by Comunalia and Ellas.</span></h3>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">4.&lsquo;What Happens When Everyone is a Donor?&rsquo;&nbsp;by Ford Foundation and ICOM.</span></h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Lightening Talks</strong></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Lightening Talks were short speeches by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/victoria-grant\">Victoria Grant</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/felecia-lucky\">Felicia Lucky</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cpsummit.ngo/jiangangzhu\">Jiangang Zhu</a>. Victoria Grant from Community Foundations of Canada talked about diversity. Diversity is natural and community foundation shouldn&rsquo;t have to overcome it. She gave an example of indigenous people in Canada. Felicia Lucky from Black Belt Community Foundation talked about the use of social and human resources, including the creation of powerful narratives about programs and the impact of the foundations. Finally, Jiangang Zhu talked specifically about Community Foundations operating in China.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Sketches%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:300px\" />&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161201_131112.jpg\" style=\"height:533px; width:300px\" /></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Open Session</strong></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Open Session was a voluntary session where each participant could initiate discussion on special issues of philanthropy. This gave participants the opportunity to get involved in the forum by choosing the issues or topics important to them. The speakers of this Open Session were Foundations for Peace, the Southern Africa Trust, WITS University, the Global Fund for Community Foundations,&nbsp;the <a href=\"http://www.racialequity.org/\">Philanthropic Initiative for Racial Equity</a>&nbsp;(PRE), the Ibero-American Network of Community Foundations, ICOM, and the Zambian Governance Foundation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During the conference, the Fourth Olga Alexeeva Memorial Prize was also awarded. The nominees of the Prize were Paul Bacher, Artemisa Castro Felix, Audrey Elster, Neville Gabriel, Laurence Lien, Bhekinkosi Moyo, and Maria Amalia Souza. In the end, the winner of the Fourth Olga Alexeeva Memorial Prize was Bhekinkosi Moyo, Executive Director of Southern Africa Trust and Chair of the Africa Philanthropy Network.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Finalists%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">If you would like to learn more about the conference from social media (Twitter), search the hashtag #ShiftThePower or check the official account of Global Summit on Community Philanthropy, Global Fund for Community Foundations @Globalfundcf.</span></p>\n', 'c64884280b3d06c3ac74e4f58476bdc0.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-04 08:13:34', '2018-02-19 14:49:01', 5, '-event-global-summit-on-community-philanthropy', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'OUyUiUnUvIgKVDu', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(389, 'Talkshow Zakat Outlook 2017, Peluncuran Majalah Matahati, dan Program Unggulan 2017', '', 'Talkshow Zakat Outlook 2017, Peluncuran Majalah Matahati, dan Program Unggulan 2017 diselenggarakan oleh LazisMu pada Kamis, 12 Januari 2017 di Hotel Arya Duta, Jakarta. ', '', 'db86894d19ac867597a7faf82bfcf1a4.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-10 07:20:57', '2017-01-10 14:20:57', 5, 'talkshow-zakat-outlook-2017-peluncuran-majalah-matahati-dan-program-unggulan-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'k5WtdX4EsS3mvDS', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-12 00:00:00', '2017-01-12 23:59:59'),
(390, 'Talkshow Zakat Outlook 2017, Launching Matahati Magazine, and Ultimate Program 2017 ', '', 'Talkshow Zakat Outlook 2017, Launching Matahati Magazine, and Ultimate Program 2017 by LazisMu in Arya Duta Hotel, Jakarta, Indonesia. ', '', 'db86894d19ac867597a7faf82bfcf1a4.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-10 07:20:58', '2017-01-10 14:20:57', 5, 'talkshow-zakat-outlook-2017-launching-matahati-magazine-and-ultimate-program-2017-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'k5WtdX4EsS3mvDS', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-12 00:00:00', '2017-01-12 23:59:59'),
(391, '[Siaran Pers] BAZNAS Tandatangani Kerjasama Sanitasi Warga Miskin dengan Bappenas', '', 'Badan Amil Zakat Nasional (BAZNAS) menandatangani nota kesepahaman (MoU) kerjasama penyediaan sanitasi dan air bersih dengan Badan Perencanaan Pembangunan Nasional (Bappenas), Majelis Ulama Indonesia (MUI) dan Badan Wakaf Indonesia (BWI) di Kantor Bappenas, Selasa (10/1).', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Badan Amil Zakat Nasional (BAZNAS) menandatangani nota kesepahaman (MoU) kerjasama penyediaan sanitasi dan air bersih dengan Badan Perencanaan Pembangunan Nasional (Bappenas), Majelis Ulama Indonesia (MUI) dan Badan Wakaf Indonesia (BWI) di Kantor Bappenas, Selasa (10/1).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Para pihak bersepakat untuk bekerja sama dalam melaksanakan program pemerintah di bidang pendayagunaan dana zakat, infak, sedekah, dan wakaf (ziswaf) serta dana sosial keagamaan lainnya untuk pembangunan sarana air minum dan sanitasi bagi masyarakat, yang mengadopsi pendekatan Sanitasi Total Berbasis Masyarakat (STBM).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ketua BAZNAS, Prof. Dr. Bambang Sudibyo mengatakan bahwa kerjasama ini ialah momentum bagi BAZNAS untuk menyalurkan dana zakat, infak, sedekah dan dana keagamaan lainnya dengan sebaik-baiknya.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;<em>BAZNAS mendukung program penyediaan sanitasi dan air bersih ini dan kami akan melakukan penyaluran sesuai asnaf (golongan yang berhak menerima zakat), bukan hanya di BAZNAS Pusat namun juga akan kami libatkan seluruh BAZNAS Provinsi dan Lembaga Amil Zakat</em>,&rdquo; katanya saat memberikan sambutan sebelum prosesi penandatanganan MoU.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Prof. Bambang mengatakan kerjasama ini merupakan program yang akan dengan mudah menarik <em>muzaki</em> untuk berzakat melalui lembaga zakat resmi. Sebab salah satu masalah ialah banyak <em>muzak</em>i yang belum berzakat melalui amil zakat resmi seperti tuntunan Al-Quran dan aturan di Undang-undang.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;<em>Untuk menghimpun zakat sebaik-baiknya perlu penyaluran yang kredibel, akuntable, dan sesuai sasaran sehingga dapat membebaskan masyarakat miskin dari berbagai permasalahan, salah satunya ialah masalah air bersih dan sanitasi</em>,&rdquo; katanya.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ia mengatakan, BAZNAS sepenuhnya akan mendukung program ini karena sesuai apa yang sudah dicanangkan oleh Bappenas, bahwa zakat, infak, dan sedekah merupakan bagian dari program untuk mencapai <em>Sustainable Development Goals</em> (SDGs). Zakat juga sudah masuk ke masterplan arsitektur keuangan syariah yang dirancang oleh Bappenas. BAZNAS akan menyiapkan dengan sebaik-baiknya karena dengan demikian, semua organisasi pengelola zakat yang resmi akan menjadi lembaga keuangan syariah yang diawasi dan supervisi oleh Otoritas Jasa Keuangan (OJK).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara itu, Menteri Perencanaan Pembangunan Nasional (PPN)/Kepala Bappenas, Bambang Brojonegoro, mengatakan, kerjasama ini diinisiasi oleh Bappenas selaku koordinator SDGs dengan MUI yang berwenang mengeluarkan Fatwa Ziswaf untuk keperluan air bersih dan sanitasi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Salah satu tujuan ambisius dari program ini adalah &#39;<em>No Poverty&#39;</em>, yaitu memfokuskan diri untuk penanggulangan kemiskinan di Indonesia, salah satunya keterbatasan akses layanan dasar.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;<em>Dalam penyediaan akses dasar, kadang kadang kita lupa dengan air bersih dan sanitasi. Tanpa itu, kita tidak mungkin menciptakan keluarga yang sehat, bahkan sepertiga balita di Indonesia mengalami stunting (gizi buruk)</em>,&rdquo; kata Menteri Bambang.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ia mengatakan bahwa salah satu cara untuk mencegahnya ialah dengan memberikan akses sanitasi dan air bersih yang memadai. Pemerintah menyediakan dana melalui APBN dan APBD namun jumlahnya terbatas, sehingga perlu dibantu dengan anggaran lain yakni zakat dan wakaf.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;<em>Kami berterimakasih karena MUI sudah mengeluarkan fatwa yang mendorong ziswaf utuk menunjang program air bersih dan sanitasi. Kami berharap, BAZNAS dan BWI bisa mendorong pemanfaatan ziswaf utuk kesejahteraan masyarakat</em>,&rdquo; katanya.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Penyaluran ziswaf dalam program akan mempercepat pengurangan kemiskinan di Indonesia dan menolong masyarakat yang belum memiliki akses air bersih.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">#KuatKarenaZakat</p>\n\n<p>Informasi lebih lanjut, dapat menghubungi: Ndari +62 87889573889.</p>\n', '08d56e973ddbfe7760245602da637f9a.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-11 08:20:18', '2018-02-23 09:43:19', 5, '-siaran-pers-baznas-tandatangani-kerjasama-sanitasi-warga-miskin-dengan-bappenas', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'CUmMhJzUEyaU9OY', 'N', '', 'BAZNAS', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(392, '[Press Release] BAZNAS Signs Poverty Sanitation Partnership with Bappenas', '', 'The National Amil Zakat Agency (BAZNAS) signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) promising cooperation on the provision of sanitation and clean water with the National Development Planning Agency (Bappenas), the Indonesian Ulema Council (MUI) and the Indonesian Wakaf Board (BWI) at the Bappenas Office on Tuesday the 10th of January.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The National Amil Zakat Agency (BAZNAS) signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) promising cooperation on the provision of sanitation and clean water with the National Development Planning Agency (Bappenas), the Indonesian Ulema Council (MUI) and the Indonesian Wakaf Board (BWI) at the Bappenas Office on Tuesday the 10<sup>th</sup> of January.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The parties agreed to cooperate in implementing the government&#39;s program in the utilization of zakat, infaq, alms and waqf (ziswaf) funds and other religious social funds for the development of drinking water and sanitation facilities for the community, using the approach of Total Community Based Sanitation (STBM).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Chairman of BAZNAS, Prof. Dr. Bambang Sudibyo said that this cooperative will assist BAZNAS in channelling the funds of zakat, infak, alms and other religious funds to where they can be used most efficiently.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;BAZNAS supports this sanitation and clean water supply program, and we will distribute the ziswaf according to asnaf, not only in Central BAZNAS but also to all Provincial BAZNAS and Lembaga Amil Zakat,&quot; he said, while giving a speech before the procession the signing of the MoU.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prof. Bambang said this cooperation is a program that will easily attract muzaki to zakat through the official zakat institution. Because one of the problems is many muzaki who have not contributed zakat through official zakat amil, as per the guidance of the Quran and the rules in the Act.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;To collect and distribute zakat as well as possible, the process needs to be as credible, accountable, and targeted as possible. This will help to free the poor from various problems, one of which is the problem of clean water and sanitation,&quot; he said.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He said BAZNAS would fully support the program because, according to what has been announced by Bappenas, zakat, infak, and alms now form part of the program aimed at achieving the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). Zakat has also fallen under the scope of the Islamic financial architecture as designed by Bappenas. BAZNAS is preparing for the time when all official zakat management organizations become sharia financial institutions that are supervised and supervised by the Financial Services Authority (OJK).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Meanwhile, the Minister of National Development Planning, Bambang Brojonegoro, said that the cooperation was initiated by Bappenas as the coordinator of SDGs with MUI authorized to issue a Ziswaf Fatwa for clean water and sanitation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of the ambitious goals of this program is &#39;No Poverty&#39;, which focuses on poverty alleviation in Indonesia, and in turn requires access to basic services.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;In the provision of basic access, we cannot forget clean water and sanitation. Without it, we cannot create a healthy family, up to one third of children under five in Indonesia experience stunting (malnutrition), &quot;said Minister Bambang.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He said one way to prevent it is to provide access to adequate sanitation and clean water. The government provides funds through APBN and APBD but the amount is limited, so it needs to be assisted by other sources such as zakat and waqf.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;We are grateful that MUI has issued a fatwa encouraging ziswaf to support clean water and sanitation program. We hope that BAZNAS and BWI can encourage the utilization of ziswaf for the welfare of the people, &quot;he said.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The distribution of ziswaf in the program will accelerate poverty reduction in Indonesia and help people who do not have access to clean water.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">#KuatKarenaZakat</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For further information, please contact: Ndari +62 87889573889.</p>\n', '08d56e973ddbfe7760245602da637f9a.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-11 08:20:19', '2018-02-23 09:43:19', 5, '-press-release-baznas-signs-poverty-sanitation-partnership-with-bappenas', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'CUmMhJzUEyaU9OY', 'N', '', 'BAZNAS', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(393, '[Lowongan] Program Magang di Yayasan Danamon Peduli', '', 'Yayasan Danamon Peduli (Danamon Peduli) merupakan lembaga pelaksana program/kegiatan Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) dari PT Bank Danamon Indonesia, Tbk. dan PT Adira Dinamika Multifinance Tbk. yang didirikan pada 17 Februari 2006.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Yayasan Danamon Peduli (Danamon Peduli) merupakan&nbsp;lembaga&nbsp;pelaksana program/kegiatan <em>Corporate Social Responsibility</em> (CSR) dari PT Bank Danamon Indonesia,&nbsp;Tbk.&nbsp;dan PT Adira Dinamika Multifinance Tbk. yang didirikan&nbsp;pada&nbsp;17 Februari 2006.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Program-program Danamon Peduli bertujuan&nbsp;untuk&nbsp;mendukung&nbsp;Tujuan Pembangunan&nbsp;Berkelanjutan&nbsp;(<em>Sustainable Development Goals</em>/SDGs)&nbsp;yang bermanfaat langsung pada masyarakat dan melibatkan relawan dari lingkungan keluarga besar Danamon.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Adapun Program Danamon Peduli terdiri dari&nbsp;Program&nbsp;Pasar Sejahtera<strong>&nbsp;</strong>yaitu revitalisasi&nbsp;dan pendampingan&nbsp;pasar tradisional&nbsp;bermitra dengan pemerintah daerah. Sub bagian Program Pasar Sejahtera adalah:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Peduli Lingkungan, yaitu sebuah kegiatan yang berfokus di pasar seperti perbaikan Mandi&nbsp;Cuci&nbsp;Kakus (MCK), pembuatan sarana air bersih, pembuatan lubang biopori, Tempat Pengolahan Sampah Terpadu dll. Kegiatan ini dilakukan oleh seluruh karyawan Danamon dan Adira di Indonesia dan berkolaborasi dengan pemerintah daerah setempat.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Kegiatan Cepat Tanggap Bencana (CTB ), yaitu kegiatan ini merespon&nbsp;bencana yang terjadi di suatu daerah&nbsp;baik yang terjadi karena alam maupun akibat kelalaian manusia.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalam upaya mendukung mahasiwa/i tingkat akhir dalam menyelesaikan tugas akhir dan membangun pengetahuan dan kecakapan serta berbagi pengalaman dan pembelajaran yang Danamon Peduli miliki selama ini, maka kami membuka kesempatan&nbsp;bagi mahasiswa/i yang berminat untuk mendapatkan pengalaman baru dalam Program Magang di Danamon Peduli selama 1-3 bulan (tergantung divisi).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dan saat ini kami sedang membutuhkan tenaga magang yang dapat mengelola Sistem Informasi Manajemen (Management Information System/MIS) yang ada di Danamon Peduli, dengan ruang lingkup tugas sebagai berikut:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Menginput, mengolah dan menyimpan data;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Membuat sistem sederhana untuk menyimpan data;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Membuat report dalam bentuk tabel/grafik.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Persyaratan Program Magang:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">1. &nbsp;Umum:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sarjana/tingkat akhir (dalam penyelesaian);</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Jurusan:&nbsp;MIS atau Computer Science, atau Network Engineering &nbsp;atau&nbsp;jurusan lain namun mampu dan cakap dalam isu Pengelolaan Data;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Memiliki semangat kerja dalam sektor pembangunan kemasyarakatan/organisasi;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Mampu berbahasa Inggris, minimum pasif;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Memiliki kemampuan komunikasi yang baik;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Mampu bekerja dalam tim;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Menguasai MS Office dan internet.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">2. Administrasi:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Surat Pengantar dari Universitas (Ditujukan kepada: Direktur Eksekutif Yayasan Danamon Peduli);</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Transkrip nilai</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Curiculum Vitae (CV)</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Satu halaman cover letter yang menjelaskan latar belakang pendidikan dan pekerjaan (jika sudah ada)</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">3-4 paragraf penjelasan mengenai motivasi magang di sektor pembangunan/pembangunan kemasyarakatan di&nbsp;Danamon Peduli, dan bagaimana ilmu dan pengetahuan anda bisa memberi kontribusi di&nbsp;Danamon Peduli&nbsp;serta rencana untuk memanfaatkan pengalaman setelah magang;</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Karya tulis/blog&nbsp;(jika ada)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Berkas dikirimkan dalam bentuk pdf maksimal 6 MB melalui email ke&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:hrd@danamonpeduli.or.id\" target=\"_blank\">christian@danamonpeduli.or.id</a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Manfaat&nbsp;magang&nbsp;di&nbsp;Danamon Peduli:</p>\n\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-alpha\">\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Memahami isu-isu&nbsp;pembangunan&nbsp;kemasyarakatan (<em>social development</em>).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Mendapat <em>hands-on experience</em> di sektor pembangunan kemasyarakatan dan CSR&nbsp;di lembaga yang kredibel dalam hal pengelolaan program, komunikasi, tata kelola pemerintahan, TI, dan lain-lain.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Mengembangkan dan mempraktikkan <em>hard skills</em> dan <em>soft skills</em>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk info lebih lanjut silahkan menghubungi: Christian Paendong melalui Telpon&nbsp;(021) 80645299, Faks (021) 80645288/89, email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:christian@danamonpeduli.or.id\" target=\"_blank\">christian@danamonpeduli.or.id</a></p>\n', 'a7dcd5e26f2f5cdba48ba48dc5fb8c2e.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-11 08:47:39', '2018-02-23 09:42:04', 5, '-lowongan-program-magang-di-yayasan-danamon-peduli', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '8IOlbHNxTaiCOd7', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Danamon Peduli', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(394, '[Vacancy] Internship Program - Yayasan Danamon Peduli', '', 'The Danamon Peduli Foundation (Danamon Peduli) is the implementing institution of Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) programs for PT Bank Danamon Indonesia, Tbk. and PT Adira Dinamika Multifinance Tbk. which was established on February 17, 2006.', '<p>The Danamon Peduli Foundation (Danamon Peduli) is the implementing institution of Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) programs for PT Bank Danamon Indonesia, Tbk. and PT Adira Dinamika Multifinance Tbk. which was established on February 17, 2006.</p>\n\n<p>Danamon Peduli&#39;s programs aim to support Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) that are directly beneficial to the community, and involve volunteers from the Danamon family.</p>\n\n<p>Danamon Peduli Program consists of the Pasar Sejahtera Program (Prosperous Market Program) that provides revitalization and traditional market assistance partnering with local government. The sub-divisions of the Prosperous Market Program are:</p>\n\n<p>1. Care for the Environment, which is a market-focused activity providing infrastructure such as public washing facilities (Mandi, Cuci, Kakus or MCKs), clean water facilities, biopori hole making, Integrated Waste Processing Sites etc. This activity was conducted by all Danamon and Adira employees in Indonesia in collaboration with the local government.</p>\n\n<p>2. Quick Disaster Response Activities (CTB). This program is situated to respond to disasters occurring in an area whether occurring due to nature or due to human negligence.</p>\n\n<p>In an effort to support the final year students in completing their final projects and building knowledge and skills, and sharing the experience and lessons that Danamon Peduli has gained, we are opening the opportunity for interested students to gain new experience via the Danamon Peduli Internship Program over a period of 1-3 months (depending on division).</p>\n\n<p>At present, we are in need of apprentices who can manage the Management Information System (MIS) in Danamon Peduli. This entails the following duties:</p>\n\n<p>1. input, process and store data;</p>\n\n<p>2. Creating a simple system for storing data;</p>\n\n<p>3. Creating reports in the form of tables / graphs.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Internship Program Requirements:</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. General:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Bachelor / masters (in progress);</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Department: MIS or Computer Science, Network Engineering or other majors, but capable and competent in the issue of Data Management;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Have an interest in the social / organizational development sector;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; The ability to speak English, a passive minimum;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Having good communication skills;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; The ability to work in teams;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Knowledge of MS Office and internet.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>2. Administrative:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Letter of Introduction from the University (Addressed to: Executive Director of Danamon Peduli Foundation);</p>\n\n<p>&bull;Transcripts</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Curiculum Vitae (CV)</p>\n\n<p>&bull; One cover letter page explaining the candidates educational and occupational background (if one already exists)</p>\n\n<p>&bull; 3-4 explanatory paragraphs on apprenticeship motivation in the development / community development sector at Danamon Peduli, and how your knowledge and knowledge can contribute to Danamon Peduli as well as plans to take advantage of after-apprenticeship experience;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Examples of writing / blogs (if any)</p>\n\n<p>The file is to be submitted in pdf format up to 6 MB in size, via email to <a href=\"mailto:christian@danamonpeduli.or.id\">christian@danamonpeduli.or.id</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The benefits of an internship at Danamon Peduli include:</p>\n\n<p>1. A better understanding of social development issues.</p>\n\n<p>2. Gaining hands-on experience in the community development sector and CSR in a credible institution in terms of program management, communications, governance, IT, and others.</p>\n\n<p>c. Development and practicing hard skills and soft skills.</p>\n\n<p>For further information please contact: Christian Paendong via Phone (021) 80645299, Fax (021) 80645288/89, or email at christian@danamonpeduli.or.id</p>\n', 'a7dcd5e26f2f5cdba48ba48dc5fb8c2e.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-11 08:47:39', '2018-02-23 09:42:04', 5, '-vacancy-internship-program-yayasan-danamon-peduli', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '8IOlbHNxTaiCOd7', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Danamon Peduli', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(395, '[Beasiswa] Seleksi Beasiswa Tanoto Foundation National Champion Scholarship 2017', '', 'Tanoto Foundation didirikan oleh Sukanto Tanoto dan Tinah Bingei Tanoto sebagai perwujudan kepedulian terhadap sesama untuk menanggulangi kemiskinan. Sejak tahun 1981, Tanoto Foundation berupaya menjadi pusat unggulan dalam penanggulangan kemiskinan melalui 3 pilar: Pendidikan, Pemberdayaan, dan Peningkatan Kualitas Hidup.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tanoto Foundation didirikan oleh Sukanto Tanoto dan Tinah Bingei Tanoto sebagai perwujudan kepedulian terhadap sesama untuk menanggulangi kemiskinan. Sejak tahun 1981, Tanoto Foundation berupaya menjadi pusat unggulan dalam penanggulangan kemiskinan melalui 3 pilar: Pendidikan, Pemberdayaan, dan Peningkatan Kualitas Hidup.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalam pilar Pendidikan, Tanoto Foundation melaksanakan program yang bertujuan untuk meningkatkan akses pada pendidikan dan peningkatan kualitas pendidikan di Indonesia. Dalam pilar Pemberdayaan, Tanoto Foundation melaksanakan program yang bertujuan untuk memaksimalkan potensi ekonomi individu, rumah tangga dan komunitasnya. Dalam pilar Peningkatan Kualitas Hidup, Tanoto Foundation melaksanakan program yang mendukung komunitas, baik infrastruktur maupun berbagai fasilitas bagi masyarakat untuk meningkatkan kualitas hidup.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Salah satu Program Pendidikan Tanoto Foundation adalah pemberian beasiswa kepada mahasiswa Program S-1 dan S-2 yang berprestasi, memiliki potensi kepemimpinan tetapi menghadapi kendala ekonomi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk tahun 2017, Tanoto Foundation memberikan kesempatan menjadi penerima beasiswa Tanoto Foundation, Program <em>National Champion Scholarship</em>, &nbsp;kepada 275 mahasiswa (250 mahasiswa Program Sarjana Strata 1 atau S-1, &nbsp;dan 25 mahasiswa Program Sarjana Strata 2 atau S-2) dari berbagai disiplin ilmu.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Penerima beasiswa akan mendapatkan manfaat sebagai berikut:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Tunjangan uang kuliah maksimum Rp 5.000.000,00/semester (program S-1) sampai semester ke-8 (delapan) atau maksimum Rp 15.000.000,00/semester (program S-2) sampai semester ke-4 (empat).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Tunjangan biaya hidup sebesar Rp 600.000,00/bulan (program S-1) sampai semester ke-8 (delapan) atau Rp 1.200.000,00/bulan (program S-2) sampai semester ke-4 (empat).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Program pelatihan kepemimpinan dan pengembangan <em>soft skill.</em></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Program pengabdian masyarakat melalui <em>Tanoto Scholars Association.</em></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Program pengembangan jejaring melalui <em>Tanoto Scholars Gathering.</em></li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Program konseling bagi Tanoto Scholars yang mengalami kendala pencapaian akademis.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Program magang di perusahaan yang tergabung dalam grup Royal Golden Eagle (RGE).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Kesempatan untuk ikut seleksi beasiswa ikatan dinas Tanoto Foundation.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pendaftaran secara online dibuka tanggal <strong>4 Januari - 15 Maret 2017</strong>. Informasi lebih lanjut terkait Seleksi&nbsp;Beasiswa Tanoto Foundation National Champion Scholarship 2017, dapat dilihat di <a href=\"http://www.tanotofoundation.org/education/id/2017/01/seleksi-beasiswa-tanoto-foundation-national-champion-scholarship-2017/\">www.tanotofoundation.org</a>.</p>\n', '3cc533f4304962c3df222d57449a885a.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-12 07:34:04', '2018-02-23 09:41:13', 5, '-beasiswa-seleksi-beasiswa-tanoto-foundation-national-champion-scholarship-2017', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'E5JG1OK7IdcrsWQ', 'N', '', 'Tanoto Foundation', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(396, '[Scholarship] Tanoto Foundation National Champion Scholarship 2017', '', 'Tanoto Foundation was founded by Sukanto Tanoto and Tinah Bingei Tanoto as a manifestation of caring for others to overcome poverty. Since 1981, Tanoto Foundation strives to be the center of poverty reduction through three pillars: Education, Empowerment, and Improving Quality of Life.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Tanoto Foundation was founded by Sukanto Tanoto and Tinah Bingei Tanoto as an organisation premised on caring for others and helping them to overcome poverty. Since 1981, Tanoto Foundation has strived to be the centre of poverty reduction through its focus on the areas it sees as most important: education, empowerment, and improving quality of Life.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the Educational sphere, Tanoto Foundation is implementing programs aimed at improving access to education and improving the quality of education in Indonesia. In terms of Empowerment, they are implementing programs that aim to maximize the economic potential of individuals, households and communities. To Improve quality of life, the Tanoto Foundation is implementing programs that support the community, both in terms of infrastructure and facilities for their collective use</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of the Tanoto Foundation&rsquo;s Educational Programs sees the award of scholarships to undergraduates of S-1 and S-2, students who show leadership potential, but face economic constraints in its application.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For the year 2017, Tanoto Foundation will provide 275 students, from various disciplines, the opportunity to receive the National Champion Scholarship Program. Scholarship recipients will benefit as follows:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Maximum tuition allowance of Rp 5.000.000,00 / semester (S-1 program) until the eighth semester (eight) or maximum Rp 15.000.000,00 / semester (S-2 program) until the 4th semester four).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Allowance for living expenses of Rp 600.000,00 / month (S-1 program) until the eighth semester (eight) or Rp 1,200,000.00 / month (S-2 program) until the fourth semester (four).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Leadership training and soft skills development programs.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Community service program through the Tanoto Scholars Association.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Network development program through the Tanoto Scholars Gathering.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Counselling program for Tanoto Scholars experiencing obstacles in their academic achievement.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Apprenticeship programs in companies incorporated in the Royal Golden Eagle (RGE) group.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Opportunities to join the Tanoto Foundation scholarship selection.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Online registration opens on 4<sup>th</sup> January until the 15<sup>th</sup> March 2017. More information regarding the Tanoto Foundation National Champion Scholarship 2017 Scholarship Selection can be found at <a href=\"http://www.tanotofoundation.org\">www.tanotofoundation.org</a>.</p>\n', '3cc533f4304962c3df222d57449a885a.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-12 07:34:04', '2018-02-23 09:41:13', 5, '-scholarship-tanoto-foundation-national-champion-scholarship-2017', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'E5JG1OK7IdcrsWQ', 'N', '', 'Tanoto Foundation', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(397, 'Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017: Optimalisasi Zakat menuju Indonesia Berkemajuan', '', 'Pada hari Kamis (12/1) lalu, Filantropi Indonesia mendapat undangan untuk menghadiri acara Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017 serta peluncuran Majalah Matahati dan Program Unggulan LazisMu tahun 2017. Acara yang berlangsung di Hotel Arya Duta, Jakarta ini diselenggarakan oleh LazisMu, sebuah lembaga zakat di Indonesia yang menjadi anggota Filantropi Indonesia sejak 2016.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada hari Kamis (12/1) lalu, Filantropi Indonesia mendapat undangan untuk menghadiri acara Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017 serta peluncuran Majalah Matahati dan Program Unggulan LazisMu tahun 2017. Acara yang berlangsung di Hotel Arya Duta, Jakarta ini diselenggarakan oleh LazisMu, sebuah lembaga zakat di Indonesia yang menjadi anggota Filantropi Indonesia sejak 2016. Dalam acara ini, LazisMu menghadirkan narasumber,&nbsp;Prof. Dr. H. Muhadjir Effendy, M.A.P (Menteri Pendidikan &amp; Kebudayaan), &nbsp;Drs. Hajriyanto Y. Thohari, MA (Ketua PP Muhammadiyah), Regi Wahyu (CEO Dattabot/Mediatrac), Samsul Huda (Ketua NU Care &ndash; LazisNu), dan Hilman Latief, MA, Ph.D (Ketua Badan Pengurus LazisMu).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara Zakat Outlook 2017 bertujuan untuk memperkokoh konsolidasi nasional LazisMu dengan para pemangku kepentingan terkait konsep dan program-program LazisMu di tahun 2017. Selain itu, acara ini juga bertujuan untuk memperkokoh sinergi dalam ruang lingkup antarkomunitas profesional, komunitas hobi, dan semua orang yang terlibat dalam ekosistem zakat di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Berdasarkan hasil survei dari lembaga PIRAC dan BAZNAS, potensi zakat di Indonesia menunjukkan perkembangan yang pesat dari masa ke masa. Zakat diyakini mampu bersumbangsih dalam mendorong keadilan sosial, pembangunan manusia, serta pengentasan kemiskinan di Indonesia. Hal ini sejalan dengan latar belakang berdirinya LazisMu oleh PP Muhammadiyah pada tahun 2002, yaitu:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>Pertama, </em>fakta bahwa Indonesia masih mengalami kemiskinan, kebodohan, dan indeks pembangunan manusia yang sangat rendah. <em>Kedua</em>, zakat diyakini mampu bersumbangsih dalam mendorong keadilan sosial, pembangunan manusia, dan mampu mengentaskan kemiskinan. Sebagai negara berpenduduk muslim terbesar di dunia, Indonesia memiliki potensi zakat, infaq, dan wakaf yang tinggi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Di sini lain, untuk merespon isu internasional, kinerja LazisMu juga mengacu pada 17 Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (<em>Sustainable Development Goals</em>/SDGs). Dari tujuan no.8, 13, dan 17 acuan program, LazisMu membaginya dalam 3 hal: sosial dakwah dan pendidikan, ekonomi kreatif-produktif, advokasi kebijakan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Terkait dengan program unggulan di tahun 2017, LazisMu menetapkan sasaran program pada kawasan 3 T (Terdepan, Terluar, dan Tertinggal) di Indonesia. Ulasan serta informasi&nbsp;programnya pun akan&nbsp;disampaikan secara luas kepada masyarakat melalui berbagai rubrik yang terdapat di Majalah Matahati.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Pendidikan</strong>, yaitu Save Our School, GN-OTA, Trensains, dan Sejuta Sarjana,</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Ekonomi</strong>, yaitu Tani Bangkit, Sejuta UMKM,</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Pemberdayaan ekonomi</strong>, yaitu Youth Entrepreneurship, Bina Usaha Ekonomi Keluarga, dan penyertaan modal BTM, Surya LED, Safaro, Kampung ternak dan Desbumi.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Sosial</strong>, meliputi Tanggap Darurat Bencana, Dai Mandiri, Muhammadiyah Aid, Kurban Pak Kumis, dan Mobil Klinik.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Inovasi program</strong>, yaitu program Indonesia Terang dan Klinik Apung Said Tuhuleley.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">* Disarikan dari Rilis Media Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017: Optimalisasi Zakat menuju Indonesia Berkemajuan.</p>\n', '0e673fd6837a3cc39a869a198b9ba0f3.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-16 04:17:26', '2018-02-23 09:39:54', 5, 'zakat-outlook-lazismu-2017-optimalisasi-zakat-menuju-indonesia-berkemajuan', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '0PGjvvLZCTEBjLv', 'N', '', 'LazisMu', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(398, 'Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017: Optimization of Zakat in Indonesia Progress', '', 'On Thursday (12/1), Filantropi Indonesia received an invitation to attend Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017 and the launch of Matahati Magazine and LazisMu Superior Program in 2017. The event which took place at Hotel Arya Duta, Jakarta was organized by LazisMu, an institution of zakat in Indonesia who has been a member of Indonesia Philanthropy Association since 2016.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On Thursday 12<sup>th</sup> January 2017, Philanthropy Indonesia received an invitation to attend the Zakat Outlook LazisMu 2017 event and the launch of Matahati Magazine and your LazisMu Superior Program in 2017. The event, which took place at Hotel Arya Duta, Jakarta, was organized by LazisMu, an institution of zakat in&nbsp;Indonesia who has been a member of Indonesian Philanthropy since 2016. In this event, LazisMu hosted speakers Prof.Dr.&nbsp;H. Muhadjir Effendy, M.A.P (Minister of Education &amp; Culture), Drs.&nbsp;Hajriyanto Y. Thohari, MA (Chairman of PP Muhammadiyah), Regi Wahyu (CEO of Dattabot / Mediatrac), Samsul Huda (Chairman of NU Care - LazisNu), and Hilman Latief, MA, Ph.D (the Chairman of the Board of LazisMu).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Zakat Outlook 2017 aimed to strengthen LazisMu&#39;s national consolidation with stakeholders regarding the concept and programs of LazisMu in 2017. It also aimed to strengthen the synergy within the professional community, hobby community and everyone involved&nbsp;in the zakat system in Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Based on survey results produced by PIRAC and BAZNAS institutions, zakat potential in Indonesia has shown rapid growth over time.&nbsp;Zakat is believed to be able to contribute in promoting social justice, human development, and poverty alleviation in Indonesia.&nbsp;This is in line with the establishment goal of LazisMu by PP Muhammadiyah in 2002.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Indonesia is still experiencing poverty, lack of education, and the index of human development is very low.&nbsp;Zakat is believed to be able to contribute in promoting social justice, human development, and to help in the alleviation of poverty.&nbsp;As the country with the largest Muslim population in the world, Indonesia has high potential for zakat, infaq, and waqf contributions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The LazisMu performance report also referred to the 17 Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). From the objectives of goals numbers 8, 13, and 17 of the program, LazisMufoced on 3 areas: social da&#39;wah and education, creative-production economy and policy advocacy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In relation to the flagship program in 2017, LazisMu set program targets across all levels of development, from Leading, Outermost and Underdeveloped, across regions in Indonesia. The reviews and program information will be widely presented to the public through various rubrics contained in Matahati Magazine. Some key programs are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Education, namely Save Our School, GN-OTA, Trensains, and One Million Graduate,</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Economy, ie Tani Bangkit, Million SMEs,</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Economic empowerment, namely Youth Entrepreneurship, Family Economic Business Development, and BTM&#39;s capital participation, Surya LED, Safaro, Livestock Village and Desbumi.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Social, covering Disaster Emergency Response, Dai Mandiri, Muhammadiyah Aid, Sacrifice Pak Mustache, and Car Clinic.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Innovation of the program, the program of Terang Indonesia and the Floating Clinic Said Tuhuleley.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">* Excerpted from Zakat Media Release Outlook LazisMu 2017: Optimizing Zakat to Indonesia Berkemajuan.Source : LazisMu</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n', '0e673fd6837a3cc39a869a198b9ba0f3.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-16 04:17:26', '2018-02-23 09:39:54', 5, 'zakat-outlook-lazismu-2017-optimization-of-zakat-in-indonesia-progress', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', '0PGjvvLZCTEBjLv', 'N', '', 'LazisMu', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(399, 'Philanthropy Summit 2017 Innovate for Impact', '', 'Innovation is playing an increasingly crucial role in the success of communities, organisations and even countries and can fundamentally shift the impact of philanthropy.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Innovation is playing an increasingly crucial role in the success of communities, organisations and even countries and can fundamentally shift the impact of philanthropy.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif\">In May 2017, we are hosting the country&rsquo;s largest gathering of leaders involved with philanthropy. Held at Te Papa, Innovate for Impact will bring together global and local thought leaders from philanthropy, business, iwi, government, investment and the community sector along with innovators for the two-day summit that will inform, inspire and challenge you.<br />\n<br />\nThe Summit will explore global and local perspectives on innovation in philanthropy and provide unique networking opportunities.<br />\n<br />\nWe have an impressive line-up of speakers from near and far, including <strong>Katy Love</strong>, Wikimedia Foundation (USA); <strong>Allan and Rachel English</strong>, English Family Foundation, (AUS); <strong>Donna Flavell</strong>, Waikato-Tainui (NZ); <strong>Judge Carolyn Henwood</strong> (NZ), <strong>Dai Henwood</strong> (NZ) and <strong>Rangimarie Naida Glavish</strong>, co-chair of her iwi Te R?nanga o Ng?ti Wh?tua (NZ).<br />\n<br />\nThere will also be specialised breakout sessions, and &lsquo;pockets of change&rsquo;&mdash;unique stories of innovation from global and local funders who have challenged the norm, thought outside the square and changed their world.<br />\n<br />\nFor the first time, Philanthropy New Zealand is opening Summit registration to our community members and other not-for-profits in a solicitation-free environment.<br />\n<br />\nWe look forward to seeing you there&nbsp;and together learning about game-changing strategies and innovative ways to maximise our impact in philanthropy. For more info, please <a href=\"https://www.eiseverywhere.com/ehome/index.php?eventid=161783&amp;\">click here</a>.</span></span></p>\n', '27692fea0e18fe854d8ec4e7ad71f8d2.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-17 03:23:34', '2017-01-17 10:23:34', 5, 'philanthropy-summit-2017-innovate-for-impact', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'fE08sVrLV6cHULQ', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-10 00:00:00', '2017-05-12 23:59:59'),
(400, 'Philanthropy Summit 2017 Innovate for Impact', '', 'Innovation is playing an increasingly crucial role in the success of communities, organisations and even countries and can fundamentally shift the impact of philanthropy.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:12px\">Innovation is playing an increasingly crucial role in the success of communities, organisations and even countries and can fundamentally shift the impact of philanthropy.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif\">In May 2017, we are hosting the country&rsquo;s largest gathering of leaders involved with philanthropy. Held at Te Papa, Innovate for Impact will bring together global and local thought leaders from philanthropy, business, iwi, government, investment and the community sector along with innovators for the two-day summit that will inform, inspire and challenge you.<br />\n<br />\nThe Summit will explore global and local perspectives on innovation in philanthropy and provide unique networking opportunities.<br />\n<br />\nWe have an impressive line-up of speakers from near and far, including <strong>Katy Love</strong>, Wikimedia Foundation (USA); <strong>Allan and Rachel English</strong>, English Family Foundation, (AUS); <strong>Donna Flavell</strong>, Waikato-Tainui (NZ); <strong>Judge Carolyn Henwood</strong> (NZ), <strong>Dai Henwood</strong> (NZ) and <strong>Rangimarie Naida Glavish</strong>, co-chair of her iwi Te R?nanga o Ng?ti Wh?tua (NZ).<br />\n<br />\nThere will also be specialised breakout sessions, and &lsquo;pockets of change&rsquo;&mdash;unique stories of innovation from global and local funders who have challenged the norm, thought outside the square and changed their world.<br />\n<br />\nFor the first time, Philanthropy New Zealand is opening Summit registration to our community members and other not-for-profits in a solicitation-free environment.<br />\n<br />\nWe look forward to seeing you there&nbsp;and together learning about game-changing strategies and innovative ways to maximise our impact in philanthropy. For more info, please <a href=\"https://www.eiseverywhere.com/ehome/index.php?eventid=161783&amp;\">click here</a>.</span></span></p>\n', '27692fea0e18fe854d8ec4e7ad71f8d2.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-17 03:23:34', '2017-01-17 10:23:34', 5, 'philanthropy-summit-2017-innovate-for-impact', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'fE08sVrLV6cHULQ', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-10 00:00:00', '2017-05-12 23:59:59'),
(401, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Peran Filantropi Dalam Penanganan Nutrisi Bangsa', '', 'Laporan pelaksanaan PLF ke-12 mengenai nutrisi ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tidak selamanya masalah nutrisi berkaitan dengan makanan, namun juga kebiasaan pola makan dan pengetahuan tentang makanan. Untuk dapat menyelesaikan permasalahan nutrisi bangsa yang telah mengakar ke banyak bidang, dibutuhkan kerjasama yang berkelanjutan, terencana dan terukur dari berbagai pihak. Untuk itulah pada Selasa, 20 Desember 2016, Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan Philanthropy Learning Forum ke-12 dengan mengambil tema<em> <strong>Peran Filantropi Dalam Penanganan Nutrisi Bangsa</strong> </em>yang dilaksanakan di Wisma Indocement, Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara yang dimoderatori oleh S.A.M August ini menghadirkan empat narasumber yang kredibel dalam bidang nutrisi yaitu Franciscus Welirang dari PT. Indofood Sukses Makmur Tbk, Andi Prasetyo mewakili Japfa Foundation, dr. Amaranila Lalita Drijono yang merupakan <em>founder</em> dari Gerakan Makanan Sehat Anak Sekolah (GEMMAS), dan Nugroho Indera dari Plan International Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202016-12-20%20at%203.13.56%20PM.jpeg\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai pembuka, Franciscus Welirang memaparkan bahwa masalah nutrisi berkaitan dengan SDGs nomor dua yaitu tanpa kelaparan. Mengingat pada tahun 2013 bahwa 37,2 % dari total penduduk Indonesia mengalami stunting dimana NTT menduduki peringkat teratas, sebagai provinsi yang paling banyak mengalami kasus stunting. Menurutnya, kriteria <em>under nutrition</em> meliputi kekurangan viatamin A (KVA), gangguan akibat kekurangan iodium (GAKI), gizi kurang, stunting, dan anemia. Sebagai bagian dari sektor bisnis, Indofood membantu pengentasan malnutrisi dengan berbagai cara. Salah satunya adalah kerjasama dengan PDRC FKM-UI untuk merintis posyandu di daerah Kalibaru. Program perintisan posyandu tersebut juga diimplentasikan di tempat lain secara berkelanjutan hingga tahun 2020. Program ini menyasar tiga hal yaitu penurunan balita bawah garis merah (BGM), peningkatan kapasitas sumber daya manusia, dan pemenuhan sarana prasarana.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara Andi Prasetyo menyatakan bahwa Japfa adalah perusahaan Indonesia yang fokus sosialnya adalah mendukung pembangunan khususnya pembangunan pendidikan dan nutrisi. &nbsp;Pembentukan Japfa Foundation adalah sebagai sebuah yayasan yang membantu masyarakat. Melalui berbagai insiatif, program dan proyek pembangunan di bidang pendidikan dan nutrisi, Japfa Foundation bertekad untuk bergerak dengan akurat, akuntabel dan terukur. Salah satu tonggak gerakan pembangunan nutrisi atau gizi masyarakat adalah dengan memberikan contoh konkrit dan dapat diturunkan langsung ke berbagai lapisan masyarakat melalui Konferensi Indonesia Bergizi, INZI Creative Projects dan Inisiatif Duta Gizi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pembicara selanjutnya datang dari kalangan ahli nutrisi. &ldquo;Proses memasak merupakan hal yang penting dan dan berpengaruh untuk pembentukan pola makan yang sehat&rdquo;, demikian dr. Nila berujar. Makanan sehat mempengaruhi gizi anak yang akan berdampak pada perkembangan anak. Saat ini, rendahnya pengetahuan akan nutrisi juga terjadi di perkotaan yaitu masyarakat kelas atas. Hal ini dipengaruhi oleh iklan serta gaya hidup.&nbsp; Anak -anak di perkotaan telah diberikan kebebasan untuk memilih makanannya sendiri, namun karena keterbatasan pengetahuan serta usia, mayoritas anak tidak memilih makanan yang sehat. Di sisi lain, 12 tahun pertama merupakan masa emas untuk anak. Menurut dr. Nila, periode pendidikan di usia SD juga mempengaruhi kebiasaan makan anak di kemudian hari. Oleh karena inilah <em>food education</em> harus dapat dijadikan kebijakan strategis bangsa.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_141303.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Narasumber terakhir adalah Plan International Indonesia yang menjelaskan mengenai program mereka dalam mengatasi nutrisi anak dan ibu. Dari seluruh kawasan yang ada di Indonesia, Indonesia Timur sering dianggap sebagai kawasan miskin dengan tingkat kesehatan yang rendah. Hal ini membuat Plan International Indonesia kerap menjadikan wilayah tersebut sebagai wilayah kerjanya. Menurut Nugroho Indera, tantangan ke depan mengenai permasalahan nutrisi di Indonesia adalah peran aktif semua lapisan masyarakat dan koordinasi lintas sektor, termasuk filantropi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">PLF 12 ini menyimpulkan bahwa sektor swasta dan filantropi sangat berperan dalam pengembangan nutrisi bangsa. Perusahaan yang mengelola makanan bertanggung jawab untuk memastikan kandungan nutrisi produknya sesuai dengan kebutuhan anak dan menyehatkan. Dengan adanya kesadaran bersama, termasuk pihak pemerintah, sekolah dan keluarga, maka tingkat gizi dan nutrisi anak Indonesia dapat ditingkatkan dan diperbaiki tanpa harus banyak menguras sumber daya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Materi presentasi Narasumber PLF 12 dapat diunduh di sini:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6sueDFJVkMwWmxtaHM?usp=sharing\"><input name=\"MATERI PLF 12\" type=\"button\" value=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6sueDFJVkMwWmxtaHM?usp=sharing\" /></a></p>\n', 'f39c1a2621b805aa917984c1d945896d.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-17 05:02:31', '2018-02-19 14:51:23', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-peran-filantropi-dalam-penanganan-nutrisi-bangsa', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'Whu0h44d1EhnB3T', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(402, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] The Role of Philanthropy in Developing National Nutrition', '', 'Report of the 12th PLF on philanthropy and nutrition', '<p>Healthy eating is not always just about which foods to eat, it is also related to eating habits and knowledge about food safety. In order to ensure this knowledge reaches as many people as possible, we need a sustainable, well-planned, and measurable partnership with all stakeholders to overcome the problems about nutrition in Indonesia. That is why the Indonesia Philanthropy Association held the 12<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Philanthropy Learning Forum on December 20, 2016, in Wisma Indocement, Jakarta with the theme being &lsquo;The Role of Philanthropy in Developing National Nutrition&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>There were four speakers at this event: Franciscus Welirang from PT Indofood, Sukses Makmur Tbk, Andi Prasetyo from Japfa Foundation, Dr. Amaranila Lalita Drijono, founder of&nbsp;<em>Gerakan Makanan Sehat Anak Sekolah</em>(GEMMAS - a healthy food movement for students at school), and Nugroho Indera from Plan International Indonesia. The discussion was moderated by S.A.M August.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202016-12-20%20at%203.13.56%20PM%281%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>As an opening, Franciscus Welirang reminded the audience that nutrition is incorporated in Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) number 2, Zero Hunger. &nbsp;In 2013, a startling 37.2 percent of the Indonesian population suffered from stunted growth with Nusa Tenggara Timur (NTT) having the highest incidence of stunting in Indonesia. According to Mr. Welirang, the criteria for malnutrition in children are a lack of vitamin A and iodine, malnutrition, stunting, and anaemia. As a part of its business plan, Indofood helps in eradicating malnutrition through various means. For example, Indofood collaborated with PDRC (Positive Deviance Resource Centre) FKM (Faculty of Public Health) at the University of Indonesia, and initiated Posyandu (Pusat Pelayanan Terpadu or Integrated Services Centre) in Kalibaru. These programs will also be implemented in other regions until 2020. There are three targets underlying these programs: decreasing the number of infants below the red line (Bawah Garis Merah/BGM), improving the capacity of human resources, and improvement of health infrastructures.</p>\n\n<p>The second speaker was Andi Prasetyo from JAPFA Foundation. He explained that as a company, Japfa has a social focus, which is to support the development of education and nutrition. Through its many initiatives, programs, and projects in education and nutrition, Japfa Foundation has committed itself to maintain accuracy, accountability, and measurability. One of the milestones in the nutrition programs development was by giving a real example that applies to the society, through the Indonesia Nutrition Conference, INZI Creative Projects, and Nutrition Ambassador.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The next speaker was health and nutrition expert, Dr. Nila. She stated that the &ldquo;Cooking process is the most important part and it affects to formation of healthy eating patterns&rdquo;. Healthy food influences children&rsquo;s nutrition and it also affects their development. However, she continued, there is a limited knowledge of nutrition in major cities, ever amongst the upper economic class. Eating habits are instead heavily influenced by advertisements and life style. Children in the cities have freedom to choose what they eat, and because of their limited knowledge and young age, most children do not choose healthy food. This is concerning because the first &lsquo;12 years&rsquo; is an essential period of children&rsquo;s development. According to Dr. Nila, the elementary school period influences the eating habit of the children in the future. That is why food education has to be implemented as a strategic national policy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/P_20161220_141303%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>The last speaker was Nugroho Indera from Plan International Indonesia who discussed a program aimed at addressing nutrition problems present in mothers and children. Out of all regions in Indonesia, East Indonesia is often considered as the poorest with a correspondingly low level of health. This prompted Plan International Indonesia to begin operations in East Indonesia. According to Nugroho Indera, the future challenge about addressing nutrition problems in Indonesia involves an active role for society and the need for cross sector collaboration, especially philanthropy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The 12<sup>th&nbsp;</sup>Philanthropy Learning Forum concluded with the observation that private sectors and philanthropy organisations have prominent roles in developing the nutrition levels of the nation. Companies that produce food are responsible to ensuring the nutrition of the products is in keeping with the needs of children. Knowledge disseminated by relevant bodies including government, schools, and families can help in improving the level of children&rsquo;s nutrition without a significant increase in spending.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Download the presentations of the speakers here (in Bahasa Indonesia):</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6sueDFJVkMwWmxtaHM\">https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6sueDFJVkMwWmxtaHM</a></p>\n', 'f39c1a2621b805aa917984c1d945896d.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-17 05:02:31', '2018-02-19 14:51:23', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-the-role-of-philanthropy-in-developing-national-nutrition', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'Whu0h44d1EhnB3T', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(407, 'Workshop Pasca-Lab untuk Pendanaan Program Vaksinasi di Asia Tenggara - Milken Institute', '', 'Workshop kali ini merupakan tindak lanjut dari worskhop pertama yang diselenggarakan oleh Milken Institute pada bulan Juli 2016. Tujuannya adalah untuk mengimplementasikan ide pembiayaan yang dihasilkan di Lab dan untuk mendukung proyek demonstrasi demam berdarah dari Departemen Kesehatan di Jakarta dan daerah lainnya. ', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic;\">Workshop Pasca-Lab untuk Pendanaan Program Vaksinasi di Asia Tenggara</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sesi kelompok kerja ini merupakan kelanjutan dari perbincangan awal&nbsp;Inovasi keuangan Lab dari Milken Institute sebelumnya, &quot;Model Baru untuk Pembiayaan Program Vaksinasi di Asia Tenggara&quot;, yang diselenggarakan pada 29 Juli 2016 di Jakarta. Peserta di Lab mengeksplorasi hambatan-hambatan&nbsp;dalam memperkenalkan vaksin baru di Indonesia, dengan fokus khusus pada: 1) tantangan biaya pengadaan, 2) pelatihan tenaga kesehatan, dan 3) penerimaan masyarakat terhadap vaksinasi. Solusi pembiayaan dan daftar peserta yang hadir dapat dibaca di <a href=\"http://assets1c.milkeninstitute.org/assets/Publication/InnovationLab/PDF/VaxPrgrmsSEAsia4WEB.pdf\">laporan</a> yang dapat diunduh&nbsp;mengenai &quot;Model Baru untuk Pembiayaan Program Vaksinasi di Asia Tenggara&quot;.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Untuk mengatasi hambatan ini, Lab dibahas mekanisme pembiayaan yang inovatif, termasuk pengembangan obligasi dampak, program bantuan tunai bersyarat, dan dana pengadaan menggenang. peserta diusulkan proyek percontohan yang akan menggunakan solusi pembiayaan tersebut untuk mendanai roll-out dari dengue baru vaksin di Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Financing%20Vaccination%20Programs%20-%20Work%20Session%20Feb%208%2C%202017.pdf\">Unduh AGENDA Workshop</a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Untuk mengetahui lebih lanjut mengenai Financial Innovations Lab, <a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Financial%20Innovations%20Lab%20-%20Global%20Challenges.pdf\">unduh di sini untuk membaca RINGKASAN</a></p>\n', 'bb22e31ba1d51cf4f7311c5e486e2670.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-19 02:15:45', '2017-01-19 09:15:44', 5, 'workshop-pasca-lab-untuk-pendanaan-program-vaksinasi-di-asia-tenggara-milken-institute', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'YGlIYiXkMoXxPfx', 'N', '', '', '2017-02-08 00:00:00', '2017-02-08 23:59:59'),
(408, 'Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia Post-Lab Working Group Session - Milken Institute', '', 'This is a follow up workshop that Milken Institute hosted back in July 2016. The goals will be to operationalize the financing ideas generated at the Lab and to support the dengue demonstration project the Ministry of Health would like to run in Jakarta and other regions.', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic;\">Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia Post-Lab Working Group Session</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This working group session is a continuation of the conversation from the previous Milken Institute Financial Innovations Lab, &ldquo;New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia&rdquo;, held on 29 July 2016 in Jakarta. Participants at the Lab explored barriers in introducing new vaccines in Indonesia, with a specific focus on: 1) the challenges of procurement costs, 2) health worker training, and 3) community acceptance of vaccinations. The financing solutions and a list of participants are available in the downloadable <a href=\"http://assets1c.milkeninstitute.org/assets/Publication/InnovationLab/PDF/VaxPrgrmsSEAsia4WEB.pdf\">report</a> on &ldquo;New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To address these barriers, the Lab discussed innovative financing mechanisms, including development impact bonds, conditional cash transfer programs, and pooled procurement funds. Participants proposed a demonstration project that will use these financing solutions to fund the roll-out of the new dengue vaccine in Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Financing%20Vaccination%20Programs%20-%20Work%20Session%20Feb%208%2C%202017%281%29.pdf\">Download the workshop&#39;s AGENDA</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">More information on Milken Institute&#39;s Financial Innovation Lab: <a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Financial%20Innovations%20Lab%20-%20Global%20Challenges%281%29.pdf\">Download SUMMARY</a></p>\n', 'bb22e31ba1d51cf4f7311c5e486e2670.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-19 02:15:45', '2017-01-19 09:15:44', 5, 'financing-vaccination-programs-in-southeast-asia-post-lab-working-group-session-milken-institute', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'YGlIYiXkMoXxPfx', 'N', '', '', '2017-02-08 00:00:00', '2017-02-08 23:59:59'),
(409, 'Focus Group Discussion Kajian Kebijakan yang Mendukung dan Tidak Mendukung Keterlibatan dan Peran Serta Filantropi dalam Mendorong Pencapaian Target SDG di Indonesia', '', 'Focus Group Discussion ini akan membahas hasil kajian terhadap kebijakan-kebijakan pemerintah berdasarkan penelitian Atmajaya. Tujuan penelitian ini adalah untuk mengidentifikasi dan menganalisis produk-produk hukum negara yang mendukung dan tidak mendukung keterlibatan dan peran serta filantropi dalam mendorong pencapaian target SDGs di Indonesia', '<h1>LATAR BELAKANG</h1>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SDGs merupakan agenda pembangunan yang komprehensif dan tidak terpisahkan dengan agenda pembangunan nasional. Dengan memiliki 17 tujuan yang terintegrasi dan 169 target turunan, dapat dimaknai bahwa tujuan SDGs bersifat <em>interrelated</em> dan <em>interdependent</em>. Selain tambahan pada tujuan agenda pembangunan global sebelumnya, di dalam SDGs juga terdapat beberapa tujuan yang belum terselesaikan secara penuh, seperti pengakhiran kemiskinan dalam segala bentuk, status nutrisi, kesehatan ibu dan anak, akses terhadap air bersih dan sanitasi, kesetaraan gender dan pemberdayaan perempuan, ketersediaan anggaran, serta perubahan iklim dan energi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Oleh karenanya, untuk mencapai tujuan-tujuan tersebut diperlukan koordinasi lintas pemangku kepentingan dan peran aktif masyarakat. Peran para pemangku kepentingan di sini tidak hanya dari segi pelaksanaan, namun juga dari segi pemantauan, mengingat target SDGs yang lebih luas. Untuk itu, proses implementasi SDGs ini diharapkan dapat dijalankan dengan efektif jika dimulai dengan mengumpulkan informasi tentang apa saja yang akan menjadi tantangan dan hambatan dalam pencapaian target-target sehingga dapat segera diantisipasi oleh semua pihak, termasuk kebijakan-kebijakan pembangunan Indonesia.</p>\n\n<h1>AKTIVITAS KEGIATAN</h1>\n\n<p><em>Focus Group Discussion</em> hasil penelitian:</p>\n\n<p><strong>KAJIAN KEBIJAKAN YANG MENDUKUNG DAN TIDAK MENDUKUNG KETERLIBATAN DAN PERAN SERTA FILANTROPI DALAM MENDORONG PENCAPAIAN TARGET SDGS</strong></p>\n\n<p><em>Focus Group Discussion</em> akan dilaksanakan pada hari <strong>Senin, 23 Januari 2017</strong>, di UNIKA ATMA JAYA<strong>. </strong>FGD ini dilakukan dengan mengundang anggota-anggota dan mitra dari Filantropi Indonesia (undangan tertutup).</p>\n', '761f4575d7414b53174e4b150334e5b6.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-19 02:33:08', '2017-01-19 09:33:08', 5, 'focus-group-discussion-kajian-kebijakan-yang-mendukung-dan-tidak-mendukung-keterlibatan-dan-peran-serta-filantropi-dalam-mendorong-pencapaian-target-sdg-di-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'cE2dCOiEDggwLXF', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-23 00:00:00', '2017-01-23 23:59:59'),
(410, 'Focus Group Discussion on Policy Studies Which Support or Do Not Support the Engagement and Participation of Philanthropy in Promoting the Achievement of SDG in Indonesia', '', 'This Focus Group Discussion will discuss the results of a study of government policies based on the research by Atma Jaya University. The purpose of this study is to identify and analyze the products of law that support and does not support the involvement and participation of philanthropy in encouraging the achievement of SDGs in Indonesia', '<h1>BACKGROUND</h1>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SDG&nbsp;is a comprehensive development agenda and should be integrated&nbsp;national development agenda. By having an integrated 17 objectives and 169 targets derivatives, can be interpreted that the destination SDGs are interrelated and interdependent. In addition to additional destinations global development agenda earlier, in the SDGs are also several destinations that have not been resolved fully, such as the termination of poverty in all its forms, nutritional status, maternal and child health, access to clean water and sanitation, gender equality and the empowerment of women, the availability of budget, as well as climate change and energy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Therefore, to achieve these goals required the coordination of multi-stakeholder and active role of the community. The role of stakeholders here not only in terms of implementation, but also in terms of monitoring, given the broader SDGs targets. To that end, the implementation process is expected SDGs can be run effectively if it starts with collecting information about what will be the challenges and obstacles in the achievement of targets that can be anticipated by all parties, including the development policies of Indonesia.</p>\n\n<h1>ACTIVITIES&nbsp;</h1>\n\n<p>Focus Group Discussion of the research:</p>\n\n<p>ASSESSMENT OF POLICIES WHICH&nbsp;SUPPORT AND DO&nbsp;NOT SUPPORT THE ENGAGEMENT AND PARTICIPATION OF PHILANTHROPY IN PROMOTING THE ACHIEVEMENT OF SDGs</p>\n\n<p>The Focus Group Discussion will be held on Monday, January 23, 2017, in UNIKA ATMAJAYA. Invitations&nbsp;are only for&nbsp;members and partners of the Indonesian Philanthropy Association (closed invitation).</p>\n', '761f4575d7414b53174e4b150334e5b6.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-19 02:33:08', '2017-01-19 09:33:08', 5, 'focus-group-discussion-on-policy-studies-which-support-or-do-not-support-the-engagement-and-participation-of-philanthropy-in-promoting-the-achievement-of-sdg-in-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'cE2dCOiEDggwLXF', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-23 00:00:00', '2017-01-23 23:59:59'),
(411, 'New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia', '', '', '', 'Milken_Institute.jpg', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-01-19 02:36:32', '2017-01-19 09:37:44', 5, 'new-models-for-financing-vaccination-programs-in-southeast-asia', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'Milken_Institute-New_Models_for_Financing_Vaccination_Programs_in_SE_Asia.pdf', '', '', '', 'Jruio420ewi4uIU', 'EMb5mr5a36H6HM1', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(412, 'New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia', '', '', '', 'Milken_Institute.jpg', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-01-19 02:36:32', '2017-01-19 09:37:44', 5, 'new-models-for-financing-vaccination-programs-in-southeast-asia', 'download', 0, '', 'en', 'Milken_Institute-New_Models_for_Financing_Vaccination_Programs_in_SE_Asia.pdf', '', '', '', 'Jruio420ewi4uIU', 'EMb5mr5a36H6HM1', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(415, 'Focus Group Discussion: PENELITIAN TENTANG INSENTIF PAJAK UNTUK KEGIATAN FILANTROPI', '', 'PSHK, bekerja sama dengan Filantropi Indonesia (FI) dan Knowledge Sector Initiative (KSI), mengadakan penelitian tentang insentif pajak untuk filantropi. Sebagai bagian dari penelitian tersebut, PSHK bermaksud mengadakan Focus Group Discussion untuk memperoleh masukan, pendapat, dan usulan dari para narasumber yang dianggap memiliki pengetahuan dan pengalaman.', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>PENELITIAN TENTANG INSENTIF PAJAK UNTUK KEGIATAN FILANTROPI</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Focus Group Discussion</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Pusat Studi Hukum dan Kebijakan Indonesia (PSHK)</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Jakarta, 24 Januari 2017</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">PSHK, bekerja sama dengan Filantropi Indonesia (FI) dan Knowledge Sector Initiative (KSI), mengadakan penelitian tentang insentif pajak untuk filantropi. Sebagai bagian dari penelitian tersebut, PSHK bermaksud mengadakan <em>Focus Group Discussion </em>untuk memperoleh masukan, pendapat, dan usulan dari para narasumber yang dianggap memiliki pengetahuan dan pengalaman, khususnya mengenai permasalahan akan pelaksanaan insentif pajak di Indonesia. Hasil FGD akan ditindaklanjuti oleh tim PSHK dan diharapkan dapat memberikan kontribusi untuk pengembangan kebijakan insentif pajak yang jelas bagi filantropi, dapat diakses secara luas, dan dapat digunakan secara efektif oleh para pemangku kepentingan. Selanjutnya, laporan penelitian ini juga diharapkan dapat diadopsi oleh pembuat kebijakan agar tercipta lingkungan yang kondusif bagi filantropi di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tujuan kegiatan ini untuk memperoleh masukan, pendapat, dan usulan dari para narasumber dalam rangka menciptakan alternatif solusi bagi permasalahan pelaksanaan insentif pajak terhadap filantropi di Indonesia. Hasil dari laporan penelitian ini diharapkan dapat menjadi acuan dalam perubahan kebijakan yang berkaitan dengan insentif pajak bagi filantropi di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Focus Group Discussion </em>akan diikuti oleh 20 (dua puluh) orang peserta. Para narasumber terdiri dari unsur pembuat kebijakan, praktisi, unsur organisasi non-profit, unsur lembaga filantropi, dan unsur donor.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pada awal diskusi, akan ada dua pemicu diskusi yang akan diminta untuk memaparkan beberapa isu terkait dengan kebijakan insentif pajak untuk filantropi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20FGD%20Insentif%20Pajak%20Filantropi%2024%20Jan%202017.pdf\">UNDUH TOR</a></p>\n', 'a91b4379a28713cf976cb32efd4892c8.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-23 10:08:02', '2017-01-23 17:08:01', 5, 'focus-group-discussion-penelitian-tentang-insentif-pajak-untuk-kegiatan-filantropi', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'FOHDabraaeUY3VV', 'N', '', '', '2017-01-24 00:00:00', '2017-01-24 23:59:59');
