(430, 'Global Festival of Ideas for Sustainable Development 2017', '', 'The Global Festival of Ideas is the first in a series of annual forums, hosted by the UN SDG Action Campaign and supported by the Federal Government of Germany. The Festival brings together leading thinkers, policy-makers and civil society, together with gaming experts and policy simulators, to deliver the world’s first playable policy conference.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Global Festival of Ideas for Sustainable Development is brought to you by the UN SDG Action campaign and the Overseas Development Institute (ODI), together with Cepei, Data-Pop Alliance, Plan International, Salzburg Global Seminar, the World Food Programme (WFP) and the World Resources Institute (WRI). New partners are welcomed &ndash; the organisers are committed to working with many organisations from different regions and sectors to produce an event that is dynamic and innovative, and built on the best knowledge and experience.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa;font-style:italic;\">About the Festival</h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On 25 September 2015, the 193 member states of the United Nations agreed a global agenda, unprecedented in its scope and ambition. If successful, the attainment of the 17 Sustainable Development Goals by 2030 will represent a leap forward in the fight against poverty and inequality, as well as the struggle for environmental sustainability.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The goals were agreed after a global consultation between the UN, governments, civil society, youth groups, business, academia and millions of citizens. Taken together, they represent a holistic agenda, which can only succeed if policy areas often deemed to be in opposition can be reconciled. The Global Festival of Ideas will allow participants a unique opportunity to chart new thinking on how to overcome seemingly conflicting, and contradictory, objectives.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Global Festival of Ideas is the first in a series of annual forums, hosted by the UN SDG Action Campaign and supported by the Federal Government of Germany. The Festival brings together leading thinkers, policy-makers and civil society, together with gaming experts and policy simulators, to deliver&nbsp;<strong>the world&rsquo;s first playable policy conference</strong>.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Too often, policy-makers focus on one development objective, at the expense of others. But in the SDG era, a radically different approach must be found: we must be able to promote economic growth and prosperity with environmental sustainability; we must challenge inequality and exclusion in a rapidly globalising world; and we must find ways of protecting individuals and communities caught up in conflict or affected by mass migration; we must deliver effective health services, even though resources are limited.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By transforming participants from passive delegates to active players, the Festival will provoke new thinking on these global challenges, involving policy-makers, the private sector, investors and civil society. The interactive event will feature:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>High level plenary sessions, presentations, discussion and debates to share critical ideas, showcase success and hear from keynote speakers.</li>\n	<li>Real time problem-solving through policy simulations and participatory games based on interactive technology, built by expert game designers.</li>\n	<li>Innovation hubs that showcase the work of wide variety of organisations.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The festival will be held in Bonn, Germany on March 1-3, 2017.</p>\n\n<p>For more information on the event and how to register please visit the <a href=\"http://globalfestivalofideas.org/\">OFFICIAL WEBSITE</a></p>\n', '8a726a77ac49621e2db217810292e65a.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-27 03:50:27', '2017-01-27 10:50:27', 5, 'global-festival-of-ideas-for-sustainable-development-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', '1IYiEiqa17FD3gY', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-01 00:00:00', '2017-03-03 23:59:59'),
(431, 'The State of Venture Philanthropy and Social Investment (VP/SI) in Europe – The EVPA Survey 2015/2016', '', '', '', 'f44727677afde8d04f7dc53546b7de5d.png', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-01-27 04:22:18', '2017-01-27 11:22:18', 5, 'the-state-of-venture-philanthropy-and-social-investment-vp-si-in-europe-the-evpa-survey-2015-2016', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'The_state_of_Venture_Philanthropy_and_Social_Investiment_in_Europe_2015-2016_survey.pdf', '', '', '', 'Uej408Ieo348054', 'uWsxlrIxqBYplnh', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(432, 'The State of Venture Philanthropy and Social Investment (VP/SI) in Europe – The EVPA Survey 2015/2016', '', '', '', 'f44727677afde8d04f7dc53546b7de5d.png', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-01-27 04:22:18', '2017-01-27 11:22:18', 5, 'the-state-of-venture-philanthropy-and-social-investment-vp-si-in-europe-the-evpa-survey-2015-2016', 'download', 0, '', 'en', 'The_state_of_Venture_Philanthropy_and_Social_Investiment_in_Europe_2015-2016_survey.pdf', '', '', '', 'Uej408Ieo348054', 'uWsxlrIxqBYplnh', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(435, 'The 20th Annual Milken Institute Global Conference', '', 'The Global Conference convenes some of the world\'s most extraordinary people to explore solutions to today\'s most pressing challenges in financial markets, industry sectors, health, government and education. Where others see problems, we seek solutions. ', '<h2 style=\"font-style: italic; text-align: center;\">The 20th Annual Milken Institute Global Conference</h2>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style: italic; text-align: center;\">&quot;BUILDING MEANINGFUL LIVES&quot;&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: rgb(170, 170, 170); font-style: italic; text-align: center;\">The Beverley Hilton, Los Angeles</h3>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Global Conference convenes the best minds in the world to tackle the most stubborn challenges. That commitment to the power of ideas has set this event apart for two decades. It is a unique setting in which the individuals with the capital, power and influence to move the world meet face-to-face with those whose expertise and creativity are reinventing industry, philanthropy and media.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Expand your network of accomplished and influential people - 3,500 attendees from 50 countries, all senior decision-makers in their fields.</p>\n\n<p>For more information visit the <a href=\"http://www.cvent.com/events/2017-milken-institute-global-conference/event-summary-6c6c3f78682540ae95b73d44a279f750.aspx\">EVENT WEBSITE</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'c798f21e2957c809290d75c38686c2d9.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-31 06:06:13', '2017-01-31 13:06:13', 5, 'the-20th-annual-milken-institute-global-conference', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'dkqLe6OCJJl0j6w', 'N', '', '', '2017-04-30 00:00:00', '2017-05-03 23:59:59'),
(436, 'The 20th Annual Milken Institute Global Conference', '', 'The Global Conference convenes some of the world\'s most extraordinary people to explore solutions to today\'s most pressing challenges in financial markets, industry sectors, health, government and education. Where others see problems, we seek solutions. ', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic; text-align:center\">The 20th Annual Milken Institute Global Conference</h2>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic; text-align:center\">&quot;BUILDING MEANINGFUL LIVES&quot;&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:rgb(170, 170, 170); font-style:italic; text-align:center\">The Beverley Hilton, Los Angeles</h3>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Global Conference convenes the best minds in the world to tackle the most stubborn challenges. That commitment to the power of ideas has set this event apart for two decades. It is a unique setting in which the individuals with the capital, power and influence to move the world meet face-to-face with those whose expertise and creativity are reinventing industry, philanthropy and media.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Expand your network of accomplished and influential people - 3,500 attendees from 50 countries, all senior decision-makers in their fields.</p>\n\n<p>For more information visit the <a href=\"http://www.cvent.com/events/2017-milken-institute-global-conference/event-summary-6c6c3f78682540ae95b73d44a279f750.aspx\">EVENT WEBSITE</a></p>\n', 'c798f21e2957c809290d75c38686c2d9.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-31 06:06:13', '2017-01-31 13:06:13', 5, 'the-20th-annual-milken-institute-global-conference', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'dkqLe6OCJJl0j6w', 'N', '', '', '2017-04-30 00:00:00', '2017-05-03 23:59:59'),
(437, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Zakat On SDGs', '', 'Laporan pelaksanaan Philanthropy Learning Forum pertama di tahun 2017, Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan Baznas dan UNDP untuk membahas topik menarik terkait Zakat on SDGs. PLF 13 ini memecahkan rekor dengan jumlah peserta terbanyak, mencapai 150 orang.', '<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">Zakat On SDGs: Potensi, Peran, Dan Tantangan Pendayagunaan Zakat Untuk Mendukung SDGs</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada Kamis, 26 Januari 2017 Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan Badan Amil Zakat Nasional (BAZNAS) dan&nbsp; United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) menggelar Philanthropy Learning Forum (PLF) 13. Bertempat di kantor UNDP yang berada di Menara Thamrin, tema yang diangkat dalam PLF 13 kali ini adalah Zakat On SDGs: Potensi, Peran, Dan Tantangan Pendayagunaan Zakat Untuk Mendukung SDGs. Tema ini diambil mengingat zakat dapat menjadi sumber daya alternatif dalam mendukung pencapaian SDGs di Indonesia serta sumber daya filantropi yang paling potensial di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pemateri pertama, Wahyuningsih Darajati yang merupakan Direktur Kehutanan Dan Konservasi Sumber Daya Air Kementrian PPN/ Bappenas mengatakan perlu dibuat perpres mengenai SDGs. Belia juga memaparkan 4 pilar SDGs yaitu pilar pembangunan sosial, pilar pembangunan ekonomi, pilar pembangunan lingkungan, dan pilar pembangunan hukum dan tata kelola. Dalam rangka pencapaian SDGs maka dibentuk Tim Koordinasi Nasional yaitu Dewan Pengarah, Tim Pelaksana, Kelompok Kerja, dan Dewan Pakar. Dewan Pengarah merupakan Presiden dengan dibantu 4 menteri. Sementara untuk tim pelaksana berada di bawah tanggung jawab Bappenas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0128.png\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara itu, Nana Mintarti yang merupakan anggota Baznas menyatakan bahwa di Indonesia ada trend peningkatan ZIS (Zakat, Infaq, Shadaqoh) dari tahun ke tahun, meskipun belum didukung perkembangan implementasinya. Berdasarkan data dari UIN Syarif Hidayahtullah, apabila benar-benar dikembangkan potensi data zakat nasional dapat mencapai Rp. 19,3 triliun. Fakta lain diungkapkan beliau bahwa di Indonesia, zakat paling banyak bukan dikeluarkan oleh individu tetapi lembaga. Selain itu beliau juga membahas mengenai proposi penyaluran utama zakat yang masih kebanyakan untuk bidang sosial dan pendidikan. Ibu Nana juga mengingatkan bahwa diperlukan audit syariah dari Kementrian Agama agar manajemen zakat dapat berjalan baik.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai pemateri terakhir, Haidar Bagir menegaskan bahwa harus dibedakan antara zakat, infaq, dan sedekah. Akan ada banyak manfaat apabila zakat dikaitkan dengan SDGs. Berkaitan dengan itu, ia menambahkan bahwa di antara 8 asnaf, ada makna bahwa amil berhak atas zakat meskipun mereka kaya. Dalam hal ini berarti amil berhak dalam pengelolaan zakat. Ia juga mepertegas untuk jangan merekut amil karena mereka tidak memiliki kerjaan. Oleh karena itu dibutuhkan <em>resource</em> zakat yang mumpuni baik nasional maupun internasional. Integrasi zakat ke dalam SDGs bukanlah sebuah perkara yang mudah karena ada beberapa tantangan yang harus dijawab. Apakah SDGs sudah sesuai dengan asnaf? SDGs bersifat universal tanpa memandang agama, apakah zakat bisa demikian?</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0186.png\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tidak dapat dipungkiri bahwa Lembaga Amil Zakat (LAZ) juga telah berkembang pesat di Indonesia. Sering kali terjadi tindakan mengklaim keberhasilan dan kesuksesan pemberdayaan masyarakat diantara LAZ. Tentu tindakan tersebut tidak dapat dibenarkan, karena untuk mewujudkan sistem pengelolaan zakat yang mumpuni diperlukan kerjasama antar berbagai pihak. Oleh karena itulah untuk masing-masing poin SDGs yang berjumlah 17 perlu diciptakan suatu indikator yang dapat digunakan oleh lembaga zakat dalam pengelolan zakat, beserta metodologinya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6suRU5yLVBrQUZMOFk\">DOWNLOAD SPEAKERS PRESENTATION</a></p>\n', 'dac3d34837a024c8bf6c4167f9e70292.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-31 10:15:48', '2018-02-19 14:55:20', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-zakat-on-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '6nr10qYHAdufi1r', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(438, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Zakat on SDGs', '', 'The report of the first Philanthropy Learning Forum in 2017, Indonesia Philanthropy Association in partnership with Baznas (National Zakat Agency) and UNDP brought up an exciting theme about Zakat on SDGs. The 13th PLF broke the record for most attendees, with 150 participants.', '<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">Zakat on SDGs: Potential, Roles, and Implication Challenges to Support SDGs</h2>\n\n<p>On Thursday January 26 2017, in partnership with the National Zakat Agency (BAZNAS) and the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP), the Indonesia Philanthropy Association (FI) held Philanthropy Learning Forum for the thirteenth time. The event took place at the UNDP office located in Menara Thamrin, with the theme &ldquo;Zakat on SDGs: Potential, Roles, Implications and Challenges in Supporting SDGs&rdquo;.&nbsp;This theme is important to consider given that zakat exists as one of the most potentially effective alternative sources in supporting SDGs in Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The first speaker, Wahyuningsih Darajati who is the Director of Forestry and Conservation of Water Resources Ministry of Planning / Bappenas said that there needs to be a Presidential Decree regarding SDGs.&nbsp;She also mentioned about the four pillars of SDGs: the pillars of social development, economic development, environmental development and law and governance.&nbsp;To pursue the SDGs, the government formed the National Coordination Team which consists of an Advisory Board, Executive Team, Working Group, and the Board of Experts.&nbsp;The President is one member of the Advisory Board and he is assisted by four ministers.&nbsp;The implementation team is managed by Bappenas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0128%281%29.png\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Nana Mintarti, who is a member of Baznas, said that in Indonesia the trend of ZIS (Zakat, Infaq, Shadaqoh) is increasing every year, although it has not been supported by any progress of implementation.&nbsp;Based on data from UIN Syarif Hidayatullah, if the potential national zakat (charity) is completely developed it can reach up to IDR&nbsp;19,3 trillion.&nbsp;Another fact revealed that in Indonesia, most zakat is not issued by an individual but an institution.&nbsp;In addition, she also discussed about the proportion of the primary distribution of zakat, which is heavily dedicated to social and educational programs.&nbsp;She also reminded that it is necessary to implement sharia audits by the Ministry of Religion so that zakat can be managed effectively.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">As the last speaker, Haidar Bagir stressed that we should distinguish between zakat, infaq, and shadaqoh.&nbsp;There will be many benefits if zakat is associated with the SDGs. He also added that among the ashnaf (those entitled to receive zakat), there is the condition that amil (the collectors and distributers of zakat) are entitled to zakat for their role in its management, even though they are often wealthy.&nbsp;Therefore, there needs to be a qualified zakat&nbsp;resource&nbsp;both nationally and globally.&nbsp;Integrating zakat into SDGs is not an easy task because of religious interpretation challenges.&nbsp;Are SDGs in accordance with ashnaf groups?&nbsp;SDGs have universal value regardless of religion; can zakat be utilised in the same way?</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0186%281%29.png\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It is undeniable that Amil Zakat Institutions (LAZ) have been growing rapidly in Indonesia.&nbsp;Often, they claim the success of community empowerment over the other zakat organisations.&nbsp;However, to implement an effective zakat management system there should be strong partnership between the various parties.&nbsp;Therefore, for each of the 17 SDGs, it is necessary to create specific indicators and methodologies, outside those provided by the SDGs themselves, that can be used by institutions in their management of zakat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6suRU5yLVBrQUZMOFk\">DOWNLOAD SPEAKERS PRESENTATION</a></p>\n', 'dac3d34837a024c8bf6c4167f9e70292.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-01-31 10:15:48', '2018-02-19 14:55:20', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-zakat-on-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '6nr10qYHAdufi1r', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(439, 'Diseminasi Hasil Studi: Kesiapan Lembaga Filantropi Indonesia  dalam Mendukung Pencapaian SDGs', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan PIRAC dalam melakukan studi bertajuk \"Kesiapan Lembaga Filantropi Indonesia dalam Mendukung Pencapaian SDGs\". Forum ini merupakan bentuk diseminasi kepada publik mengenai hasil penelitian yang akan berguna untuk setiap aktor di berbagai sektor pembangunan.', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSde-kmn-EL_4h6JKfqEODgGy3mVHxTuSrM17xkd_YyrRgPaOw/viewform?usp=sf_link\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202017-03-06%20at%2009.19.11.jpeg\" style=\"height:1036px; width:800px\" /></a></p>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic; text-align:center\">Studi Kesiapan Lembaga Filantropi Indonesia dalam Mendukung Pencapaian SDG</h2>\n\n<p>Penelitian ini mengkaji bagaimana kesiapan organisasi filantropi, baik berupa penerimaan pemahaman, program, sumber daya yang dimiliki organisasi, transparansi dan akuntabilitas lembaga. Hal ini didasarkan atas kesadaran bahwa agenda pembangunan global perlu untuk merangkul seluruh sektor sehingga pencapaian target SDG dapat dilakukan secara maksimal. Kerja-kerja sektor filantropi yang selama ini telah berfokus pada pembangunan masyarakat ternyata memiliki keselarasan dengan tujuan-tujuan SDG.</p>\n\n<p>Tujuan dari penelitian ini adalah untuk memetakan, mengidentifikasi, mengeksplorasi, dan menganalisis kesiapan organisasi filantropi dalam merespon agenda SDG. Penelitian ini akan melakukan eksplorasi secara detail terkait:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Peta organisasi filantropi yang berkontribusi terhadap pencapaian SDG (program, lokasi, target penerima manfaat, mitra, pelaksana program, dan lain-lain).</li>\n	<li>Tingkat pemahaman, persepsi dan penerimaan organisasi filantropi terkait dengan SDG.</li>\n	<li>Mengetahui kapasitas organisasi filantropi dalam mendukung SDG. Dalam hal ini, penelitian ini akan memotret bagaimana peran dan posisi organisasi filantropi, tantangan dan hambatan, dan rekomendasi agenda kerja dalam menghadapi SDG.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Diseminasi studi ini akan diselenggarakan atas kerja sama antara Filantropi Indonesia dan PIRAC dengan dukungan dari Kementerian Koordinator Bidang&nbsp;Pembangunan Manusia dan Kebudayaan.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Diseminasi%20Riset%20Filantropi%20SDGs_OKE.pdf\">UNDUH KERANGKA ACUAN ACARA</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6sucjM1Y2NXTF9kdjg\">UNDUH RINGKASAN RISET DAN MATERI PEMBICARA</a></p>\n', '0593094f1eaecafd3a37a0a9eba9410b.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-01 09:43:51', '2017-03-14 10:30:19', 5, 'diseminasi-hasil-studi-kesiapan-lembaga-filantropi-indonesia-dalam-mendukung-pencapaian-sdgs', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'AnkOdomRZSrXJxp', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-13 00:00:00', '2017-03-13 23:59:59'),
(440, 'Research dissemination: Readiness of Philanthropy Organization in Indonesia to support SDGs Achievement', '', 'Indonesia Philanthropy Association in partnership with PIRAC (Public Interest Research & Advocacy Center), conducted a study titled \"Readiness of Philanthropy Organization in Indonesia to support SDGs Achievement\". The purpose of this forum is to disseminate the result of the study to the public, especially to give an idea to all actors in sustainable development.', '<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSde-kmn-EL_4h6JKfqEODgGy3mVHxTuSrM17xkd_YyrRgPaOw/viewform?usp=sf_link\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202017-03-06%20at%2009.19.11%281%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:1036px; width:800px\" /></a></p>\n\n<h2 style=\"font-style:italic; text-align:center\">Readiness of Philanthropy Organizations in Indonesia to support SDGs Achievement</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This study examines whether philanthropy&nbsp;organizations are ready for SDGs, both in the form of acceptance, of understanding, programs, resources owned by the organization, transparency and accountability of institutions. It is based on the awareness that the global development agenda needs to embrace all sectors so that the achievement of SDG can be done optimally. The works of philanthropy&nbsp;sector that mostly&nbsp;focus&nbsp;on community development turned out to have an alignment with the objectives of SDG.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The purpose of this study is to map, identify, explore, and analyze readiness of philanthropic organizations in responding to the SDG agenda. This study will explore in detail:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Map of philanthropic organizations that contribute to the achievement of SDGs (program, location, target beneficiaries, partners, program managers, and others).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The level of understanding, perception and acceptance of philanthropic organizations associated with SDG.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The capacity of philanthropic organizations in support of SDG. In this case, the research will snapshot the role and position of philanthropic organizations, challenges and obstacles, and&nbsp;work agenda recommendations regarding SDG.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dissemination of this study will be held in partnership between Indonesia Philanthropy Association&nbsp;and PIRAC, with the support of&nbsp;Coordinating Ministry of Human Development and Culture.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Diseminasi%20Riset%20Filantropi%20SDGs_OKE%281%29.pdf\">DOWNLOAD TERMS OF REFERENCE</a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6sucjM1Y2NXTF9kdjg\">DOWNLOAD RESEARCH SUMMARY AND PRESENTATION MATERIALS</a></p>\n', '0593094f1eaecafd3a37a0a9eba9410b.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-01 09:43:51', '2017-03-14 10:30:19', 5, 'research-dissemination-readiness-of-philanthropy-organization-in-indonesia-to-support-sdgs-achievement', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'AnkOdomRZSrXJxp', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-13 00:00:00', '2017-03-13 23:59:59'),
(443, 'MajalahCSR.ID', '', '', '', 'b71bb9675f9896386ae3991f82fc820f.jpg', 'http://majalahcsr.id/', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-13 05:58:46', '2017-02-13 13:57:18', 5, 'majalahcsr-id', 'mitra', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'eEsBIr9A71tI6as', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(444, 'MajalahCSR.ID', '', '', '', 'b71bb9675f9896386ae3991f82fc820f.jpg', 'http://majalahcsr.id/', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-13 05:58:46', '2017-02-13 13:57:18', 5, 'majalahcsr-id', 'mitra', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'eEsBIr9A71tI6as', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(445, 'Model Pendanaan Baru Program Vaksinasi di Asia Tenggara - Post-Lab Working Group Session', '', 'Laporan kegiatan yang diadakan oleh Milken Institute di Filantropi Indonesia terkait inovasi model pendanaan program vaksinasi di Indonesia', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada hari Rabu, 8 Februari 2017 kemarin, Filantropi Indonesia menjadi tuan rumah dari sesi kedua pertemuan kelompok kerja yang diselenggarakan oleh Milken Institute dengan topik <em>New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia</em> (Model Pendanaan Baru Program Vaksinasi di Asia Tenggara). Pada pertemuan kedua ini (baca mengenai pertemuan pertama), sesi diadakan lebih pendek &ndash; setengah hari &ndash; namun tetap dihadiri oleh para pemangku kepentingan program vaksinasi di Indonesia. Peserta yang hadir mewakili semua sektor baik filantropi dan bisnis, NGO atau nonprofit dan pemerintah: World Health Organization (WHO), Universitas Gadjah Mada, ITAGI, Wahana Visi Indonesa, Yayasan Tahija, Tanoto Foundation, Clinton Health Access Initiative, Sanofi Pasteur, Kementerian Kesehatan, dan Dinas Kesehatan Pemprov DKI Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0254_edit.png\" style=\"height:416px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sesi ini ditujukan untuk menentukan hambatan mana yang perlu ditangani secara khusus serta apa solusi pendanaan yang inovatif untuk hambatan tersebut. Diskusi berlangsung hangat dan peserta sesi memberikan banyak masukan serta berbagi pengalaman dari praktek program vaksinasi yang sudah ada baik di skala nasional maupun provinsi. Milken Institue mengajukan untuk dilakukan <em>demonstration project</em> di Jakarta dan peserta mendiskusikan apa saja solusi pendanaan di tiap bentuk aktivitas (mulai dari <em>database</em>, <em>procurement</em>, implementasi dan biaya dari masyarakat).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada akhir diskusi, Caitlin MacLean dari Milken Institute menantang peserta sesi untuk membentuk steering committee dari projek ini di Indonesia agar ada koordinator dan pemangku kepentingan yang jelas dari program ini. Selanjutnya diharapkan akan ada pertemuan yang lebih intim dari tiap pemangku kepentingan termasuk sektor filantropi dan investor di Indonesia yang ingin terlibat.</p>\n', '4cdd6db7637520163698a7774a27b6b4.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-14 07:04:59', '2018-02-19 14:56:21', 5, 'model-pendanaan-baru-program-vaksinasi-di-asia-tenggara-post-lab-working-group-session', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'yhVALvwln7BU2Ec', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(446, 'New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia Post-Lab Working Group Session', '', 'Event report of a meeting organized by Milken Institute, hosted by Indonesia Philanthropy Association to discuss innovative models to finance vaccination programs in Indonesia', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On Wednesday, February 8, 2017, Indonesia Philanthropy Association hosted the second working group session on New Models for Financing Vaccination Programs in Southeast Asia, organized by the Milken Institute. The second meeting is a shorter half-day session compared to the first one, but it was also well attended by various stakeholders of vaccination programs in Indonesia. The participants represented all sectors: from philanthropy and business, to NGO or nonprofit and government. They are&nbsp;World Health Organization (WHO), the University of Gadjah Mada, ITAGI, Wahana Visi Indonesia (World Vision), Tahija Foundation, Tanoto Foundation, Clinton Health Access Initiative, Sanofi Pasteur, the Indonesian Ministry of Health, and Department of Health Jakarta Provincial Government.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0254_edit%281%29.png\" style=\"height:416px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>This session was intended to identify the barriers of vaccination programs&nbsp;and to propose innovative funding solutions to overcome them. The discussion was lively and the participants participated actively by sharing their experiences with current vaccination programs on both the national and provincial levels. Milken Institute proposed a demonstration project in Jakarta and participants discussed which funding solutions may help each activity (ranging from database and surveillance, procurement, implementation and cost to community/raising awareness).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At the end of the discussion, Caitlin MacLean of the Milken Institute session challenged all participants to create a steering committee of this project in Indonesia so there is an effective leadership for the cause. The next meeting is expected to be more intimate, and includes actors from each sector including philanthropists, donors and investors in Indonesia who want to get involved.</p>\n', '4cdd6db7637520163698a7774a27b6b4.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-14 07:04:59', '2018-02-19 14:56:21', 5, 'new-models-for-financing-vaccination-programs-in-southeast-asia-post-lab-working-group-session', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'yhVALvwln7BU2Ec', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(449, 'Diskusi Buku ', '', 'Diskusi ini merupakan bagian dari Seri Cultural Hotspot Makassar, dimana Koalisi Seni Indonesia bekerja sama dengan Tribun Timur dan Filantropi Indonesia untuk mengadakan diskusi buku dan seminar mengenai penggalangan dana untuk seni budaya', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">SERI CULTURAL HOTSPOT MAKASSAR&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:11px\">KOALISI SENI INDONESIA BEKERJA SAMA DENGAN TRIBUN TIMUR</span></span><br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI. Diskusi Buku &quot;Filantropi di Indonesia: Mengapa Tidak untuk Kesenian?&quot;</h3>\n\n<div style=\"background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Hasil penelitian PIRAC, didukung oleh Koalisi Seni Indonesia dan Filantropi Indonesia</div>\n\n<h4><u>Waktu dan lokasi:</u><br />\n<br />\nRabu, 22 Februari 2017</h4>\n\n<h4>Pukul: 10.00-12.00 WITA<br />\n<br />\nKantor Tribun Timur, Lt.4</h4>\n\n<h4>Jl. Cendrawasih No.430, Sambung Jawa, Makassar, Kota Makassar, Sulawesi Selatan 90134<br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Setelah Era Reformasi, kegiatan filantropi di Indonesia telah berkembang pesat, terutama dalam bentuk pengorganisasian dan alokasi sektoral. Kemajuan tersebut menciptakan peluang percepatan pembangunan terhadap bidang-bidang sosial di masyarakat, yang mana menjadi bagian pendukung dari agenda pembangunan pemerintah.<br />\n<br />\nSayangnya, perkembangan filantropi yang meningkat ini belum mendukung bidang kesenian. Dukungan filantropi masih teralokasi untuk bidang kesehatan, pendidikan, kemiskinan, dan sebagainya. Hal ini terbukti pada survei PIRAC mengenai pola perilaku menyumbang masyarakat dalam bentuk donasi dan sponsor. Seni budaya hanya disumbang oleh 3% responden penelitian. Dukungan untuk kesenian dari masyarakat sendiri melalui perilaku masih rendah.<br />\n<br />\nDi satu sisi, telah diresmikan PP No.93/2010 sebagai peraturan di Indonesia yang memberi keringanan insentif pajak untuk kesenian, di mana item &lsquo;seni budaya&rsquo; masuk ke dalam kategori sumbangan sosial. Kebijakan pendanaan kesenian seperti ini seharusnya dialokasikan dengan porsi yang seimbang, di mana kesenian didukung melalui anggaran pemerintah maupun sumbangan dari swasta.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nHampir seluruh negara demokratis di dunia memiliki mekanisme pendanaan dalam mengembangkan seni budaya mereka. Kesenian dipandang berkontribusi mengangkat nilai-nilai kemanusiaan, menciptakan keberagaman, dan bagian dari restorasi sosial.<br />\n<br />\nKata Kunci: Filantropi, insentif pajak, pemberdayaan ekosistem komunitas.<br />\n<br />\nPembahasan Utama:</h4>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Iklim Filantropi di Indonesia dan Daya Dukungnya terhadap Kesenian | Bapak Hamid Abidin (peneliti PIRAC)</h4>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi sebagai alternatif pendanaan kesenian</h4>\n	</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\">II. &quot;Penggalangan Dana untuk Komunitas Seni&quot;</h3>\n\n<div style=\"background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Pengetahuan Dasar tentang Cara Menggalang Dana</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><u>Waktu dan lokasi</u></h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Rabu, 22 Februari 2017</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Pukul: 13.00-15.00 WITA<br />\n<br />\nKantor Tribun Timur, Lt.4</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Jl. Cendrawasih No.430, Sambung Jawa, Makassar, Kota Makassar, Sulawesi Selatan 90134</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;<br />\nPenggalangan dana (fundraising) merupakan kegiatan yang sangat penting bagi komunitas dalam upaya mendukung jalannya program dan menjalankan roda operasionalnya. Karena perannya yang strategis, maka kegiatan fundraising seyogyanya mendapatkan perhatian khusus agar dapat berjalan secara efektif dan efisien.</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Sayangnya, sebagian besar lembaga sosial yang kurang memahami dan memberi perhatian terhadap pentingnya bagi pendanaan&nbsp; program dan keberlanjutan komunitas. Fundraising kerapkali dilakukan secara sporadis, tidak direncanakan secara matang, dan tidak diarahkan dalam rencana jangka panjang. Metode yang digunakan juga terbatas pada pengiriman proposal kepada lembaga donor lokal maupun internasional.<br />\nSementara potensi sumber dana di dalam negeri, seperti donatur perorangan, perusahaan, pemerintah dan yayasan amal, dan sumber dana lainnya belum banyak digalang. Pola penggalangan dana semacam ini terjadi karena minimnya pengetahuan dan pemahaman aktivis organisasi sosial terhadap berbagai aspek fundraising, khususnya metode penggalangan dana dari sumber daya lokal.</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Sesi ini mendatangkan Hamid Abidin, peneliti filantropi dan pendiri Sekolah Fundraising PIRAC (<a href=\"http://sekolahfundraising.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://sekolahfundraising.com</a>) dan Linda Hoemar Abidin dari Koalisi Seni Indonesia (<a href=\"http://koalisiseni.or.id/\" target=\"_blank\">http://koalisiseni.or.id</a>).<br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span class=\"marker\"><u><strong>Acara di atas gratis dan terbuka untuk umum.</strong></u></span><br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Narahubung:<br />\n<br />\nBobhy 085241776363<br />\n<br />\nCaca 087785147595</h4>\n', '749e47c353750e3aa1ee46b49b47af43.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-20 04:10:22', '2017-02-20 11:19:19', 5, 'diskusi-buku-filantropi-di-indonesia-mengapa-tidak-untuk-kesenian-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', '7m3pQeqF0EO43UT', 'N', '', '', '2017-02-22 00:00:00', '2017-02-22 23:59:59'),
(450, 'Book Discussion: ', '', 'This event is a part of the Cultural Series Hotspot Makassar, where the Koalisi Seni Indonesia (Coalition of Indonesian Arts) in cooperation with Tribun Timur and Indonesia Philanthropy Association will hold a book discussion and a seminar on fundraising for arts and culture', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">SERI CULTURAL HOTSPOT MAKASSAR&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:11px\">KOALISI SENI INDONESIA in partnership with TRIBUN TIMUR and FILANTROPI INDONESIA</span></span><br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI. Book Discussion &quot;Philanthropy in&nbsp;Indonesia: Why Not for Art?&quot;</h3>\n\n<div style=\"background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;\">PIRAC research study, supported by Koalisi Seni Indonesia and&nbsp;Filantropi Indonesia</div>\n\n<h4><u>Time and location:</u><br />\n<br />\nWednesday, 22 February&nbsp;2017<br />\n<br />\nKantor Tribun Timur, Lt.4<br />\n<br />\n10.00 am - 12.00 pm WITA</h4>\n\n<p>After the Reformation Era, philanthropy in Indonesia has been growing rapidly, especially in the form of organizing and sectoral allocations. Progress is creating opportunities accelerated development of the social sectors in the community, which became part of the supporting government&#39;s development agenda.</p>\n\n<p>Unfortunately, the development of philanthropy increased not support the arts. Support philanthropy is still allocated to health, education, poverty, and so on. This was evident in the survey accounted PIRAC about behavior patterns of society in the form of donations and sponsorships. Cultural art contributed by only 3% of respondents research. Support for the arts from the community itself through its behavior is still low.</p>\n\n<p>On the one hand, has unveiled PP 93/2010 as regulations in Indonesia that gives relief tax incentives for art, in which the items &#39;arts and culture&#39; into the category of social contribution. Arts funding policy like this should have been allocated to the portion of the balance, in which the arts are supported by the state budget and donations from the private sector.</p>\n\n<p>Almost all democratic countries in the world have a funding mechanism in developing the art of their culture. Art seen as contributing to elevate the values ??of humanity, creating diversity, and part of the social restoration.</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Keywords: philanthropy, tax incentive, community ecosystem empowerment.<br />\n<br />\nMain Discussion:</h4>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropy climate in Indonesia and Its Support Power for the Arts&nbsp;| Hamid Abidin (PIRAC researcher)</h4>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropy as an alternative resoruce for arts</h4>\n	</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\">II. &quot;Fundraising for Art Communities&quot;</h3>\n\n<div style=\"background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Basic Knowledge on How to Raise Funds</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><u>Time and location:</u></h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Wednesday, 22 February&nbsp;2017<br />\n<br />\nKantor Tribun Timur, Lt.4<br />\n<br />\n13.00-15.00 pm WITA<br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Fundraising is a very important activity for the community to support the course of the program and run the operations. Because of the strategic role, then the fundraising activities should receive special attention in order to run effectively and efficiently.</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Unfortunately, the majority of social institutions that are less understanding and give attention to the importance of funding for programs and community sustainability. Fundraising is often done sporadically, not carefully planned, and not directed for a long-term plan. The method is also limited to sending&nbsp;proposals to local and international donors.</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">While other&nbsp;potential source of funds in the country, such as individual donors, corporations, governments and charitable foundations, and other funding sources have&nbsp;not been touched. The pattern of this kind of fundraising occurs because of lack of knowledge and understanding of social activists on various aspects of the organization of fundraising, in particular the method of raising funds from local resources.</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">This session will have Hamid Abidin, a philanthropy researcher and founder of&nbsp;PIRAC Fundraising School (<a href=\"http://sekolahfundraising.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://sekolahfundraising.com</a>) and Linda Hoemar Abidin from Koalisi Seni Indonesia (<a href=\"http://koalisiseni.or.id/\" target=\"_blank\">http://koalisiseni.or.id</a>).</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><u><strong>The event is free and open for public.</strong></u><br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Contact person:<br />\n<br />\nBobhy 085241776363<br />\n<br />\nCaca 087785147595</h4>\n', '749e47c353750e3aa1ee46b49b47af43.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-20 04:10:22', '2017-02-20 11:19:19', 5, 'book-discussion-philanthropy-in-indonesia-why-not-for-art-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', '7m3pQeqF0EO43UT', 'N', '', '', '2017-02-22 00:00:00', '2017-02-22 23:59:59'),
(451, 'Menata Ulang Sistem Registrasi Penduduk Indonesia untuk Mendukung Program SDGs dan Perencanaan Pembangunan', '', '', '', '7fdc9a006763674742dfd2b899f67e72.png', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-02-24 08:24:45', '2017-02-24 15:24:45', 5, 'menata-ulang-sistem-registrasi-penduduk-indonesia-untuk-mendukung-program-sdgs-dan-perencanaan-pembangunan', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'registrasipenduduk_SMERU_Research_Institute.pdf', '', '', '', 'Kdowi2048iodkdw', 'BEMbl19WfeAAMdg', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(452, 'Reorganizing Indonesia\'s Population Registration System to Support SDGs and Development Planning Program', '', '', '', '7fdc9a006763674742dfd2b899f67e72.png', '', 0, 'N', 'P', '2017-02-24 08:24:45', '2017-02-24 15:24:45', 5, 'reorganizing-indonesia-s-population-registration-system-to-support-sdgs-and-development-planning-program', 'download', 0, '', 'en', 'registrasipenduduk_SMERU_Research_Institute.pdf', '', '', '', 'Kdowi2048iodkdw', 'BEMbl19WfeAAMdg', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(453, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Perlindungan dan Kesejahteraan Bagi Pegiat Filantropi dan Volunter', '', 'Laporan pelaksanaan PLF ke-14, di mana FI bekerja sama dengan BPJS Ketenagakerjaan untuk mengulas bagaimana negara, sektor swasta, dan organisasi sosial dapat bekerja sama untuk membangun sistem perlindungan pekerja dan relawan di bidang sosial dan pembangunan', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada Kamis, 23 Februari yang lalu, Filantropi Indonesia (FI) kembali mengadakan Philanthropy Learning Forum ke-14 yang dilaksanakan di Creative Stage, SMESCO, Jakarta. Pada kesempatan ini, FI melaksanakan PLF dengan menggandeng BPJS Ketenagakerjaan (BPJS TK) yang adalah salah satu mitra utama dalam pencapaian SDGs. Tema yang diangkat dalam forum diskusi kali ini adalah isu yang sangat penting namun seringkali terabaikan oleh organisasi sosial maupun pemberi kerja di bidang nirlaba. Karena itu narasumber yang didatangkan adalah mereka yang berperan aktif di dunia kerelawanan, aktivis HAM, serta perwakilan dari BPJS TK yang hadir untuk memberikan solusi. Mereka adalah Maria Anik Wusari, Direktur Yayasan Indonesia untuk Kemanusiaan; Marsya Anggia, Direktur Indorelawan; dan Subhan, Kepala Bidang Pemasaran BPJS TK Pusat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0321.JPG\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pekerjaan yang dilakukan para pekerja dan relawan organisasi filantropi/nirlaba tergolong pekerjaan yang rentan dan memiliki resiko yang besar. Sayangnya, para pegiat filantropi dan volunter yang mengalami kecelakaan kerja atau meninggal hanya mendapatkan santunan dalam jumlah yang tidak memadai. Menurut Anik, jaminan keselamatan dan kesejahteraan para pegiat filantropi /nirlaba dan volunter itu sebenarnya sudah diatur dalam peraturan perundang-undangan kita: dalam UU 13/2003, Undang-Undang nomor 1/1970, UU 3/1992, Peraturan Pemerintah nomor 14/1993, Keputusan Presiden nomor 22/1993, Peraturan Menteri No 1/1998 serta Peraturan Menteri nomor 4/1993. Dalam pemaparannya Anik juga menekankan bahwa para penyitas HAM dan pekerja kemanusiaan butuh diberi kemudahan akses seperti kesehatan dan jaminan kecelakaan kerja serta kematian, pelayanan psikososial, serta penggunaan sistem rujukan untuk mendukung mereka.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sedangkan Marsya dari Indorelawan membagikan pengalaman serta pelajaran mengenai pentingnya perlindungan tersebut. Pada awalnya Indorelawan hanya fokus untuk mengajak sebanyak mungkin masyarakat untuk menjadi relawan, namun setelah bekerja sama dengan suatu sekolah internasional, mereka mulai memikirkan tanggung jawab untuk keselamatan para volunter (yang adalah siswa/i) yang turun langsung ke lapangan. Marsya juga mengkhawatirkan ormas dan komunitas yang tidak berbadan hukum namun memiliki banyak volunter dalam melaksanakan kegiatannya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0338.JPG\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Subhan, perwakilan dari BPJS TK kemudian memberikan informasi mengenai program GN Lingkaran dan berbagai bentuk perlindungan dan jaminan yang bisa didapati para pegiat filantropi dan volunter. Akhirnya selama diskusi tanya jawab, banyak peserta yang aktif bertanya kepada Subhan mengenai berbagai hal &ndash; mulai dari hal teknis sampai masukan untuk perbaikan. Seperti misalnya ada pertanyaan mengenai perlindungan volunter yang hanya direkrut untuk kegiatan sosial selama satu hari; dan ternyata mereka tetap bisa dilindungi dengan membayar iuran BPJS TK untuk sebulan yang biayanya Rp 16.800,- (sudah termasuk perlindungan kecelakaan kerja dan kematian).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0353.JPG\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada dasarnya, semua setuju bahwa perlindungan dan jaminan itu diperlukan dan wajib hukumnya karena diatur dalam UU. Namun berbagai hal seperti kemudahan untuk bergabung, akses untuk registrasi, proses pendaftaran, informasi yang terbatas, serta pemahaman masyarakat yang kurang membuat banyaknya kasus di mana pegiat filantropi maupun relawan tidak dapat menikmati fasilitas ini. Hamid Abidin selaku Direktur FI, pada akhir diskusi mengusulkan adanya pilot project antara Indorelawan dan BPJS TK untuk membuat skema ideal bagi organisasi masyarakat maupun komunitas sosial agar dapat melindungi mereka yang sudah memberikan diri untuk membantu sesama.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6suMG9xZm9lbnF1NHM?usp=sharing\">DOWNLOAD MATERI PRESENTASI</a></p>\n', '77ef9f3e6bfe07d9b958d6c20dea8c7f.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-02-28 04:00:42', '2018-02-19 14:58:14', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-perlindungan-dan-kesejahteraan-bagi-pegiat-filantropi-dan-volunter', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'yrSpKJFObAhveFs', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
