(481, 'Roadshow Dialog dan Bedah Buku \"Filantropi di Indonesia: Mengapa Tidak untuk Kesenian?\"', '', 'Pergerakan Mahasiswa Islam Indonesia Rayon Ilmu Budaya, Universitas Jember mempersembahkan Dialog dan Bedah Buku \"Filantropi di Indonesia: Mengapa Tidak untuk Kesenian?\" yang didukung oleh Prosalina Jember dan Teras (teater PMII Rayon Sastra)', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20event%20buku%20kesenian%20Jember.jpeg\" style=\"height:1138px; width:804px\" /></p>\n', '714f78bc51b4cf051c37e0a5b609bd62.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-08 10:02:44', '2017-03-08 17:02:43', 5, 'roadshow-dialog-dan-bedah-buku-filantropi-di-indonesia-mengapa-tidak-untuk-kesenian-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'PbSNEzSroTol0JB', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-11 00:00:00', '2017-03-11 23:59:59'),
(482, 'Roadshow Dialogue and Book Review \"Philanthropy in Indonesia: Why not for art?\"', '', 'The Islamic Student Movement of Cultural Studies at University of Jember presents, Public Discussion and Book Review of \"Philanthropy in Indonesia: Why not for art?\", supported by Prosalina Jember and Teras (teater PMII Rayon Sastra)', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20event%20buku%20kesenian%20Jember%281%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:1133px; width:800px\" /></p>\n', '714f78bc51b4cf051c37e0a5b609bd62.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-08 10:02:44', '2017-03-08 17:02:43', 5, 'roadshow-dialogue-and-book-review-philanthropy-in-indonesia-why-not-for-art-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'PbSNEzSroTol0JB', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-11 00:00:00', '2017-03-11 23:59:59'),
(483, '[Siaran Pers] Tinggi, Minat Filantropi Dukung SDGs', '', 'Berita mengenai hasil Diskusi Publik dan Diseminasi Riset \"Kesiapan Lembaga Filantropi Indonesia dalam Mendukung Pencapaian SDGs\"', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Antusiasme lembaga-lembaga filantropi untuk terlibat dan mendukung pencapaian SDGs (<em>Sustainable Development Goals</em>) di Indonesia ternyata cukup tinggi. Hasil riset PIRAC (<em>Public Interest Research and Advocacy Center</em>) dan Filantropi Indonesia menunjukkan bahwa sebagian besar (82%) organisasi filantropi ingin terlibat dan mendukung program-program terkait SDGs. Antusiasme Dukungan ini juga ditunjang tingkat pemahaman terhadap SDGs yang tinggi serta komitmen dan kapasitas kelembagaan. Namun, dukungan lembaga filantropi belum merata ke semua tujuan SDGs dan masih terfokus pada beberapa tujuan SDGs &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hal itu tergambar dari hasil riset PIRAC dan Filantropi Indonesia<a href=\"#_ftn1\" name=\"_ftnref1\" title=\"\">[1]</a> mengenai &ldquo;<strong><em>Kesiapan Lembaga Filantropi Indonesia dalam Mendukung Pencapaian SDGs</em></strong>&rdquo;. Hasil &nbsp;penelitian ini dipresentasikan pada acara diskusi publik dan diseminasi hasil riset yang digelar di Auditorium Kemenko PMK, Jakarta, selasa siang (13/3). Acara yang dibuka oleh Menko PMK Puan Maharani ini dihadiri para pegiat filantropi, pejabat pemerintah, akademisi dan pihak-pihak yang terlibat dalam SDGs.&nbsp; &nbsp;Acara itu juga menghadirkan 3 narasumber sebagai pembahas, yakni Ghafur Akbar Dharma Putera (Staf ahli Kemenko PMK bidang SDGs Pasca 2015), Nur Efendy (Ketua FOZ/ Forum Zakat).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hasil riset PIRAC dan Filantropi Indonesia menunjukkan sebagian besar (82%) dari 85 organisasi filantropi yang menjadi responden ingin terlibat dan mendukung program-program terkait SDGs. Hanya 13% dari responden yang menjawab tidak ingin terlibat dalam SDGs. Dari jumlah tersebut, 51% diantaranya mengaku sebelumnya terlibat dalam program MDGs (Millenium Development Goals). Hal ini mengindikasikan bahwa lembaga-lembaga filantropi yang sebelumnya tidak terlibat dalam MDGs menunjukkan minat dan antusiasme untuk terlibat dalam SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tingginya minat lembaga filantropi untuk terlibat dan berperan dalam program-program SDGs itu dipengaruhi oleh pemahaman dan persepsi mereka terhadap SDGs. Hasil riset menunjukkan bahwa 73% responden mengetahui tentang SDGs. Riset juga memetakan 3 tingkatan pengetahuan lembaga filantropi dalam memahami SDGs. <em>Pertama</em>, responden hanya mengetahui informasi-informasi umum seputar SDGs. <em>Kedua</em>, responden memahami 17 tujuan SDGs dan bisa mengaitkan serta menyelaraskannya dengan program-program lembaga. <em>Ketiga</em>, Pemahaman responden sudah mencapai target dan indikator-indikator SDGs serta mengaitkan dengan program-program organisasinya. Pegiat filantropi juga memahami bentuk-bentuk keterlibatan dan kontribusi lembaga dalam mendukung SDGs serta manfaat yang didapat dengan mendukung SDGs. Beberapa lembaga filantropi bahkan berhasil memobilisasi dukungan publik dan sektor swasta dengan mengaitkan program dengan tujuan dan target SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hasil riset juga menunjukkan bahwa lembaga filantropi yang jadi responden memiliki persepsi yang baik terhadap SDGs. Mayoritas dari mereka setuju bahwa SDGs memiliki keselarasan terhadap program dan kerja lembaga. Hal ini dikarenakan sebelum adanya SDGs, lembaga filantropi telah memiliki program-program peningkatan kesejahteraan masyarakat seperti kesehatan, pendidikan, penyantunan dan lain-lain seperti dalam tujuan SDGs. Mayoritas lembaga filantropi juga berpendapat bahwa mereka harus mengawal dan mengawasi pencapaian SDGs. Lembaga filantropi yakin bahwa perangkat kerja (tools) SDGs yang digunakan dapat memastikan program-program dapat terimplementasi dan berkontribusi pada pencapaian SDGs. Dalam pelaksanaan program, kemitraan menjadi perhatian bagi lembaga filantropi. Mayoritas lembaga filantropi berpendapat bahwa dalam menjalankan program SDGs lembaga harus bermitra dengan pemerintah dan pemangku kepentingan nya, seperti LSM, perusahaan, perguruan tinggi, dan yayasan sosial lainnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Penelitian juga mengkaji keselarasan program-program lembaga filantropi dengan 17 tujuan SDGs. Hasil analisis menunjukkan bahwa program-program yang dijalankan lembaga filantropi terkait dan selaras dengan 17 tujuan SDGs. Konvergensi program-program lembaga filantropi ini dapat menjadi kontribusi mereka bagi pencapaian SDGs. Konvergensi disini dimaknai sebagai pengintegrasian capaian program untuk digunakan dan diarahkan sebagai kontribusi lembaga filantropi dalam pencapaian tujuan dan target SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Penelitian menemukan bahwa sebagian besar lembaga filantropi mendukung dan menjalankan program pendidikan (25%), kesehatan (18%), penyantunan dan pelayanan sosial (15%), kebencanaan dan kedaruratan (10%) dan ekonomi produktif (10%). Jika dikaitkan dengan 17 tujuan SDGs, tergambar adanya ketimpangan dukungan pada masing-masing tujuan SDGs. Hasil riset menunjukkan bahwa program-program filantropi banyak terkait dan mendukung pencapaian tujuan 1 (tanpa kemiskinan), tujuan 3 (kehidupan yang sehat dan sejahtera) dan&nbsp; dan tujuan 4 (pendidikan berkualitas). Ini jadi tantangan yang perlu dipikirkan bersama pemecahannya agar tujuan-tujuan SDGs lainnya bisa mendapatkan dukungan dan targernya. ercapai&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara kajian terhadap kapasitas organisasi filantropi dalam mendukung SDGs menunjukkan nilai di atas rata-rata atau hampir mendekati katagori kuat. Dari 16 komponen kapasitas organisasi yang dinilai, kapasitas organisasi yang memiliki nilai tinggi adalah perencanaan program dan kegiatan, pengembangan dan inovasi program, monitoring dan evaluasi, serta penyebaran dan penyediaan informasi untuk publik. Sementara Komponen kapasitas dan profesionalisme staf mendapatkan nilai terendah dan menjadi tantangan mereka dalam pengembangan program dan organisasi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Agar dukungan dan kontribusi lembaga filantropi lebih optimal dalam mendukung SDGs, diperlukan upaya sosialisasi SDG di semua level organisasi. Kurangnya pemahaman terkait posisi strategis dan relevansi SDG dengan pengembangan organisasi, agenda pembangunan nasional dan daerah membuat SDG dipandang sebatas agenda internasional. Hal ini berdampak pada rendahnya komitmen organisasi dan lemahnya inisiatif dalam mendayagunakan SDG sebagai kerangka kerja dan alat bantu untuk mengakselerasi capaian program serta mendukung pembangunan nasional dan global.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selain itu, organisasi filantropi perlu didorong untuk lebih membuka diri, bersinergi dan membangun kemitraan dengan stakeholder SDGs lainnya. Keragaman organisasi dan program lembaga filantropi mestinya menjadi peluang atau kekuatan untuk saling melengkapi dalam pelaksanaan program-program terkait SDGs. Sinergi program antara organisasi dapat melengkapi ketidak tersediaan cabang organisasi filantropi, membantu dalam menjangkau sebaran wilayah program dan penyebaran dukungan terhadap isu yang diusung. Sementara Pemerintah diharapkan berperan lebih aktif sebagai koordinator dan fasilitator untuk mewujudkan sinergi dan kemitraan tersebut. Pemerintah juga diharapkan menyediakan kebijakan yang lebih kondusif melalui kemudahan, fasilitasi, apresiasi serta insentif perpajakan bagi lembaga-lembaga filantropi yang mendukung pencapaian SDGs.</p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;\n<hr />\n<div id=\"ftn1\">\n<p><a href=\"#_ftnref1\" name=\"_ftn1\" title=\"\">[1]</a> <small>Penelitian menggunakan metode kuantitatif dan kualitatif serta melibatkan 85 organisasi filantropi sebagai responden Pengambilan datanya dilakukan melalui kajian dokumen/pustaka, survei, wawancara mendalam dan FGD (Focussed Group discussion)</small></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6sucjM1Y2NXTF9kdjg\">UNDUH MATERI</a></p>\n', '8dd820067300dd170af8e02b384beb7f.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-14 07:49:30', '2018-02-19 14:59:29', 5, '-siaran-pers-tinggi-minat-filantropi-dukung-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'fDd5D4uW41YNLeP', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(484, '[Press Release] Philanthropy\'s interest in supporting SDGs is high', '', 'Press release of the Public Discussion Forum on a research by PIRAC: Philanthropy Agencies Readiness to Support SDGs Achievement in Indonesia', '<pre>\nThe enthusiasm of philanthropic institutions to engage and support the achievement of SDGs (Sustainable Development Goals) in Indonesia is quite high. The research<sup>1</sup> results of the Public Interest Research and Advocacy Center (PIRAC) and Philanthropy Indonesia show that the vast majority of philanthropic organizations want to engage and support programs related to SDGs. This enthusiasm is also supported by a high level of understanding of SDG requirements, as well as institutional commitments and capacities. However, the support of philanthropic agencies is not evenly distributed over all SDGs with some taking precedence over others.\n</pre>\n\n<pre>\nThis is illustrated within the results of PIRAC and Philanthropy Indonesia&rsquo;s research on the &quot;Readiness of Indonesian Philanthropic Institution in Supporting Achievement of SDGs&quot;. The results of this study were presented at a public discussion held at the Auditorium Kemenko PMK, Jakarta, on Tuesday 13<sup>th</sup> March. The event was opened by the Coordinating Minister for Political and Security Affairs, Puan Maharani, and was attended by philanthropy activists, government officials, academics and parties involved in the pursuit of the SDGs. The event also featured noted speakers, namely Ghafur Akbar Dharma Putera (Expert at Kemenko PMK in the field of Post-2015 Elementary School), and Nur Efendy (Chairman of FOZ / Zakat Forum).</pre>\n\n<p><br />\nThe results of PIRAC and Philanthropy Indonesia research show that 82% of the 85 philanthropic organizations that responded want to engage and support programs related to the achievement of SDGs. Only 13% of respondents who answered did not want to be involved in SDGs. Of these, 51% of them claimed to have previously been involved in the Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) program. This indicates that philanthropic institutions that were not previously involved in the MDGs showed more interest and enthusiasm for engaging in SDGs. The high interest of philanthropic institutions to engage and participate in SDG programs is seemingly influenced by their understanding and perception of SDGs. The results showed that 73% of respondents knew about SDGs. The Research also defined and mapped three levels of knowledge related to philanthropic institution&rsquo;s understanding of SDGs. The first level was characterised by respondents only knowing general information about SDGs. The Second level respondents understood the 17 objectives of the SDGs and could link and synchronize them with institutional programs. The Third level showed a clear level of understanding relating to the targets and indicators of SDGs and an incorporation into the organization&#39;s current programs. Groups also understood the forms of possible institutional involvement and contributions in supporting SDGs, and the benefits gained by supporting SDGs. Some philanthropic agencies have even managed to mobilize public and private sector support through their linking of programs to the goals and targets of the SDGs.</p>\n\n<p>The results also show that the philanthropic institutions who responded have a good perception of the SDGs. The majority of them agree that SDGs have alignment to the current programs and work of their organisation. This is expected, because prior to the existence of SDGs, philanthropy institutions already had programs to improve the welfare of the community such as health, education and sponsorship, as per the goals of the SDGs. The targets and indicators set by the SDGs are also regarded as an effective means of ensuring that programs are implemented towards, and contribute to the achievement of the SDGs. In the implementation of SDG programs, partnerships are of concern to philanthropic institutions. The majority of philanthropic institutions argue that in running the program SDG agencies should partner with governments and stakeholders, such as NGOs, companies, colleges, and other social foundations. The study also critically examined the alignment of philanthropic institutional programs with the 17 SDG objectives. The results of the analysis show that programs run by philanthropic institutions are linked and align closely with the 17 objectives set forth in the SDGs. The convergence of these philanthropic programs will be integral to the achievement of SDGs.</p>\n\n<pre>\nThe study found that most philanthropic institutions support and run educational programs (25%), health (18%), sponsorship and social services (15%), disaster and emergency (10%) and productive economies (10%). When associated with the 17 objectives of the SDGs, there is an imbalance of support for each of the SDGs. Research results show that philanthropic programs are particularly supportive of achieving goal 1 (an absence of poverty), goal 3 (ensuring healthy and prosperous lives) and goal 4 (the provision of quality education). The challenge then becomes gaining significant support and resources for the realization of the other goals. \n</pre>\n\n<pre>\nWhile the study of the capacity of philanthropic organizations in supporting SDGs showed it was generally high, some criteria score higher than others. Of the 16 assessed organizational capacity components, the highest scoring areas were program planning and activities, program development, innovation, monitorization and evaluation, and dissemination and provision of information to the public. The lowest scoring criteria was individual capacity and professionalism of staff, signifying a potential obstacle in the development of programs and organizations.\n</pre>\n\n<pre>\nIn order to make contribution of philanthropy institutions more optimal in supporting SDGs, it is necessary to incorporate SDG at all levels of the organization. The lack of understanding of the strategic position and relevance of SDG to organizational, national and regional development agendas has made SDG consideration limited to the international agenda. This has shown itself as a low level of organizational commitment and weak initiative in utilizing SDG as a framework and tools to accelerate program achievement and support national and global development.\n</pre>\n\n<pre>\nIn addition, philanthropic organizations should be encouraged to be more open, and to build partnerships with other stakeholders of SDGs. The diversity of organizations and programs of philanthropic institutions should be an opportunity to strengthen and complement each other in the implementation of programs related to SDGs. Program synergies between organizations can complement any deficiencies present within single philanthropic organizations, assist in reaching the program areas in full, and gaining support for the issues being promoted. The Government is expected to play a more active role as coordinator and facilitator to realize this synergism. The government is also expected to provide more conducive policies through ease, facilitation, appreciation and tax incentives for philanthropic institutions that support the achievement of SDGs.</pre>\n\n<div>\n<hr /></div>\n\n<div>\n<p><br />\n<small>[1] The research used quantitative and qualitative methods and involved 85 philanthropic organizations as respondents. Data were collected through document / literature reviews, surveys, in-depth interviews and FGDs (Focussed Group discussion)</small></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2ornD7Dj6sucjM1Y2NXTF9kdjg\">UNDUH MATERI</a></p>\n</div>\n', '8dd820067300dd170af8e02b384beb7f.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-14 07:49:30', '2018-02-19 14:59:29', 5, '-press-release-philanthropy-s-interest-in-supporting-sdgs-is-high', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'fDd5D4uW41YNLeP', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(493, 'Philanthropy Skill Share Forum 2', '', 'Rangkaian pelatihan dari Filantropi Indonesia kembali hadir dengan tema: Social Campaign melalui Strategi Komunikasi Kreatif dan Efektif. Segera daftarkan diri Anda!', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Lembaga filantropi dan organisasi nirlaba berkutat pada permasalahan sosial dalam masyarakat dan setiap programnya memerlukan partisipasi dari banyak pihak. Pada prinsipnya, strategi komunikasi untuk <em>social campaign</em> termasuk dalam <em>social marketing</em> yang selain diterapkan pada organisasi nirlaba juga digunakan oleh perusahaan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kebutuhan akan keahlian serta pengetahuan dalam merancang dan melaksanakan strategi komunikasi yang efektif dan kreatif untuk social campaign sangat penting di zaman digital ini. Terutama bagi para lembaga filantropi dan nirlaba yang aktif mengkampanyekan isu sosial di masyarakat, agar pesan mereka tidak kalah bersaing dengan pesan-pesan komersil dan kurang mendidik.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong><em>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum ke-2</em></strong> yang merupakan pelatihan rutin dari Filantropi Indonesia kembali hadir untuk memberi pembekalan tsb dengan tema &ldquo;<em>Social Campaign melalui Strategi Komunikasi yang Kreatif dan Efektif</em>&rdquo;. Kegiatan tersebut akan dilaksanakan pada:</p>\n\n<p>Hari/tanggal:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kamis, 30 Maret 2017</p>\n\n<p>Pukul:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 09.30 &ndash; 15.00 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Tempat:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Auditorium Filantropi Indonesia, Jl. Gunung Sahari VI No. 38, Sawah Besar, Jakarta Pusat 10720</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Kerangka%20Acuan%20PSSF%202.pdf\">UNDUH TOR</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><strong>INVESTASI</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>GRATIS&nbsp;bagi Lembaga Anggota Filantropi Indonesia (berlaku untuk 1 perwakilan peserta)</strong></p>\n\n<p>Non-anggota:</p>\n\n<p>HARGA EARLY BIRD&nbsp;Rp. 500.000,- (Lima Ratus Ribu Rupiah)</p>\n\n<p><em>Bagi Pendaftar yang menyelesaikan pembayaran </em><em>sampai dengan</em><em> tanggal </em><em><u>24</u></em> <em><u>Maret 2017</u></em></p>\n\n<p>HARGA NORMAL&nbsp;Rp. 750.000,- (Tujuh Ratus Lima Puluh Ribu Rupiah)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Pendaftaran Peserta</strong></p>\n\n<p>Email: info@filantropi.or.id</p>\n\n<p>Kontak: Hety (081328040235)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '0241443123bf5add27af7dd30f0f6b88.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-14 09:20:15', '2017-03-15 16:43:38', 5, 'philanthropy-skill-share-forum-2', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'BzqEV7S49c7zaGW', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-30 00:00:00', '2017-03-30 23:59:59'),
(494, 'Philanthropy Skill Share Forum 2', '', 'A full day workshop by Filantropi Indonesia is here for the second time. The theme for this workshop is \"Social Campaign with Creative and Effective Communication Strategies\". Register yourself soon!', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropic&nbsp;and nonprofit organizations tend to dwell on social problems in the community, which means&nbsp;each of their program requires the participation of many stakeholders. In principle, the communications strategy for social campaign is included in&nbsp;social marketing which not only applies&nbsp;to non-profit organizations, but&nbsp;also corporate or business.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The need for expertise and knowledge in designing and implementing an effective and creative communication strategy for social campaign is very important in this digital era. More so for philanthropy and nonprofit institutions who actively campaign on social issues in the community, so that their messages do not compete with commercial messages and not educating.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Philanthropy Skill Share Forum</strong>&nbsp;is a regular training or workshop class by the&nbsp;Indonesia Philanthropy Association,&nbsp;this month the 2nd class&nbsp;carries&nbsp;the theme &quot;Social Campaign through Creative and Effective Communication Strategies&quot;. The workshop&nbsp;will be held on:</p>\n\n<p>Date: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Thursday, 30 March 2017</p>\n\n<p>Time:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 09.30 &ndash; 15.00 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Location:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Auditorium Filantropi Indonesia, Jl. Gunung Sahari VI No. 38, Sawah Besar, Jakarta Pusat 10720</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Kerangka%20Acuan%20PSSF%202%282%29.pdf\">DOWNLOAD TOR</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><u><strong>REGISTRATION FEE</strong></u></p>\n\n<p><strong>FREE for members of&nbsp;Filantropi Indonesia (for one person from each organization)</strong></p>\n\n<p>Non-member:</p>\n\n<p>EARLY BIRD price IDR&nbsp;500,000&nbsp;(five hundred thousand rupiah)</p>\n\n<p><em>For participants who paid registration fee&nbsp;by <u>March 24, 2017</u>&nbsp;</em></p>\n\n<p>NORMAL PRICE IDR&nbsp;750,000&nbsp;(seven hundred and fifty thousand rupiah)</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><u><strong>RSVP</strong></u></p>\n\n<p>Email: info@filantropi.or.id</p>\n\n<p>Contact Person: Hety (081328040235</p>\n', '0241443123bf5add27af7dd30f0f6b88.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-14 09:20:15', '2017-03-15 16:43:38', 5, 'philanthropy-skill-share-forum-2', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'BzqEV7S49c7zaGW', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-30 00:00:00', '2017-03-30 23:59:59'),
(495, 'Perayaan tahun pertama Forum Komunikasi Filantropi dan Bisnis Indonesia untuk SDGs', '', 'Maret 2017 menandakan satu tahun terbentuknya FBI 4 SDGs atau Forum Komunikasi Filantropi dan Bisnis untuk SDGs. Perayaan ini sekaligus pengingat bahwa tugas masih panjang dan pekerjaan masih banyak.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada Kamis, 9 Maret 2017 yang lalu, bertempat di Indofood Tower, 10 asosiasi dan organisasi anggota Forum Komunikasi Filantropi dan Bisnis Indonesia untuk SDGs (FBI 4 SDGs) merayakan satu tahun terbentuknya Forum ini. Adalah pada Maret 2016 melalui rapat koordinasi dengan BAPPENAS yang menjadi awal dari lahirnya FBI 4 SDGs. FBI diprakarsai oleh empat organisasi: Filantropi Indonesia, KADIN, IGCN, dan IBCSD. Setelah satu tahun, forum ini berhasil melibatkan 10 organisasi dan asosiasi di dunia filantropi dan bisnis.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bapak Franky Welirang yang adalah Ketua Badan Pengurus Filantropi Indonesia membuka perayaan ini dengan menyampaikan sambutannya. Setelah itu Bapak Gellwynn Jusuf, Deputi Menteri PPN/BAPPENAS Bidang Kemaritiman dan Sumber Daya Alam, memberikan perkembangan terbaru mengenai Perpres SDGs serta mengajak FBI 4 SDGs untuk terus terlibat aktif dan meningkatkan kapasitas anggotanya. Bapak Gellwynn juga mengingatkan peran anggota-anggota FBI dalam penulisan Voluntary National Review (VNR) Indonesia yang akan dibawa ke PBB pada bulan Juli mendatang.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202017-03-09%20at%2012.29.23.jpeg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selanjutnya Bapak Timotheus Lesmana sebagai Ketua FBI 4 SDGs menyampaikan beberapa informasi terkait pencapaian forum ini sejak dibentuknya tahun lalu dan rencana ke depan. Pak Timo mengatakan bahwa tiap-tiap kelompok kerja (best practice &amp; SDG tools, deepening engagement MDGs to SDGs, advocacy and regulation, localization, awareness &amp; socialization) sudah mulai mengerjakan tugasnya. Laporan dari tiap kelompok kerja juga disampaikan oleh masing-masing PIC. Ibu Erna Witoelar kemudian menambahkan penekanan terhadap pentingnya lokalisasi SDGs dan kerja sama dengan pemda setempat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Akhirnya acara syukuran ini diakhiri dengan pemotongan kue ulang tahun, foto bersama dan makan siang. Pak Timo menyampaikan bahwa FBI 4 SDGs belum akan menambah jumlah anggotanya walau minat dari banyak bisnis cukup tinggi, namun akan fokus pada kinerja dari pokja yang sudah terbentuk dan penulisan VNR. Selanjutnya forum ini akan menyusun Rencana Aksi Nasional Filantropi dan Bisnis terkait SDGs di akhir bulan Maret.&nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n', 'dc69b035dcc9c2b6892a797f4a0c5455.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-16 04:02:36', '2018-02-19 15:00:25', 5, 'perayaan-tahun-pertama-forum-komunikasi-filantropi-dan-bisnis-indonesia-untuk-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'O1wf8UXBrUxEWNO', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(496, 'First anniversary of Communication Forum Philanthropy and Business Indonesia for SDGs', '', 'March 2017 marks one-year of FBI 4 SDGs or Philanthropy and Business Communication Forum for SDGs. This celebration is also a reminder that we still have a long way to go and there are still many work to do', '<p>On Thursday 9<sup>th</sup> of March 2017, at Indofood Tower, 10 associations and member organizations of the Philanthropy and Business Communication Forum Indonesia for SDGs (FBI 4 SDGs) celebrated the one-year anniversary&nbsp;of this Forum. It was a coordination meeting with BAPPENAS that would eventually become the beginning of&nbsp;FBI 4 SDGs. The forum was initiated by four organizations: Indonesia Philanthropy Association, Indonesia Chamber of Commerce, IGCN, and IBCSD. Over the last year, the forum has grown and now&nbsp;consists of 10 organizations and associations in the philanthropy and business sectors.</p>\n\n<p>Mr Franky Welirang, the Co-Chair of Indonesia Philanthropy Association Advisory Board, opened the celebration with a congratulatory speech. Mr. Gellwynn Jusuf, Deputy Minister of National Development Planning Agency Maritime Affairs and Natural Resources Division, followed with the latest developments regarding SDG regulation in the government sphere and encouraged the forum to continue engaging government actively and increasing the capacity of its members. Mr. Gellwynn also reminded the role of forum members in the writing of Indonesia&#39;s Voluntary National Review (VNR) which will be presented at the United Nations High Level Political Forum in July.</p>\n\n<p>Mr. Timotheus Lesmana, Chairman of FBI 4 SDGs, continued sharing some updates related to the achievements of the forum since its inception and future plans. Mr. Lesmana said that each working group (SDG &amp; best practice tools, deepening engagement, MDGs to SDGs, advocacy and regulation, localization, awareness and socialization) had started with their respective tasks. Reports from each working group were also briefly shared by their respective representatives. Mrs. Erna Witoelar spoke next, emphasising the importance of SDGs localization and effective partnership with local governments.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202017-03-09%20at%2012.29.27.jpeg\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The celebration event was concluded with the cutting of the first birthday cake, a group photo and lunch. Mr. Lesmana said that FBI 4 SDGs would not add more members despite the high level of interest shown by many businesses to join, instead focusing on the performance of each task force that has been formed and the writing of the VNR. The forum will also begin a draft National Action Plan for Philanthropy and Business-related SDGs at the end of March.</p>\n', 'dc69b035dcc9c2b6892a797f4a0c5455.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-16 04:02:37', '2018-02-19 15:00:25', 5, 'first-anniversary-of-communication-forum-philanthropy-and-business-indonesia-for-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'O1wf8UXBrUxEWNO', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(509, 'Diskusi Publik dan Diseminasi Hasil Riset KEBIJAKAN YANG MENDUKUNG DAN MENGHAMBAT FILANTROPI  DALAM MENDUKUNG PENCAPAIAN SDGS DI INDONESIA', '', 'Diskusi Publik dan Diseminasi Hasil Riset kerja sama antara Filantropi Indonesia dan Unika Atmajaya dengan dukungan dari Ford Foundation\n', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/diskusi23maret\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/1%283%29.png\" style=\"height:990px; width:700px\" /></a>Kesuksasan pencapaian SDGs sangat bergantung pada dukungan dan keterlibatan filantropi dan pemangku kepentingan lainnya (pemerintah, parlemen, masyarakat sipil, sektor swasta, akademisi dan lembaga-lembaga PBB). Namun, keterlibatan dan dukungan para pemanggku kepentingan ini tidak akan optimal jika tidak ditunjang dengan kebijakan-kebijakan yang kondusif. Karena itu, perlu kajian untuk mengidentifikasi dan menganalisis kebijakan-kebijakan yang mendukung dan menghambat filantropi dalam mendukung pencapaian SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Fakultas Hukum Unika Atma Jaya bekerjasama dengan Filantropi Indonesia &nbsp;telah melakukan sebuah penelitian mengenai kebijakan-kebijakan yang mendukung dan menghambat peran dan kontribusi filantropi dalam mendukung SDGs. Hasil penelitian tersebut akan didesiminasikan pada acara diskusi yang akan diselenggarakan pada:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Hari/tanggal</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; : Kamis, 23 Januari 2017</p>\n\n<p><strong>Pukul</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;: 12.00 &ndash; 16.00 WIB (diawali dengan <em>Networking Lunch</em>/ makan siang bersama)</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tempat</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : Gedung Yustinus Lantai 14, Unika Atma Jaya, Jl. Jend. Sudirman Kav. 51</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScCPhxiyrVOoFQmGVFLghOPMYOVuUDjBQFqk04d5ZPHMZK1iw/viewform?usp=sf_link\">PENDAFTARAN PESERTA</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Diskusi%20Publik%20dan%20Diseminasi%20Unika%20Atmajaya.pdf\">UNDUH TOR</a></p>\n', 'f6e38856b9369a656ebad1ed49c6f9a6.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-17 09:51:22', '2017-03-20 10:40:19', 5, 'diskusi-publik-dan-diseminasi-hasil-riset-kebijakan-yang-mendukung-dan-menghambat-filantropi-dalam-mendukung-pencapaian-sdgs-di-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'Lr1nYuQQedEuPEU', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-23 00:00:00', '2017-03-23 23:59:59');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(510, 'Public Discussion and Dissemination of Research POLICIES THAT SUPPORT AND INHIBIT Philanthropy IN SUPPORTING SDGs ACHIEVEMENT IN INDONESIA', '', 'Public Discussion and Dissemination of a Research by Indonesia Philanthropy Association and Atmajaya University, supported by Ford Foundation', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/diskusi23maret\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/1%284%29.png\" style=\"height:990px; width:700px\" /></a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) is a comprehensive and an integral national development agenda. With 17 integrated goals and 169 targets, it is&nbsp;understood&nbsp;that the SDGs are interrelated and interdependent. The involvement of philanthropy and other stakeholders (government, parliament, civil society, private sector, academia and UN agencies) is necessary for the success of achieving the SDGs, because it will depend on a partnership that is inclusive. However, the involvement and support of these stakeholders will not be optimal if it is not supported by conducive policies that support these stakeholders to work&nbsp;effectively.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In order for synergies and partnerships for the implementation of SDGs can run effectively, it is necessary to identify and analyze policies related to agencies and philanthropic programs in support of SDGs. From this analysis, we can map any policies that support and hinder philanthropy in supporting the SDGs. The results of the research are expected to provide an overview on policies that are potentials and opportunities as well as challenges and obstacles, especially for institutions or philanthropy&nbsp;sector, in achieving the SDGs so it can be anticipated and addressed.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Fakultas Hukum Unika Atma Jaya bekerjasama dengan Filantropi Indonesia telah melakukan sebuah penelitian mengenai kebijakan-kebijakan yang berkaitan dengan sektor filantropi yang dinilai mendukung dan menghambat peran dan kontribusi mereka dalam mendukung SDGs. Hasil penelitian tersebut akan didesiminasikan pada acara diskusi publik untuk masukan peserta diskusi.</p>\n\n<p>The Faculty of Law in Atma Jaya Catholic University partnered with Indonesia&nbsp;Philanthropy Association&nbsp;has conducted a study on policies relating to the philanthropic sector that support and hinder philanthropy&#39;s role and contribution in support of SDGs. The research results will be disseminated to the public for feedback from participants.</p>\n\n<p>This event will be held on:</p>\n\n<p>Day / Date: Thursday, January 23, 2017</p>\n\n<p>Time: 12:00 to 16:00 pm (preceded by Networking Lunch / lunch)</p>\n\n<p>Place: Justin Floor 14, Atma Jaya Catholic University, Jl. Jend. Sudirman Kav. 51</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScCPhxiyrVOoFQmGVFLghOPMYOVuUDjBQFqk04d5ZPHMZK1iw/viewform?usp=sf_link\">REGISTRATION</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Diskusi%20Publik%20dan%20Diseminasi%20Unika%20Atmajaya%281%29.pdf\">TERMS OF REFERENCE</a></p>\n', 'f6e38856b9369a656ebad1ed49c6f9a6.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-17 09:51:22', '2017-03-20 10:40:19', 5, 'public-discussion-and-dissemination-of-research-policies-that-support-and-inhibit-philanthropy-in-supporting-sdgs-achievement-in-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'Lr1nYuQQedEuPEU', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-23 00:00:00', '2017-03-23 23:59:59'),
(517, 'Lokakarya Rancangan Undang Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan Publik', '', 'Kementerian Sosial RI dan Masyarakat Penanggulangan Bencana Indonesia, didukung oleh Oxfam akan mengadakan lokakarya untuk membahas rancangan naskah akademik dan RUU pengganti UU No. 9 tahun 1961 terkait pengumpulan atau barang', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Undang-undang Nomor 9 Tahun 1961 tentang Pengumpulan Uang atau Barang itu telah menjadi dasar pemberian izin pengumpulan uang atau barang sampai saat ini. Dengan berkembangnya kondisi masyarakat, jumlah pengumpul uang atau barang untuk beragam bentuk tujuan, baik untuk kebencanaan, atau kegiatan lainnya, serta untuk meningkatkan perhatian masyarakat menyangkut akuntabilitas para pengumpul uang atau barang, maka sudah waktunya menilik ulang apakah peraturan yang dimaksud masih efektif untuk memayungi praktik-praktik penyelenggaraan sumbangan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sejak tahun 2015 Masyarakat Penanggulangan Bencana Indonesia (MPBI) telah bekerjasama dengan Kementerian Sosial RI dan BNPB didukung Oxfam telah menyelenggarakan seri diskusi. Pada periode tahun 2014 bekerjasama dengan Sekretariat Negara, MPBI telah memulainya dalam seri diskusi akuntabilitas kemanusiaan. Sepanjang tahun 2016 telah diadakan seri diskusi dan lokakarya serta kunjungan belajar ke Inggris untuk belajar dari Charity Commission dan lembaga sejenisnya. Pada tahun 2017 seri diskusi akan diadakan bersama untuk&nbsp;merumuskan rancangan Naskah Akademik dan rancangan Undang-undang pengganti UU Nomor 9 Tahun 1961.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lokakarya dilaksanakan di Jakarta Pusat (kepastian tempat disampaikan kepada peserta yang konfirmasi saja).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hari, tanggal : Senin, 27 Maret 2017</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Jam : 08:00 -17:00 WIB</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa;font-style:italic;\">Pendaftaran</h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Konfirmasi kehadiran dengan mengirimkan lembar konfirmasi yang sudah terisi kepada e-mail panitia :<br />\nperkumpulanmpbi@yahoo.co.id; godemoenk@gmail.com.<br />\nSelambatnya hari <u><strong>Jumat, 24 Maret 2017, jam 12:00 WIB</strong></u>. Peserta akan diinformasikan tempat pelaksanaan oleh panitia penyelenggara selambatnya jam 16:00 hari Jumat, 24 April 2017. Pendaftaran ditutup oleh Panitia Penyelenggara, apabila jumlah pendaftar lokakarya melampaui batas maksimal. Panitia Penyelenggara tidak menerima pendaftaran di lokasi lokakarya.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa;font-style:italic;\">Penyelenggara</h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Penyelenggara adalah Kementerian Sosial Republik Indonesia dan Masyarakat Penanggulangan Bencana Indonesia (MPBI) dengan dukungan Oxfam.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kontak:<br />\nSekretariat MPBI (Bapak Mulya Disurya)<br />\nGedung Suara Merdeka, Jl. Wahid Hasyim No 2, Jakarta Pusat 10340 Telepon : 021 80872587, 0819 1050 8541, 0857 7109 1697 (WA). E-mail: perkumpulanmpbi@yahoo.co.id. ; godemoenk@gmail.com.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Kerangka%20Acuan%20Acara%20Lokakarya.pdf\">UNDUH KERANGKA ACUAN ACARA</a></p>\n', '8e5f21d7e0958615be5f2a70c2016469.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-24 03:22:32', '2017-03-24 10:22:32', 5, 'lokakarya-rancangan-undang-penyelenggaraan-sumbangan-publik', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'IeiR0wL1eES9EQp', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-27 00:00:00', '2017-03-27 23:59:59'),
(518, 'Draft of the Implementation for Public Donations Law Workshop ', '', 'The Ministry of Social Affairs and the Indonesian Society for Disaster Management, supported by Oxfam will hold a workshop to discuss the draft text of an academic and a draft amendment to Act No. 9 1961 regarding the collection or goods', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Law No. 9 of 1961 on Collecting money or goods have become the standard for the collection of money or goods permission until today. With the growing conditions of the community, the number of actors who collect&nbsp;money or goods for different interests, either for disaster relief&nbsp;or other activities, as well as to raise public awareness regarding the accountability of collecting money or goods;&nbsp;then it is time to consider whether the regulation is still effective as the overarching law for all practices of organized&nbsp;collection of donation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 2015, the Indonesian Society for Disaster Management (MPBI) has been in partnership with the Ministry of Social Affairs and BNPB, supported by Oxfam, to organize&nbsp;a series of discussions. In&nbsp;2014 MPBI worked with the Secretariat of State, and started a series of discussions in humanitarian accountability. Throughout&nbsp;2016 they have also held a series of discussions and workshops and study visits to the UK to learn from the Charity Commission and likewise. In 2017, a series of discussions will be held to formulate&nbsp;the Academic Paper draft and the Law draft to replace Law No. 9 of 1961.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The workshop will be held in Central Jakarta (the exact location will be given to participants who have confirmend their attendance).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Date : Monday, 27 March 2017</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Time: 08:00 -17:00 WIB</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\">Registration</h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Send an email to: perkumpulanmpbi@yahoo.co.id; godemoenk@gmail.com.<br />\nAt the latest on Friday, March 24, 2017 at 12:00 PM WIB.&nbsp;Those who made the list will be informed the location and event venue at 4 pm on Friday March 24, 2017.&nbsp;The host and organizer will close registration once the quota is reached. There is no walk-in registration on the venue during the event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\">Host</h3>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This event is hosted and organized by the Ministry of Social Affairs and the Indonesian Society for Disaster Management (MPBI) with the support of Oxfam.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Contact:<br />\nSekretariat MPBI (Bapak Mulya Disurya)<br />\nGedung Suara Merdeka, Jl. Wahid Hasyim No 2, Jakarta Pusat 10340 Telepon : 021 80872587, 0819 1050 8541, 0857 7109 1697 (WA). E-mail: perkumpulanmpbi@yahoo.co.id.; godemoenk@gmail.com.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Kerangka%20Acuan%20Acara%20Lokakarya.pdf\">UNDUH KERANGKA ACUAN ACARA</a></p>\n', '8e5f21d7e0958615be5f2a70c2016469.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-24 03:22:32', '2017-03-24 10:22:32', 5, 'draft-of-the-implementation-for-public-donations-law-workshop-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'IeiR0wL1eES9EQp', 'N', '', '', '2017-03-27 00:00:00', '2017-03-27 23:59:59'),
(519, 'Diskusi Publik dan Diseminasi Hasil Riset Kebijakan yang Mendukung dan Menghambat Filantropi dalam Pencapaian SDGs', '', 'Laporan kegiatan diskusi mengenai hasil riset yang dilakukan oleh Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan UNIKA Atmajaya dan didukung oleh Ford Foundation', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Beberapa tahun terakhir, aktivitas filantropi berkembang cukup pesat di Indonesia. Bahkan tema filantropi telah masuk ke ranah akademisi. Perkembangan ini tentunya membuat diperlukannya regulasi hukum yang jelas. Hal inilah yang mendorong Filantropi Indonesia, bekerjasama dengan Fakultas Hukum Unika Atma Jaya mengadakan riset bersama untuk memetakan kebijakan-kebijakan di Indonesia yang mendukung dan menghambat kegiatan filantropi dalam implementasi SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Setelah melakukan penelitian selama kurang lebih 6 bulan, maka pada Kamis, 23 Maret 2017 hasil riset dipublikasikan melalui kegiatan &ldquo;Dikusi Publik Dan Diseminasi Hasil Riset Kebijakan yang Mendukung dan Menghambat Filantropi Dalam Pencapaian SDGs&rdquo;. Terdapat tiga narasumber dalam acara tersebut yaitu Daniel Yusmic sebagai ketua tim peneliti, Efirda Lubis yang merupakan akademisi dari Institut Pertanian Bogor, dan Bivitri Susanti dari Pusat Studi Hukum dan Kebijakan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0590%282%29.png\" style=\"height:370px; width:700px\" />Daniel menyebutkan bahwa terdapat 88 (delapan puluh delapan) Undang-Undang yang dikaji dalam riset ini. Dimana UU tertua yang dikaji adalah UU no 9 tahun 1961 tentang PUB dan UU terbaru adalah UU no 17 tahun 2013 tentang organisai kemasyarakatan yang didalamnya termasuk yayasan dan perkumpulan. Dalam penelitian tersebut terdapat 9 aspek yang dikaji yaitu kelembagaan, kegiatan, perizinan, pembiayaan, pembinaan, pengawasan, insentif, transparansi, dan sanksi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara itu, Efrida Lubis menyatakan bahwa ada banyak pengertian mengenai filantropi dan hingga sekarang belum ada kesepakatan pasti mengenai pengertian tersebut. Dia memaparkan beberapa UU yang berkaitan antara Filantropi dan SDGs yaitu Pasal 34 UUD 45, UU Perumahan dan permukiman, UU Rumah Susun, UU Penanganan Fakir Miskin, UU Jaminan Sosial, UU wakaf, UU Yayasan, UU Pengelolaan Zakat. Meskipun demikian hingga sekarang di Indonesia belum terdapat pemetaan&nbsp; UU yang mengarah ke SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0579%281%29.png\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Berkaitan dengan kegiatan tersebut, Bivitri menambahkan bahwa PSHK juga melakukan kerjasama penelitian dengan Filantropi Indonesia mengenai insentif pajak untuk filantropi. Masalah yang diangkat dalam penelitian tersebut adalah eksistensi organisasi nirlaba, RUU perkumpulan, dan revisi UU ormas. &nbsp;Terdapat tiga tantangan dalam insentif pajak tersebut yaitu minimnya informasi yang tersedia, rincian peraturan yang ambigu, serta banyak donor yang enggan menggunakan insentif pajak karena prosedurnya yang rumit.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalam diskusi penutup, para peserta yang hadir mengharapkan akan ada kelanjutan dari hasil penelitian yaitu dengan membawanya ke pemerintah. Selain itu perlu ada upaya penetapan standar ukuran yang disepakati bersama mengenai pemetaan UU mana saja yang mendukung dan menghambat filantropi dalam SDGs.</p>\n', 'd63b35dd743f32291e01017516034548.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-31 06:40:10', '2018-02-19 15:10:44', 5, 'diskusi-publik-dan-diseminasi-hasil-riset-kebijakan-yang-mendukung-dan-menghambat-filantropi-dalam-pencapaian-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'FTTNOSd7m7xhcsW', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(520, 'Public Discussion and Dissemination of Research Results on Policies that Support and Inhibit Philanthropy in Achieving SDGs', '', 'The activity report on the discussion about a research conducted by the Indonesia Philanthropy Association in partnership with Atma Jaya Catholic University and supported by the Ford Foundation', '<p>In recent years, philanthropic activities have developed rapidly in Indonesia.&nbsp;This growth has increased the need for clearer legal regulations.&nbsp;That is why Indonesia Philanthropy Association, in cooperation with the Faculty of Law at Atma Jaya Catholic University, conducted a public discussion seminar in order to identify public laws and policies in Indonesia that support and hinder philanthropy for the implementation of SDGs.</p>\n\n<p>After approximately 6 months of research, the authors published the research results on Thursday 23<sup>rd</sup> of March, 2017. The &quot;Discussion of Public Policy Research and Dissemination of Public Policies that Support and Inhibit Philanthropy in Achieving the SDGs&quot; event was conducted in support of the occasion.&nbsp;There were three speakers present for the discussion: Daniel Yusmic, the chairman of the research team, Efirda Lubis, a professor from Bogor Agricultural University (IPB), and Bivitri Susanti, from the Centre for Law and Policy Studies (PSHK).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0590%283%29.png\" style=\"height:370px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Daniel Yusmic explained how they studied eighty-eight acts over the course of their research. The oldest law studied was Law No. 9 of 1961 concerning the collection of money and goods, while the latest one was Law No. 17 of 2013 concerning social organizations that includes foundations and associations.&nbsp;In this study, 9 aspects were examined, namely institutional, activities, licensing, financing, construction, supervision, incentives, transparency, and sanctions.</p>\n\n<p>Efrida Lubis stated that while there is a lot of understanding of philanthropy itself, until now there has been no definitive agreement on the above terms.&nbsp;She explained several laws related to philanthropy, which were Article 34 of the Constitution 45, Law on Housing and settlements, Law on Housing, Poverty Management Law, Social Security Law, Law on endowments, the Law Foundation, Zakat Management Act.&nbsp;Yet until now there has been no architecture in Indonesian laws which supports the achievement of the SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0579%282%29.png\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Bivitri added that PSHK also conducts collaborative research with the Indonesia Philanthropy Association regarding tax incentives for philanthropy.&nbsp;The issues raised in the study related to non-profit organizations, the associations Bill, and the revised Law on civil society organizations.&nbsp;There are three challenges in tax incentives: lack of available information, the details of the rules are ambiguous, and many donors are reluctant to use tax incentives because the procedure is complicated.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the closing session, participants discussed the need for a continuation of the research and the need to bring it to the government.&nbsp;They also agreed that there should be standard-setting efforts made whereby parties jointly agree to map any laws that support or hinder philanthropy in achieving the SDGs.</p>\n', 'd63b35dd743f32291e01017516034548.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-31 06:40:11', '2018-02-19 15:10:44', 5, 'public-discussion-and-dissemination-of-research-results-on-policies-that-support-and-inhibit-philanthropy-in-achieving-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'FTTNOSd7m7xhcsW', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(525, '[Philanthropy Skill Share Forum] Kampanye Sosial melalui Strategi Komunikasi yang Efektif dan Kreatif', '', 'Laporan pelatihan rutin yang dilakukan Filantropi Indonesia untuk memperkuat kapasitas lembaga anggotanya.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk kedua kalinya Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan pelatihan teknis bagi para anggotanya dan pegiat filantropi lainnya pada hari Kamis, 30 Maret 2017. Topik pelatihan kali ini adalah &ldquo;Social Campaign melalui Strategi Komunikasi Efektif dan Kreatif&rdquo; dengan narasumber SAM August Himmawan, Direktur DASA Strategic Communication dan Redaktur Pelaksana MajalahCSR.ID. Dengan latar belakang di dunia periklanan, humas dan marketing communication selama belasan tahun, Bapak SAM membagikan ilmunya kepada para peserta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kampanye yang mengangkat isu sosial memiliki tantangan dan kendala yang berbeda dari kampanye yang bersifat komersil, karena itu diperlukan strategi komunikasi yang berbeda. Di sesi pertama beberapa ilmu dasar strategi komunikasi mulai dari perencanaan hingga implementasi dibagikan dan peserta mendiskusikan contoh-contoh kasus yang sudah ada.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada sesi siang hari, peserta diajak untuk praktek membuat kampanye sosial dengan isu yang beragam, seperti penggunaan kantong plastik, kain tenun tradisional dan pendidikan. Mereka harus mempresentasikan strategi komunikasi yang akan mereka lakukan dan mendapat saran dan masukan dari peserta lain.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropy Skill Share Forum ke-3 akan datang kembali di bulan Juni 2017 mendatang. Simak terus situs resmi dan sosial media Filantropi Indonesia untuk mengetahui topik apa yang akan kami bahas selanjutnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0732.JPG\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0749.JPG\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0812.JPG\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', '6ce6260531225bc8e27fcc1780402775.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-31 06:58:09', '2018-02-19 15:13:02', 5, '-philanthropy-skill-share-forum-kampanye-sosial-melalui-strategi-komunikasi-yang-efektif-dan-kreatif', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'PQbmlNyivE3Uhbz', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(526, '[Philanthropy Skill Share Forum] Social campaigns through effective communication strategy and creative', '', 'Short report on the regular training by Indonesia Philanthropy Association to build the capacity of its member institutions.', '<p>Indonesia Philanthropy Association held its second skill training session for its members and other philanthropy organizations on Thursday 30<sup>th</sup> of March, 2017. The topic for this event was &quot;Social Campaign: Effective and Creative Communication Strategies&quot;, with guest speaker Sam August Himmawan, the Director of DASA Strategic Communication and the Senior Editor of MajalahCSR.ID. Mr. Himmawan shared his knowledge and experience gained over 10 years of experience in advertising, public relations and marketing communications.</p>\n\n<p>Campaigns advancing social issues have different challenges and problems when compared to commercial campaigns because they require different communication strategies.&nbsp;In the first session, some basic information regarding communication strategies, from planning to implementation, was shared and participants discussed some relevant case studies in light of their new understanding.</p>\n\n<p>In the afternoon session, participants were invited to practice creating a social campaign around diverse issues such as the use of plastic bags, traditional fabrics and education.&nbsp;They then had to present what communication strategies they used to the group, with other participants asked to give advice and feedback.</p>\n\n<p>The third Philanthropy Skill Share Forum will be back in June 2017.&nbsp;Please stay tuned to our official website and social media accounts to find out which topic will be discussed next.</p>\n', '6ce6260531225bc8e27fcc1780402775.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-03-31 06:58:09', '2018-02-19 15:13:02', 5, '-philanthropy-skill-share-forum-social-campaigns-through-effective-communication-strategy-and-creative', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'PQbmlNyivE3Uhbz', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(533, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 15: Membedah RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan', '', 'PLF ke-15 akan membahas mengenai RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan yang akan mengatur pengumpulan, pengelolaan serta pelaporan sumbangan dan aktivitas filantropi di Indonesia', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dalam 15 tahun terakhir kegiatan filantropi tengah berkembang pesat di Indonesia. Kegiatan berderma dan menolong sesama sedang marak di masyarakat. Meningkatnya sumbangan masyarakat ini telah memberikan momentum bagi berkembangnya kegiatan penggalangan dan penyaluran donasi serta bentuk-bentuk dukungan lainnya dari masyarakat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sayangnya, perkembangan filantropi yang cukup pesat belum ditopang dengan regulasi atau kebijakan yang kondusif dan menjadi <em>enabling</em> <em>environment</em> bagi kegiatan filantropi. Salah satu regulasi yang dianggap menghambat adalah UU No.9/1961 Tentang PUB (Penggalangan Uang dan Barang). Selain menerapkan mekanisme perijinan dan pelaporan yang sangat ketat, beberapa ketentuan dalam UU ini juga dinilai sudah ketinggalan jaman.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Untuk merevisi UU PUB, beberapa organisasi masyarakat sipil dan Kementerian Sosial menginisiasi perumusan RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan untuk merevisi dan menggantikan UU PUB. Perumusan RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan diharapkan tidak menghambat kegiatan filantropi yang sekarang tengah marak dan berkembang pesat di masyarakat. Di sisi lain, Perumusan RUU tersebut juga diharapkan mampu meningkatkan transparansi dan akuntabilitas penyelenggaraan sumbangan, serta mencegah penyalahgunaan dalam penggalangan, pengelolaan dan pendayagunaannya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hal inilah yang mendorong Filantropi Indonesia berkerjasama dengan Oxfam Indonesia untuk mendiskusikan RUU tersebut dalam <em>Philanthropy Learning Forum 15</em>. Kegiatan ini diharapkan bisa membedah RUU PUB serta memberikan berbagai masukan dan rekomendasi untuk penyempurnaan pasal-pasal yang ada di dalamnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20PLF_RUU%20Penyelenggaraan%20Sumbangan.pdf\">UNDUH KERANGKA ACUAN ACARA</a></p>\n', '16cb35ad5ea31b7efd8cfcb5e4faefce.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-04-12 06:55:07', '2017-04-12 13:55:07', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-15-membedah-ruu-penyelenggaraan-sumbangan', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'aFkE5iMsSOzF8hQ', 'N', '', '', '2017-04-25 00:00:00', '2017-04-25 23:59:59'),
(534, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 15: Dissecting the Donation Management Bill', '', 'The 15th PLF will discuss the draft of Donations Management Bill that will affect philanthropy activities such as fundraising, donation management, distribution, and reporting.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the last 15 years philanthropy activities have been rapidly growing in Indonesia. Charities and fundraising for a cause are emerging. The increase in public donations has provided a momentum for the development of fundraising activities, donations distribution and other forms of support from the community.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unfortunately, the rapid development of philanthropy is not supported by conducive regulation or public policy that creates an enabling environment for philanthropy. One of the regulations that inhibits philanthropy&rsquo;s development is the Law No.9 / 1961 about PUB (Raising Money and Goods). This law enforces a very strict licensing and reporting mechanisms, moreover some of the provisions in this Act are also considered outdated.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To revise the Law, several civil society organizations and the Ministry of Social Affairs initiated the formulation of Donations Management Bill to revise and replace the PUB Act. It is expected that the formulation of this bill should not impede the contribution of philanthropy that is now growing and thriving in the community. On the other hand, the formulation of the bill is also expected to increase the transparency and accountability of donations, as well as preventing abuse in the mobilization, management and utilization.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The urgency of formulating the bill has encouraged the Indonesian Philanthropy Association in collaboration with Oxfam Indonesia to discuss the issue in Philanthropy Learning Forum 15. This discussion is expected to dissect the bill and provide advice and recommendations to improve some articles and points.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20PLF_RUU%20Penyelenggaraan%20Sumbangan%281%29.pdf\">DOWNLOAD TOR (in Bahasa Indonesia)</a></p>\n', '16cb35ad5ea31b7efd8cfcb5e4faefce.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-04-12 06:55:07', '2017-04-12 13:55:07', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-15-dissecting-the-donation-management-bill', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'aFkE5iMsSOzF8hQ', 'N', '', '', '2017-04-25 00:00:00', '2017-04-25 23:59:59'),
(545, '[Lowongan] Program Officer di Mien R Uno Foundation', '', 'Mien R Uno Foundation merupakan yayasan keluarga yang mendedikasikan diri untuk mendidik dan mengasah social entrepreneur muda Indonesia dengan program ENVOY (Entrepreneurship Development Scholarship for Youth)', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Loker%20Program%20Officer%20MRUF%20April%202017.jpeg\" style=\"height:1000px; width:800px\" /></p>\n', 'c61ecec3c17f4d01780bb61abd11060a.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-04-20 02:57:44', '2017-04-20 09:57:43', 5, '-lowongan-program-officer-di-mien-r-uno-foundation', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'KgWKU5gTNPqwIsO', 'N', '', 'Mien R Uno Foundation', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(546, '[Vacancy] Program officer at Mien R Uno Foundation', '', 'Mien R Uno Foundation is a family foundation that is dedicated to educate and empower young social entrepreneurs in Indonesia with ENVOY (Entrepreneurship Development Scholarship for Youth) program', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Loker%20Program%20Officer%20MRUF%20April%202017%281%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:1000px; width:800px\" /></p>\n', 'c61ecec3c17f4d01780bb61abd11060a.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-04-20 02:57:44', '2017-04-20 09:57:43', 5, '-vacancy-program-officer-at-mien-r-uno-foundation', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'KgWKU5gTNPqwIsO', 'N', '', 'Mien R Uno Foundation', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(553, 'Philanthropy Sharing Session: Mengkomunikasikan dan Mempromosikan  Gerakan Filantropi Secara Kreatif ', '', 'Melalui acara ini Private Wealth Network, The Man Cave, Good Pitch2 Australia, dan Genashtim akan berbagi pengalaman dan keterampilan mereka dalam mempromosikan program-programnya agar mendapatkan dukungan dari mitra dan donatur. Sesi ini merupakan kerja sama antara Filantropi Indonesia, In-Docs dan Kedutaan Australia.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kesuksesan gerakan filantropi memerlukan keterlibatan dari banyak pihak mulai dari para stakeholder hingga masyarakat sipil. Disadari bahwa tidak mudah mengajak mereka untuk ikut terlibat dan mendukung kegiatan dan program yang dilakukan, khususnya program-program non karitatif namun berdimensi strategis dan jangka panjang. Masih banyak masyarakat yang belum dapat memahami bahwa gerakan filantropi dapat juga berfungsi untuk mengkampanyekan program strategis jangka panjang, tidak hanya sekadar <em>charity</em>.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk dapat menggugah masyarakat agar ikut ambil bagian dari gerakan filantropi maka diperlukan upaya komunikasi dan promosi secara efektif dan kreatif. Dalam stratifikasi sosial masyarakat, masing&ndash;masing kelas memiliki karakter serta cara komunikasi yang berbeda. Oleh karena itu agar kampanye gerakan filantropi dapat tersampaikan maka terlebih dahulu harus dapat dipahami siapakah sasarannya. Selain itu konsep promosi gerakan filantropi juga harus dibuat secara menarik. Masyarakat akan lebih menyukai konsep promosi yang interaktif dengan menggunakan metode yang kreatif, tanpa menghilangkan makna esensial yang menjadi tujuan gerakan filantropi tersebut.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pentingnya upaya mempromosikan gerakan filantropi secara kreatif merupakan salah satu kunci sukses gerakan filantropi. Karena itulah Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan In-Docs dan Kedutaan Australian untuk menggelar <em>Philanthropy</em> S<em>haring Ses</em><em>sion </em>dengan mengangkat tema tersebut. Melalui acara ini <em>Private Wealth Network, The Man Cave, Good Pitch<sup>2</sup> Australia</em>, dan <em>Genashtim</em> akan berbagi pengalaman dan keterampilan mereka dalam mempromosikan program-programnya agar mendapatkan dukungan dari mitra dan donatur. &nbsp;Dari pemaparan ketiga lembaga tersebut diharapkan bisa dirumuskan model dan strategi promosi yang tepat yang dapat diadaptasi dan dapat di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Note: Sesi diskusi ini untuk kalangan terbatas dan tidak ada registrasi di tempat</strong></p>\n', '6e6a73d35ba8fd2f1413c7c8f9db46a7.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-04-21 09:22:26', '2017-04-26 09:27:29', 5, 'philanthropy-sharing-session-mengkomunikasikan-dan-mempromosikan-gerakan-filantropi-secara-kreatif-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'wqh78ochG1gDA9D', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-05 00:00:00', '2017-05-05 23:59:59'),
(554, 'Philanthropy Sharing Session: To Communicate and Promote Philanthropic Works Creatively', '', 'Private Wealth Network, The Man Cave, Good Pitch2 Australia, and Genashtim will share how to create and promote philanthropic activities creatively, and how to connect with partners and potential funders. Philanthropy Learning Session is jointly organized between Filantropi Indonesia, In-Docs, and Australian Embassy. ', '<p>The success of a philanthropic organization lies on the participation of many stakeholders across civil society. Many Indonesian organizations realize that expanding supporters is challenging, especially to contribute to programs with long-term strategic dimension but non-charity in nature. Most Indonesians like to donate to religious-based activities and charitable causes, like building schools, providing medical treatment, or granting scholarships.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>To galvanize a wider range of supporters, philanthropic movements need to create special programs that can attract different target groups. Promotion also has to be tailored to each group creatively and effectively.</p>\n\n<p>They will share how to create and promote philanthropic activities creatively, and how to connect with partners and potential funders. <em>Philanthropy Learning Session</em> is jointly organized between Filantropi Indonesia, In-Docs, and Australian Embassy. We hope that the exchange session can pinpoint some models and strategies that can be adapted in Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p><strong>NOTE: This event is by invitation only, there will be no registration on the spot</strong></p>\n', '6e6a73d35ba8fd2f1413c7c8f9db46a7.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-04-21 09:22:26', '2017-04-26 09:27:29', 5, 'philanthropy-sharing-session-to-communicate-and-promote-philanthropic-works-creatively', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'wqh78ochG1gDA9D', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-05 00:00:00', '2017-05-05 23:59:59'),
(557, '[SIARAN PERS] Kasus Sumbangan Cak Budi: Pengelola Abaikan Peraturan dan Etika', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia mengambil sikap mengenai kasus sumbangan Cak Budi di situs crowdfunding', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai lembaga yang memberi perhatian khusus terhadap kegiatan filantropi atau kedermawanan sosial di Indonesia, Filantropi Indonesia (FI) mencermati&nbsp;polemik dan kontroversi seputar pengelolaan sumbangan yg dilakukan oleh Cak Budi, yang banyak diperbincangkan di media sosial dan diliput banyak media. FI menilai kasus ini bisa berdampak terhadap kepercayaan donatur kepada lembaga-lembaga filantropi/nirlaba dan bisa menghambat perkembangan dan kemajuan filantropi di Indonesia. Namun, kasus ini juga bisa jadi momentum pembenahan dan pembelajaran bagi individu, komunitas dan lembaga filantropi/nirlaba yang saat ini tengah melakukan penggalangan sumbangan masyarakat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia menghargai dan mendukung inisiatif individu, komunitas dan lembaga filantropi/nirlaba dalam memobilisasi donasi dan bentuk-bentuk sumbangan lainnya dalam rangka mengatasi persoalan sosial dan memajukan kepentingan publik. Namun, agar inisiatif tersebut bisa terus mendapat dukungan dan kepercayaan masyarakat serta memberikan manfaat dan dampak yang optimal, FI mendorong agar penggalangan, pengelolaan dan penyaluran sumbangannya dilakukan secara profesional, transparan dan akuntabel dengan mengacu pada peraturan yang berlaku dan kode etik Filantropi Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Menyikapi polemik seputar penggalangan sumbangan yang diinisiasi Cak Budi, FI&nbsp;menilai ada beberapa aspek atau ketentuan hukum dan etika yang tidak diperhatikan dan dipatuhi oleh Cak Budi, sehingga menyebabkan munculnya polemik dan kontroversi di masyarakat, diantaranya:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggunaan rekening pribadi yang rentan terhadap tercampurnya sumbangan dengan dana dan transaksi pribadi, serta menyulitkan untuk dikontrol dan diawasi publik</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Transparansi dan akuntabilitas terkait pemanfaatan sumbangan. Pengelola tidak pernah menyampaikan penggunaan sumbangan untuk pembelian mobil dan HP dan baru menginformasikannya setelah dipersoalkan publik.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggunaan dana operasional yg kurang tepat, baik dari segi jumlah dan peruntukannya. Menggunakan dana sumbangan dalam jumlah besar dan digunakan untuk pembelian mobil dan <em>handphone</em> yang dikatagorikan &ldquo;mewah&rdquo; dinilai tidak etis dan bertentangan dengan peraturan yang berlaku.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Pengelola tidak memperhatikan kapasitasnya dalam menggalang dana sehingga jumlah dana yg masuk tidak sebanding dengan jumlah dan kapasitas pengelolanya. Pengelola tidak mencoba mengatasi masalah ini melalui sinergi dan kemitraan dengan lembaga sosial, tapi memaksakan diri mengelolanya dengan membeli mobil operasional dan <em>handphone</em> untuk keperluan operasional penyaluran sumbangan.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggunaan sumbangan yang tidak sesuai dengan program atau kegiatan yang dipromosikan. Sumbangan sosial yang didekasikan untuk program atau kegiatan sosial tertentu, tidak boleh dipergunakan atau dialihkan untuk pembelian mobil atau <em>handphone</em>. Perubahan alokasi sumbangan tersebut harus dilakukan dengan ijin dan persetujuan para donatur.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Pengelola tidak mengantongi ijin. Penggalangan sumbangan untuk kalangan internal dan kegiatan keagamaan memang dimungkinkan tanpa perijinan. Namun, jika penggalangan&nbsp;sumbangan tersebut menyasar masyarakat secara luas dan melibatkan dana sampai ratusan juta rupiah, maka harus mengantongi ijin dari instansi terkait agar bisa dikontrol dan diawasi.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Agar polemik dan kontoversi ini tidak berkepanjangan dan dalam rangka melindungi hak dan kepentingan para donatur, FI merekomendasikan agar kegiatan penggalangan sumbangan Cak Budi ini dihentikan sementara untuk dilakukan evaluasi dan perbaikan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Belajar dari kasus ini, Filantropi Indonesia merekomendasikan sejumlah hal yang harus diperhatikan dan dipatuhi individu, komunitas dan lembaga penggalangan sumbangan agar kasus semacam ini tidak terulang di kemudian hari:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggalang sumbangan hendaknya memperhatikan dan mematuhi peraturan terkait sumbangan dan kode etik filantropi (UU No.9/1961 tentang Pengumpulan Uang dan Barang, PP No 29/1980 tentang pelaksanaan pengumpulan sumbangan, Kode Etik Filantropi Indonesia, Kode Etik Filantropi Mediamassa, dll).</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggalang sumbangan hendaknya tidak menggunakan rekening pribadi, melainkan rekening khusus sumbangan. Individu dan komunitas yang tidak memiliki rekening khusus bisa bekerja sama dengan lembaga filantropi/nirlaba yang memiliki rekening khusus sumbangan sehingga kegiatannya terjamin akuntabilitasnya dan tidak melanggar peraturan yang berlaku.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggalang sumbangan hendaknya memperhatikan dan mematuhi ketentuan mengenai dana operasional yang sudah diatur dalam undang-undang maupun kode etik filantropi.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Penggalang sumbangan hendaknya memperhatikan kapasitas diri dan organisasinya serta tidak memaksakan diri mengelola sumbangan dalam jumlah besar. Pengelola bisa mengatasi persoalan ini dengan bersinergi dengan lembaga filantropi/nirlaba yang sudah teruji kompetensi dan akuntabilitasnya.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia juga menghimbau kepada masyarakat sebagai donatur agar lebih peka, selektif dan kritis dalam menyalurkan sumbangan serta lebih memilih penyaluran sumbangannya kepada lembaga-lembaga filantropi/nirlaba yang sudah teruji transparansi dan akuntabilitasnya.</p>\n', '', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-02 09:31:47', '2018-02-19 15:15:25', 5, '-siaran-pers-kasus-sumbangan-cak-budi-pengelola-abaikan-peraturan-dan-etika', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'RVpLDDwG8Q6WyKY', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(558, '[PRESS RELEASE] Cak Budi Donation Case: Organizer Ignores Rules and Ethics', '', 'Indonesia Philanthropy Association gave its position and opinion about the current case of Cak Budi on a crowdfunding platform ', '<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nAs an institution that gives special attention to philanthropic activities or social generosity in Indonesia, Filantropi Indonesia (FI) looks at the polemic and controversy surrounding the management of donations made by Cak Budi, which has been widely discussed in the media. FI believes that this case could have an impact on donor trust of philanthropic / non-profit institutions and could hinder the further development and progress of philanthropy in Indonesia. However, this case can also be an instigator of reform and learning for individuals, communities and philanthropic / non-profit institutions that are currently conducting community donations.\n</pre>\n\n<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nFilantropi Indonesia appreciates and supports the initiative of individual, community and philanthropic / non-profit institutions in mobilizing donations and other forms of donation in order to address social issues and advance the public interest. However, in order for these initiatives to continue to gain public support and confidence, and provide optimum benefits and impacts, FI encourages that the donation, management and distribution of donations be conducted in a professional, transparent and accountable manner by referring to all applicable regulations and the philanthropy code of ethics of Indonesia.\n</pre>\n\n<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nIn response to the polemic surrounding the donation of donations initiated by Cak Budi, FI considered that there are several aspects or provisions of law and ethics that are not observed and obeyed by Cak Budi, causing the current controversy in the community. These include:\n</pre>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>\n	<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nThe use of private accounts that are vulnerable to mixed donations with personal funds and transactions, and makes it difficult for public control and monitoring\n</pre>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nTransparency and accountability regarding the use of donations. Managers never submitted the use of donations for the purchase of cars and telephones, and only informed authorities after public questioning.\n</pre>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nUnacceptable use of operational funds, both in terms of quantity and allocation. Using large amounts of donations for the purchase of cars and mobile phones categorized as &quot;luxury&quot; is considered unethical and contrary to prevailing regulations.\n</pre>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nManagers do not pay attention to their capacity to raise funds so that the amount of incoming funds is not proportional to the number and capacity of managers. Managers do not try to solve this problem through synergy and partnership with social institutions. \n</pre>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nUse of donations that are inconsistent with the program or activity being promoted. Social donations dedicated to a particular program or social activity may not be used or transferred for the purchase of cars or mobile phones. Changes in the allocation of donations must only be made with consent from the donors.\n</pre>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nThe manager does not have a permit. The raising of donations for internal and religious activities is possible without permission. However, if the donation raising targeted the public at large and involves funds of up to hundreds of millions of rupiah, it requires permission from the relevant agencies to be controlled and supervised.</pre>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<pre style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n\nIn order to subdue the current controversy, and to protect the rights and interests of donors, FI recommends that the Cak Budi donation fundraising activity be suspended for evaluation and improvement. Learning from this case, Philanthropy Indonesia recommends a number of conditions to be observed and adhered to by individuals, communities and donation-raising agencies, so that such problems do not reoccur in the future:</pre>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1. Contribution donors should observe and comply with the rules regarding the contribution and philanthropy code of ethics (Law No.9 / 1961 on Money and Goods Collection, Government Regulation No. 29/1980 on the implementation of donation collection, Indonesian Philanthropy Code of Ethics, Mediamassa Philanthropy Code, etc.).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2. Donors should not use personal accounts, but have designated accounts for donations. Individuals and communities who do not have a special account are advised to work with a philanthropic / non-profit institution that is able to keep a special account of the donation so that its activities are assured accountability and do not violate any applicable regulations.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3. Donors should pay attention to, and comply with, the provisions concerning operational funds that are set forth in law or philanthropy code of ethics.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4. Donors should pay attention to their personal and organizational capacities, and should not force themselves to manage excessive donations. Managers can overcome this problem by synergizing with philanthropic institutions or non-profits that have shown prior competence and accountability. Indonesian philanthropy also calls on the community as a donor to be more sensitive, selective and critical in channelling donations and preferring to channel donations to the proven philanthropic institutions.</p>\n\n<pre>\n&nbsp;</pre>\n', '', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-02 09:31:47', '2018-02-19 15:15:25', 5, '-press-release-cak-budi-donation-case-organizer-ignores-rules-and-ethics', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'RVpLDDwG8Q6WyKY', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(559, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Membedah RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan', '', 'Diskusi ini diadakan berkat kerja sama antara FI, Oxfam, MPBI, Kementerian Sosial RI, dan UN OCHA. PLF ke-15 berlangsung ramai dan diikuti oleh berbagai pihak mengingat pentingnya RUU ini bagi setiap pegiat filantropi.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hingga sekarang ini, UU no 9 Tahun 1961 mengenai PUB (Pemungutan Uang dan Barang) masih menjadi panutan aturan hukum dalam kegiatan penyelenggaraan sumbangan. Perkembangan zaman membuat UU tersebut sudah tidak relavan lagi untuk digunakan. Keadaan ini yang membuat diperlukannya undang-undang baru yang dapat menjadi payung hukum bagi semua pihak yang berkepentingan dalam kegiatan penyelenggaraan sumbangan. RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan diharapkan dapat menjadi jawaban dalam persoalan tersebut.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia bekerjasama dengan OXFAM mengadakan <em>Philanthropy Learning Forum 15&nbsp;</em>untuk membedah RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan pada Selasa, 25 April 2017. &nbsp;Menurut Suratman, salah satu tim perumus manyatakan bahwa UU PUB 1961 tidak jelas karena tidak dapat memberikan kepastian hukum dan keadilan. &nbsp;Sistematika RUU baru nantinya akan ada 13 bab dan 89 pasal. Ada enam ujuan penyusunan RUU ini yaitu meningkatkan kepedulian, terhimpunya uang dan barang atau jasa, tersalurnya uang atau jasa kepada masyarakat yang membutuhkan, terciptanya transparasi dan akuntablititas, terciptanya tertib adminitrasi, dan terselenggaranya pengumpulan serta pengelolaan sumbangan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalam kegiatan ini, The Nature Conservacy (TNC) yang mewakili lembaga intermediary, mengkritisi bahwa di dalam draft naskah RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan belum tercantum mengenai hak &ndash; hak dan aturan perlindungan untuk donator. Ia juga menambahkan bahwa apabila dilihat didalam RUU tersebut stakeholder yang berkaitan hanya Kementerian Sosial, apabila dimungkinkan Kementerian Keuangan dapat dilibatkan karena berkaitan dengan insentif pajak.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Maitra W. Faiszal dari Save The Children (STC) menyambung, bahwa rata-rata income NGO, sebesar 60-70 persennya berasal dari individu. Sementara itu STC melakukan fundraising dengan berbagai chanel yaitu face to face, digital fundraising, telemarketing, event fundraising, telethon. Oleh karena itu Maitra memberikan masukan terhadap RUU tersebut dari pengalaman STC yang memang sangat sering melakukan fundraising. Berkaitan dengan registrasi kegiatan fundraising, ia mengusulkan agar tidak perlu menunggu ijin. Jikapun terdapat ijin maka untuk NGO yang memiliki aktivitas fundraising berkelanjutan, maka cukup satu kali registrasi dan dibuat system pelaporan berkala serta diperjelas siapa badan otonom yang berhak memberikan ijin tersebut. Selain itu, Maitra juga mengusulkan agar nantinya RUU tidak membatasi minimum dana oparasional&nbsp; yang dapat diambil dari perolehan fundraising.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kegiatan ini juga menghadirkan lembaga fundraising yang berasal dari inisiatif individu dan komunitas yaitu Kitabisa.com yang merupakan website atau platform yang mewadai atau memfasilitasi orang2 yang ingin berpatisipasi untuk menyumbang atau menggalang dana. <em>Campaigner</em> bisa berasal dari mana saja, mulai lembaga-lembaga formal, informal, dan individu. Kitabisa.com sendiri mengambil 5 persen untuk dana operasional. Berkaitan dengan RUU, Vikra Ijas mempertanyakan dimana posisi kitabisa apakah pengumpul, penerima, atau penyalur. Ia juga mempertanyakan persoalan perizinan&nbsp;apakah harus Kitabisa yang mengajukan atau masing-masing campaigner. Vikra mengharapkan agar RUU baru ini nantinya tidak mematikan tetapi dapat memfasilitasi para pegiat fundraising.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ketidakjelasan aturan kegiatan yang berkaitan dengan sumbangan telah memunculkan banyak kasus gugatan. Salah satunya adalah kasus gugatan konsumen terhadap Alfamart. Nur Rahman, mewakili Alfamart menyatakan bahwa Alfamart bukanlah badan publik melainkan perusahaan publik. Berkaitan dengan RUU, Alfamart memberikan masukan yaitu agar pengajuan perizinan dilakukan oleh pihak yayasan yang bekerja sama dengan pengumpula atau penyedia tempat seperti perusahaan Ritel, Mall, Restoran, dsb. Proses pengurusan izin penggalangan sumbangan dibuat online sepenuhnya, termasuk permohonan rekomendasi dari Dinas Sosial. Dalam RUU diharapkan lebih jelas tanggung jawab dan kewajiban secara hukum antara pihak pengumpull atau penyedia tempat dan pengelola atau penerima sumbangan masyarakat. Dan audit oleh akuntan publik independen dilakukan setiap tahun bukan setiap program karena akan memberatkan pihak lembaga sosial.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada akhirnya draft naskah RUU Penyelenggaraan Sumbangan masih perlu untuk dimatangkan lagi. Mengingat bahwa ruang lingkup kegiatan fundraising sangat luas dan dapat melibatkan kemitraan multipihak. Payung hukum yang jelas bagi semua pihak sangat diperlukan akan dapat terciptanya akuntabilitas dan transparasi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6suT0I0S3FaNlNzLUE?usp=sharing\">UNDUH MATERI PRESENTASI&nbsp;DAN DRAFT RUU&nbsp;</a></p>\n', 'f0788a433ee999ff3cd9b9df1318fef2.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-05 06:44:25', '2018-02-19 15:16:44', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-membedah-ruu-penyelenggaraan-sumbangan', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'U855cNCtO6lrQhN', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(560, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Dissecting the Donation Management Bill', '', 'This forum was held thanks to a collaboration between FI, Oxfam, MPBI, Ministry of Social Affaris, and UN OCHA. The discussion was lively and the event was well attended by participants from various organizations. It shows how important the Bill is for philanthropy in Indonesia.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Up until now, Law No. 9 on the Collection of Money and Goods (PUB) still determined the organization of donations This law was originally drafted in 1961. Time and the rapid development of new technologies has made the law increasingly less relevant.&nbsp; Of particular need is the provision of a legal umbrella for all parties concerned in the activities of organizing donations.&nbsp;The donation bill is expected to be the answer to this issue.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Filantropi Indonesia, in collaboration with OXFAM,&nbsp;held the 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Philanthropy&nbsp;Learning Forum to discuss the Implementation Bill on Tuesday, April 25<sup>th</sup>, 2017. According to Suratman, one of the drafting team, the PUB Act 1961 is not clear because it cannot provide legal certainty and fairness.&nbsp;The new Bill system will have 102 chapters in total.&nbsp;There are six objectives of the drafting of this bill: raising awareness, preventing the loss of money, goods or services, the effective channelling of money or services to the people in need, the creation of transparency and accountability, the creation of orderly administration, and the implementation of collection, and management of donations.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this discussion, Stefanus Aryawan of Yayasan Konservasi Alam Indonesia gave his opinion from the perspective of an intermediary institution, criticizing the draft Bill for its lack of rules and rights offering protection for donors.&nbsp;He also added that the bill lists the only relevant stakeholder as the Ministry of Social Affairs. He noted&nbsp;that the Ministry of Finance should be involved because of its relation to tax incentives.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Maitra W. Faiszal from Yayasan Sayangi Tunas Cilik (STC) continued, noting that the funding of NGOs overwhelmingly comes from individual donations, constituting around 60-70 percent of the total. Fundraising through various channels, such as face to face, digital fundraising, telemarketing, event fundraising, telethon provides the remainder. Regarding the registration of fundraising activities, she proposed&nbsp;that there should be no need to wait for permission.&nbsp;Even if there was a permit required for NGOs that have ongoing fundraising activities, then it should just be one registration process with a periodic reporting system.&nbsp; She also acknowledged the need for a clear rule on&nbsp;which&nbsp;autonomous entities are entitled to grant the permit.&nbsp;In addition, Maitra also proposed that the bill should not limit the minimum operational funds that can be taken from fundraising.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">FI also invited a speaker from the crowdfunding platform Kitabisa.com, which is a website that facilitates the public participation in donating or raising funds. The campaigners&nbsp;can come from anywhere, formal and&nbsp;informal institutions, as well as&nbsp;individuals. Kitabisa takes five percent of the donation for its operational funds.&nbsp;Regarding the bill, Vikra Ijas questioned where the role of Kitabisa is placed as&nbsp;the collector, the recipient, or the dealer.&nbsp;He also questioned the issue of applying for the permit, whether it should be the platform (in this case Kitabisa) or each campaigner.&nbsp;Vikra expects the new bill to be non-lethal but can facilitate fundraising activists.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unclear rules of activity relating to donations have led to many cases of lawsuits.&nbsp;One of them was a case of consumer lawsuit brought against Alfamart. In relation to the bill, Alfamart provided input for the submission of licensing done by the company in cooperation with pengumpula, the provider of spaces for retail, malls, restaurants, etc.&nbsp;The process of obtaining a donation collection permit is made online entirely, including a recommendation request from the Social Service.&nbsp;The bill is expected to have clearer legal responsibilities and obligations between the collecting party or the provider of the place and the manager or the recipient of the community&#39;s contribution.&nbsp;Audits by independent public accountants are conducted annually instead of every program because it will incriminate the social institutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The draft of the Bill on the Management of Donations still has many areas in which it can be improved.&nbsp;Given that the scope of fundraising activities is extensive and can involve multi-stakeholder partnerships, a&nbsp;clear legal umbrella for all parties is needed to provide accountability and transparency.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6suT0I0S3FaNlNzLUE?usp=sharing\">DOWNLOAD PRESENTASION AND THE BILL</a></p>\n', 'f0788a433ee999ff3cd9b9df1318fef2.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-05 06:44:25', '2018-02-19 15:16:44', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-dissecting-the-donation-management-bil', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'U855cNCtO6lrQhN', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(577, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 16', '', 'Diskusi bulanan Filantropi Indonesia kali ini bekerja sama dengan Yayasan Institut Danone dan Knowledge Sector Initiative (KSI) untuk mengangkat tema tentang riset', '<p>Untuk meningkatkan pemahaman dan kesadaran organisasi filantropi dan pelaku bisnis dalam mendukung pendanaan penelitian, Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan Knowledge Sector Initiative (KSI) dan Yayasan Institut Danone mengadakan Philanthropy Learning Forum ke-16 dengan tema &quot;<strong>Penguatan Kemitraan Filantropi dan Bisnis untuk Pengembangan Riset di Indonesia</strong>&quot;. Tujuan dari kegiatan ini adalah untuk memastikan bahwa ilmu sosial cukup terwakili dalam diskusi mengenai riset dan usaha untuk menyelesaikan masalah pendanaan dalam riset akan menjadi tema yang menarik.</p>\n\n<p>Secara khusus kegiatan ini bertujuan untuk:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Meningkatkan komunikasi dan dialog antara organisasi filantropi, sektor swasta dan pemerintah mengenai fungsi dan peran strategis penelitian dalam pembangunan nasional</li>\n	<li>Mengelaborasi beragam peluang dan skema kemitraan yang bisa dilakukan lembaga filantropi, sektor swasta dan pemerintah dalam pengembangan riset</li>\n	<li>mengidentifikasi kebijakan-kebijakan pemerintah &nbsp;yang mendukung dan menghambat filantropi dan bisnis dalam mendukung pengembangan riset di Indonesia</li>\n	<li>Mengidentifikasi tantangan dan hambatan serta solusinya dalam pembanguan kemitraan bagi pengembangan riset di Indonesia</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Narasumber:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Ocky Karna Radjasa</strong>, Direktorat Riset dan Pengabdian Masyarakat Kemenristek Dikti</li>\n	<li><strong>Annisa S. Febrina</strong>, Manajer Program Newton Fund</li>\n	<li><strong>Indrayana</strong>, GM Corporate Communication Indofood</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20PLF%2016.pdf\">UNDUH KERANGKA ACUAN ACARA</a></p>\n', 'fcc51a2913e471bbd175c5f833993685.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-15 07:55:01', '2017-05-15 15:07:35', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-16', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'Q9VgtvoF2kTzf3H', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-23 00:00:00', '2017-05-23 23:59:59'),
(578, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 16', '', 'This Filantropi Indonesia\'s monthly forum is in partnership with Danone Institute Foundation and Knowledge Sector Initiative (KSI) to discuss about philanthropy and business for research', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To enhance the understanding and awareness of philanthropic organizations and business actors in supporting research funding, Filantropi Indonesia in collaboration with the Knowledge Sector Initiative (KSI) and Danone Institute Foundation will hold the 16<sup>th</sup> Philanthropy Learning Forum with the theme &quot;<strong>Strengthening Philanthropy and Business Partnerships for Research Development in Indonesia</strong>&quot;. The purpose of this discussion is to ensure that social science is adequately represented in discussions about research and efforts to resolve funding issues in research will be an interesting theme.</p>\n\n<p>In particular this forum aims to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Improving communication and dialogue between philanthropic organizations, the private sector and the government on the function and role of strategic research in national development</li>\n	<li>Elaborate the various opportunities and partnership schemes that philanthropic agencies, the private sector and the government can engage in research development</li>\n	<li>Identify government policies that support and hinder philanthropy and business in support of research development in Indonesia</li>\n	<li>Identify challenges and constraints and solutions in developing partnerships for research development in Indonesia</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Speakers:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Ocky Karna Radjasa</strong>, Direktorat Riset dan Pengabdian Masyarakat Kemenristek Dikti</li>\n	<li><strong>Annisa S. Febrina</strong>, Manajer Program Newton Fund</li>\n	<li><strong>Indrayana</strong>, GM Corporate Communication Indofood</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20PLF%2016%281%29.pdf\">DOWNLOAD TERMS OF REFERENCE</a> (in Indonesian)</p>\n', 'fcc51a2913e471bbd175c5f833993685.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-15 07:55:01', '2017-05-15 15:07:35', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-16', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'Q9VgtvoF2kTzf3H', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-23 00:00:00', '2017-05-23 23:59:59'),
(579, 'Asia Venture Philanthropy Network Conference 2017', '', 'Konferensi tahunan dari AVPN diadakan untuk yang kelima kalinya. Tema tahun ini adalah \"Collaborating for Impact\" dan akan diadakan di Bangkok, Thailand. Acara ini memberi kesempatan untuk berbagi pengetahuan, kolaborasi dan advokasi untuk pertumbuhan ekosistem sosial di Asia.', '<h2>Collaborating for Impact</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The 3 day gathering will feature examples of collaboration from AVPN members across Asia including deep dives into sectors like: education, health, livelihoods, the environment, and more. The program will also include an overview of the social investment landscape in Asia, highlighting key challenges and opportunities across the spectrum of investment stages from grants to impact investment.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This year&rsquo;s theme &ldquo;Collaborating for Impact&rdquo; reflects the importance of partnership across sectors and borders when looking to tackle some of Asia&rsquo;s biggest challenges. The event will focus on the need for strategic and outcome-focused approaches to social investing across the full spectrum of social and financial returns &ndash; from grantmakers to impact investors.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At this year&rsquo;s Conference, speakers will include thought leaders, innovators and practitioners from across the region that are all making strides to grow and improve the philanthropy and social investment sector in Asia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://2017.avpn.asia/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/avpn-banner-horizontal.png\" style=\"height:419px; width:800px\" /></a></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n', '0dd43a18f035e69d8480b5df3537aa55.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-16 02:55:49', '2017-05-16 14:20:59', 5, 'asia-venture-philanthropy-network-conference-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'JeqUW2DvJX1Olts', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-07 00:00:00', '2017-06-09 23:59:59'),
(580, 'Asia Venture Philanthropy Network Conference 2017', '', 'The annual conference of AVPN will be held for the fifth time. This year\'s theme is \"Collaborating for Impact\" and will be held in Bangkok, Thailand. This event provides an opportunity to share knowledge, collaboration and advocacy for the growth of social ecosystems in Asia.', '<h2>Collaborating for Impact</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The 3 day gathering will feature examples of collaboration from AVPN members across Asia including deep dives into sectors like: education, health, livelihoods, the environment, and more. The program will also include an overview of the social investment landscape in Asia, highlighting key challenges and opportunities across the spectrum of investment stages from grants to impact investment.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This year&rsquo;s theme &ldquo;Collaborating for Impact&rdquo; reflects the importance of partnership across sectors and borders when looking to tackle some of Asia&rsquo;s biggest challenges. The event will focus on the need for strategic and outcome-focused approaches to social investing across the full spectrum of social and financial returns &ndash; from grantmakers to impact investors.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At this year&rsquo;s Conference, speakers will include thought leaders, innovators and practitioners from across the region that are all making strides to grow and improve the philanthropy and social investment sector in Asia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://2017.avpn.asia/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/avpn-banner-horizontal%281%29.png\" style=\"height:419px; width:800px\" /></a></p>\n', '0dd43a18f035e69d8480b5df3537aa55.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-16 02:55:49', '2017-05-16 14:20:59', 5, 'asia-venture-philanthropy-network-conference-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'JeqUW2DvJX1Olts', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-07 00:00:00', '2017-06-09 23:59:59'),
(581, 'Indonesia Company Award & SRI KEHATI Appreciation 2017', '', 'Acara ini diselenggarakan oleh Majalah SWA, Swanetwork dan Yayasan KEHATI ', '<p><a href=\"https://swa.co.id/swa/announcement/indonesia-green-company-award-sri-kehati-appreciation-2017\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Indonesia-Green-Company-Award-Sri-Kehati-Appreciation-2017.jpg\" style=\"height:494px; width:700px\" /></a></p>\n', 'd46495ad27940943360cf8c216b6d524.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-16 07:28:39', '2017-05-16 14:28:39', 5, 'indonesia-company-award-sri-kehati-appreciation-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'cOFEHrUYUdzrxMR', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-07 00:00:00', '2017-06-07 23:59:59'),
(582, 'Indonesia Company Award & SRI KEHATI Appreciation 2017', '', 'This event is brought to you by SWA Magazine, Swanetwork and KEHATI Foundation', '<p><a href=\"https://swa.co.id/swa/announcement/indonesia-green-company-award-sri-kehati-appreciation-2017\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Indonesia-Green-Company-Award-Sri-Kehati-Appreciation-2017%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:494px; width:700px\" /></a></p>\n', 'd46495ad27940943360cf8c216b6d524.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-16 07:28:39', '2017-05-16 14:28:39', 5, 'indonesia-company-award-sri-kehati-appreciation-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'cOFEHrUYUdzrxMR', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-07 00:00:00', '2017-06-07 23:59:59'),
(583, 'WORKSHOP DIGITAL FUNDRAISING & LAUNCHING AKSIBERSAMA.ID DAN SESAMA.ID', '', 'Lazismu mengadakan workshop digital fundraising mengingat pentingnya banyaknya penggalangan dana melalui media digital. Acara ini sekaligus launching platform aksibersama.ID dan sesama.ID', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Launching%20aksi%20bersama%20Lazismu.jpg\" style=\"height:877px; width:620px\" /></p>\n', '1959536afabbe8edd84c8d5ee3ba0752.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-16 07:52:00', '2017-05-16 14:52:00', 5, 'workshop-digital-fundraising-launching-aksibersama-id-dan-sesama-id', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'pOVCOzEdmPzLe5O', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-17 00:00:00', '2017-05-17 23:59:59'),
(584, 'WORKSHOP DIGITAL FUNDRAISING & LAUNCHING AKSIBERSAMA.ID DAN SESAMA.ID', '', 'Lazismu will hold a workshop on digital fundraising because of the importance of fundraising using digital media nowadays. This event is also the launching of aksibersama.id and sesama.id as their new platform.', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Launching%20aksi%20bersama%20Lazismu%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:877px; width:620px\" /></p>\n', '1959536afabbe8edd84c8d5ee3ba0752.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-16 07:52:00', '2017-05-16 14:52:00', 5, 'workshop-digital-fundraising-launching-aksibersama-id-dan-sesama-id', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'pOVCOzEdmPzLe5O', 'N', '', '', '2017-05-17 00:00:00', '2017-05-17 23:59:59'),
(585, '[Philanthropy Sharing Session] To Communicate and Promote Philanthropic Works Creatively', '', 'Sharing session ini merupakan bagian dari rangkaian acara Good Pitch2 SE Asia dan diselenggarakan berkat kerja sama antara Filantropi Indonesia, In-Docs dan Australian Embassy', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk pertama kalinya Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan In-Docs dan Kedutaan Besar Australia untuk menyelenggarakan suatu acara eksklusif bertajuk Philanthropy Sharing Session pada Jumat, 5 Mei 2017. Sesi ini diadakan sebagai bagian dari acara <a href=\"https://www.goodpitch2sea.org/\">Good Pitch<sup>2</sup> Southeast Asia</a> yang diadakan satu hari sebelumnya di Goethe Institute. Pada acara tersebut, Good Pitch<sup>2</sup> SE Asia bekerja sama dengan Good Pitch<sup>2</sup> Australia&nbsp;mendatangkan beberapa tamu dari sektor filantropi di negara kanguru tersebut.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1144.jpg\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropy Sharing Session ini diadakan di Kedutaan Besar Australia dan bersifat intim dengan peserta dari anggota dan mitra Filantropi Indonesia. Tema yang diangkat berkaitan dengan seni kreativitas dalam&nbsp; aktivitas filantropi, &ldquo;<strong>Mengkomunikasikan dan Mempromosikan Gerakan Filantropi Secara Kreatif</strong>&rdquo;. Empat tamu pembicara yang hadir adalah Sita Bala (Communications, Private Wealth Network), Hunter Johnson (Co-Founder, The Man Cave), Malinda Wink (Executive Director, Good Pitch2 Australia), dan Thomas Ng (Founder and Director, Genashtim); dengan moderator dari In-Docs, Amelia Hapsari. Sebelum dimulai, Alison Purnell (Counselor Advocacy and Outreach, Australian Embassy) memberikan ucapan selamat datang bagi para hadirin. Dilanjutkan kata sambutan perwakilan dari Filantropi Indonesia, Ibu Erna Witoelar yang mengungkapkan bahwa filantropi Indonesia dan Australia harus terus memperkuat relasi dan membangun jejaring.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1101.jpg\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Keempat pembicara membagikan pengalaman mereka, baik cerita sukses maupun kegagalan dalam mengkampanyekan isu sosial yang mereka perjuangkan. Malinda Wink menceritakan bagaimana kesulitan yang dia alami untuk meyakinkan donor bahwa film dokumenter bisa menjadi alat untuk mendorong perubahan sosial. Sita Bala dari PWN juga bercerita bagaimana organisasinya mengakomodasi kepentingan anggota-anggotanya dari keluarga HNWI yang beragam agar dapat fokus ke isu yang penting dan urgent. Hunter Johnson dari the Man Cave mengingatkan pentingnya untuk menjangkau anak muda dan memiliki strategi khusus untuk menggaet filantrop dari kalangan millennial. Sedangkan Thomas Ng memberikan perspektif dari sisi investasi sosial saat membangun organisasinya yang adalah B corporation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1083.jpg\" style=\"height:449px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Diskusi dan tanya jawab juga berlangsung hangat dan terarah dari sekitar 50 peserta mewakili&nbsp;yayasan dan lembaga filantropi di Indonesia yang ingin belajar langsung tentang cara-cara kreatif dan praktis dalam melaksanakan programnya. Dari acara ini kami berharap banyak pertukaran pikiran dan ide serta kerja sama yang terjalin antara sektor filantropi di kedua negara. Filantropi Indonesia akan terus berupaya untuk mendukung aktivitas filantropi bagi kelestarian seni kreativitas maupun sebaliknya.</p>\n', '13a67b6b8b8d485f0190c0dd8f516201.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-17 03:45:35', '2018-02-19 15:18:46', 5, '-philanthropy-sharing-session-to-communicate-and-promote-philanthropic-works-creatively', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '6mf0Z1q1wNxsnMR', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(586, '[Philanthropy Sharing Session] To Communicate and Promote Philanthropic Works Creatively', '', 'This exclusive sharing session is part of the Good Pitch2 SE Asia event, and was a collaboration between Filantropi Indonesia, In-Docs and the Australian Embassy', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For the first time, Filantropi Indonesia, in collaboration with In-Docs and the Australian Embassy, organized an exclusive event titled Philanthropy Sharing Session on Friday, May 5, 2017. It was a part of the&nbsp;Good Pitch<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;Southeast Asia&nbsp;event which was held a day earlier at the Goethe Institute.&nbsp; Good Pitch<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;SE Asia, in collaboration with the Good Pitch&nbsp;<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;Australia and the Australian Embassy, invited some guests from the philanthropic sector.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1144%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Philanthropy Sharing Session was held at the Australian Embassy, providing an intimate discussion with participants from members and partners of Filantropi Indonesia.&nbsp;The theme was &quot;<strong>To Communicate and Promote Philanthropic Works Creatively</strong>&quot;.&nbsp;The four guest speakers present were Sita Bala (Communications, Private Wealth Network), Hunter Johnson (Co-Founder, The Man Cave), Malinda Wink (Executive Director, Good Pitch2 Australia), and Thomas Ng (Founder and Director, Genashtim);&nbsp;the moderator was Amelia Hapsari, the Program Director for In-Docs.&nbsp;Before the discussion, Alison Purnell (Counselor Advocacy and Outreach, Australian Embassy) gave a warm welcome to the audience. This was&nbsp;followed by an opening speech from Erna Witoelar who shared her hope that Indonesian and Australian philanthropic organisations would continue to strengthen their relations and build networks.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1101%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The four speakers then shared their experiences, both successful and otherwise, in communicating the social issues they were advocating.&nbsp;Malinda Wink recounted the difficulties she had in convincing donors that documentary films could be a tool to encourage social change.&nbsp;Sita Bala from PWN shared how her organization accommodates the interests of its members from diverse, wealthy families in order to focus on important and urgent issues.&nbsp;Hunter Johnson of the Man Cave reminded the importance of reaching out to young people and shared his strategy for attracting millennial philanthropists.&nbsp;Finally, Thomas Ng gave a perspective from the social investment world, explain why he founded his B corporation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1083%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:393px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The discussion was rich and focused with around 50 participants representing&nbsp;foundations and philanthropy organizations in Indonesia who wanted to learn about creative and practical ways of implementing their programs from successful practitioners.&nbsp; We hope there were many exchanges of knowledge and ideas, as well as increased scope for future partnerships between the philanthropy sector in both countries.&nbsp;Filantropi Indonesia will continue to strive to support philanthropic activities aimed at the preservation of creative arts and culture.</p>\n', '13a67b6b8b8d485f0190c0dd8f516201.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-17 03:45:35', '2018-02-19 15:18:46', 5, '-philanthropy-sharing-session-to-communicate-and-promote-philanthropic-works-creatively', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '6mf0Z1q1wNxsnMR', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(597, 'Fresh Crowdfunding, Lazismu Luncurkan Aksibersama.ID dan Sesama.ID, Laboratorium Kewirausahaan Sosial dan Filantropi Islam FEB-UHAMKA', '', 'Lembaga Amil Zakat Nasional (Lazismu) meluncurkan platform baru: aksibersama.id dan sesama.id yang dibalut konsep inovasi berbagi. Kedua platform ini sebagai jembatan bagi masyarakat yang ingin berbagi kepada siapapun secara online.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><small>17 Mei 2017, Jakarta</small></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><small>Sumber: Siaran pers Lazismu (<a href=\"http://www.lazismu.org/fresh-crowdfunding-lazismu-luncurkan-platform-aksi-bersama-dan-sesama/\">http://www.lazismu.org/fresh-crowdfunding-lazismu-luncurkan-platform-aksi-bersama-dan-sesama</a>)</small></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Lembaga Amil Zakat Nasional (Lazismu), salah satu anggota Filantropi Indonesia kemarin (17/5) meluncurkan sebuah platform baru: <em>aksibersama.id</em> dan <em>sesama.id</em> yang dibalut konsep inovasi berbagi. Kedua platform ini berperan sebagai jembatan bagi masyarakat yang ingin berbagi kepada siapapun secara online. Layaknya platform <em>crowdfunding</em>, aksibersama.id memfasilitasi dermawan baik perorangan maupun komunitas untuk menggalang dana dan berkampanye dalam aksi sosial dan kemanusiaan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hilman Latief, Ketua Badan Pengurus Lazismu mengatakan, &ldquo;Aksi Bersama adalah dapurnya untuk mengajukan program-program sosial terbaik suatu komunitas.&rdquo; Sementara itu sesama.id adalah sejenis <em>marketplace</em> yang menghubungkan antara penjual dan pembeli untuk melakukan transaksi. Barang-barang yang diperjualbelikan juga dapat didonasikan kepada orang/lembaga lain. Pimpinan pelaksana harian Lazismu, Joko Intarto, menyampaikan bahwa kehadiran dua startup ini diharapkan akan mampu meraih audiensnya. &ldquo;Lebih luas lagi bagi kegiatan fundraising yaitu pengguna online yang sudah akrab di Indonesia dan gemar berbelanja online,&rdquo; paparnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selain peluncuran platform online tersebut, Lazismu bersama FEB-UHAMKA juga meluncurkan Laboratorium Kewirausahaan Sosial dan Filantropi Islam FEB-UHAMKA. Menurut Dekan FEB-UHAMKA, laboratorium ini merupakan suatu wadah pendidikan yang memberikan kesempatan bagi mahasiswa untuk meningkatkan kemampuan di bidang bisnis yang berdampak sosial dan mengukuhkan filantropi Islam.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Informasi lebih lanjut, hubungi:</p>\n\n<p>Sdr. Falhan: 0857 1498 8979</p>\n\n<p>Sdr. Author: 0815 9830 757</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.lazismu.org\">www.lazismu.org</a></p>\n', 'b8167ed3edab4b2e0f15eb2156756710.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-18 07:28:17', '2018-02-23 09:33:52', 5, 'fresh-crowdfunding-lazismu-luncurkan-aksibersama-id-dan-sesama-id-laboratorium-kewirausahaan-sosial-dan-filantropi-islam-feb-uhamka', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'spkuuGQBM8OgOTp', 'N', '', 'Lazismu', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(598, 'Lazismu launches Aksibersama.ID and Sesama.ID, Social Entrepreneurship Lab and Islamic Philanthropy with FEB-UHAMKA', '', 'The National Institute of Amil Zakat (Lazismu) launches new platforms: aksibersama.id and sesama.id with the concept of sharing innovation. Both of these platforms will be a bridge for people who want to share resources online.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><small>Jakarta, May 17, 2017</small></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><small>Source: Press Release <a href=\"http://www.lazismu.org/fresh-crowdfunding-lazismu-luncurkan-platform-aksi-bersama-dan-sesama/\">http://www.lazismu.org/fresh-crowdfunding-lazismu-luncurkan-platform-aksi-bersama-dan-sesama/</a></small></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lazismu (National Institute of Amil Zakat), one of the members of Filantropi Indonesia, launched two new platforms yesterday (May 17, 2017), with the aim of encouraging and sharing innovations.&nbsp;Both <em>aksibersama.id</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>sesama.id</em> serve as channels for people who want to share resources with other users online.&nbsp;The first platform, aksibersama.id, is a peer-to-peer finance provider. Like most crowdfunding&nbsp;platforms, aksibersama.id facilitates both individual and community philanthropists in raising funds and advancing their campaigns for social and humanitarian action.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hilman Latief, Chairman of Lazismu Management Board said, &quot;Aksi Bersama (Joint Action) is the source for the best social programs for communities.&quot; Meanwhile sesama.id is a&nbsp;marketplace&nbsp;that connects buyers and sellers interested in mutual transactions.&nbsp;The goods traded can also be donated to other people / institutions.&nbsp;The chief executive of Lazismu, Joko Intarto, said that the presence of the two start-ups is expected to service a much broader audience both &ldquo;for fundraising activities by online users who are familiar in Indonesia and those who love to shop online,&quot; he explained.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In addition to the launching of the online platform, Lazismu collaborated with FEB-UHAMKA in launching the Social Entrepreneurship laboratory, and Philanthropy Laboratory of Islam.&nbsp;According to the Dean of FEB-UHAMKA, the laboratory is an educational tool that provides an opportunity for students to improve their ability in those business fields which have social impact and ultimately strengthen Islamic philanthropy.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>For more information contact:</p>\n\n<p>Falhan: 0857 1498 8979</p>\n\n<p>Author: 0815 9830 757</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.lazismu.org/\">w</a><a href=\"https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&amp;prev=_t&amp;sl=id&amp;tl=en&amp;u=http://www.lazismu.org\">ww.lazismu.org</a></p>\n', 'b8167ed3edab4b2e0f15eb2156756710.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-18 07:28:17', '2018-02-23 09:33:52', 5, 'lazismu-launches-aksibersama-id-and-sesama-id-social-entrepreneurship-lab-and-islamic-philanthropy-with-feb-uhamka', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'spkuuGQBM8OgOTp', 'N', '', 'Lazismu', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(599, 'DAAI Night 2017: &quot;My Dream: China Disabled People&#039;s Performing Art Troupe&quot;', '', 'Selama 10 tahun DAAI TV Indonesia konsisten menyajikan tayangan yang Benar, Bajik, Indah bagi para pemirsa setianya. Sebagai wujud terima kasih kepada para Corporate Sponsor, Friends of DAAI, dan Pemirsa setia, DAAI TV mempersembahkan acara DAAI Night 2017.Di acara ini, DAAI TV menghadirkan China Disabled People’s Performing Art Troupe (CDPPAT) dari Beijing, Tiongkok dengan pertunjukan memukau mereka yang bertajuk “My Dream Dream”.', '<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/2017%2005%2024%20Panduan%20untuk%20titip%20distirbusi%20undangan_Lengkap.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DAAI%20TV%20poster%20komunitas%20%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:980px; width:700px\" /></a></p>\n', '58de2c08c3a52a0af1412a5f4c4de333.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-26 03:33:48', '2017-06-02 03:06:18', 5, 'daai-night-2017-my-dream-china-disabled-people-s-performing-art-troupe-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'UL3bzxerEFOaI5d', 'N', '', '', '2017-07-29 00:00:00', '2017-07-30 23:59:59'),
(600, 'DAAI Night 2017: &quot;My Dream: China Disabled People&#039;s Performing Art Troupe&quot;', '', 'For 10 years DAAI TV Indonesia consistently presents True, Wholesome, Beautiful for its loyal viewers. As a show of gratitude to the Corporate Sponsors, Friends of DAAI and Loyal Viewers, DAAI TV presents DAAI Night 2017. In this event, DAAI TV presents China Disabled People\'s Performing Art Troupe (CDPPAT) from Beijing, China with stunning performances by those who Titled \"My Dream Dream\".', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DAAI%20TV%20poster%20komunitas%20%281%29%281%29.jpg\" style=\"width:800px\" /></p>\n', '58de2c08c3a52a0af1412a5f4c4de333.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-26 03:33:48', '2017-06-02 03:06:18', 5, 'daai-night-2017-my-dream-china-disabled-people-s-performing-art-troupe-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'UL3bzxerEFOaI5d', 'N', '', '', '2017-07-29 00:00:00', '2017-07-30 23:59:59'),
(601, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 17: Mempromosikan Keberagaman Melalui Filantropi Lintas Iman', '', 'Diskusi bulan Ramadhan kali ini khusus membahas mengenai filantropi sebagai alat untuk mempromosikan keberagaman di Indonesia dengan mendatangkan narasumber yang mendukung kerukunan antar umat beragama melalui aktivitas kedermawanan mereka', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Di tengah meningkatnya kekerasan, intoleransi, radikalisme dan diskriminasi atas nama agama, kegiatan filantropi yang dilakukan oleh komunitas, kelompok dan organisasi yang berafiliasi pada agama tertentu juga berkembang pesat. Meski berbasis agama tertentu, dalam praktiknya kegiatan berbagi dan menolong sesama yang dilakukan oleh lembaga-lembaga ini dilakukan tanpa membeda-bedakan suku, agama atau ras tertentu. Mereka memberikan dukungan dan bantuan mereka kepada individu atau kelompok-kelompok lainnya tanpa diskriminasi, tanpa melihat latar belakang etnis, suku atau agama penerima manfaat.<br />\n<br />\nFilantropi lintas iman dipercaya dapat menjadi instrumen untuk mempromosikan kerukunan beragama dan toleransi di Indonesia. Praktek filantropi antar umat beragama tidak hanya memberikan kontribusi yang signifikan dalam menyemai bibit perdamaian, toleransi beragama dan dialog antaragama, tetapi juga memajukan ekonomi, kesehatan, pendidikan dan kesejahteraan masyarakat.<br />\n<br />\nMenyadari bahwa filantropi lintas iman dapat menjadi instrumen dalam menciptakan kerukunan dan gotong royong, Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan @america mengundang Anda&nbsp;untuk berpartisipasi dalam acara <strong><em>Philanthropy Learning Forum</em> 17</strong> dengan tema<strong> &ldquo;Menyatukan Keberagaman Melalui Filantropi Lintas Iman&rdquo;</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/15l3QAsWl1XBRhYN2\">DAFTAR PESERTA</a></p>\n', '5b8dedb139ab2b77c1cfe677a6148d85.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-29 09:30:39', '2017-06-05 10:22:26', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-17-mempromosikan-keberagaman-melalui-filantropi-lintas-iman', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', '50XS4HCpTK0ObBA', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-06 00:00:00', '2017-06-06 23:59:59'),
(602, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum 17: Promoting Diversity through Interfaith Philanthropy', '', 'This special Ramadhan PLF discussion is specifically about philanthropy as a tool to promote diversity in Indonesia by bringing in speakers who support harmony between religious communities through their philanthropy activities', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the midst of increasing violence, intolerance, radicalism and discrimination in the name of religion, philanthropy activities carried out by communities, groups and organizations affiliated with certain religions are also growing rapidly. Although based on certain religions, in practice the sharing and helping activities of fellow committed by these institutions are conducted without distinction of a particular tribe, religion or race. They provide their support and assistance to individuals or other groups without discrimination, regardless of the ethnic, tribal or religious background of the beneficiaries.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Interfaith philanthropy is believed to be an instrument to promote religious harmony and tolerance in Indonesia. The practice of inter-faith philanthropy not only contributes significantly to the seedling of peace, religious tolerance and interreligious dialogue, but also promotes economic, health, education and welfare.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Recognizing that interfaith philanthropy can be instrumental in creating harmony and mutual cooperation, Filantropi Indonesia in collaboration with @america invite&nbsp;you to participate in the Philanthropy Learning Forum 17 event with the theme &quot;<strong>Uniting Diversity Through Interfaith Philanthrop</strong>y&quot;.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/15l3QAsWl1XBRhYN2\">REGISTRATION</a></p>\n', '5b8dedb139ab2b77c1cfe677a6148d85.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-29 09:30:39', '2017-06-05 10:22:26', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-17-promoting-diversity-through-interfaith-philanthropy', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', '50XS4HCpTK0ObBA', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-06 00:00:00', '2017-06-06 23:59:59'),
(609, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Penguatan Kemitraan Filantropi dan Bisnis untuk Pengembangan Riset di Indonesia', '', 'PLF ke-16 diselenggarakan berkat kemitraan dengan Knowledge Sector Initiative dan Yayasan Danone Institut. Dalam diskusi ini, kami berbicara tentang bagaimana sumber daya dari filantropi dan sektor bisnis dapat mendukung penelitian dan oleh karena itu mendukung pemerintah untuk mencapai tujuan pembangunan berkelanjutan', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Di Indonesia pengembangan riset masih dianggap berada di bawah&nbsp;tanggung jawab pemerintah. Hal tersebut menjadi salah satu penyebab mengapa riset di Indonesia mengalami ketertinggalan dibandingkan negara lain di Asia Tenggara, seperti Malaysia dan Thailand. Untuk memajukan riset di Indonesia dibutuhkan kemitraan yang strategis, salah satunya melibatkan&nbsp;filantropi dan bisnis. Menyadari pentingnya kemitraan dalam riset maka Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan <em>Philanthropy Learning Forum </em>ke<em>-</em>16 pada Selasa, 23 Mei 2017 dengan tema <em>Penguatan Kemitraan Filantropi dan Bisns untuk Pengembangan Riset di Indonesia.</em> Dalam kesempatan tersebut dihadirkan empat narasumber yaitu, Okky K. Radjasa dari Kemenristek Dikti, Annisa S. Febrina dan Femmy Soemantri dari Newton Fund, serta Deni Puspahadi dari Indofood Riset Nugraha.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1225%281%29.JPG\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Okky menyatakan bahwa semenjak tahun 2014 daya saing upaya penelitian di Indonesia turun dari tahun ke tahun. Sebanyak 60 persen asset penelitian atau belanja R&amp;D (research &amp; development)&nbsp;yang ada di Indonesia dikendalikan oleh Amerika, Cina, Jepang dan Korea Selatan. Sementara itu hanya 60 persen dana BOPTN yang digunakan untuk riset. Hal ini terjadi karena riset di Indonesia masih belum diperhatikan maka belum dapat didanai secara penuh. Apabila dibandingkan, perkembangan riset Indonesia pada tahun 2040 baru dapat dianggap setara dengan Korea Selatan pada tahun 2015.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk dapat memajukan riset di Indonesia dibutuhkan peran dari organisasi riset di luar pemerintah seperti Newton Fund&nbsp;yang merupakan program kemitraan riset yang memberikan dampak sosial ekonomi dan memiliki paham trasnparan dan kompetitif. Newton Fund lebih memiliki jaringan yang kuat dengan pihak luar, khususnya British Council. Secara keseluruhan investasi yang dilakukan Inggris di Indonesia&nbsp;16 persennya dilakukan untuk riset di Indonesia. Di Indonesia riset yang dilakukan Newton Fund sudah dimulai sejak&nbsp;September 2014. Bentuk kegiatannnya adalah <em>open call</em>, ada 2 <em>regular calls</em> (tiap tahun) dan <em>thematic calls</em> (<em>one-off</em>). Salah satu contoh riset yang telah dilakukan adalah riset yang bekerja sama dengan universitas di Makassar untuk melakukakn riset tentang coklat (cocoa). Dalam pelaksanaan risetnya Newton Fund menggunakan konsep kemitraan bisnis akademisi dengan pemerintah.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1224.JPG\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kemitraan bisnis dalam riset juga memiliki poin&nbsp;penting. Seperti yang dilakukan oleh Indofood Riset Nugraha (IRN). Dalam sejarahnya, program ini dulunya bernama Program Bogasari Nugraha yang berlangsung antara tahun 1998-2005. Semenjak itu berubah menjadi Indofood Riset Nugraha hingga sekarang. IRN merupakan CSR pillar Platform yang bertujuan membuat hidup menjadi lebih dalam bidang ekonomi, kemanusiaan dan dll. Tetapi lebih berfokus pada ketahanan pangan baik itu dalam produk lokal maupun impor. Setiap tahunan Indofood Riset Nugraha setiap tahunnya melakukan riset utuk ketahanan pangan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dari diskusi ini terlihat bahwa kemitraan filantropi dan bisnis dapat menjadi solusi baru dalam pengembangan riset. Mengingat bahwa pada dasawarsa terakhir ini lembaga filantropi berkembang pesat dengan berbagai fokus kerja. Selain itu diharapkan dengan dorongan sumber daya yang cukup besar dari filantropi dan bisnis, riset yang dikerjakan tidak hanya berhenti sampai publikasi, namun dapat diaplikasikan sesuai hasil penelitian.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n', 'c86ca3f67326cb1093cfcf13c54459aa.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-30 04:41:13', '2018-02-19 15:20:54', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-penguatan-kemitraan-filantropi-dan-bisnis-untuk-pengembangan-riset-di-indonesia', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '9HO9WDSFNOUF3Zh', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(610, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Strengthening Philanthropy and Business Partnerships for Research Development in Indonesia', '', 'The 16th PLF was held in partnership with Knowledge Sector Initiative and Danone Institute Foundation. In this discussion, we talked about how resources from philanthropy and business sector can support research and therefore support the government to achieve development goals ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In Indonesia, the responsibility for research development is seen as remaining in the hands of the government.&nbsp;This is one of the reasons why research in Indonesia is lagging behind other countries such as Malaysia and Thailand.&nbsp;To promote research in Indonesia requires strategic partnerships, namely, the involvement of philanthropic and business elements.&nbsp;Recognizing the importance of partnerships in Indonesia, Filantropi Indonesia held the 16<sup>th</sup> Philanthropy Learning Forum<em>,</em> with the theme of&nbsp;Strengthening Partnership for Development, Business Philanthropy, and Research in Indonesia on the 23<sup>rd</sup> of May, 2017<em>.</em>&nbsp;On this occasion, there were four speakers, Okky K. Radjasa from Kemenristek Dikti, Annisa S. Febrina and Femmy Soemantri from Newton Fund, and Deni Puspahadi from Indofood Research Nugraha.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1225.JPG\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Okky stated that since 2014 the competitiveness of research efforts in Indonesia has declined year by year.&nbsp;As much as 60 percent of research assets or R &amp; D spending in Indonesia is controlled by America, China, Japan and South Korea.&nbsp;Meanwhile only 60 percent of BOPTN funds are used for research.&nbsp;This happens because some research in Indonesia is still not considered official, so it cannot be fully funded.&nbsp;When compared, the forecast development of Indonesian research in 2040 can only be considered equivalent to South Korea in 2015.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In order to advance research in Indonesia, the role of non-governmental research organizations must become more integral. Organisations such as the Newton Foundation, a research partnership program that seeks to make a socio-economic impact, are increasingly important to incorporate into research networks.&nbsp;The Newton Foundation has a stronger network with outsiders, especially the British Council. Of the overall investments made by the UK in Indonesia, 16 percent is allocated towards research in Indonesia.&nbsp;The research conducted by the Newton Fund in Indonesia began in September 2014. The form of activities is open call, with 2 regular calls (annual) and thematic calls (one-off).&nbsp;One example of these successful partnerships was the research done on the cocoa plant in collaboration with universities in Makassar.&nbsp;In the implementation of their research, the Newton Fund uses the concept of academic business partnership with the government.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1224%281%29.JPG\" style=\"height:600px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Business partnerships in research are also important.&nbsp;Some examples include those partnerships undertaken by Indofood Research Nugraha (IRN).&nbsp;Historically, this program used to be called Bogasari Nugraha Program which took place between 1998 - 2005. Since then it has been renamed as Indofood Research Nugraha.&nbsp;IRN is a pillar platform for CSR that aims to improve economic and humanitarian conditions, with a focus on food security both in terms of local and imported products.&nbsp;Every year Indofood Research Nugraha conducts research directly into these areas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">From this discussion it was seen how philanthropic and business partnerships can provide a new solution for lagging research development, especially given that in the last decade philanthropic institutions have grown rapidly with a variety of focus areas. It is also hoped that with a substantial increase in resources that the philanthropic and business organisations may provide, the work done can continue past publication into the real-world application.</p>\n', 'c86ca3f67326cb1093cfcf13c54459aa.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-30 04:41:13', '2018-02-19 15:20:54', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-strengthening-philanthropy-and-business-partnerships-for-research-development-in-indonesia', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '9HO9WDSFNOUF3Zh', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(617, 'Ramadhan Talk @america: Volunteering and Giving Back to Community', '', 'Ramadhan adalah bulan penuh berkah. Kami berkolaborasi dengan @america untuk mengadakan Ramadhan talk dan mendatangkan pembicara yang aktif di bidang filantropi melalui kegiatan relawan dan berdonasi.', '<p style=\"margin-left:0.5pt; text-align:justify\">Kegiatan filantropi atau yang lebih dikenal berbagi dapat dilakukan oleh siapa saja. Di tengah masyarakat modern yang hidup di kota &ndash; kota besar kesibukan pekerjaan nyatanya tidak dapat membatasi aktivitas sosial.&nbsp;Tidak mudah untuk dapat meluangkan waktu diantara kesibukan pekerjaan untuk aktivitas kerelawanan. Kerelawanan merupakan sebuah upaya untuk membantu orang lain tanpa ada paksaan dan tanpa imbalan. Apa yang mereka lakukan ini akan dapat menjadi contoh baik bagi orang lain termasuk para generasi muda.</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.5pt; text-align:justify\">Bentuk keralawanan dari para professional memiliki banyak cara dan model yang unik serta kreatif. Bantuan mereka tidak hanya sekadar memberikan bantuan materi tetapi juga membangun sistem pemberdayaan secara berkelanjutan. Kegiatan sosial tersebut tidak hanya dilakukan secara individual tetapi juga kelompok. Tidak jarang mereka pun mendirikan komunitas untuk dapat menjadi wadah bersama dalam berinteraksi dan melakukan gerakan sosial. Dampak positif dari kegiatan kerelawanan para professional tidak hanya terbantunya orang lain tetapi juga dapat menjadi media untuk memperluas pertemanan, jaringan, dan kemitraan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Oleh karena itu Filantropi Indonesia bersama dengan @america akan mengadakan <em>Ramadhan Talk</em> dengan tema <strong>&quot;<em>Volunteering and Giving Back to Community</em>&quot;</strong><em>. </em>Acara ini nantinya merupakan sharing pengalaman dari para professional tentang aktivitas kerelawanan mereka yang meliputi alasan, hambatan dan harapan. Kegiatan ini akan dapat memberikan inspirasi bagi mereka yang hadir untuk dapat lebih peduli kepada orang lain.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><u>Bio singkat nara sumber:</u></h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Zohra Atmar</strong>&nbsp;is a State Department Foreign Service Officer (FSO) who is currently working as Conflict Advisor in the Bureau for Conflict and Stabilization Operations</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Qorsho Hassan<em>&nbsp;</em></strong>is<strong>&nbsp;</strong>a graduate student obtaining a Master&rsquo;s in Education, and a compassionate and devoted bilingual educator who serves at-risk Somali students.</li>\n	<li><strong>Wayah Wiroto, PhD</strong>&nbsp;is the&nbsp;GE Renewable Hydro Country Leader, GE Indonesia.&nbsp;Since 2016 &ndash; now GE Volunteers Chairman Indonesia.&nbsp; 2011-now, International Advisory Board at YCAB Foundation. &nbsp;</li>\n	<li><strong>Sita Supomo</strong> is the Chief Volunteer Architect at Volunteer ID who design employee volunteering for sustainable development program and employee volunteering policy</li>\n	<li><strong>Muhammad Fikri</strong>, volunteer at Rotaract Club Semanggi</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/bVBw0ty0bbPDRkqb2\">PENDAFTARAN PESERTA</a></p>\n', 'ff77bef1d0cd3ebc539969d133a62def.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-31 07:28:21', '2017-06-09 12:10:37', 5, 'ramadhan-talk-america-volunteering-and-giving-back-to-community', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'KQN0yJEHc4bhD0s', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-13 00:00:00', '2017-06-13 23:59:59'),
(618, 'Ramadhan Talk @america: Volunteering and Giving Back to Community', '', 'Ramadhan is a month of giving; we collaborate with @america to present you a small talk with speakers who are heavily involved in doing philanthropy work through volunteering and giving.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropic activities or better known sharing can be done by anyone. In the midst of modern society living in big cities busy work can not in fact limit social activity. It is not easy to spend time among the busy work for voluntary activities. Volunteering is an effort to help others without coercion and without rewards. What they do this will be a good example for others including the younger generation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The form of volunteering&nbsp;from professionals has many unique and creative ways and models. Their assistance not only provides material assistance but also builds a sustainable empowerment system. Social activities are not only done individually but also groups. Not infrequently they also set up a community to be a joint container in interacting and performing social movements. The positive impact of voluntary activities of professionals not only help others but also can be used for expanding friendships, networks, and partnerships.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Therefore Filantropi Indonesia together with @america will hold a&nbsp;Ramadhan Talk with the theme &quot;V<strong>olunteering and Giving Back to Community</strong>&quot;. This event will be a sharing of experience from professionals about their volunteering activities which include their motivations, obstacles and expectations. This activity will be able to inspire those present to be more caring to others.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><u>Short bio of the speakers</u>:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Zohra Atmar</strong>&nbsp;is a State Department Foreign Service Officer (FSO) who is currently working as Conflict Advisor in the Bureau for Conflict and Stabilization Operations</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Qorsho Hassan<em>&nbsp;</em></strong>is<strong>&nbsp;</strong>a graduate student obtaining a Master&rsquo;s in Education, and a compassionate and devoted bilingual educator who serves at-risk Somali students.</li>\n	<li><strong>Wayah Wiroto, PhD</strong>&nbsp;is the&nbsp;GE Renewable Hydro Country Leader, GE Indonesia.&nbsp;Since 2016 &ndash; now GE Volunteers Chairman Indonesia.&nbsp; 2011-now, International Advisory Board at YCAB Foundation. &nbsp;</li>\n	<li><strong>Sita Supomo</strong> is the Chief Volunteer Architect at Volunteer ID who design employee volunteering for sustainable development program and employee volunteering policy</li>\n	<li><strong>Muhammad Fikri </strong>is a&nbsp;volunteer at Rotaract Club Semanggi</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/bVBw0ty0bbPDRkqb2\">REGISTER HERE</a></p>\n', 'ff77bef1d0cd3ebc539969d133a62def.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-05-31 07:28:21', '2017-06-09 12:10:37', 5, 'ramadhan-talk-america-volunteering-and-giving-back-to-community', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'KQN0yJEHc4bhD0s', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-13 00:00:00', '2017-06-13 23:59:59'),
(627, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Mempromosikan Keberagaman melalui Filantropi Lintas Iman', '', 'Di bulan Ramadhan ini, Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan @america untuk berbicara tentang filantropi lintas iman atau inklusif. Tema diskusi ini dianggap tepat dan sesuai dengan kondisi hari ini di mana agama dan ras dijadikan alasan untuk membenci dan menolak untuk saling tolong menolong. ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ujaran kebencian (<em>hate speech</em>) terhadap agama serta etnis yang dianggap berbeda makin marak di masyarakat belakangan ini. Dampak negatif dari situasi tersebut telah meningkatkan kekerasan, intoleransi dan diskriminasi atas nama agama. Ditengah situasi tersebut kegiatan filantropi yang dilakukan oleh komunitas, kelompok dan organisasi yang berafiliasi pada agama tertentu juga berkembang pesat. Meski berbasis agama tertentu, dalam praktiknya kegiatan berbagi dan menolong sesama yang dilakukan oleh lembaga-lembaga ini dilakukan tanpa membeda-bedakan suku, agama atau ras tertentu.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_5554.JPG\" style=\"height:534px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Menyadari bahwa filantropi lintas iman dapat menjadi instrumen dalam menciptakan kerukunan, toleransi dan gotong royong, maka Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan @America mengangkat masalah tersebut dalam acara <em>Philanthropy Learning Forum 17</em> yang diselenggarakan pada Selasa, 6 Juni 2017. Tema yang diangkat dalam kegiatan ini adalah &ldquo;Mempromosikan Keberagaman Melalui Filantropi Lintas Iman&rdquo;. Dihadirkan tiga pembicara dalam acara tersebut, Haidar Bagir dari Filantropi Indonesia, J. Victor Rembeth mewakli Humanitarian Forum Indonesia (HFI), dan Muhammad Nuzul dari Gerakan Mari Berbagi (GMB).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bagi Haidar, tidak ada batas garis jika ingin melakukan filantropi. Keliru jika ada pendapat umum bila zakat hanya untuk muslim, serta kegiatan filantropi yang dilakukan umat muslim hanya sebatas untuk menolong sesama muslim. Dia menekankan bahwa membagi-bagi kemanusiaan sesuai dengan garis-garis agama tidak bisa dibenarkan dalam tradisi agama Islam. Bahwa Allah mengajarkan bersikap adil yang artinya bermoral dan berbuat baik terhadap mereka yang juga berbuat adil bahkan terhadap non-muslim. Ia mengingatkan bahwa saling memberi lintas iman adalah kunci dari melawan radikalisme yang didasarkan kebencian.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_5571_edit.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara itu Victor menjelaskan bahwa ruang lingkup HFI hampir sama seperti filantropi dengan mengutamakan persatuan perbedaan dan kejujuran. Ia mengutarakan bahwa tugas utama lembaga kemanusiaan adalah untuk memartabatkan manusia. Selain itu Victor juga mendorong agar dialog dan wacana lintas agama harus menjunjung tinggi kejujuran, dalam arti jangan hanya di depan terlihat baik tapi di belakang malah saling menghujat kembali. HFI sendiri banyak mengalami kasus di mana organisasi lintas agama bisa saling menghormati demi isu kemanusiaan khususnya pada saat bencana atau situasi darurat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nuzul dari GMB membagikan tentang misi dari organisasinya. Ia mengatakan gerakan ini mengajak anak muda untuk merasakan langsung bagaimana dia menerima bantuan dari orang lain dan juga berbagi dengan orang lain tanpa memandang latar belakang. GMB ingin mengajarkan bahwa berbagi dalam perbedaan harus dimulai dari diri sendiri dan kemudian ditularkan kepada orang lain.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_5589_edit.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bicara mengenai filantropi lintas iman, yang pertama bukan bicara soal keyakinannya, tetapi mengenai nilai-nilai dari agama. Penting untuk menjernihkan sikap agama dalam hubungan antar umat beragama. Mengingat bahwa sekarang ini, dimana berbagai penafsiran mengenai agama nyatanya membuat situasi menjadi meruncing. Upaya untuk menjernihkan sikap beragama juga tidak boleh berhenti hanya pada wacana. Organisasi seperti Filantropi Indonesia dan lembaga lainnya harus terus menerus menyebarkan berita dan melakukan upaya nyata yang memperlihatkan tentang kegiatan filantropi lintas iman.&nbsp;Kita juga harus menggunakan pendidikan dasar dan pendidikan tinggi untuk mengajarkan hidup bertoleransi di tengah masyarakat yang beragam, karena sebagian besar dari mereka tidak tahu mengenai isu dan konteksnya.</p>\n', '188780f5b1fc48e848df1713b176cdc8.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-09 08:23:40', '2018-02-19 15:23:16', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-mempromosikan-keberagaman-melalui-filantropi-lintas-iman', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '1gswIK3X14y8JrN', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(628, '[Philanthropy Learning Forum] Promoting Diversity through Interfaith Philanthropy', '', 'During Ramadhan month, Filantropi Indonesia partnered with @america to talk about interfaith or inclusive philanthropy. The discussion is very fitted to current situation where religion and race become tools to hate and to refuse helping each other.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hate speech&nbsp;against certain religions and ethnicities has been increasing in our society recently.&nbsp;This has increased violence, intolerance and discrimination in the name of religion.&nbsp;In contrast with this situation, or perhaps because of, the amount of philanthropic activities by communities, groups and organizations affiliated with certain religions is also growing rapidly.&nbsp;Although they are based on distinct religions, the sharing and assistance activities by these institutions are conducted without discriminating between groups, religions or race.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_5554_edit.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Recognizing that interfaith philanthropy can be instrumental in creating harmony, tolerance and mutual cooperation, Filantropi Indonesia, in partnership with @america (US cultural centre based in Jakarta), raised the issue of inclusive philanthropy in the 17<sup>th</sup> Philanthropy<em> Learning Forum </em>held on the Tuesday the 6<sup>th</sup> of June 6, 2017. The theme was &quot;Promoting Diversity through Interfaith Philanthropy&quot;.&nbsp;There were three speakers at the event, Haidar Bagir from Filantropi Indonesia, J. Victor Rembeth from Humanitarian Forum Indonesia (HFI), and Muhammad Nuzul from Gerakan Mari Berbagi (GMB).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For Haidar, there should be no boundaries if you want to engage in philanthropy. It is wrong to say that zakat is only for Muslims, and that philanthropic activities undertaken by Muslims should be limited to helping only fellow Muslims. He stressed that dividing humanity according to their religions is not justified within the Islamic religious tradition. He reminded the audience that Allah teaches humans to be fair, which means to be morally good and to act with kindness towards all religions. He concluded with the observation that interfaith giving is the key to resisting hate-based radicalism.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_5571_edit%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>J. Victor Rembeth followed, explaining how the work of HFI is almost the same as philanthropy in prioritizing unity in diversity. He pointed out that the main task of humanitarian agencies is to humanize people and encourage empathy. Victor also explained the benefits of dialogue and interfaith discourse in upholding honesty. The example he gave was that of talking positively in front of people but then talking negatively behind them. HFI itself has experienced many cases where interfaith organizations have shown respect for each other in humanitarian issues, especially in times of disaster or emergency situations.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Muhammad Nuzul then shared the mission of his organization, GMB. He said the movement invites young people to feel first-hand the positive effects of helping others and sharing with others regardless of their background. GMB wants to teach that sharing in diversity must begin with oneself and only then can be transmitted to others.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_5589_edit%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:534px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Talking about&nbsp;interfaith philanthropy<em>,</em> it is not about the faith itself that is most important, but the values. It is important to clarify the point of view of religions in interfaith relations.&nbsp;Looking at the condition right now, various interpretations of the religious values make the discourse universal.&nbsp;Efforts to clarify religious values should not stop only on discourse, however. Organizations such as Filantropi Indonesia must persistently publish news and make conscious effort that demonstrates interfaith philanthropic activities. We must also utilize primary and higher education to teach students about living in a diverse community, as some of them are simply not aware of the context in which they live.</p>\n', '188780f5b1fc48e848df1713b176cdc8.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-09 08:23:40', '2018-02-19 15:23:16', 5, '-philanthropy-learning-forum-promoting-diversity-through-interfaith-philanthropy', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '1gswIK3X14y8JrN', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(637, 'Ramadhan Talk: Volunteering and Giving Back to the Community', '', 'Ini adalah kali kedua FI menyelenggarakan acara dengan @america di bulan Ramadhan. Diskusi kali ini menginspirasi anak muda untuk memberikan waktu dan tenaga mereka secara sukarela untuk menolong sesama, karena pada akhirnya kebaikan tersebut akan membuat mereka menjadi pribadi yang lebih baik', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selasa kemarin, 13 Juni 2017, @america menggandeng Filantropi Indonesia untuk Bersama mengadakan Ramadhan Talk dengan tema &ldquo;Volunteering and giving back to the community&rdquo;. Pada sesi talk show ini ada tiga pembicara dari Indonesia, yaitu Wayah Wiroto (Chairman GE Volunteers), Sita Supomo (Founder Volunteer ID), dan Muhammad Fikri (Head of Community Management BukaLapak.com), dan satu pembicara tamu dari Amerika Serikat, Qorsho Hassan (Fulbright Alumni).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Diskusi dimoderatori oleh Ratnasari Dewi Public, Public Affair Specialist dari&nbsp;US Embassy dan acara dibuka dengan kata sambutan dari Max Harrington perwakilan US Embassy. Setiap pembicara kemudian membagikan pengalaman mereka dalam melakukan kegiatan kerelawanan yang juga merupakan bagian dari filantropi. Pak Wayah memulai dengan menjelaskan kenapa GE memiliki program khusus employee volunteering dan bagaimana mereka menjalankannya. Ternyata karyawan di suatu perusahaan besar seperti GE (General Electric) tetap menyempatkan untuk memberikan tenaga dan waktu demi menolong orang lain. Bahkan tiap tahun mereka berlomba untuk meningkatkan jumlah waktu (jam) berkegiatan sosial atau volunteering.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_7066_edit.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kemudian perbincangan dialihkan ke Qorsho via Skype yang tinggal di Ohio dan sedang mengejar S2-nya di program Pendidikan. Qorsho bercerita pengalamannya saat menjadi relawan di Malaysia selama satu tahun. Dia juga mengatakan bahwa kegiatan volunteering membuat perspektif kita lebih terbuka dan mengesampingkan perbedaan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Lain lagi dengan Fikri yang aktif di berbagai organisasi dan komunitas sosial seperti Rotaract Club Semanggi, Indonesia Berkibar, dan Peace Generation. Dia mempunyai segudang pengalaman sejak kuliah dan sekarang pun saat ia bekerja di Bukalapak.com, Fikri tetap menjalankan passion-nya untuk pengembangan masyarakat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_7089_edit.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Karena kebanyakan dari peserta diskusi adalah mahasiswa, Ibu Sita Supomo dalam presentasinya menekankan pentingnya untuk aktif volunteering di luar kegiatan kuliah. Bahwa di dunia kerja yang seringkali dilihat adalah pengalaman dan aktivitas non-akademis, bukan IPK.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dari diskusi tanya jawab dapat disimpulkan bahwa kegiatan volunteering dapat menolong kita untuk menghargai perbedaan dan meningkatkan persaudaraan. Selain itu, semua panelis percaya bahwa dengan aktif menjadi relawan, kita dapat mengasah kemampuan seperti kerja tim, pengambilan keputusan, dan mencari solusi bersama. Filantropi tidak melulu memberikan uang atau barang, tetapi menyumbangkan tenaga, waktu, pikiran dan perhatian kita juga merupakan bentuk kasih kita terhadap sesama dan lingkungan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_7046_edit.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', '383154605d78b4a09ee4987ee5caec8d.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-15 03:21:06', '2018-02-19 15:25:18', 5, 'ramadhan-talk-volunteering-and-giving-back-to-the-community', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'pvqyDONpxwCPOEC', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(638, 'Ramadhan Talk: Volunteering and Giving Back to the Community', '', 'It is the second event that we held with @america this Ramadhan month. The session inspires young people to start giving their time and energy to help others in any way they can, because eventually the act of kindness will help them to be a better person', '<p>On Tuesday, June 13, 2017, @america, together with Filantropi Indonesia, held a Ramadan Talk with the theme &quot;Volunteering and giving back to the community&quot;.&nbsp;There were three speakers from Indonesia, Wayah Wiroto (Chairman of GE Volunteers), Sita Supomo (Founder of Volunteer ID), and Muhammad Fikri (Head of Community Management at BukaLapak.com), and a guest speaker from the United States, Qorsho Hassan (Fulbright Alumni).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The discussion was moderated by Dewi, a Public Affair Specialist&nbsp;from the US Embassy, with the opening remarks delivered by Max Harrington in his capacity as US Embassy representative.&nbsp;Each speaker then shared their experiences in voluntary activities that support philanthropy.&nbsp;Wayah started by explaining General Electric&rsquo;s (GE) employee volunteering program and how they manage it.&nbsp;We learned that even large companies like GE still give their time and energy to help others.&nbsp;Every year, the employees always try to increase the number of volunteering hours and beat the previous year&rsquo;s record.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_7066_edit%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Following this, Qorsho shared her story via Skype. Qorsho currently lives in Ohio and is pursuing her Master&rsquo;s degree in Education.&nbsp;Qorsho told of her wonderful experience volunteering in Malaysia for a year.&nbsp;She also explained how volunteering activities open up our perspective towards others and help people put aside their differences.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our third speaker, Fikri, has always been active in various charity organizations and social communities, such as Rotaract Club Semanggi, Indonesia Berkibar, and Peace Generation.&nbsp;He has had a lot of volunteering experience since college and continues this work today at Bukalapak.com. Fikri is still active in pursuing his passion for community development. He discussed his experiences in the voluntary sector and was met with keen interest.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_7089_edit%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Sita Supomo stressed the importance of active volunteering outside of classroom learning environments in her presentation.&nbsp;Since most of the discussion participants were students, this was a useful insight. She said that in today&rsquo;s workplace, employers often look at the non-academic experiences and activities, rather than someone&rsquo;s GPA.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">From the discussion, it can be concluded that volunteering activities can help us to appreciate differences and look for common grounds.&nbsp; All panellists were in agreement that by actively volunteering, we can hone skills such as teamwork, decision-making, and problem-solving.&nbsp;Philanthropy is not only about the giving of money or goods, but donating our energy, time, thought and attention as an expression of our love for one another&nbsp;and our environment.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/DSC_7046_edit%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', '383154605d78b4a09ee4987ee5caec8d.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-15 03:21:06', '2018-02-19 15:25:18', 5, 'ramadhan-talk-volunteering-and-giving-back-to-the-community', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'pvqyDONpxwCPOEC', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(649, 'Philanthropy Skill Share Forum 3', '', 'Workshop Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan In-Docs dengan tema \"Video Documentation for Philanthropy\"', '<p><a href=\"http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF3\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20PSSF%203_new.png\" style=\"height:1123px; width:794px\" /></a></p>\n', 'aaa6bc8c02a4718f0e361d3d8fd78452.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-15 07:50:55', '2017-07-12 11:06:18', 5, 'philanthropy-skill-share-forum-3', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', '5cU92isUdnTuXcV', 'N', '', '', '2017-08-02 00:00:00', '2017-08-03 23:59:59'),
(650, 'Philanthropy Skill Share Forum 3', '', 'Another workshop in partnership with In-Docs with the topic \"Video Documentation for Philanthropy\"', '<p><a href=\"http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF3\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20PSSF%203_new%281%29.png\" style=\"height:1123px; width:794px\" /></a></p>\n\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">This workshop is open for beginners or those with no experience in video documentation</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span class=\"marker\">Please bring your own video camera (smartphone camera is acceptable) and laptop</span></p>\n\n<h2>Investment cost</h2>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong><u>FILANTROPI INDONESIA MEMBERS</u></strong><br />\nMembers of FI receive special price at IDR 500,000 for one person maximum as early bird price (payment until 18 July 2017) and IDR 750,000 for normal price (payment after July 18).<br />\n<br />\n<strong><u>NON-MEMBERS</u></strong><br />\nFor organizations who are not a member yet, the investment cost is IDR 1,000,000 for early bird price (payment until 18 July 2017) and IDR 1,250,000 after July 18.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>REGISTRATION</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Fill the registration form at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF3\">http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF3</a></li>\n	<li>Transfer the investment cost to&nbsp;<strong>Bank BRI 111.901.000.208.307 KCP Tomang atas nama Perhimpunan Filantropi Indonesia</strong></li>\n	<li>Send your proof of payment including your name and contact (phone &amp; email) to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:informasi@filantropi-indonesia.org?subject=Bukti%20pembayaran%20workshop%20Filantropi%20Indonesia\" target=\"_blank\">info@filantropi</a><a href=\"mailto:info@filantropi.or.id?subject=Pendaftaran%20PSSF%202%20dan%20bukti%20transfer\" target=\"_blank\">.or.id</a></li>\n	<li>You will receive a confirmation email that guarantees your seat&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>For more information please contact us at&nbsp;021 6287454 or email to&nbsp;info@filantropi.or.id</p>\n', 'aaa6bc8c02a4718f0e361d3d8fd78452.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-15 07:50:55', '2017-07-12 11:06:18', 5, 'philanthropy-skill-share-forum-3', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', '5cU92isUdnTuXcV', 'N', '', '', '2017-08-02 00:00:00', '2017-08-03 23:59:59'),
(651, 'Libur Lebaran kantor Filantropi Indonesia', '', 'Kantor sekretariat Filantropi Indonesia akan tutup pada 26-28 Juni 2017 dalam rangka libur Hari Raya Idul Fitri', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic;\">Segenap jajaran Badan Pengurus dan Staf Sekretariat Filantropi Indonesia mengucapkan Minal Aidin Wal Faidzin mohon maaf lahir dan batin&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nSELAMAT HARI RAYA IDUL FITRI 1438 HIJRIAH</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa;font-style:italic;\"><strong>Walaupun kantor kami akan buka kembali pada 29 Juni 2017, kami&nbsp;dapat secara efektif melayani Anda mulai 3 Juli 2017</strong></h3>\n', '215ce50a10e7ac446178c8ad6f2e1f61.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-19 05:04:44', '2017-06-19 12:11:41', 5, 'libur-lebaran-kantor-filantropi-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'Z3awqZ2mQLU5cvF', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-26 00:00:00', '2017-06-28 23:59:59'),
(652, 'Office closing for Lebaran ', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia\'s office is closed between June 26-28, 2017 for Idul Fitri celebration', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\">On behalf of the Board Members and Staff of Filantropi Indonesia<br />\n<br />\nHAPPY EID MUBARAK and HAPPY HOLIDAY</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\"><strong>Even though our office is open in June 29, 2017, we will be able to effectively serve you again on July&nbsp;3, 2017</strong></h3>\n', '215ce50a10e7ac446178c8ad6f2e1f61.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-06-19 05:04:44', '2017-06-19 12:11:41', 5, 'office-closing-for-lebaran-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'Z3awqZ2mQLU5cvF', 'N', '', '', '2017-06-26 00:00:00', '2017-06-28 23:59:59'),
