(709, 'Impact Fund Manager’s training at 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia dan Intellecap mengundang manajer impact fund yang ingin mengikuti pelatihan intensif selama satu hari di Sankalp Summit Asia Tenggara ke-3. Pelatihan ini bertujuan untuk memberdayakan dan mendidik para calon manajer impact investment yang baru untuk peran katalitik mereka dalam menyediakan modal bagi para pengusaha di seluruh dunia. ', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong><em>Impact Fund Manager&rsquo;s training at 3<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit</em></strong></h2>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Filantropi%202.png\" style=\"height:723px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia dan <strong><u><a href=\"http://www.intellecap.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Intellecap</a>&nbsp;</u></strong>mengundang manajer impact fund yang ingin mengikuti pelatihan intensif&nbsp;di Sankalp Summit Asia Tenggara ke-3. Pelatihan ini bertujuan untuk memberdayakan dan mendidik para calon manajer impact investment yang baru untuk peran katalitik mereka dalam menyediakan modal bagi para pengusaha di seluruh dunia. Pelatihan ini akan mencakup pengukuran dampak, pengembangan tesis investasi, pengembangan lembaran berjangka serta tantangan pasca investasi. Dengan pengalaman Aavishkaar Intellecap Group yang meningkatkan dan mengelola dana di India, Afrika dan Asia Tenggara, pelatihan ini sangat relevan bagi mereka yang ingin bekerja di bidang ini. Pelatihan ini akan dipimpin oleh Kepala Investment Banking Aavishkaar-Intellecap Group dan akan menampilkan pembicara dari <a href=\"http://capria.vc/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Capria</strong></a>, akselerator global pertama untuk pengelola dana dampak, dan investor dampak terkemuka.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Pelatihan ini akan mencakup:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Introduction to Impact Investing Perkenalan Impact Investing</li>\n	<li>Impact Measurement</li>\n	<li>Creating an Investment Strategy and Pipeline Menciptakan Strategi dan Pipeline Investment</li>\n	<li>Valuing Social Enterprises Menghargai Usaha Sosial</li>\n	<li>Termsheet/ Due diligence/ shareholder agreements</li>\n	<li>Post-Investment Challenges Unique to Impact Investments</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Narasumber:&nbsp;<strong>Gagandeep Bakshi</strong>, Associate Director - Investment Banking Intellecap - <a href=\"http://www.intellecap.com/our-company/leadership/management\">Click here for bio</a></p>\n\n<p>Pelatihan ini akan diadakan pada <strong>Selasa, 19 September 2017 pukul 9.00 WIB di Hotel Bidakara Jakarta</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Biaya investasi pelatihan adalah US $500 (lima ratus dollar AS), biaya ini&nbsp;mencakup registrasi untuk lokakarya sehari penuh serta tiket masuk Sankalp Summit yang bernilai US $350.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><a href=\"https://events.bizzabo.com/seasia2017\">REGISTRASI PESERTA</a>*&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<address><span style=\"font-size:12px\">*pembayaran online&nbsp;Credit Card.</span></address>\n\n<address>&nbsp;</address>\n\n<address>\n<p>Bagi Anda yang memilih untuk metode pembayaran via transfer bank dapat mengirimkannya ke:</p>\n\n<p><strong>BRI&nbsp;111.901.000.208.307 KCP Tomang atas nama Perhimpunan Filantropi Indonesia</strong></p>\n\n<p>Setelah melakukan pembayaran mohon mengirimkan bukti beserta data peserta ke <a href=\"mailto:info@filantropi.or.id?subject=Impact%20Fund%20Managers%20Training%20Sankalp\">info@filantropi.or.id</a></p>\n</address>\n', 'f7691db5ba15629878bad061a4a51714.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-07-24 06:04:41', '2017-09-05 09:52:01', 5, 'impact-fund-manager-s-training-at-3rd-sankalp-southeast-asia-summit', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sze3Scm9tQkAEzo', 'N', '', '', '2017-09-19 00:00:00', '2017-09-19 23:59:59');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(710, 'Impact Fund Manager’s training at 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia and Intellecap invite aspiring impact fund managers to join for a one-day intensive training on September 19th at the 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit. The training aims to empower and educate new or aspiring impact fund managers for their catalytic role in providing capital to impact entrepreneurs around the world.', '<h2 style=\"font-style:italic\"><strong>Impact Fund Manager&rsquo;s training at 3<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit</strong></h2>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Filantropi%202%281%29.png\" style=\"height:632px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia and&nbsp;<strong><u><a href=\"http://www.intellecap.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Intellecap</a></u></strong>&nbsp;invite aspiring impact fund managers to join for an intensive training on&nbsp;September 19th&nbsp;at the 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit. The training aims to empower and educate new or aspiring impact fund managers for their catalytic role in providing capital to impact entrepreneurs around the world. The training will cover impact measurement, developing an investment thesis, term sheet development as well as post-investment challenges. With the Aavishkaar Intellecap Group&rsquo;s experience raising and managing funds in India, Africa and Southeast Asia, this training is particularly relevant for those desiring to work in these geographies. The training will be led by the Aavishkaar-Intellecap Group&rsquo;s Head of Investment Banking and will feature speakers from<a href=\"http://capria.vc/\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;<strong>Capria</strong></a>, the first global accelerator for impact fund managers, and leading impact investors.</p>\n\n<p>Training will include the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Introduction to Impact Investing</li>\n	<li>Impact Measurement</li>\n	<li>Creating an Investment Strategy and Pipeline</li>\n	<li>Valuing Social Enterprises</li>\n	<li>Termsheet/ Due diligence/ shareholder agreements</li>\n	<li>Post-Investment Challenges Unique to Impact Investments</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Trainer:&nbsp;<strong>Gagandeep Bakshi</strong>, Associate Director - Investment Banking Intellecap - <a href=\"http://www.intellecap.com/our-company/leadership/management\">Click here for bio</a></p>\n\n<p>Training will be held on <strong>Tuesday, September 19, 2017 at 9 AM in Bidakara Hotel, Jakarta</strong></p>\n\n<p>The cost for the training is USD 500, the ticket cost will cover attendance for the day long workshop as well as the cost of the Summit entrance fee worth $350.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><a href=\"https://events.bizzabo.com/seasia2017\">REGISTER HERE</a>*</span></p>\n\n<p><em><small>*online payment with credit card</small></em></p>\n\n<p>If you would like to pay the training fee via bank transfer please send your payment to:</p>\n\n<p><strong>BRI&nbsp;111.901.000.208.307 KCP Tomang (Perhimpunan Filantropi Indonesia)</strong></p>\n\n<p>Please send the payment proof and your information to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:info@filantropi.or.id?subject=Impact%20Fund%20Managers%20Training%20Sankalp\">info@filantropi.or.id</a></p>\n', 'f7691db5ba15629878bad061a4a51714.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-07-24 06:04:41', '2017-09-05 09:52:01', 5, 'impact-fund-manager-s-training-at-3rd-sankalp-southeast-asia-summit', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sze3Scm9tQkAEzo', 'N', '', '', '2017-09-19 00:00:00', '2017-09-19 23:59:59'),
(711, '3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2017', '', 'Bergabunglah dengan Pertemuan Tingkat Tinggi Sankalp Asia Tenggara ke-3 di Jakarta - sebuah platform yang sangat menarik yang bertujuan untuk memperkuat ekosistem kewiraswastaan Asia Tenggara. Setiap tahun, KTT menyatukan 500+ pemain global dan regional termasuk pengusaha, investor, perusahaan, pemerintah dan penyandang dana dengan tujuan memfasilitasi koneksi, pembelajaran kolektif dan pendekatan kolaboratif terhadap ekonomi inklusif.', '<h2>About 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Join us for the 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit in Jakarta- a highly engaging platform that aims to strengthen Southeast Asia&#39;s entrepreneurship ecosystem. Every year, the Summit brings together 500+ global and regional players including entrepreneurs, investors, corporations, governments and funders with the purpose of facilitating connections, collective learning and a collaborative approach towards an inclusive economy. Premised on the insight that sustainable entrepreneurship can catalyze inclusive development, this 3rd edition will bring together over 600 global and regional delegates to ponder on the theme- Local Problems, Global Solutions. Don&#39;t miss out on your chance to network, share, learn, inspire and get inspired!</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://seasia2017.sankalpforum.com/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Sankalp-SE-ASIA-infographic-_v.jpg\" style=\"height:1199px; width:736px\" /></a></p>\n', '5ffb5140e7e1d7ad58644f6b6c988b0b.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-07-25 04:17:25', '2017-07-25 11:17:25', 5, '3rd-sankalp-southeast-asia-summit-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'HPIMnBEhDUerYkg', 'N', '', '', '2017-09-19 00:00:00', '2017-09-20 23:59:59'),
(712, '3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit 2017', '', 'Join the 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit in Jakarta- a highly engaging platform that aims to strengthen Southeast Asia\'s entrepreneurship ecosystem. Every year, the Summit brings together 500+ global and regional players including entrepreneurs, investors, corporations, governments and funders with the purpose of facilitating connections, collective learning and a collaborative approach towards an inclusive economy.', '<h2>About 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit</h2>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Join us for the 3rd Sankalp Southeast Asia Summit in Jakarta- a highly engaging platform that aims to strengthen Southeast Asia&#39;s entrepreneurship ecosystem. Every year, the Summit brings together 500+ global and regional players including entrepreneurs, investors, corporations, governments and funders with the purpose of facilitating connections, collective learning and a collaborative approach towards an inclusive economy. Premised on the insight that sustainable entrepreneurship can catalyze inclusive development, this 3rd edition will bring together over 600 global and regional delegates to ponder on the theme- Local Problems, Global Solutions. Don&#39;t miss out on your chance to network, share, learn, inspire and get inspired!</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://seasia2017.sankalpforum.com/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Sankalp-SE-ASIA-infographic-_v%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:1199px; width:736px\" /></a></p>\n', '5ffb5140e7e1d7ad58644f6b6c988b0b.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-07-25 04:17:26', '2017-07-25 11:17:25', 5, '3rd-sankalp-southeast-asia-summit-2017', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'HPIMnBEhDUerYkg', 'N', '', '', '2017-09-19 00:00:00', '2017-09-20 23:59:59'),
(725, 'BAZNAS dan Filantropi Indonesia Inisiasi Fiqih Zakat on SDGs', '', 'BAZNAS (Badan Amil Zakat) dan FI (Filantropi Indonesia) menggandeng ulama, pegiat zakat, akademisi dan para pegiat filantropi di Indonesia untuk menginisiasi perumusan Fiqih Zakat on SDGs. ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai bagian dari lembaga filantropi di Indonesia, BAZIS (Badan Amil Zakat Infaq dan Sedekah) dan LAZIS (Lembaga Amil Zakat Infaq dan Sedekah) bisa berkontribusi dalam pencapaian Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) melalui pengembangan berbagai program yang sudah dilakukan. Zakat bisa menjadi sumber daya alternatif dalam mendukung pencapaian SDGs dengan mengedepankan pendekatan yang inklusif dan program yang strategis, berorientasi jangka panjang dan berkelanjutan. Sementara itu, SDGs dapat digunakan sebagai alat ukur dan menjadi panduan program-program pemberdayaan yang dilakukan oleh berbagai lembaga pengelola zakat.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Melihat pentingnya justifikasi teologis dalam bentuk fatwa ulama dalam penggalangan, pengelolaan dan penyaluran zakat untuk mendukung pencapaian program SDGs (Fiqih Zakat on SDGs), Filantropi Indonesia dan BAZNAS (Badan Amil Zakat Nasional) menggelar <em>Philanthropy Learning Forum</em> (PLF) 18 yang mengangkat tema Merumuskan Fiqih Zakat on SDGs pada Rabu, 26 Juli 2017. Diskusi ini bertujuan untuk menjaring masukan dari para ulama, pegiat zakat, akademisi dan pegiat filantropi nirlaba bagi inisisiatif penyusunan Fiqih Zakat on SDGs yang diinisiasi oleh BAZNAS bekerja sama dengan UIN Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara tersebut menghadirkan empat pembicara yaitu: Suzanty Sitorus (Sekretaris Badan Pengurus Filantropi Indonesia), KH. Masdar F. Mas&rsquo;udi (Baznas), Hasanuddin Abdul Fatah (Ketua Komisi Fatwa MUI), serta Tim Perumus Fiqih Zakat Untuk SDGs yang diwakili oleh M. Maskum. Sebagai pembuka acara, Suzanty memaparkan bahwa SDGs merupakan seperangkat tujuan global yang disepakati oleh negara-negara anggota PBB dan menjadi komitmen komunitas global dan nasional. Salah satu perbedaan yang mendasari antara Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) dan SDGs adalah jumlah tujuan yang ingin dicapai. Sebelumnya MDGs hanya memiliki 8 tujuan dan banyak yang tidak tercapai. Sementara SDGs memiliki 17 tujuan, dengan 169 target dan 124 indikator. Tujuan zakat sendiri telah tercakup dalam SDGs. Dalam pencapaian SDGs, kelompok yang paling potensial adalah filantropi keagamaan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sementara itu, menurut Hasanuddin, terlebih dahulu harus dipahami apa itu fiqih zakat. Landasan hukum fiqih zakat berkaitan dengan hukum islam, yaitu wahyu dan wahyu plus akal (fiqih). Keduanya mempunyai karakteristik yg berbeda. Wahyu adalah kebenaran yang selalu benar (absolut), permanen dan universal. Sedangkan fiqih, kebenarannya relatif, tidak permanen dan tidak universal. Zakat sendiri mengandung dua aspek yaitu ibadah (dari wahyu dan tidak boleh dirasionalkan) dan muamalah (boleh dilakukan, bisa dirasionalkan).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Masdar menambahkan dari 5 rukun Islam, zakat terkadang ditelantarkan. Padahal potensi zakat bisa Rp 217 triliun per tahun. Sedangkan yang baru terkumpul sejumlah Rp 5 &ndash; 6 triliun. Mengapa bisa demikian? Zakat tidak dapat ditunggu, karena harus dipungut. Tapi faktanya terbalik, harus ditunggu dan dipungut. Padahal ada perintah &ldquo;Ambilah harta mereka untuk zakat&rdquo;. Lembaga Amil Zakat memiliki tantangan yang berat untuk dapat memungut zakat. Bagaimana LAZ harus dapat meningkatkan posisinya untuk berada dalam posisi memungut bukan menerima. Beberapa aturan mungkin dapat diubah guna memfasilitasi pengembangan zakat. Misalnya apakah pajak dan zakat dapat disinergikan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Senada dengan itu, Maskum juga memperkuat argumen bahwa zakat juga dapat digunakan untuk SDGs. Bahkan dalam sejarahnya zakat pernah digunakan sebagai sumber pendapatan negara dan bagaimana proses pengumpulan zakat menjadu tugas negara. Oleh karena itu karakteristik penerimaan zakat harus diperjelas. Beberapa usulan yang dikemukaan dalam acara tersebut diantaranya, fiqih harus sesui dengan SDGs, semua pengelola zakat harus mempunyai kesempatan yang sama untuk pengumpulan, zakat tidak hanya menjadi alternatif tapi juga pradigma keseluruhan, zakat dalam aspek ekonomi supaya harta tidak tertahan tapi dapat terkumpul, soal bagaimana isu-isu krusial dalam zakat, apakah boleh muslim dan non-muslim menerima zakat, dan apakah zakat boleh digunakan untuk kepentingan lain. Jadi sebelum zakat benar-benar digunakan untuk implementasi SDGs, terlebih dahulu harus dirumuskan secara jelas aturannya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6sucFVoVnVnWVRZdTA?usp=sharing\">UNDUH MATERI PRESENTASI</a></p>\n', '9f1e1483e21d03eab9e5f247478775d8.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-07 03:48:31', '2018-02-19 15:26:00', 5, 'baznas-dan-filantropi-indonesia-inisiasi-fiqih-zakat-on-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '6gsR4xqCWO1gV9X', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(726, 'BAZNAS and Filantropi Indonesia Initiated Fiqh Zakat on SDGs', '', 'BAZNAS (Amil Zakat Board) and FI (Philanthropy Indonesia) collaborate with scholars, zakat activists, academics and philanthropy actors in Indonesia to initiate the formulation of Fiqh Zakat on SDGs.', '<p>As part of the philanthropic community in Indonesia, BAZIS (Amil Zakat Infaq and Sedekah Agency) and LAZIS (Amil Zakat Institute of Infaq and Sedekah) can contribute to the achievement of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) through the development of effective Zakat programs.&nbsp;Zakat can be an alternative resource in supporting the achievement of SDGs by promoting an inclusive, strategic, long-term, and sustainable approach.&nbsp;Simultaneously, SDGs can be used as a measuring tool and guide the empowerment programs undertaken by various zakat management institutions.</p>\n\n<p>Seeing the importance of theological justification in the form of fatwas in the raising of, management and distribution of zakat to support the achievement of program SDGs (Fiqh of Zakat on SDGs), Filantropi Indonesia and BAZNAS (Badan Amil Zakat Nasional) held&nbsp;the 18<sup>th</sup> Philanthropy Learning Forum&nbsp;(PLF) with the theme &lsquo;Formulating Fiqh Zakat on SDGs&rdquo; on Wednesday the 26<sup>th</sup> of July, 2017. This discussion aimed to capture input from scholars, zakat activists, academics and non-profit philanthropic activists for the preparation of Fiqh Zakat on SDGs, initiated by BAZNAS in cooperation with UIN Jakarta.</p>\n\n<p>There were&nbsp;four speakers present: Suzanty Sitorus (Secretary of Indonesian Philanthropy Assoication Board), KH.&nbsp;Masdar F. Mas&#39;udi (Baznas), Hasanuddin Abdul Fatah (Chairman of the MUI Fatwa Committee), and the Zakat Fiqh Formulating Team for SDGs represented by M. Maskum. During&nbsp;her presentation, Suzanty explained that the SDGs are a set of global goals set by UN member states and a commitment towards the global, national and local communities.&nbsp;One of the underlying differences between the Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) and SDGs is the number of goals to be achieved.&nbsp;The previous MDGs consisted of only 8 goals, many of which were not achieved,&nbsp;while the SDGs have 17 goals. These set 169 individual performance targets and provide 124 indicators for use in assessing progress.&nbsp;In the achievement of SDGs, the group with the most untapped potential is religious philanthropy.</p>\n\n<p>According to Hasanuddin, the jurisprudence of zakat must first be understood.&nbsp;The legal basis of Fiqh zakat is related to Islamic law, that is revelation and revelation plus reason (Fiqh).&nbsp;Both have different characteristics.&nbsp;Revelation is a truth that is always true, absolute, permanent and universal.&nbsp;In Fiqh, however, the truth is relative, not permanent and not universal.&nbsp;Zakat itself contains two aspects of worship: revelation (cannot be rationalized) and muamalah (may be done, can be rationalized).</p>\n\n<p>Masdar noted that of the 5 pillars of Islam, zakat is sometimes overlooked.&nbsp;Whereas the potential contribution of zakat could amount to IDR 217 trillion per year, the amount collected recently was around IDR 5 - 6 trillion.&nbsp;The problem lies in the difficulty of collection.&nbsp;Though there is a command &quot;Take their property for charity&quot;,&nbsp;The Amil Zakat Institute faces a great challenge in the collection of zakat.&nbsp;The difficulty now lies in how LAZ can improve its capacity to act, rather than passively receiving donations.&nbsp;One potential solution is whether some rules may be modified in order to facilitate the development of zakat,&nbsp;for example, whether taxes and zakat can be synergized.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Maskum also agrees with the argument that zakat can also be used for SDGs.&nbsp;Earlier in its history, zakat was used as a source of state income and the process of collecting zakat existed as a state duty.&nbsp;Therefore, the conditions and requirements of zakat may potentially be modified.&nbsp;Some of the proposals made at the event include: Fiqh must be in accordance with the SDGs, all zakat managers must have equal opportunity for collection, zakat may not exist as an alternative but also the overall paradigm, define the economic aspects which allow property to be withheld, whether non-Muslims can receive zakat, and whether zakat may be used for other purposes.&nbsp;In summation, before zakat can be organised towards and used effectively for the implementation of SDGs, the rules&nbsp;must first be agreed upon by the religious authorities.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B2ornD7Dj6sucFVoVnVnWVRZdTA?usp=sharing\">DOWNLOAD PRESENTATION</a></p>\n', '9f1e1483e21d03eab9e5f247478775d8.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-07 03:48:31', '2018-02-19 15:26:00', 5, 'baznas-and-filantropi-indonesia-initiated-fiqh-zakat-on-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '6gsR4xqCWO1gV9X', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(727, 'Pelatihan Membuat Video Dokumenter yang Menarik dan Profesional', '', 'Pelatihan Philanthropy Skill Share Forum 3 bekerja sama dengan In-Docs dan LAZISMU dengan tema \"Creating Engaging Visuals: Membuat Video Dokumenter Layaknya Profesional\"', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada hari Rabu, 2 Agustus &ndash; Kamis, 3 Agustus yang lalu, Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan In-Docs mengadakan pelatihan rutin, Philanthropy Skill Share Forum (PSSF) yang ke-3. Pelatihan kali ini spesial karena diadakan selama dua hari penuh dengan mendatangkan dua trainer yang sudah sangat ahli dan berpengalaman di bidang video dan film dokumenter. Ada Amelia Hapsari, Program Director In-Docs dengan pengalaman membuat film lebih dari 15 tahun dan memenangkan banyak film festival lokal maupun internasional. Lalu Sidi Saleh yang reputasinya juga sudah tidak perlu dipertanyakan, pemenang international film festival berkat karyanya Maryam (2014), Fitri (2014) dan Postcards from the Zoo (2012).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Peserta pelatihan kali ini cukup beragam, baik dari anggota Filantropi Indonesia, lembaga komunitas, maupun perusahaan. Semua antusias dan aktif berpartisipasi selama pelatihan dua hari tersebut. Pada hari pertama di sesi pagi hari, Amelia dan Sidi memaparkan beberapa teori dan pengetahuan dasar tentang membuat video documenter seperti penokohan dan storytelling.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">PSSF 3 juga dapat terwujud berkat dukungan dari LAZISMU yang menyediakan ruangan pelatihan. Peserta juga mendapat kesempatan spesial untuk mengunjungi studio dan redaksi dari TV MU, stasiun televisi milik MU. Direktur Utama TV MU, Bpk. Gatot Triyanto juga sempat membagikan informasi mengenai sejarah dan program stasiun TV MU.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selama pelatihan peserta belajar untuk membuat proposal cerita dan menentukan gambar apa yang mewakili cerita tsb, serta menghasilkan video pendek berdurasi 1-3 menit yang harus mereka rekam dan edit sendiri. Walaupun pelatihan ini durasinya terbilang pendek untuk membuat video, namun diharapkan dapat menambah pengetahuan serta keahlian peserta dalam menghasilkan dokumentasi dan dokumenter yang berkualitas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Jika Anda tertarik untuk mengikuti pelatihan membuat video dokumentasi yang lebih dalam dan komprehensif, hubungi kami di <a href=\"mailto:info@filantropi.or.id\">info@filantropi.or.id</a> agar menjadi pertimbangan untuk pelatihan lanjutan.</p>\n', 'b3cb1dcba9ad154ec699489e5043321f.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-07 05:03:42', '2018-02-19 15:26:43', 5, 'pelatihan-membuat-video-dokumenter-yang-menarik-dan-profesional', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'w1Urpt12UbgR2OE', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(728, 'Creating an Engaging and Professional Video Documentary Training', '', 'Philanthropy Skill Share Forum 3 training was a collaboration between Filantropi Indonesia with In-Docs and LAZISMU with the theme \"Creating Engaging Visuals: Making Video Documentary Like a Professional\"', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On Wednesday, August 2<sup>nd</sup>&nbsp;- Thursday, August 3<sup>rd</sup>, Filantropi Indonesia collaborated with In-Docs to conduct our Philanthropy Skill Share Forum (PSSF) for the 3rd time.&nbsp;This special training is held for two full days and was delivered by two highly skilled and experienced video and documentary makers. The first presenter was Amelia Hapsari, the&nbsp;Program Director of In-Docs, who has more than 15 years of film experience, and numerous wins across many local and international film festivals.&nbsp;The second trainer was&nbsp;Sidi Saleh whose reputation is also unquestionable. He is the winner of a number of international film festivals thanks to his work Maryam (2014), Fitri (2014) and Postcards from the Zoo (2012).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The participants in this training were quite diverse, from members of Filantropi Indonesia, community institutions, and companies.&nbsp;All participated enthusiastically and actively during the two-day training.&nbsp;On the first day of the morning session, Amelia and Sidi presented some basic theory and knowledge used in the making of documentaries such as characterization and storytelling.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">PSSF 3 was possible thanks to the support of LAZISMU who provided the training rooms.&nbsp;Participants also received a special opportunity to visit the studios and editors of MU TV at MU&#39;s television station. Director of TV MU, Bpk.&nbsp;Gatot Triyanto also gave his time to share information about the history and programs of TV stations MU.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During the training, participants learned how to make a story proposal, decide which images best represent their story, and produce a short 1-3-minute video which they recorded and edited on their own. Although the training is short in duration, it is expected to increase the participants&#39; knowledge and skills in producing quality documentaries for use in their organisations.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are interested in further training on how to make video documentaries, please contact us at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:info@filantropi.or.id\">info@filantropi.or.id</a>.</p>\n', 'b3cb1dcba9ad154ec699489e5043321f.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-07 05:03:42', '2018-02-19 15:26:43', 5, 'creating-an-engaging-and-professional-video-documentary-training', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'w1Urpt12UbgR2OE', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(729, 'Filantropi Indonesia Dukung Kolaborasi Lazismu – NuCare Salurkan Kurban Dalam Bentuk Rendang Kemasan', '', 'Lembaga Amil Zakat Nasional Muhammadiyah (LAZISMU) dan Lembaga Amil Zakat Nahdatul Ulama (NU Care-Lazisnu) pada Idhul Adha 1438 H kembali berkolaborasi menyelenggarakan kurban bersama secara Nasional dengan tema Nusantara Berkurban untuk Indonesia Berkemajuan.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nusantara Berkurban Untuk Indonesia Berkemajuan (NBIB) adalah program bersama LAZISMU dan NU-CARE LAZISNU untuk memfasilitasi umat Islam dalam menunaikan ibadah kurban. Dengan prinsip kebersamaan yang pelaksanaan pengelolaan kurbannya dilakukan bersama-sama diharapkan penghimpunan, pemotongan, pengalengan/pengemasan dan pendistribusian hewan kurban menjadi tepat sasaran.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Program ini juga mendukung pelaksanaan Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) sebagai Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (TPB) agar bernilai strategis dan inklusif, berdampak luas, serta dapat bersinergi dan berkontribusi terhadap keberhasilan program-program pemerintah dan pencapaian tujuan pembangunan nasional.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Berbeda dengan tahun sebelumnya, Nusantara Berkurban untuk Indonesia Berkemajuan ini menawarkan konsep baru; Menjangkau yang tidak terjangkau. LAZISMU dan NU Care-Lazisnu akan mendistribusikan daging kurban sampai ke pelosok Nusantara dan Mancanegara dalam bentuk rendang kemasan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Rendang merupakan khazanah kuliner Nusantara yang menjadi masakan terlezat di jagat raya. Begitu pula Nusantara Berkurban untuk Indonesia Berkemajuan. LAZISMU dan NU Care-Lazisnu berharap agar program ini menjadi sumbangsih umat Islam Indonesia untuk persaudaraan dan kemanusiaan di seluruh dunia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/Proposal%20Program%20NBIB%20NEW.pdf\">UNDUH PROPOSAL NBIB</a></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20OL%20Qurban%20NBIB%201438H%20%20Lazismu.jpg\" style=\"height:978px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'bddeeb6f890d0d9ea3105ec34d22f4b7.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-07 05:48:49', '2018-02-23 09:33:06', 5, 'filantropi-indonesia-dukung-kolaborasi-lazismu-nucare-salurkan-kurban-dalam-bentuk-rendang-kemasan', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'THJ0YAciEyNHkN6', 'N', '', 'LAZISMU & Menara 62', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(730, 'Filantropi Indonesia Supports the Lazismu Collaboration - NuCare Distributes Sacrifice of Rendang', '', 'The National Institute of Amil Zakat Muhammadiyah (LAZISMU) and the Institute for Amil Zakat Nahdatul Ulama (NU Care-Lazisnu) on Idhul Adha 1438 H again collaborated for a joint national sacrifice (qurban) program with the theme of Nusantara Berkurban untuk Indonesia Berkemajuan.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nusantara Berkurban for Indonesia Berkemajuan (NBIB) is a joint program of LAZISMU and NU-CARE LAZISNU to aid Muslims in the performance of sacrificial worship services.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Working under the principle of togetherness, the process of sacrifice management, which includes the cutting, canning / packing and distribution of animal sacrifices, is undertaken in the spirit of fraternity.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The program also supports the implementation of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) as advancing strategic and inclusive values, widespread impacts, and contributing to the success of government programs and the achievement of national development goals.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In contrast to the previous year, the NBIB program offers a new concept: Reach the unreachable. LAZISMU and NU Care-Lazisnu will distribute the sacrificial meat to the corners of the archipelago and abroad in the form of rendang meat: the culinary treasure of the nation. LAZISMU and NU Care-Lazisnu hope that this program will be the contribution of Indonesian Muslims to fraternity and humanity throughout the world.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20OL%20Qurban%20NBIB%201438H%20%20Lazismu%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:978px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'bddeeb6f890d0d9ea3105ec34d22f4b7.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-07 05:48:49', '2018-02-23 09:33:06', 5, 'filantropi-indonesia-supports-the-lazismu-collaboration-nucare-distributes-sacrifice-of-rendang', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'THJ0YAciEyNHkN6', 'N', '', 'LAZISMU & Menara 62', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(735, 'My Dream Tampilkan Keindahan dan Harapan', '', '31 seniman difabel membawakan tarian, drama musikal, penampilan musik dan lagu, serta pertunjukan puisi isyarat tangan, yang dikemas dalam pertunjukan spektakuler bertajuk My Dream.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>China Disabled People&rsquo;s Performing Art Troupe (</em><em>CDPPAT) </em>adalah sekelompok anak muda yang memiliki impian untuk menciptakan sebuah keajaiban. Selama 20 Tahun CDPPAT telah mendatangi ratusan negara, dan menginspirasi ratusan ribu penonton.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tahun ini, dalam rangka 10 tahun DAAI TV Indonesia, Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi bersama DAAI TV mengundang CDPPAT tampil di tiga kota besar, yakni Medan 22-23 Juli 2017, Jakarta 29-30 Juli 2017 dan Surabaya 5-6 Agustus 2017.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Seniman dengan latar belakang tuna rungu dan tuna netra, menampilkan tarian dan pertunjukan yang spektakuler, seperti, keindahan harmoni gerak tangan tarian <em>Boddhisatva </em>seribu tangan yang ditampilkan oleh seniman penyandang tuna rungu. Ada pula tarian <em>Melihat Musim Semi</em> dan pertunjukan musik yang dibawakan oleh penyandang tuna netra.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Di Usianya yang ke&ndash;10 Tahun, kehadiran kelompok seniman perdamaian UNESCO ini, diharapkan dapat menyebarkan nilai-nilai kebaikan, semangat hidup dan rasa bersyukur yang sejalan dengan misi televisi cinta kasih, DAAI TV.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;<em>Sebagai Televisi Cinta kasih DAAI TV ingin memberikan semangat hidup dan bersyukur menghargai kehidupan. Berkat keuletan, kedisiplinan dan kerja keras, kelompok CDPPAT mampu mematahkan stigma, tentang kemampuan orang-orang yang memiliki keterbatasan. Karya mereka bisa dinikmati masyarakat dunia dan memberi motivasi hidup</em>.&rdquo; Ungkap CEO DAAI TV Hong Thjin</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Humas Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi, Suriadi Huang mengatakan, kehadiran CDPPAT ke Indonesia bisa mengubah pandangan masyarakat terhadap keberadaan para penyandang disablitas. <em>&ldquo;Bagi saya p</em><em>ertunjukan seni </em><em>China Disabled People&rsquo;s Performing Art Troupe memberikan pesan penting tentang arti &ldquo;kesempurnaan&rdquo;, dimana para disablitas berperan memberikan inspirasi kepada masyarakat yang fisiknya lebih baik</em>,&rdquo; ujar Suriadi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>CDPPAT Pukau Penonton di Medan </strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Medan menjadi kota pertama digelarnya pertunjukan M<em>y Dream.</em> Berlangsung pada tanggal 29 Juli dan 30 Juli di <em>Sky Continental Hall</em>, Cemara Asri Medan, sebanyak 6000 penonton terpukau menyaksikan seluruh pertunjukan yang dipersembahkan oleh <em>My Dream. </em>Bahkan mereka&nbsp; &nbsp;mampu membangkitkan rasa cinta tanah air penonton Medan, lewat lagu <em>Indonesia Pusaka. </em></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Acara ini juga dihadiri oleh Gubernur Sumatera Utara, Tengku Erry Nuradi, tokoh masyarakat dan tokoh agama, dan kelompok disabilitas kota Medan.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Melihat tingginya antusiasme penonton <em>My Dream </em>di kota Medan, salah satu anggota CDPPAT Wang Qi yang juga penyandang tuna netra merasa bangga. Meski tidak bisa melihat, namun ia bisa merasakan apresiasi terhadap penampilan kelompoknya, &rdquo;<em>Setelah tampil saya bisa merasakan dukungan lewat gemuruh tepuk tangan, yang tak putus-putus</em>,&rdquo;ujarnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Karena keramahan masyarakat Indonesia, V<em>ice President</em> CDPPAT Wang Jing, telah menganggap Indonesia sebagai rumah kedua<em>, &rdquo;Kami terkesan dengan keramahan masyarakat Indonesia. Saya bahkan sangat bahagia bisa datang ke Indonesia lagi karena seperti pulang ke rumah sendiri,&rdquo; </em>ungkap Wang Jing.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Profil DAAI TV</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">DAAI TV Indonesia memiliki misi menjernihkan hati manusia melalui tayangan yang bersifat inspiratif, edukatif dan informatif. Berpegang pada nilai Kebenaran, Kebajikan dan Keindahan DAAI TV terus berusaha mengasah kepekaan masyarakat, memberi pesan cinta kasih dalam setiap tayangannya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Profil Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi Indonesia</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tzu Chi merupakan lembaga sosial kemanusiaan lintas suku, agama, ras, dan negara. Berawal dari welas asih Pendiri Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi, Master Cheng Yen, Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi telah menyebarkan cinta kasih di lebih dari 51 negara, salah satunya Indonesia. Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi Indonesia telah menebar cinta kasih di Indonesia sejak tahun 1993, lewat 4 misi utama.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Aktivitas Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi dibagi dalam 4 misi utama:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Misi Amal, membantu masyarakat tidak mampu maupun yang tertimpa bencana alam/musibah.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Misi Kesehatan, memberikan pelayanan kesehatan kepada masyarakat dengan mengadakan pengobatan gratis, mendirikan rumah sakit, sekolah kedokteran, dan poliklinik.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Misi Pendidikan, membentuk manusia seutuhnya, tidak hanya mengajarkan pengetahuan dan keterampilan, tapi juga budi pekerti dan nilai-nilai kemanusiaan.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Misi Budaya Humanis, menjernihkan batin manusia melalui media cetak, elektronik, dan internet dengan melandaskan budaya cinta kasih universal.</li>\n</ul>\n', 'f1bfabe0a202564ca50f3955f02dfaed.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-09 07:08:45', '2018-02-23 09:28:35', 5, 'my-dream-tampilkan-keindahan-dan-harapan', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'MrBsufeikGGTpCn', 'N', '', 'DAAI TV', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(736, 'My Dream Show Beauty and Hope', '', '31 disable artists performed dances, musical dramas, musical performances and songs, as well as hand gesture poetry performances, packed in a spectacular show called My Dream.', '<p>China Disabled People&#39;s Performing Art Troupe (CDPPAT) is a group of young people who dream of creating a miracle. Over the past 20 years CDPPAT has visited hundreds of countries, and inspired hundreds of thousands of spectators.</p>\n\n<p>This year, the Tzu Chi Buddha Foundation and DAAI TV invited CDPPAT to perform in three Indonesian cities, Medan on the 22<sup>nd</sup>-23<sup>rd</sup> July 2017, Jakarta on the 29<sup>th</sup>-30<sup>th</sup> July 2017 and in Surabaya on the 5<sup>th</sup>-6<sup>th</sup> August 2017.</p>\n\n<p>Artists with hearing and sight impairments performed spectacular dances and performances, such as beautiful Boddhisatva hand dance harmonies performed by deaf artists, and spring dances and musical performances performed by the blind.</p>\n\n<p>At its 10th Anniversary, the UNESCO peacekeeping group&#39;s presence is expected to spread the virtues of kindness and gratitude that are aligned with the mission of love advanced by DAAI TV.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;DAAI TV wants to give spirit to life, and to instill an appreciation of life. Thanks to tenacity, discipline and hard work, the CDPPAT group is able to combat the negative perceptions regarding the capabilities of people with disabilities. Their work can be enjoyed by the global community and provide motivation for everyone&quot; said DAAI TV CEO Hong Thjin</p>\n\n<p>Tzu Chi Buddhist Foundation Public Relations officer, Suriadi Huang said, the presence of CDPPAT in Indonesia can change the public view of people with disabilities. &quot;For me, the China Art Disabled People&#39;s Performing Art Troupe performance provides an important message about the meaning of &quot;perfection&quot;, in which the disability plays an inspiration to a better physical society,&quot; Suriadi said.<br />\nCDPPAT Pukau Personton in Medan was the first city to host the &lsquo;My Dream&rsquo; show. Taking place on July 29<sup>th</sup> and July 30<sup>th</sup> at Sky Continental Hall, Cemara Asri Medan, a total of 6000 audience members enjoyed the spectacle. Particularly moving was the performance of the song Indonesia Pusaka. The event was also attended by the Governor of North Sumatra, Tengku Erry Nuradi as well as community leaders, religious leaders, and disability groups in Medan. Experiencing the high enthusiasm shown by the My Dream audience in Medan, one member of the CDPPAT, Wang Qi, who is also visually impaired, felt proud. Although not able to see, he could feel the appreciation of the performance of his group, &quot;After appearing, I could feel their support through the roar of applause, which was unbroken,&quot; he said. Owing to the friendliness of Indonesian society, CDPPAT vice president Wang Jing, now regards Indonesia as a second home, &quot;We are impressed with the friendliness of Indonesian society&quot; said Wang Jing, continuing &ldquo;I am very happy to come to Indonesia again because it is like coming home&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u>DAAI TV Profile </u></p>\n\n<p>DAAI TV Indonesia has a mission to lift the hearts of people through programming that is inspirational, educational and informative. Sticking to the values of truth, virtue and beauty, DAAI TV continues to strive to sharpen people&#39;s sensitivity, to convey a message of love in every show. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u>Profile of Yayasan Buddha Tzu Chi Indonesia </u></p>\n\n<p>Tzu Chi is a humanitarian institution operating across ethnic, religious, racial, and state divisions. Starting from the compassion of the founder of the Tzu Chi Buddhist Foundation, Master Cheng Yen, the Tzu Chi Buddhist Foundation has spread love in more than 51 countries, one of which is Indonesia where it has been operating since 1993. The activities of the Tzu Chi Buddhist Foundation are in support of 4 main missions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Charity: helping the communities hit by natural disasters</li>\n	<li>Health: providing health services to the community by providing free medical treatment, establishing hospitals, medical schools, and clinics</li>\n	<li>Education: forming complete human beings, teaching not only knowledge and skills, but also the manners and values ??of humanity.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Humanist Culture:&nbsp; instilling the human mind with the universal culture of love through print, electronic, and internet media.</li>\n</ul>\n', 'f1bfabe0a202564ca50f3955f02dfaed.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-09 07:08:45', '2018-02-23 09:28:35', 5, 'my-dream-show-beauty-and-hope', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'MrBsufeikGGTpCn', 'N', '', 'DAAI TV', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(737, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs - Banjarmasin', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia memulai roadshow sosialisasi SDGs untuk lembaga filantropi di kota pertama, Banjarmasin. Pelaksanaan ini akan bekerja sama dengan Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Philanthropy%20Learning%20Forum%20on%20SDGs%20-%20Banjarmasin.png\" style=\"height:700px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">SDGs (<em>Sustainable Development Goals</em>) atau Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (TPB) merupakan seperangkat tujuan universal, target, dan indikator dari agenda pembangunan yang disepakati di tingkat global. SDGs diharapkan dapat menanggulangi berbagai masalah global, termasuk menghapuskan kemiskinan dan kelaparan, memajukan kesehatan dan pendidikan, membangun kota-kota secara berkelanjutan, memerangi perubahan iklim serta melindungi lautan dan hutan. SDGs didukung oleh 193 negara anggota PBB dan digunakan untuk membingkai rencana pembangunan nasional negara-negara diseluruh dunia selama 15 tahun ke depan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Keterlibatan lembaga filantropi dalam pencapaian SDGs bukan hanya berdampak pada optimalisasi program pada masyarakat, tapi juga peningkatan kapasitas lembaga filantropi. Melalui keterlibatannya dalam SDGs, organisasi filantropi bisa lebih mempertajam target sasaran programnya dengan mengacu pada target dan indikator SDGs. Lembaga filantropi juga bisa mengukur dampak dan kontribusi programnya pada pembangunan sosial dan pembangunan global. SDGs juga memberikan kesempatan kepada lembaga filantropi untuk mempromosikan program dan inisiatifnya ke level nasional dan global, serta memperluas jaringan dan menjajaki kemitraan dengan lembaga-lembaga filantropi nasional dan global.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Masih banyak lembaga filantropi terutama di daerah yang belum dapat memahami SDGs secara keseluruhan serta perangkatnya. Hal inilah yang mendorong <strong>Filantropi Indonesia</strong> bersama <strong>Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri Banjarmasin</strong> mengadakan acara <strong><em>Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs</em></strong> dengan tema &ldquo;<strong><em>SDGs Sebagai Tools Peningkatan Kapasitas dan Pengembangan Kemitraan&rdquo;</em></strong>. Tujuan dari agenda ini adalah ingin memberikan pelatihan singkat guna memahami seluk beluk SDGs bagi lembaga filantropi lokal dan <em>stakeholder-</em>nya serta mencoba mencari persoalan apa saja yang mereka hadapi berkaitan dengan pemahaman SDGs dan mencari solusinya. Kegiatan tersebut akan diadakan pada:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hari/tanggal&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : Kamis, 24 Agustus 2017</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pukul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : 11.00 &ndash; 17.00 WITA (diawali dengan makan siang bersama)</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tempat &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;:&nbsp;Aula Rektorat Lt. 1 Universitas Lambung Mangkurat, Jalan Brigjen Hasan Basri Kayu Tangi Banjarmasin</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><ins>Registrasi Peserta</ins></p>\n\n<p>Kontak: Ibu Rina (Adaro)</p>\n\n<p>HP: 0811-5119-249</p>\n\n<p>Email:&nbsp;Rina.Ermadeni@yabn.org</p>\n', 'a572a38d097c90f839f4e82e7f65c12d.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-09 08:17:03', '2017-08-16 16:09:54', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-banjarmasin', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'FfvmTu4juKOZtum', 'N', '', '', '2017-08-24 00:00:00', '2017-08-24 23:59:59'),
(738, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs - Banjarmasin', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia started the socialization roadshow on SDGs for philanthropy institutions in the first city, Banjarmasin.  will work together with Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Philanthropy%20Learning%20Forum%20on%20SDGs%20-%20Banjarmasin%281%29.png\" style=\"height:700px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">SDGs (Sustainable Development Goals) are a set of universal goals, targets, and indicators of an agreed development agenda at the global level. SDGs are expected to tackle global issues, including eliminating poverty and hunger, promoting health and education, sustainable building cities, combating climate change and protecting oceans and forests. SDGs are supported by 193 UN member states and are used to frame national development plans of countries around the world over the next 15 years.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The involvement of philanthropic institutions in achieving SDGs not only has an impact on program optimization on society, but also the capacity building of philanthropic institutions. Through its involvement in SDGs, philanthropy organizations can further sharpen their program targets by referring to the target and indicators of the SDGs. The philanthropic institution can also measure the impact and contribution of its programs to social development and global development. SDGs also provides opportunities for philanthropic agencies to promote their programs and initiatives to national and global levels, and expand the network and explore partnerships with national and global philanthropic institutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are still many philanthropic institutions especially in areas that have not been able to understand the overall SDGs as well as their devices. This is what encouraged Filantropi&nbsp;Indonesia with Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri Banjarmasin held a Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs with the theme &quot;SDGs as Tools for Capacity Building and Partnership Development&quot;. The purpose of this agenda is to provide a short training to understand the ins and outs of SDGs for local philanthropic institutions and their stakeholders and to try to find out what issues they are dealing with understanding the SDGs and seek solutions. The activities will be held on:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Day / Date: Thursday, August 24, 2017</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Time: 11.00 - 17.00 WITA (lunch provided)</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Location: Aula Rektorat Lt. 1 Universitas Lambung Mangkurat, Jalan Brigjen Hasan Basri Kayu Tangi Banjarmasin</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><ins>Registration</ins></p>\n\n<p>Contact person: Ibu Rina (Adaro)</p>\n\n<p>Phone: 0811-5119-249</p>\n\n<p>Email:&nbsp;Rina.Ermadeni@yabn.org</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'a572a38d097c90f839f4e82e7f65c12d.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-09 08:17:03', '2017-08-16 16:09:54', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-banjarmasin', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'FfvmTu4juKOZtum', 'N', '', '', '2017-08-24 00:00:00', '2017-08-24 23:59:59'),
(745, 'Docs By The Sea', '', 'Docs By The Sea adalah forum dokumenter internasional untuk projek dokumenter kreatif dengan fokus di Asia Tenggara. ', '<p>Docs By The Sea</p>\n\n<p>Bali,&nbsp;29 - 30 August 2017</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Docs By The Sea adalah forum dokumenter internasional untuk proyek dokumenter kreatif dengan fokus Asia Tenggara. Acara ini adalah platform yang sangat baik untuk memperluas jaringan, mendapatkan wawasan industri, dan membuat proyek Anda didanai dan didistribusikan.</p>\n\n<p>Tiga puluh proyek dokumenter akan dipilih untuk diputar. Lebih dari dua puluh lima pengambil keputusan internasional diundang untuk memberikan umpan balik dan mempertimbangkan kolaborasi dengan proyek terpilih.</p>\n\n<p>Filantropi Indonesia diwakili oleh Bapak Timotheus Lesmana sebagai Ketua Badan pengurus, akan menjadi salah satu &quot;decision makers&quot; dan membuka kesempatan kolaborasi terhadap projek tersebut.</p>\n\n<p>Docs By The Sea merupakan inisiatif dari BEKRAF (Badan Ekonomi Kreatif) bekerja sama dengan In-Docs.</p>\n\n<p>Untuk info lebih lanjut, silakan kunjungi: <a href=\"http://www.docsbythesea.org/index.php?p=home\">http://www.docsbythesea.org/</a></p>\n', '77e06be54516be86c08a082c787dc316.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-18 07:33:20', '2017-08-18 15:09:02', 5, 'docs-by-the-sea', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'wgsnlWYa7vm3eqj', 'N', '', '', '2017-08-29 00:00:00', '2017-08-30 23:59:59'),
(746, 'Docs By The Sea', '', 'Docs By The Sea is an international documentary forum for creative documentary projects with the focus of Southeast Asia.', '<p>Docs By The Sea</p>\n\n<p>Bali,&nbsp;29 - 30 August 2017</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Docs By The Sea is an international documentary forum for creative documentary projects with the focus of Southeast Asia. It is an excellent platform to network, obtain industry insights, and get your projects funded and distributed.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nThirty documentary projects will be selected to pitch. More than twenty five international decision makers are invited to provide feedback and to consider collaborations with selected projects.</p>\n\n<p>Filantropi Indonesia, represented by Mr. Timotheus Lesmana as Chairman of the Board, will be one of the decision makers&nbsp;and open up opportunities for collaboration on the project.</p>\n\n<p>Docs By The Sea is an initiative by BEKRAF (Creative Economic Agency) in collaboration with In-Docs.</p>\n\n<p>For more info, please visit:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.docsbythesea.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.docsbythesea.org/</a></p>\n', '77e06be54516be86c08a082c787dc316.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-18 07:33:20', '2017-08-18 15:09:02', 5, 'docs-by-the-sea', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'wgsnlWYa7vm3eqj', 'N', '', '', '2017-08-29 00:00:00', '2017-08-30 23:59:59');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(749, 'Mempererat Kemitraan Antar Lembaga Filantropi di Indonesia Untuk Pencapaian SDGs', '', 'Roadshow Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs ke 7 (tujuh) kota di Indonesia telah dimulai', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) yang diluncurkan oleh PBB pada akhir 2015 merupakan program global yang menjadi acuan pembangunan bagi negara-negara anggota PBB, hingga 2030. Indonesia telah berkomitmen untuk mendukung dan terlibat dalam program SDGs. Implementasi SDGs di Indonesia bukanlah hal yang mudah. Wilayah Indonesia yang berbentuk kepulauan serta kesenjangan kemakmuran dan perbedaan insfratruktur yang masih terlihat menonjol antara Pulau Jawa dan pulau lainnya menjadi tantangan dalam pencapaian SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia menyadari bahwa kesuksesan SDGs memerlukan keterlibatan multi pihak dalam cakupan wilayah yang luas. Di sisi lain, meskipun SDGs yang telah berjalan dua tahun ini tapi masih banyak masyarakat yang belum mengetahui serta memahami SDGs. Hal ini yang mendorong Filantropi Indonesia untuk mengedukasi dan mengampanyekan SDGs ke masyarakat melalui kegiatan Philanthropy Learning Forum On SDGs dengan tema khusus <em>SDGs Sebagai Tools Peningkatan Kapasitas dan Pengembangan Kemitraan</em>. Kegiatan diselenggarakan di 7 kota yang tersebar di 5 pulau yaitu Banjarmasin, Makassar, Surabaya, Yogyakarta, Jambi, Bengkulu dan Mataram.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selain itu kegiatan ini juga bertujuan untuk meningkatkan peran dan keterlibatan lembaga filantropi dalam pencapaian SDGs. Keterlibatan lembaga filantropi dalam SDGs bukan hanya berdampak pada optimalisasi program pada masyarakat, tapi juga peningkatan kapasitas lembaga filantropi. Melalui keterlibatannya dalam SDGs, organisasi filantropi bisa lebih mempertajam target sasaran programnya dengan mengacu pada target dan indikator SDGs. Lembaga filantropi juga bisa mengukur dampak dan kontribusi programnya pada pembangunan sosial dan pembangunan global. SDGs juga memberikan kesempatan kepada lembaga filantropi untuk mempromosikan program dan inisiatifnya ke level nasional dan global, serta memperluas jaringan dan menjajaki kemitraan dengan lembaga-lembaga filantropi nasional dan global.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Melalui kegiatan ini Filantropi Indonesia juga akan mencoba mengidentifikasi persoalan yang dihadapi lembaga filantropi lokal serta pemerintah daerah dalam memahami SDGs, serta membantu menemukan solusinya. Tidak hanya itu, kedepannya lembaga filantropi lokal diharapkan dapat didorong untuk membentuk suatu inisiatif perhimpunan filantropi di setiap daerah.</p>\n', '2dcd2fe4271952362474f1d52e485cc5.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-23 08:37:42', '2018-02-19 15:27:19', 5, 'mempererat-kemitraan-antar-lembaga-filantropi-di-indonesia-untuk-pencapaian-sdgs', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'RIdEjTdoRLhbooo', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(750, 'Strengthening Partnerships between Philanthropy Actors in Indonesia for SDGs Achievement', '', 'The kick-off of Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs roadshow to 7 (seven) cities in Indonesia', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), launched by the United Nations (UN) in September 2015, constitute a global program that serves as a benchmark for development in UN member states until 2030. Indonesia has committed itself to support and engage in programs aimed at the attainment of SDGs.&nbsp;This is no small task, however.&nbsp;The geographical arrangement of the Indonesian region, as well as the prosperity gap and infrastructural differences that still stand out between Java and other islands, exist as the main challenges for the achievement of SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Filantropi Indonesia recognizes that the realisation of SDGs requires multi-stakeholder engagement across a wide range of areas. Even though it has been two years since the announcement of the SDGs, many still do not know about them, or understand what they entail. This has prompted Filantropi Indonesia to educate about, and campaign for SDGs &nbsp;to a wider audience outside Jakarta through the Philanthropy Forum Learning on SDGs (PLF) Roadshow, with the theme&nbsp;of &ldquo;<em>SDGs as Capacity Building and Partnership Development Tools&rdquo;.</em>&nbsp;The roadshow will be held in 7 cities across five different islands: Banjarmasin (South Kalimantan), Makassar (South Sulawesi),&nbsp;Surabaya (East Java), Yogyakarta (DIY), Jambi (Jambi), Bengkulu and Mataram (West Nusa Tenggara).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The PLF also aims to enhance the role and involvement of philanthropic organizations in achieving SDGs.&nbsp;The involvement of philanthropy in achieving SDGs not only has an impact on program optimization in society, but also the capacity building of philanthropy organizations.&nbsp;Through their involvement in SDGs, these organizations can further refine their approach by referring to the targets and indicators as set by the SDGs.&nbsp;They can also scale up the impact and contribution of the programs to social development and global development.&nbsp;The SDGs also provide opportunities for philanthropic agencies to promote their programs and initiatives to national and global communities, expand their networks and explore partnership possibilities with national and global institutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Through the roadshow, Filantropi Indonesia will also try to identify problems faced by local philanthropy actors and local governments in understanding SDGs, and to help find solutions together.&nbsp;In the long term, we encourage local philanthropists and foundations to create local associations in their respective regions and create a strong support system for the sector.</p>\n', '2dcd2fe4271952362474f1d52e485cc5.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-23 08:37:42', '2018-02-19 15:27:19', 5, 'strengthening-partnerships-between-philanthropy-actors-in-indonesia-for-sdgs-achievement', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'RIdEjTdoRLhbooo', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(753, 'Philanthropy Sharing Session: Membangun Kemitraan dengan Perusahaan', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan JICA (Japan International Cooperation Agency) untuk mengadakan sesi sharing bertema \"Membangun Kemitraan dengan Perusahaan\". Sesi ini ditujukan untuk NGO atau organisasi nirlaba yang ingin mengetahui lebih lanjut bagaimana cara dan apa kiat-kiat untuk menjalin kerja sama dengan suatu perusahaan.', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(170, 170, 170); font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Terima kasih bagi para peserta yang sudah mendaftar. Kuota sudah terpenuhi sehingga registrasi harus kami tutup,&nbsp;sampai berjumpa di acara!</span></h2>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20JICA%20-%20CLOSED.png\" style=\"height:700px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Acara ini merupakan kerja sama antara Filantropi Indonesia dengan Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) untuk bersama-sama berbagi ilmu mengenai bagaimana NGO (non-governmental organization)&nbsp;atau CSO (civil society organization) menjalin relasi dan kerja sama dengan korporasi atau perusahaan.</p>\n\n<p>Narasumber:</p>\n\n<p>1.&nbsp;<strong>Trini Haryanti</strong> - Direktur Yayasan Pengembangan Perpustakaan Indonesia</p>\n\n<p>2.&nbsp;<strong>Arninta Puspitasari</strong> - Public Relations &amp; Event Manager Nutrifood</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Philanthropy%20Sharing%20Session%202%20NEW%281%29.pdf\">UNDUH KERANGKA ACUAN&nbsp;</a></p>\n', '7b8d5bc9404d95140dccc6cf97f9bbdb.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-30 06:47:58', '2017-09-26 14:15:10', 5, 'philanthropy-sharing-session-membangun-kemitraan-dengan-perusahaan', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'BQIpEdx3A2YJCLX', 'N', '', '', '2017-09-28 00:00:00', '2017-09-28 23:59:59'),
(754, 'Philanthropy Sharing Session: Corporate Funding: how to engage corporate in the long term', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia partnered with JICA (Japan International Cooperation Agency) to hold a sharing session or discussion meeting around corporate funding. This session invites all NGOs or nonprofits who want to learn more about establishing a relationship with corporate and how to maintain that partnership.', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(170, 170, 170); font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Thank you for your registration. All seats are now&nbsp;filled so we have to close the registration. See you at the event!</span></h2>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/Poster%20JICA%20-%20CLOSED%281%29.png\" style=\"height:700px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p>This event is a collaboration between Filantropi Indonesia and Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) to provide an opportunity for NGOs and CSOs to share knowledge on how to establish a relationship and partnership&nbsp;with corporation.</p>\n\n<p>Speakers:</p>\n\n<p>1.&nbsp;<strong>Trini Haryanti</strong> - Director of Yayasan Pengembangan Perpustakaan Indonesia</p>\n\n<p>2.&nbsp;<strong>Arninta Puspitasari</strong> - Public Relations &amp; Event Manager Nutrifood</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Philanthropy%20Sharing%20Session%202%20NEW.pdf\">D</a><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/TOR%20Philanthropy%20Sharing%20Session%202%20NEW%282%29.pdf\">OWNLOAD TERMS OF REFERENCE</a></p>\n', '7b8d5bc9404d95140dccc6cf97f9bbdb.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-08-30 06:47:59', '2017-09-26 14:15:10', 5, 'philanthropy-sharing-session-corporate-funding-how-to-engage-corporate-in-the-long-term', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'BQIpEdx3A2YJCLX', 'N', '', '', '2017-09-28 00:00:00', '2017-09-28 23:59:59'),
(755, 'Launching Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs di Banjarmasin ', '', 'PLF on SDGs dimulai di Banjarmasin di mana para peserta dan narasumber dari sektor filantropi dan bisnis, pemerintah serta akademisi saling bertukar pikiran mengenai penerapan SDGs di area masing-masing', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs Roadshow diawali di kota Banjarmasin, Kalimantan Selatan pada Kamis, 24 Agustus 2017 yang lalu. Acara ini merupakan rangkaian roadshow di 7 kota di Indonesia oleh Filantropi Indonesia dengan dukungan dari Ford Foundation. Pelaksanaan PLF on SDGs Banjarmasin juga berkat kerja sama dengan Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri (YABN) dan Universitas Lambung Mangkurat yang juga berperan sebagai tuan rumah. Kegiatan ini dihadiri sekitar 90 peserta dari berbagai kalangan dan diliput juga oleh Banjarmasin Post dan Duta TV sebagai media partner.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kegiatan ini diawali dengan sambutan dari Bapak Timotheus Lesmana selaku Ketua Badan Pengurus Filantropi Indonesia dan Sambutan dari Bapak Harris Maki selaku Sekretaris Daerah Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan sekaligus membuka acara. Sekda Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan mengapresiasi pelaksanaan kegiatan PLF on SDGs ini dengan harapan agar kegiatan ini mampu menjadi langkah awal dalam pelibatan seluruh pihak utamanya pegiat Filantropi di Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan dalam membangun Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan pada khususnya serta Indonesia pada umumnya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202017-08-24%20at%2012.35.31%20PM.jpeg\" style=\"height:449px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada kegiatan ini juga dilakukan peluncuran buku <em><strong>Berbagi dan Berkolaborasi untuk SDGs: Panduan Praktis Implementasi SDGs Sektor Filantropi</strong></em> yang disusun oleh Filantropi Indonesia. Acara kemudian dilanjutkan dengan diskusi dan pemaparan materi oleh Timotheus Lesmana (Ketua Badan Pengurus Filantropi Indonesia), Okty Damayanti (Ketua Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri), Prof. DR. H. Sutarto Hadi, M.Si, M.Sc (Rektor Universitas Lambung Mangkurat), dan Harris Makki (Sekretaris Daerah Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dari hasil diskusi dan tanya jawab, pemahaman tentang SDGs sendiri masih cukup rendah di kalangan peserta yang hadir. Selain itu keterlibatan masyarakat daerah setempat juga sangat penting demi mendukung tercapainya SDGs di masing-masing kota atau provinsi.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ibu Okty bercerita bahwa Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri (YABN) yang merupakan bagian dari Adaro Group berfungsi untuk menciptakan dan melaksanakan program-program jangka menengah dan jangka panjang dari CSR Adaro Group secara independen. Konsep From Global to Local (Glocal) untuk SDGs menjadi acuan program YABN.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bapak Prof. Sutarto lebih banyak menyoroti tentang peran-peran akademisi yang mungkin dilakukan dalam mendukung implementasi dan kesuksesan SDGs. Pelibatan berbagai pakar dalam pengembangan program-program yang akan dijalankan akan sangat diperlukan dalam menjalankan berbagai aktifitas SDGs secara efektif dan efisien. Beliau juga memberikan berbagai contoh yang telah dilakukan di Kalimantan Selatan, serta berbagai wilayah lain di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bapak Harris Maki lebih berfokus dalam mendorong aktifitas berbagai lembaga yang terlibat dalam SDGs untuk dapat juga mengembangkan Kalimantan Selatan, sebagaimana prinsip yang diusung &ldquo;<em>No one left behind</em>&rdquo;. Bapak Sekda juga mengharapkan agar program-program SDGs yang dijalankan secara lokal dapat diselaraskan dengan prioritas program di Kalimantan Selatan, sebagaimana visinya untuk menjadikan Kalimantan Selatan Sehat dan Mandiri.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dari diskusi ini diharapkan lembaga filantropi, masyarakat sipil, akademis dan pemerintah daerah di Banjarmasin, Kalsel dapat bersinergi dan bekerja sama mendukung pelaksanaan dan pencapaian SDGs. Buku panduan praktis yang telah terbit juga dapat dipakai untuk menolong lembaga filantropi yang ingin memulai dan menerapkan prinsip SDGs dalam program mereka yang sudah berjalan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/15vBqHZiTB35K37gAQwsrKzmW3683OKNK?usp=sharing\">UNDUH MATERI PRESENTASI</a></p>\n', '0cc7f52f2d659bfd5eafd628f4e90c55.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-09-04 06:41:43', '2018-02-19 15:29:05', 5, 'launching-philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-di-banjarmasin-', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'QAQrEHAZ72ZUWnJ', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(756, 'The Launching of Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs in Banjarmasin ', '', 'PLF on SDGs started off in Banjarmasin where participants and speakers from the philanthropy and business, government and academia discussed ideas on the implementation of SDGs in their respective areas', '<p>The Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs Roadshow started in Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan on Thursday, August 24, 2017.&nbsp;This event is a series of roadshows in 7 cities across Indonesia organised by Filantropi Indonesia with support from the Ford Foundation.&nbsp;The event was held in partnership with Yayasan Adaro Bangun Negeri (YABN) and Universitas Lambung Mangkurat, who was also the host.&nbsp;Around 90 participants from various backgrounds attended the event with coverage Banjarmasin Post and TV Ambassador as media partner.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mr. Timotheus Lesmana, Chairman of the Board of Philanthropy Indonesia, opened the event with the welcoming speech being delivered by Mr. Harris Maki, the Regional Secretary of South Kalimantan.&nbsp;He saw the PLF on SDGs as a positive undertaking and hoped that it would be the first step in bringing together all of the main philanthropic actors and stakeholders in Southern Kalimantan towards the development of the province, as well as Indonesia in general.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202017-08-24%20at%2012.35.31%20PM%281%29.jpeg\" style=\"height:449px; width:800px\" /></p>\n\n<p>The launch of Filantropi Indonesia&rsquo;s latest book, titled&nbsp;<em>Sharing and Collaboration for SDGs</em>:&nbsp;<em>A Practical Guide to the Implementation of SDGs in Philanthropy,</em>&nbsp;also took place during the event.&nbsp;The event was then followed by discussion and a presentation delivered by Timotheus Lesmana, Okty Damayanti (Chairman of YABN), Prof.&nbsp;DR.&nbsp;H. Sutarto Hadi, M.Si, M.Sc (Rector of Universitas Lambung Mangkurat), and Harris Makki.</p>\n\n<p>From the discussions that took place in the Q&amp;A session, it appears that the understanding of SDGs itself is still quite low among the participants. However, everyone could easily appreciate the need for local community involvement in achieving SDGs in each city or province.</p>\n\n<p>Okty Damayanti shared how YABN, which is part of the Adaro Group, works to create and implement the medium and long-term CSR programs of the Adaro Group independently.&nbsp;The concept of &ldquo;From Global to Local: SDGs&rdquo; encapsulates the principle of the YABN program.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Mr.&nbsp;Sutarto discussed the role of academia in supporting the implementation and success of the SDGs.&nbsp;The involvement of various experts in the development of programs will be necessary in carrying out the various activities needed for the attainment of SDGs effectively and efficiently.&nbsp;He also gave examples of what has been achieved in South Kalimantan, as well as various other regions across Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p>Mr. Harris Maki focused more on encouraging the activities of various institutions involved in pursuing SDGs and their ability to help develop South Kalimantan, and the applicability of the &quot;No one left behind&quot; principle.&nbsp;The Secretary also hopes that locally run SDG programs can be harmonized with government priorities in South Kalimantan. He concluded with a depiction of his vision to increase the health and independence of South Kalimantan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">From this discussion, it is hoped that philanthropy, civil society, academic and local government institutions in Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan can work together and support the implementation and achievement of SDGs.&nbsp;The practical handbook that has been published can also be used to help philanthropy organisations who want to apply the underlying principles of the SDGs in their existing programs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/15vBqHZiTB35K37gAQwsrKzmW3683OKNK?usp=sharing\">DOWNLOAD PRESENTATION</a></p>\n', '0cc7f52f2d659bfd5eafd628f4e90c55.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-09-04 06:41:43', '2018-02-19 15:29:05', 5, 'the-launching-of-philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-in-banjarmasin-', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'QAQrEHAZ72ZUWnJ', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
