(854, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs in Yogyakarta', '', 'PLF Roadshow on SDGs has reached the 4th city, Yogyakarta, where FI supported by Dompet Dhuafa and Hoshizora Foundation held a dinner and discussion forum to encourage multi-stakeholder synergies and partnerships for the achievement of SDGs', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Filantropi Indonesia (FI), supported by Dompet Dhuafa and assisted by our local partner Hoshizora Foundation, conducted a series of activities aimed at SDGs socialization in Yogyakarta across the 23rd &ndash; 24th of October 2017. The activities in Yogyakarta were a bit different from the previous three cities, consisting of two separate events: The Philanthropy &amp; Business Networking Dinner, and the Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs. Both are interrelated with the joint purpose of encouraging philanthropic and business actors in Yogyakarta to work together and collaborate with local actors.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/20171023_202900%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The dinner was held on Monday 23<sup>rd</sup> October, and was the product of a collaboration with Forum CSR DIY, chaired by GKR Mangkubumi. GKR Mangkubumi herself came along with some guests from both the business sector and the philanthropy sector. The informal evening discussion was facilitated by Erna Witoelar, Co-Chair of the FI Advisory Board. Active participation from the participants was evident, with many ideas on how to start an effective philanthropic and business sector in Yogya aimed at the achievement of SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On Tuesday, PLF on SDGs was held at Jogja Expo Center. In this open discussion there were four speakers in the panel: Timotheus Lesmana (Chairman of FI Executive Board), Abu Yazid (Head of Social Welfare Division Bappeda DIY), Maharani Hapsari (Professor of Gadjah Mada University) and Sabeth Abilawa (GM Corporate Secretary Dompet Dhuafa). The moderator was Reky Martha, Co-Founder of the Hoshizora Foundation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_0706%281%29.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From the approximately 60 participants who attended, most were already aware of the SDGs, but did not possess a deep understanding. Timotheus Lesmana explained specifically what philanthropy is and why the philanthropy sector needs to engage in partnerships and collaborations in pursuing the SDGs. Abu Yazid from Bappeda then explained the current social conditions and issues of concern to the government. He also acknowledged the importance of the private sector and civil society in helping to achieve those targets essential to regional development.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Maharani Hapsari from UGM presented insights from the perspective of academia regarding inclusive partnership platforms and the role of philanthropy in development. The last speaker, Sabeth Abilawa from Dompet Dhuafa (DD), gave a real-life example of what DD has done in the context of achieving SDGs through their cooperation with government and other sectors.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The discussion was rich with some interesting questions and opinions from participants. These ranged from whether the SDGs have adequately considered the disabled within the principle of &quot;no one left behind&quot;, to how the enabling role of the state can affect how the SDG agenda is determined in civil society.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From the roadshow event in Yogyakarta, it appears that enthusiasm about partnerships for SDGs is already strong. The goal is now to sustain this group spirit and establish networks for cross-sectoral partnerships in pursuit of the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B2FWo5jiyFAaZV9INGZVQW5IaTg\">DOWNLOAD PRESENTATION</a> (IN BAHASA INDONESIA)</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"/pubs/uploads/files/LAPORAN%20PELAKSANAAN%20Filantropi%20SDGs%20Learning%20Forum%281%29.pdf\">DOWNLOAD MINUTES</a> (IN BAHASA INDONESIA)</p>\n', '2376340d5bd75f4907fe9ed820a1dd0c.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-10-31 06:49:53', '2018-02-19 15:47:15', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-in-yogyakarta', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'LqUOIg6DExW0ory', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(865, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs di Jambi', '', 'Roadshow PLF on SDGs di kota Jambi, di mana FI berkolaborasi dengan Yayasan Mitra Aksi dan mendatangkan peserta dari berbagai kalangan untuk membahas peran masing-masing dalam pencapaian SDGs', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Jambi menjadi kota ketiga dalam rangkaian roadshow Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs di tujuh kota di Indonesia. Pada Kamis (19/10) yang lalu, Filantropi Indonesia bekerja sama dengan Yayasan Mitra Aksi menyelenggarakan Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs di aula Bappeda Provinsi Jambi. Dengan mengangkat topik yang sama dengan kota-kota sebelumnya, yaitu &lsquo;SDGs Sebagai Tools Peningkatan Kapasitas dan Pengembangan Kemitraan&rsquo;, forum ini dihadiri oleh puluhan aktivis dan pegiat filantropi di kota Jambi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ada empat pembicara yang memberikan paparan dalam forum ini, yaitu Hamid Abidin, Direktur Eksekutif Filantropi Indonesia, Arifin Purwakananta, Deputi Baznas, Ade, perwakilan Bappeda Jambi, dan perwakilan Yayasan Mitra Aksi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/pubs/uploads/images/IMG_1886.JPG\" style=\"height:525px; width:700px\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dari paparan Ade, selaku perwakilan Bappeda Provinsi Jambi, diketahui bahwa pemerintah daerah sudah melakukan sosialisasi SDGs kepada seluruh jajaran dinas. Bahkan, pemerintah daerah, saat ini, berencana untuk membuat Rencana Aksi Daerah sebagai bagian dari implementasi SDGs di daerah. Walaupun demikian, diakui Ade bahwa, pemerintah daerah Jambi belum menyertakan lembaga sosial maupun lembaga filantropi di dalamnya. Melalui forum Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs ini, Bappeda mendapatkan masukan untuk menyertakan lembaga-lembaga tersebut dalam pembuatan Rencana Aksi Daerah.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebaliknya, dari paparan ketiga narasumber yang berasal dari lembaga filantropi tersebut semakin diketahui bahwa lembaga filantropi juga mempunyai andil yang besar untuk menyukseskan SDGs. Karena terbukti selama ini, tanpa melibatkan pemerintah pun, lembaga filantropi memberikan bantuan kepada masyarakat di berbagai daerah. Seperti bantuan pemeriksaan kesehatan, bantuan pendidikan, sampai bantuan advokasi hukum.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Forum di Jambi ini diakhiri dengan sinergi dan kolaborasi antara lembaga filantropi lokal dan pemerintah daerah Jambi. Beberapa peserta yang berasal dari organisasi non-profit juga saling bertukar informasi tentang apa yang sudah dilakukan dan peluang kolaborasi dengan aktor lainnya. Sebut saja, perwakilan dari Pundi Sumatera dan Setara Jambi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selain penyelenggaraan forum, Filantropi Indonesia juga mendapatkan kesempatan untuk siaran di radio lokal Jambi, bersama dua lembaga lokal, tentang apa itu SDGs dan apa yang dapat dilakukan oleh masyarakat untuk ikut berkontribusi.</p>\n', '1edcd1bb68a28203fbe1fdcd794ad459.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-11-01 08:34:24', '2018-02-19 15:51:32', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-di-jambi', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'NIiIRAjn9OI29FZ', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(866, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs in Jambi', '', 'PLF on SDGs Roadshow arrived in Jambi, where FI collaborated with Yayasan Mitra Aksi and brought in participants from various sectors to discuss their respective roles in achieving SDGs', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Jambi was the third of seven cities in the Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs roadshow across Indonesia. On Thursday 19 October, Filantropi Indonesia, in collaboration with Mitra Aksi Foundation, held the Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs (PLF on SDGs) in the offices of the Jambi Province Bappeda organisation. Continuing the topic of &#39;SDGs As a Capacity Building and Partnership Development Tool&#39;, this forum was attended by dozens of philanthropy actors from across the city of Jambi.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There were four speakers in this forum: Hamid Abidin, Executive Director of Filantropi Indonesia, Arifin Purwakananta, Chief Deputy of Baznas, Ade, representative of Bappeda Jambi, and Mitra Aksi, representative of Yayasan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ade, as the representative of Bappeda Jambi Province, explained how the local government has considered SDGs at all levels of service. Furthermore, they are currently planning to make local action plans a part of the implementation of SDGs in the region. However, Ade acknowledged that the Jambi regional government has not included any social institution or philanthropy sector actors in their planning. One particularly promising outcome of this particular PLF was the Bappeda Jambi acknowledgement of the need to include these institutions in formulating Local Action Plans.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In contrast, the presentation of the other three speakers from philanthropy organizations, illustrated the large contribution that philanthropy has made to the current progress towards achieving SDGs. Without significant involvement from the government, philanthropy has been providing assistance to the communities in various regions, across areas such as assistance in medical examination, education, and legal advocacy.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The forum in Jambi concluded with a restatement of the need for collaboration between local philanthropy actors and institutions, and the local government of Jambi. Some participants from non-profit organizations, such as the representatives of Pundi Sumatera and Setara Jambi, also shared information about what they had achieved as well as potential opportunities for collaboration with other stakeholders.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At the conclusion of the forum, Filantropi Indonesia also had a chance to participate in a live broadcast on Jambi local radio, along with two local organizations, to explain what the SDGs are and what people can do to contribute.</p>\n', '1edcd1bb68a28203fbe1fdcd794ad459.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-11-01 08:34:24', '2018-02-19 15:51:32', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-on-sdgs-in-jambi', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'NIiIRAjn9OI29FZ', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(873, 'Philanthropy Learning on SDGs - Surabaya', '', 'PLF on SDGs dengan tema \"SDGs Sebagai Tools Peningkatan Kapasitas dan Pengembangan Kemitraan\" kembali hadir kali ini bekerja sama dengan Wahana Visi Indonesia and Social Investment Indonesia di Surabaya', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SDGs (<em>Sustainable Development Goals</em>) atau Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (TPB) merupakan seperangkat tujuan universal, target, dan indikator dari agenda pembangunan yang disepakati di tingkat global. SDGs diharapkan dapat menanggulangi berbagai masalah global, termasuk menghapuskan kemiskinan dan kelaparan, memajukan kesehatan dan pendidikan, membangun kota-kota secara berkelanjutan, memerangi perubahan iklim serta melindungi lautan dan hutan. SDGs didukung oleh 193 negara anggota PBB dan digunakan untuk membingkai rencana pembangunan nasional negara-negara diseluruh dunia selama 15 tahun ke depan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Keterlibatan lembaga filantropi dalam pencapaian SDGs bukan hanya berdampak pada optimalisasi program pada masyarakat, tapi juga peningkatan kapasitas lembaga filantropi. Melalui keterlibatannya dalam SDGs, organisasi filantropi bisa lebih mempertajam target sasaran programnya dengan mengacu pada target dan indikator SDGs. Lembaga filantropi juga bisa mengukur dampak dan kontribusi programnya pada pembangunan sosial dan pembangunan global. SDGs juga memberikan kesempatan kepada lembaga filantropi untuk mempromosikan program dan inisiatifnya ke level nasional dan global, serta memperluas jaringan dan menjajaki kemitraan dengan lembaga-lembaga filantropi nasional dan global.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Masih banyak lembaga filantropi terutama di daerah yang belum dapat memahami SDGs secara keseluruhan serta perangkatnya. Hal inilah yang mendorong <strong>Filantropi Indonesia</strong> bersama <strong>Wahana Visi Indonesia&nbsp;</strong><strong>dan Social Investment Indonesia&nbsp;</strong>untuk mengadakan acara <em><strong>Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs</strong></em> dengan tema &ldquo;<em><strong>SDGs Sebagai Tools Peningkatan Kapasitas dan Pengembangan Kemitraan&rdquo;</strong></em>. Tujuan dari agenda ini adalah ingin memberikan pelatihan singkat guna memahami seluk beluk SDGs bagi lembaga filantropi lokal dan <em>stakeholder-</em>nya serta mencoba mencari persoalan apa saja yang mereka hadapi berkaitan dengan pemahaman SDGs dan mencari solusinya. Kegiatan tersebut akan diadakan pada:</p>\n\n<p>Hari/tanggal&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : Kamis, 23 November 2017</p>\n\n<p>Pukul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : 12.00 &ndash; 16.00 WIB (diawali dengan makan siang bersama)</p>\n\n<p>Tempat &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Kampus Universitas Airlangga (<em>dalam konfirmasi</em>)</p>\n', 'ed913376431be38f32d6782ffd3177a5.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-11-08 02:49:36', '2017-11-08 09:49:36', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-on-sdgs-surabaya', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'GlvwtAUgtJp8mya', 'N', '', '', '2017-11-23 00:00:00', '2017-11-23 23:59:59'),
(874, 'Philanthropy Learning on SDGs - Surabaya', '', 'PLF on SDGs with the theme \"SDGs as Tools for Capacity Building and Partnership Development\" returns this time in partnership with Wahana Visi Indonesia and Social Investment Indonesia to be held in Surabaya', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SDGs (Sustainable Development Goals) are a set of universal goals, targets, and indicators of an agreed development agenda at the global level. SDGs are expected to tackle global issues, including eliminating poverty and hunger, promoting health and education, sustainable building cities, combating climate change and protecting oceans and forests. SDGs are supported by 193 UN member states and are used to frame national development plans of countries around the world over the next 15 years.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The involvement of philanthropic institutions in achieving SDGs not only has an impact on program optimization on society, but also the capacity building of philanthropic institutions. Through its involvement in SDGs, philanthropy organizations can further sharpen their program targets by referring to the target and indicators of the SDGs. The philanthropic institution can also measure the impact and contribution of its programs to social development and global development. SDGs also provides opportunities for philanthropic agencies to promote their programs and initiatives to national and global levels, and expand the network and explore partnerships with national and global philanthropic institutions.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are still many philanthropic institutions especially in areas that have not been able to understand the overall SDGs as well as their devices. This is what encouraged Filantropi&nbsp;Indonesia in partnership with Wahana Visi Indonesia and Social Investment Indonesia&nbsp;in Surabaya to hold the&nbsp;Philanthropy Learning Forum on SDGs with the theme &quot;<em>SDGs as Tools for Capacity Building and Partnership Development</em>&quot;. The purpose of this agenda is to provide a short training to understand the ins and outs of SDGs for local philanthropy&nbsp;organizations and their stakeholders and to try to find out what issues they are dealing with understanding the SDGs and seek solutions. The event will be held on:</p>\n\n<p>Date: Thursday/ November 23, 2017</p>\n\n<p>Time: 12.00 - 16.00 WIB (lunch provided)</p>\n\n<p>Location:<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Universitas Airlangga (<em>to be confirmed</em>)</p>\n', 'ed913376431be38f32d6782ffd3177a5.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2017-11-08 02:49:36', '2017-11-08 09:49:36', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-on-sdgs-surabaya', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'GlvwtAUgtJp8mya', 'N', '', '', '2017-11-23 00:00:00', '2017-11-23 23:59:59'),
