(1097, 'Alliance Magazine December 2018: Royal Philanthropy', '', '', '', '914b99c44718491040c184b39e86e363.png', '', 0, 'N', 'M', '2019-01-09 04:52:04', '2019-06-19 14:43:10', 5, 'alliance-magazine-december-2018-royal-philanthropy', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'december-2018.pdf', '', '', '', 'Uej408Ieo348054', 'YDdTUECNRJcPQ9c', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1098, 'Alliance Magazine December 2018: Royal Philanthropy', '', '', '', '914b99c44718491040c184b39e86e363.png', '', 0, 'N', 'M', '2019-01-09 04:52:04', '2019-06-19 14:43:10', 5, 'alliance-magazine-december-2018-royal-philanthropy', 'download', 0, '', 'en', 'december-2018.pdf', '', '', '', 'Uej408Ieo348054', 'YDdTUECNRJcPQ9c', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1099, 'WINGS Philanthropy Support Associations for the Future 2019', '', 'Acara ini bertujuan untuk mendukung jaringan filantropi baru maupun asosiasi filantropi yang sudah ada sebagai upaya dalam mengembangkan sumber daya lokal untuk masyarakat di suatu negara dan memperkuat kinerja organisasi.', '<p>Pada bulan April tanggal 24-26, WINGS akan berkolaborasi dengan Caribbean Network of Foundations untuk&nbsp;menjadi tuan rumah dalam acara &#39;peer-learning&#39; di&nbsp;Kingston, Jamaika, dengan tema&nbsp;&ldquo;Philanthropy Support Associations for the Future: Action Learning to Create the Networks We Need&ldquo;. Tujuan dari acara ini adalah&nbsp;untuk mendukung jaringan filantropi baru maupun asosiasi filantropi yang sudah ada sebagai upaya dalam mengembangkan sumber daya lokal untuk masyarakat di suatu negara dan memperkuat kinerja organisasi.</p>\n\n<p>Dalam acara ini, akan dibahas bagaimana peran sebuah asosiasi filantropi di masa depan, identifikasi aktor yang berpengaruh serta sumber daya apa saja yang diperlukan. Filantropi dan berbagai konteks yang mengikutinya berkembang cepat, termasuk tantangan dan kesempatan yang dihadapi oleh asosiasi filantropi itu sendiri. Di level global sendiri, ada kesepatan bahwa kita membutuhkan ekosistem yang dapat mendukung filantropi namun informasi dan pengetahuan terkait hal itu masih sangat terbatas.</p>\n\n<p>Acara ini akan memberikan informasi dan pengetahuan tentang cakupan kerja asosiasi filantropi,&nbsp;yang pada akhirnya berpengaruh pada anggota, jaringan, dan masyarakat sipil.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Untuk informasi lebih lanjut,&nbsp;dapat mengunjungi :&nbsp;https://www.tickettailor.com/events/wings/218406</p>\n', 'ce3020c3fd952869e36fd405f1871dda.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-01-10 06:49:08', '2019-01-10 14:07:54', 5, 'wings-philanthropy-support-associations-for-the-future-2019', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'CXvZUA6YDqTXxI8', 'N', '', '', '2019-04-24 00:00:00', '2019-04-26 23:59:59'),
(1100, 'WINGS Philanthropy Support Associations for the Future 2019', '', 'This event aims to support emerging philanthropic networks and existing associations as a way to develop local resources for civil society and strengthen foundation’s work.', '<p>On April 24-26, WINGS will host a peer-learning event in Kingston, Jamaica, co-hosted by the new Caribbean Network of Foundations, titled &ldquo;Philanthropy Support Associations for the Future: action learning to create the networks we need&ldquo;. The objective is to support emerging philanthropic networks and existing associations as a way to develop local resources for civil society and strengthen foundation&rsquo;s work.</p>\n\n<p>This meeting will examine the philanthropy support associations of the future, identifying factors that will help and hinder the development of the kinds of associations we want and need.&nbsp; Philanthropy and its context is changing fast, and there will be new challenges and opportunities for philanthropy support associations.&nbsp;There is general agreement that we need a strong global ecosystem of philanthropy support, but there is little knowledge about how we will achieve it. This meeting, and the larger process of recording knowledge about philanthropic association work, will help emerging and existing networks to strengthen their leadership in the philanthropic space, which in turn will strengthen their foundations&rsquo; (members) work, and ultimately, civil society.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>For detailed info, please visit:&nbsp;https://www.tickettailor.com/events/wings/218406</p>\n', 'ce3020c3fd952869e36fd405f1871dda.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-01-10 06:49:08', '2019-01-10 14:07:54', 5, 'wings-philanthropy-support-associations-for-the-future-2019', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'CXvZUA6YDqTXxI8', 'N', '', '', '2019-04-24 00:00:00', '2019-04-26 23:59:59'),
(1105, 'Acara Penghargaan SDG PIPE', '', 'Rangkaian acara SGD Pipe sudah mencapai akhirnya! Pada (05/12), bertepatan dengan Hari Relawan Internasional, diselenggarakan acara awarding event SDG PIPE di Jakarta Creative Hub ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Rangkaian acara SGD Pipe sudah mencapai akhirnya! Pada (05/12), bertepatan dengan Hari Relawan Internasional, diselenggarakan acara <em>awarding event</em> SDG PIPE di Jakarta Creative Hub. Dimana telah terpilih 5 pemenang yang sudah lolos seleksi tahap presentasi dan <em>pitching</em> kepada investor dalam agenda &ldquo;<em>Knowledge Dim sum</em>&rdquo; pada Festival Filantropi Indonesia (FIFEST) 2018 di JCC, bulan November lalu. Adapun kelima pemenang tersebut dan masing-masing program inovatifnya yaitu: Abdul Latif Wahid (Aplikasi Kepul &ndash; aplikasi dalam upaya optimalisasi jual beli sampah yang dapat di daur ulang), Budi Santoso (Gerakan CaperI atau Cerdas Anak Perempuan Indonesia &ndash; gerakan penyetaraan hak untuk anak perempuan dan pencegahan perkawinan usia dini), Fransiska Myrna Sani (Kojo - produk sirup dan dodol dari bahan dasar buah manggrove jenis Pidada), Intan Imelda F. Siagian (BacaBeraksiBermedia &ndash; <em>campaign</em> dari komunitas Indoreadgram), Yogi Adjie Driantama (Semut Sumut &ndash; program ruang belajar usia 16-25 tahun yang telah putus sekolah). Nantinya, mereka berhak mengikuti <em>capacity building</em> dalam bentuk program inkubasi, pelatihan lapangan dan <em>seed grants</em> yang telah disiapkan dimana akan berjalan hingga bulan Maret 2019.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Rangkaian acara SDG PIPE (Pemuda Indonesia Penggerak Perubahan) yang digagas sebagai hasil kerjasama dari Go Global Indonesia bersama Campaign ID, PIRAC dan Filantropi Indonesia serta dukungan oleh Yayasan Sahabat Multibintang dan <em>William &amp; Lily Foundation</em> ini, dimulai pada bulan Oktober 2018 dan memberikan kesempatan kepada para <em>SDG Young Changemaker</em> untuk menyuarakan insiatifnya dalam mendukung pencapaian Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan/ SDGs di Indonesia. Tema inovasi yang diusung meliputi Perdamaian, Pemberdayaan Perempuan dan Pemuda, Pendidikan, Lingkungan Hidup serta Kematian Ibu dan Bayi. Keputusan untuk memilih 5 pemenang telah disepakati oleh juri yang tertunjuk yakni Sinta Kaniawati (CSR <em>Director</em>, Yayasan Unilever Indonesia), Hning Wicaksono (Direktur Yayasan Sahabat Multibintang), Edwin J. Tanga (<em>Project Partner &amp; Program Director</em>, Long Haul - Indoestri Makerspace), Dian Hasan (Pendiri Impact Hub) dan Michele Soeryadjaya&nbsp;(Direktur William &amp; Lily Foundation).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dikutip dari Youngster.id, dalam acara <em>awarding event </em>turut hadir pejabat Deputi dari Kementerian Pemuda dan Olahraga, Dedy Mulyadi. Menurut Fonnyta Amran dari Go Global Indonesia, antusiasme dalam berinovasi sosial membuat perubahan positif dalam keikutsertaan acara ini sangat tinggi dan ternyata ide-ide yang masuk sangat beragam. Disamping itu, Hamid Abidin selaku Direktur Filantropi Indonesia menuturkan bahwa tahapan pemilihan hingga menjadi lima pemenang mengalami perjalanan yang berbeda dan menantang dimana inovasi tersebut harus tersusun baik dalam konsep maupun implementasinya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;&ldquo;Harapan kami dengan adanya <em>change makers</em> muda ini, mereka dapat menjadi katalis perubahan di Iingkungannya masing-masing dan mendorong lebih banyak orang terutama anak muda untuk juga membuat perubahan lain lagi. Kami yakin jika ada lebih banyak orang yang menggerakkan perubahan ini, maka nanti masyarakat lndonesia bisa menjadi masyarakat penggerak perubahan atau <em>society of changemakers</em>,&rdquo; kata Nina Nasution, Direktur Eksekutif dari Yayasan Bina Antarbudaya.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Untuk info mengenai klaster Filantropi dan update kegiatan Filantropi Indonesia, hubungi kami di info@filantropi.or.id</p>\n', '00e35a649668db260c171fd5c8432275.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-01-21 03:28:50', '2019-01-21 10:31:20', 5, 'acara-penghargaan-sdg-pipe', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'XO5jugf2Dfczi1n', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1106, 'SDG PIPE Awarding Event', '', 'A series of SDG PIPE events has come to an end! On (12/05), coincided with International Volunteer Day, was conducted SDGH PIPE awarding event at Jakarta Creative Hub.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A series of SDG PIPE events has come to an end! On (12/05), coincided with International Volunteer Day, was conducted SDGH PIPE awarding event at Jakarta Creative Hub. The event was conducted where 5 winners was chosen and got selected for presentation and pitching to an investor in an event called &ldquo;knowledge dimsum&rdquo; on Filantropi Indonesia Festival (FIFEST) 2018 at JCC last November. The five chosen winners and their innovative programs are: Abul Latif Wahid (Kepul &ndash; application for buying and selling recycled waste), Budi Santoso (Gerakan Caperi or Cerdas Anak Perempuan Indonesia. A movement about equal rights for girls and child marriage prevention) Fransiska Myrna Sanni (Kojo, a food product, syrup and dodol with basic ingredients mangrove pidada), Intan Imelda F. Siagian (BacaBeraksiBermedia a campaign from Indoreadgram community), Yogi Adjie Driantama (Semutsemut &ndash; a study program for those 16-25 years old who drop out school). Later on, they would be able to get a capacity building in the form of incubation program, field training and seed grants which has been prepared and will run until March 2019.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The series of SDG PIPE (Pemuda Indonesia Penggerak Perubahan) which was initiated as a result of collaboration of Go Global Indonesia along with Campaign ID, PIRAC, and Filantropi Indonesia with a support from Sahabat Multibintang Foundation and William &amp; Lily Foundation, started on October 2018. The event gave a chance to all the SDG Changemaker to voice their initiative in supporting the goals of SDGs in Indonesia. The innovation theme that were carried out covers peace, woman and young people empowerment, education, living environment, as well as maternal and infant mortality. The decision to choose the five winners has been agreed upon by the chosen panel which are Sinta Kaniawati (CSR Director Unilever Indonesia Foundation) Hning Wicaksono (Director of Sahabat Multibintang Foundation), Edwin J. Tangga (Project partner &amp; program director, Long Haul &ndash; Indoestri Makerspace), Dian Hasan (Founder Impact Hub) and Michelle Soeryadjaya (Director of William and Lily Foundation).</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Cited from Youngster.id, in the awarding event was also present deputi officials from Ministry youth and Sport Affairs, Dedi Mulyadi. According to Fonnyta Amran from Go Global Indonesia, the enthusiasm in social innovation has made a positive change and the participation number is also very high, the idea that came was also very diverse. Moreover, Hamid Abidin as Director of Filantropi Indonesia said that the stage of election until the chosen 5 winners faced different and challenging path where its innovation has to be well arranged either in concept or implementation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;Our hope that with these young change makers, they can be a catalyst of change in their own environment and encourage more people especially young people to make other changes. We are confident that if more people contribute in driving this change, then later on Indonesian society can be a society of changemakers&rdquo; said Nina Nasution, Executive Director of Bina AntarBudaya Foundation.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\n', '00e35a649668db260c171fd5c8432275.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-01-21 03:28:50', '2019-01-21 10:31:20', 5, 'sdg-pipe-awarding-event', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'XO5jugf2Dfczi1n', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1107, 'Disaster Outlook 2019', '', 'Disaster Management Institute of Indonesia (DMII) - Aksi Cepat Tanggap (ACT) akan menyelenggarakan Disaster Outlook 2019: “Meneropong Potensi Bencana di sepanjang 2019 dan upaya mitigasinya”', '<p>Meningkatnya kejadian bencana di beberapa tahun terakhir, termasuk sejumlah riset dari para pakar yang mengindikasikan sejumlah potensi ancaman bencana di masa mendatang, menuntut langkah-langkah mitigasi secara sistematis. Dunia usaha, Instansi Pemerintah, masyarakat umum, dan lain sebagainya tentu harus mempersiapkan diri agar memiliki daya tahan dan ketangguhan terhadap ancaman bencana.</p>\n\n<p>DMII-ACT akan menyelenggarakan<strong> Disaster Outlook 2019: &ldquo;Meneropong Potensi Bencana di Sepanjang 2019 dan Upaya Mitigasinya&rdquo;</strong> yang rencananya akan dilaksanakan pada:</p>\n\n<p>Hari/ tanggal&nbsp;: Kamis, 31 Januari 2019</p>\n\n<p>Waktu : 08.30-16.30 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Tempat : Hotel Bidakara Jakarta Selatan&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Kontribusi:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Rp 1.000.000,- per orang</p>\n\n<p>Rp 1.500.000,- per dua orang peserta</p>\n\n<p>Pembayaran dapat ditransfer ke Yayasan Aksi Cepat Tanggap Bank Mandiri Nomor Rekening 1270007669573. Konfirmasi pembayaran dan peserta melalui&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/dis-outlook\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/dis-outlook</a>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Narahubung:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Sarah Ratu 0812 9859 6193</p>\n', '32c2b1fdb977e148e441e1dd6a6415c7.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-01-22 08:09:15', '2019-01-22 15:15:33', 5, 'disaster-outlook-2019', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'YVb8BSY3SIjSCn1', 'N', '', '', '2019-01-31 00:00:00', '2019-01-31 23:59:59'),
(1108, 'Disaster Outlook 2019', '', 'Disaster Management Institute of Indonesia (DMII) - Aksi Cepat Tanggap (ACT) will host an event: Disaster Outlook 2019: “Meneropong Potensi Bencana di Sepanjang 2019 dan Upaya Mitigasinya”', '<p>Disaster Management Institute of Indonesia (DMII) - Aksi Cepat Tanggap (ACT) will host an event: Disaster Outlook 2019: <strong>&ldquo;Meneropong Potensi Bencana di Sepanjang 2019 dan Upaya Mitigasinya&rdquo;</strong></p>\n\n<p>Day/Date : Thursday, 31 January&nbsp;2019</p>\n\n<p>Time : 08.30-16.30 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Place : Hotel Bidakara, Jakarta Selatan&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>HTM:</strong></p>\n\n<p>1.000.000 IDR&nbsp;(each person)</p>\n\n<p>1.500.000 IDR&nbsp;(two people)</p>\n\n<p>Payment methods:&nbsp;Yayasan Aksi Cepat Tanggap Bank Mandiri&nbsp; No. 1270007669573. Payment confirmation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/dis-outlook\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/dis-outlook</a>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Contact Person:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Sarah Ratu 0812 9859 6193</p>\n', '32c2b1fdb977e148e441e1dd6a6415c7.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-01-22 08:09:15', '2019-01-22 15:15:33', 5, 'disaster-outlook-2019', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'YVb8BSY3SIjSCn1', 'N', '', '', '2019-01-31 00:00:00', '2019-01-31 23:59:59'),
(1109, 'Philanthropy Learning Forum ke-20 ', '', 'Philanthropy Learning Forum (PLF) ke-20 mengangkat tema \"Optimalisasi Pemanfaatan Payment Gateway untuk Kegiatan Filantropi\"', '<p>Philanthropy Learning Forum (PLF) ke-20 mengangkat tema &quot;Optimalisasi Pemanfaatan Payment Gateway untuk Kegiatan Filantropi&quot;. Tema ini diangkat karena payment gateway dapat memudahkan masyarakat untuk berdonasi, maka Filantropi Indonesia dan GO-PAY berkolaborasi untuk mengekplorasi potensi dan pemanfaatan instrumen tersebut. Tujuan yang ingin dicapai dari kegiatan ini adalah meningkatkan pemahaman bagi lembaga nirlaba dan filantropi terkait kemudahan payment gateway sebagai instrumen dalam menggerakkan kegiatan filantropi.</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>Narasumber:</strong></u></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Ricky Fahri (GO-PAY), &quot;Strategi Komunikasi &amp; Kampanye Pemanfaatan GO-PAY dalam Mengoptimalkan Penggalangan Donasi&quot;</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Ahmad Mujahid (Head of NGO Consultant Impacts Digital), &quot;Memahami Perilaku Berderma Masyarakat di Era Digital&quot;</li>\n	<li>Hafiza Elvira Nofitariani (Digital Marketing BAZNAS), &quot;Praktik Baik Pemanfaatan Payment Gateway dalam Mengoptimalkan Donasi Publik&quot;</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Hari/tanggal&nbsp; : Kamis, 14 Februari 2019</p>\n\n<p>Pukul&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: 13.00 - 16.00 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Tempat&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: Auditorium Go-Learn, GO-JEK HQ, Pasaraya Blok M Lantai 6&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Jl. Iskandarsyah II No. 7, Melawai, Kebayoran Baru, Jakarta Selatan&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>Pendaftaran Peserta:</strong></u></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bit.ly/DAFTARPLF20\">www.bit.ly/DAFTARPLF20</a></p>\n\n<p>atau Aulia (0856 9662 9680)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Keterangan lebih lanjut mengenai Go-Donation: <a href=\"http://www.bit.ly/GoDonation\">www.bit.ly/GoDonation</a></p>\n', 'dcbb65dcd02b16882fec0b45fcc60fd9.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-02-12 06:08:01', '2019-02-12 13:14:26', 5, 'philanthropy-learning-forum-ke-20-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'rHSPioB9wIWGiCS', 'N', '', '', '2019-02-14 00:00:00', '2019-02-14 23:59:59'),
(1110, 'The 20th Philanthropy Learning Forum (PLF)', '', 'The 20th Philanthropy Learning Forum (PLF) raises the theme \"Optimizing the Utilization of Payment Gateway for Philanthropic Activities\". This theme was raised because payment gateways can make it easier for people to donate.  Thus, Filantropi Indonesia and GO-PAY have collaborated to explore the potential and utilization of these instruments. The aim of this activity is to increase people\'s understanding of the opportunity for non-profit and philanthropic institutions to use payment gateways as an instrument in mobilizing philanthropic activities.', '<p><u><strong>The Speakers:</strong></u></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Ricky Fahri (GO-PAY), &quot;Communication &amp; Campaign Strategy for Using GO-PAY in Optimizing Fundraising&quot;</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Ahmad Mujahid (Head of NGO Consultant Impacts Digital), &quot;Understanding Community Charitable Behaviour in the Digital Age&quot;</li>\n	<li>Hafiza Elvira Nofitariani (Digital Marketing BAZNAS), &quot;Good Practices for Using Payment Gateway in Optimizing Public Donations&quot;</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Date&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;: Thursday, 14th February&nbsp;2019</p>\n\n<p>Time&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: 13.00 - 16.00 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Place&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; : Auditorium Go-Learn, GO-JEK HQ, Pasaraya Blok M Lantai 6&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Jl. Iskandarsyah II No. 7, Melawai, Kebayoran Baru, Jakarta Selatan&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>RSVP:</strong></u></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bit.ly/DAFTARPLF20\">www.bit.ly/DAFTARPLF20</a></p>\n\n<p>or Aulia (0856 9662 9680)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Further information about&nbsp;Go-Donation: <a href=\"http://www.bit.ly/GoDonation\">www.bit.ly/GoDonation</a></p>\n', 'dcbb65dcd02b16882fec0b45fcc60fd9.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-02-12 06:08:01', '2019-02-12 13:14:26', 5, 'the-20th-philanthropy-learning-forum-plf-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'rHSPioB9wIWGiCS', 'N', '', '', '2019-02-14 00:00:00', '2019-02-14 23:59:59'),
(1111, '[JOB VACANCY] Donor Relations Officer - UNICEF Indonesia', '', 'Are you ready to use your talents to make the world a better place for Children?\nIf you are a committed, creative professional and are passionate about making a lasting difference for children, the world’s leading children’s rights organization would like to hear from you.', '<p><strong><u>VACANCY REFERENCE: 19-013 </u></strong><br />\nTitle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: Donor Relations Officer<br />\nLevel&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: NO-B (National Professional Category)<br />\nType of Contract&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Fixed-Term, Post # 94971<br />\nDuty Station&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Jakarta, Indonesia</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>SUMMARY OF THE POST:</strong></u><br />\nThe incumbent will be responsible for managing UNICEF Indonesia&rsquo;s major gifts programme, which consists of generating significant financial contributions from high-net-worth individuals and family/corporate foundations for UNICEF&rsquo;s programmes in Indonesia and worldwide, with a focus on donors giving significant donations over USD 1 million.</p>\n\n<p>The post-holder will be the critical enabler to ensure realization of UNICEF Indonesia&rsquo;s philanthropy targets. The major gifts programme in Indonesia is still new, and a significant portion of the post-holder&rsquo;s focus will be on generating new business.<br />\nThe role includes building and maintaining personal relationships with prospects and donors, preparing compelling cases for support and other material, the active solicitation of philanthropic gifts, as well as the preparation of asks by UNICEF Indonesia&rsquo;s senior management.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<u><strong>MAIN TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></u><br />\n&bull; Identify and research potential donors among Indonesia&rsquo;s high-net-worth individuals and associated foundations (with a specific focus on those able to give gifts of US$1,000,000 and upwards)<br />\n&bull; Develop and keep up to date donor profiles, moves management, and contact reports.<br />\n&bull; Develop and cultivate personal relationships and networks of prospects, existing donors, and their advisors<br />\n&bull; Engage high-net-worth individuals both as donors to UNICEF, and as potential influencers in support of our programmatic and fundraising objectives<br />\n&bull; Effective account management/donor recognition and relevant reporting/feedback<br />\n&bull; Develop funding proposals, cases for support, compelling presentations, and other relevant materials necessary for potential donors to identify relevant funding opportunities.<br />\n&bull; Manage due diligence screenings of individuals, foundations and related companies where relevant, and advise on possible associated risks.</p>\n\n<p>Work closely with colleagues (in Indonesia and in regional/head offices) to ensure that all donations and relationships<br />\n&bull; Comply with UNICEF&rsquo;s policies<br />\n&bull; Support UNICEF&rsquo;s plans and priorities<br />\n&bull; Follow best practices in qualifying, cultivating, soliciting and stewarding donor relationships.<br />\n<br />\n<u><strong>PROFILE OF THE IDEAL CANDIDATE:</strong></u><br />\n&bull; Master&rsquo;s degree*) in management, marketing, social sciences or related field.<br />\n&bull; At least 3 (three) years of professional experience of managing high value philanthropic partnerships on the side of the recipient (i.e. a non-profit organization, university, etc.) or the side of the donor (i.e. a grant-making foundation, the personal office of a HNWI, etc.).<br />\n&bull; Significant experience in business development or building up a fundraising programme.<br />\n&bull; Fluency in English<br />\n&bull; This position is open for Indonesian national only.</p>\n\n<p><em>(*First level relevant university degree in combination with 6 years of experience may be accepted in lieu of the advanced university degree.)</em></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>For every Child, you demonstrate&hellip;</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Our core values of Commitment, Diversity and Integrity and core competencies in Communication, Working with People and Drive for Results.</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>UNICEF is committed to diversity and inclusion within its workforce and encourages qualified candidates from all backgrounds to apply.</strong></p>\n\n<p><em>UNICEF has a zero-tolerance policy on conduct that is incompatible with the aims and objectives of the United Nations, including sexual exploitation and abuse, sexual harassment, abuse of authority and discrimination. UNICEF also adheres to strict child safeguarding principles. All selected candidates will, therefore, undergo rigorous reference and background checks, and will be expected to adhere to these standards and principles.</em></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>APPLY NOW:</strong></span>&nbsp;https://www.unicef.org/about/employ/?job=520074&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Closing date: 20 March 2019</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>Disclaimer: The screening of your application will be conducted based on the information in your profile. Before applying, we strongly suggest that you review your profile to ensure accuracy and completeness. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p>\n', 'f9f6c98a0c91cdbdeaa71b9e29c7449a.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-03-11 06:57:33', '2019-07-09 14:39:57', 5, '-job-vacancy-donor-relations-officer-unicef-indonesia', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'qhxRB5aX5Ghz4YT', 'N', '', 'https://www.unicef.org/about/employ', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1112, '[JOB VACANCY] Donor Relations Officer - UNICEF Indonesia', '', 'Are you ready to use your talents to make the world a better place for Children?\nIf you are a committed, creative professional and are passionate about making a lasting difference for children, the world’s leading children’s rights organization would like to hear from you.', '<p><strong><u>VACANCY REFERENCE: 19-013 </u></strong><br />\nTitle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: Donor Relations Officer<br />\nLevel&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: NO-B (National Professional Category)<br />\nType of Contract&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Fixed-Term, Post # 94971<br />\nDuty Station&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Jakarta, Indonesia</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>SUMMARY OF THE POST:</strong></u><br />\nThe incumbent will be responsible for managing UNICEF Indonesia&rsquo;s major gifts programme, which consists of generating significant financial contributions from high-net-worth individuals and family/corporate foundations for UNICEF&rsquo;s programmes in Indonesia and worldwide, with a focus on donors giving significant donations over USD 1 million.</p>\n\n<p>The post-holder will be the critical enabler to ensure realization of UNICEF Indonesia&rsquo;s philanthropy targets. The major gifts programme in Indonesia is still new, and a significant portion of the post-holder&rsquo;s focus will be on generating new business.<br />\nThe role includes building and maintaining personal relationships with prospects and donors, preparing compelling cases for support and other material, the active solicitation of philanthropic gifts, as well as the preparation of asks by UNICEF Indonesia&rsquo;s senior management.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<u><strong>MAIN TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></u><br />\n&bull; Identify and research potential donors among Indonesia&rsquo;s high-net-worth individuals and associated foundations (with a specific focus on those able to give gifts of US$1,000,000 and upwards)<br />\n&bull; Develop and keep up to date donor profiles, moves management, and contact reports.<br />\n&bull; Develop and cultivate personal relationships and networks of prospects, existing donors, and their advisors<br />\n&bull; Engage high-net-worth individuals both as donors to UNICEF, and as potential influencers in support of our programmatic and fundraising objectives<br />\n&bull; Effective account management/donor recognition and relevant reporting/feedback<br />\n&bull; Develop funding proposals, cases for support, compelling presentations, and other relevant materials necessary for potential donors to identify relevant funding opportunities.<br />\n&bull; Manage due diligence screenings of individuals, foundations and related companies where relevant, and advise on possible associated risks.</p>\n\n<p>Work closely with colleagues (in Indonesia and in regional/head offices) to ensure that all donations and relationships<br />\n&bull; Comply with UNICEF&rsquo;s policies<br />\n&bull; Support UNICEF&rsquo;s plans and priorities<br />\n&bull; Follow best practices in qualifying, cultivating, soliciting and stewarding donor relationships.<br />\n<br />\n<u><strong>PROFILE OF THE IDEAL CANDIDATE:</strong></u><br />\n&bull; Master&rsquo;s degree*) in management, marketing, social sciences or related field.<br />\n&bull; At least 3 (three) years of professional experience of managing high value philanthropic partnerships on the side of the recipient (i.e. a non-profit organization, university, etc.) or the side of the donor (i.e. a grant-making foundation, the personal office of a HNWI, etc.).<br />\n&bull; Significant experience in business development or building up a fundraising programme.<br />\n&bull; Fluency in English<br />\n&bull; This position is open for Indonesian national only.</p>\n\n<p><em>(*First level relevant university degree in combination with 6 years of experience may be accepted in lieu of the advanced university degree.)</em></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>For every Child, you demonstrate&hellip;</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Our core values of Commitment, Diversity and Integrity and core competencies in Communication, Working with People and Drive for Results.</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>UNICEF is committed to diversity and inclusion within its workforce and encourages qualified candidates from all backgrounds to apply.</strong></p>\n\n<p><em>UNICEF has a zero-tolerance policy on conduct that is incompatible with the aims and objectives of the United Nations, including sexual exploitation and abuse, sexual harassment, abuse of authority and discrimination. UNICEF also adheres to strict child safeguarding principles. All selected candidates will, therefore, undergo rigorous reference and background checks, and will be expected to adhere to these standards and principles.</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Closing date: 20 March 2019</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>Disclaimer: The screening of your application will be conducted based on the information in your profile. Before applying, we strongly suggest that you review your profile to ensure accuracy and completeness. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p>\n\n<p><iframe align=\"top\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"480\" name=\"Donor Relations Officer\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"https://www.unicef.org/about/employ/?job=520074\" title=\"UNICEF\" width=\"480\"></iframe></p>\n', 'f9f6c98a0c91cdbdeaa71b9e29c7449a.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-03-11 06:57:33', '2019-07-09 14:39:57', 5, '-job-vacancy-donor-relations-officer-unicef-indonesia', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'qhxRB5aX5Ghz4YT', 'N', '', 'https://www.unicef.org/about/employ', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
