(1159, '[Conservancy Talk 1] Initiating Environmental Conservation from the City', '', '\"A decent environment can be the key to happiness for the city community. Meanwhile the availability of natural resources is an important factor whether a city will be destroyed or survive\". Stated Usi Sally, Learning and Development Manager of The Nature Conservancy (TNC) in the Conservancy Talk event on Wednesday, June 19th 2019.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&quot;A decent environment can be the key to happiness for the city community. Meanwhile the availability of natural resources is an important factor whether a city will be destroyed or survive&quot;. Stated Usi Sally, Learning and Development Manager of The Nature Conservancy (TNC) in the Conservancy Talk event on Wednesday, June 19th 2019.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Conservancy Talk is a routine event which is held monthly by Filantropi Indonesia Environment and Conservancy Cluster. Conservation efforts in urban areas are the themes raised at this meeting. Many people still assume that conservancy activities can only be done in the forest, sea, or rural areas. In fact, conservancy effort can start from our closest environment including the urban areas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Urban areas conservancy becomes really important. In the world, the total of urban area is only 3 percent of all the world. Nevertheless, 60 - 80 percent of energy consumed by city residents, and 75 percent of carbon emitters produced by cities. The majority of city locations are on the coast. This is one of the reasons Indonesia is the second largest plastic waste dumper in the world. It is estimated that by 2030 there will be 5 Billion people living in the city. You can imagine how much waste will increase in the city in the coming years.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In its history, the beginning of the establishment of a city must first look at the natural system or new worlds infrastructures then plan its infrastructure development. Globally, the development of an urban area will reduce natural habitat. During 1992 &ndash; 2000, It is estimated that 190,000 km2 of green area has already gone. The interesting part is every year, the protected area in the city, becomes wider. For example, Mangrove Forest in PIK which is the last forest for coastal habitat reduce.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">TNC offers several solutions to balance people and nature which is to understand the needs of both people and nature, improve conditions for human well-being, and build cross sector coalitions. We can also take the example of A Great Green City from several countries such as planning for green (Melbourne), water security (Sao Paolo), coastal storm resilient, (New York), sponge city (Shenzhen - China), MERA (Jakarta, Semarang, Riau). A Great Green City is equitable applying the principle of equality for all, all people living in cities must have the same level of health.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The same thing was expressed by M. Syarief from the Yayasan Keanekaragaman Hayati (Kehati) who not only had conservation programs for forest, coastal and small island ecosystems but also for big cities. One of the programs is Bird watching (BW) in Pantai Indah Kapuk, which is held specifically for people aged between 16 &ndash; 35 years old. This program started in 2015 when KEHATI did a bird data collection in Jakarta, there were 164 kind of birds in Jakarta. However, 96 kind of birds has gone extinct. Those birds will live in a green habitat with the food is maintained.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Green open space in Jakarta is far from the word proportional. According to the law, a city must have 30 percent of a green area. There are 6 cities that are starting to pursue to fulfill the rules such as Surabaya and Medan. While Jakarta is still far from that standard. This year, there will be 53 green open spaces that will be opened. Now Jakarta is ranked 54 out of 60 cities in Asia that has a problem with green open space. There are 3 reasons why KEHATI do a bird watching, bird watching can be done with a naked eye. Indonesia is a crossing point for bird migration, and the aim of providing data sources and inspiration for data centers is in urban areas.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main change expected from the environmental conservation program in urban areas is a change in the community mindset. That God created nature is not only human but also an ecosystem. Thus, there will be an awareness to love this nature.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n', '34ca2e92034163c031a46ebfcc0b3713.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 07:35:10', '2019-07-05 14:35:10', 5, '-conservancy-talk-1-initiating-environmental-conservation-from-the-city', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'TuiANOyI4OegJaD', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1160, 'Peresmian Piagam Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan', '', 'Pada Festival Filantropi Indonesia (FIFest) 2018 yang lalu, Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan telah diluncurkan. Filantropi Indonesia menunjuk Tanoto Foundation sebagai kordinator untuk klaster tersebut. Salah satu langkah awal untuk kelanjutan program kerja klaster tersebut adalah penyusunan piagam klaster pendidikan. Setelah melalui proses diskusi secara internal dan masukkan dari berbagai pihak maka pada Kamis, 20 Juni 2019 Piagam Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan diresmikan. ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada Festival Filantropi Indonesia (FIFest) 2018 yang lalu, Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan telah diluncurkan. Filantropi Indonesia menunjuk Tanoto Foundation sebagai kordinator untuk klaster tersebut. Salah satu langkah awal untuk kelanjutan program kerja klaster tersebut adalah penyusunan piagam klaster pendidikan. Setelah melalui proses diskusi secara internal dan masukkan dari berbagai pihak maka pada Kamis, 20 Juni 2019 Piagam Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan diresmikan. Diharapkan Piagam Klaster Pendidikan ini dapat menjadi landasan dalam kinerja operasional lembaga filantropi yang tergabung dalam klaster pendidikan.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebanyak 13 lembaga filantropi berfokus pada pendidikan telah berkomitmen untuk mendukung Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan ini yakni; Tanoto Foundation, Filantropi Indonesia, Yayasan Bakti Barito, Yappika Action-Aid, Sampoerna Foundation, Yayasan Arsitek 86 Peduli, Yayasan Indocement dan Wahana Visi Indonesia, William and Lily Foundation, Unicef, Ancora Foundation, Yayasan Cinta Anak Bangsa dan Dompet Dhuafa.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selama ini mayoritas program filantropi Pendidikan di Indonesia masih belum terarah, bersifat jangka pendek dan charity. Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan akan berupaya untuk membuat dampak besar dalam perbaikan pendidikan melalui aktivitas filantropi yang bersifat berkelanjutan. Agar tujuan tersebut tercapai maka penting untuk dapat menciptakan kolaborasi bersama. Baik kolaborasi lintas sektor maupun sesame lembaga yang memiliki minat yang sama dalam bidang pendidikan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selain menyusun dan meresmikan Piagam Klaster Pendidikan, pada kegiatan ini para peserta yang berasal dari perwakilan lembaga filantropi juga turut membahas dan menyepakati rencana kerja tahunan serta membentuk kelompok kerja. Rencana kerja ini akan dibuat berdasarkan pemetaan kekuatan masing-masing organisasi filantropi agar bisa saling melengkapi dalam bergerak menuju pencapaian yang terarah baik jangka pendek maupun jangka panjang.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ada tiga bidang utama yang menjadi sorotan dalam rencana penyusunan program kerja klaster ini yaitu peningkatan kapasitas filantropi, memberi wadah diseminasi dan berbagi praktik baik serta advokasi kebijakan. Pada akhir acara setiap perwakilan peserta diminta untuk memilih salah satu dari program kerja yang mereka inginkan untuk menjadi kordinatornya.</p>\n', 'da566e57b244da2fc41facfb279cebb0.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 07:38:32', '2019-07-05 14:40:33', 5, 'peresmian-piagam-klaster-filantropi-pendidikan', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'bAiZNO2rdgv7WWF', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1161, 'Inauguration of Filantropi Indonesia Educational Cluster Charter', '', 'On the previous 2018 Festival Filantropi Indonesia (FIFEST), Filantropi Indonesia Education Cluster has been launched. Filantropi Indonesia appointed Tanoto Foundation as the coordinator for Education cluster. One of the initial steps for the continuation of the cluster work program was the preparation of the education cluster charter. After going through the internal discussion process and input from various parties, on Thursday, June 20th, 2019 the Charter of Filantropi Indonesia Education Cluster was inaugurated.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On the previous 2018 Festival Filantropi Indonesia (FIFEST), Filantropi Indonesia Education Cluster has been launched. Filantropi Indonesia appointed Tanoto Foundation as the coordinator for Education cluster. One of the initial steps for the continuation of the cluster work program was the preparation of the education cluster charter. After going through the internal discussion process and input from various parties, on Thursday, June 20th, 2019 the Charter of Filantropi Indonesia Education Cluster was inaugurated. It is expected that this Education Cluster Charter can become a foundation in the operational performance of philanthropic institutions incorporated in the education cluster.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">13 education-focused philanthropic institutions have committed to support this Filantropi Indonesia Education Cluster. They are; Tanoto Foundation, Filantropi Indonesia, Yayasan Bakti Barito, Yappika Action-Aid, Sampoerna Foundation, Yayasan Arsitek 86 Peduli, Yayasan Indocement and Wahana Visi Indonesia, William and Lily Foundation, Unicef, Ancora Foundation, Yayasan Cinta Anak Bangsa dand Dompet Dhuafa.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">So far, the majority of Educational philanthropy programs in Indonesia are still not directed, are short term and in a form of charity. The Filantropi Indonesia Educational Cluster will strive to make a big impact on improving education through sustainable philanthropic activities. In order for these goals to be achieved, it is important to be able to create collaborations together, both cross-sector and similar collaboration with institutions that have similar interests in the field of education.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to compiling and formalizing the Charter, the participants from the representatives of philanthropic institutions also discussed and agreed on annual work plans and formed working groups. This work plan will be made based on the mapping of the strengths of each philanthropic organization so that it can complement each other in moving towards targeted achievements both short and long term.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are three main areas that have been highlighted in the plan to form this cluster work program, they are increasing philanthropic capacity, providing a forum for dissemination and sharing of good practices and policy advocacy. At the end of the event each participant representative was asked to choose one of the work programs they wanted to become the coordinator.</p>\n', 'da566e57b244da2fc41facfb279cebb0.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 07:38:32', '2019-07-05 14:40:33', 5, 'inauguration-of-filantropi-indonesia-educational-cluster-charter', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'bAiZNO2rdgv7WWF', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1162, 'Pelatihan Sustainability Reporting GRI', '', 'Pemerintah telah menetapkan empat platform dalam pelaksanaan TPB/SDGs, antara lain: Pemerintah dan Parlemen; Akademisi dan Pakar; Lembaga Sosial Kemasyarakatan dan Media; serta Filantropi dan Bisnis. Peran sektor Filantropi dan Bisnis untuk berkontribusi dalam pencapaian TPB/ SDGs menjadi cukup diperhitungkan karena sektor ini dipandang memiliki peluang dan sumber daya (seperti pembiayaan dan akses terhadap jaringan perusahaan) yang dapat mendukung program-program pencapaian TPB/ SDGs. ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pemerintah telah menetapkan empat platform dalam pelaksanaan TPB/SDGs, antara lain: Pemerintah dan Parlemen; Akademisi dan Pakar; Lembaga Sosial Kemasyarakatan dan Media; serta Filantropi dan Bisnis. Peran sektor Filantropi dan Bisnis untuk berkontribusi dalam pencapaian TPB/ SDGs menjadi cukup diperhitungkan karena sektor ini dipandang memiliki peluang dan sumber daya (seperti pembiayaan dan akses terhadap jaringan perusahaan) yang dapat mendukung program-program pencapaian TPB/ SDGs. Setiap kegiatan yang telah mereka lakukan terkait implementasi SDGs harus terdokumentasi secara efektif dan komprehensif melalui mekanisme pelaporan yang dapat dilaksanakan secara berkelanjutan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Laporan berkelanjutan (sustainability report) adalah laporan yang diterbitkan oleh sebuah institusi, baik sektor Filantropi maupun bisnis, mengenai dampak ekonomi, lingkungan, dan sosial yang disebabkan oleh aktivitas sehari-hari institusi tersebut, disertai dengan komitmen dan rencana aksi dari institusi untuk mengurangi dampak tersebut.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sebagai sebuah asosiasi dari lembaga filantropi yang ada di Indonesia, Filantropi Indonesia telah membentuk platfrom kolaborasi bagi anggotanya yang memiliki kesamaan minat program. Hingga tahun 2019 ini, telah terbentuk enam klaster yaitu Klaster Filantropi Permukiman dan Perkotaan, Klaster Filantropi Zakat untuk SDGs (Zakat on SDGs), Klaster Filantropi Ketahanan Pangan dan Gizi, Klaster Filantropi Pendidikan, Klaster Filantropi Lingkungan Hidup dan Konservasi, dan Klaster Filantropi Kesenian dan Kebudayaan. Setiap klaster filantropi tersebut memiliki kordinator yang bertanggung jawab untuk mengorganisir jalannya klaster.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia dan Global Report Initiative (GRI) menyadari bahwa banyak lembaga filantropi termasuk di dalamnya anggota klaster masih kurang menyadari pentingnya sustainability reporting. Harus disadari bahwa sustainability report dapat juga dimanfaatkan untuk mengukur kontribusinya dalam pencapaian TPB/SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">GRI merupakan pelopor dari pelaporan keberlanjutan. Selain itu GRI juga memberikan ruang bagi penggunanya untuk bisa menambahkan klasifikasi yang ingin dilaporkan. GRI telah memiliki standar pelaporan yang didasarkan pada aspek ekonomi, lingkungan hidup, dan sosial. Selain itu GRI juga menggunakan pendekatan yang beragam baik dalam aspek pemangku kepentingan maupun penerapannya dalam praktek terkait jaringan. Jaringan GRI telah tersebar di berbagai negara dan dimanfaatkan oleh berbagai sektor.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kemitraan yang dibangun antara Filantropi Indonesia (FI) dan Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) adalah dalam rangka mengimplementasikan program Corporate Sustainability and Reporting for Competitive Business (CSRCB). Tujuan dari program ini adalah untuk berkontribusi dalam proses integrasi sektor Filantropi dan Bisnis ke dalam Global Value Chains (GVCs)/ Rantai Nilai melalui laporan berkelanjutan. Selain itu diharapkan dengan platfrom ini sektor filantropi dapat mengukur kinerja dan dampak dari program implementasi TPB/SDGs yang sudah dilaksanakan.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada tanggal 26 -27 yang lalu Filantropi Indonesia dan GRI telah sukses menyelenggarakan kegiatan pelatihan GRI yang dihadiri oleh 35 peserta. Selama 3 hari, Ibu Lany selaku Country Program Manager GRI dan Pak Hendrik memfasilitasi peserta dengan memberikan penjelasan mengenai apa itu GRI dan tujuannya, penerapan dan penggambaran GRI dalam program dan juga mengidentifikasi indicator standard GRI yang sesuai dengan nilai ataupun tujuan program di organisasi masing &ndash; masing.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Setelah pelatihan, tindak lanjut bagi masing &ndash; masing peserta adalah mencoba membuat pelaoran dengan srandard GRI. Peserta masih bisa mendapat pendampingan berlanjut dari FilantropI Indonesia maupun dari GRI. Organisasi juga dapat mengajukan pelatihan apabila dirasa membutuhkan pelatihan lebih lanjut di organisasinya masing-masing.</p>\n', 'b443de82a7b09c1e6dc3864135d6b559.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 07:43:21', '2019-07-05 15:36:45', 5, 'pelatihan-sustainability-reporting-gri', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'XEQM7UiBWOLjTvA', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1163, 'GRI Sustainability Reporting Training', '', 'The government has established four platforms in the implementation of the TPB / SDGs, including: Government and Parliament; Academics and Experts; Community and Media Social Institutions; and Philanthropy and Business. The role of the Philanthropy and Business sector to contribute to the achievement of the TPB / SDGs is quite calculated because this sector is seen as having opportunities and resources (such as financing and access to corporate networks) that can support programs to achieve TPB / SDGs. ', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The government has established four platforms in the implementation of the TPB / SDGs, including: Government and Parliament; Academics and Experts; Community and Media Social Institutions; and Philanthropy and Business. The role of the Philanthropy and Business sector to contribute to the achievement of the TPB / SDGs is quite calculated because this sector is seen as having opportunities and resources (such as financing and access to corporate networks) that can support programs to achieve TPB / SDGs. Every activity they have carried out related to the implementation of SDGs must be documented effectively and comprehensively through a reporting mechanism that can be implemented in a sustainable manner.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sustainability report is a report issued by an institution, both the Philanthropy and business sectors, regarding the economic, environmental and social impacts caused by the institution&#39;s daily activities, accompanied by commitments and action plans from the institution to reduce these impacts.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">As an association of philanthropic institutions in Indonesia, Filantropi Indonesia has formed a collaboration platform for its members who share the interests of the program. Up to 2019, six clusters have been formed, namely the Filantropi Indonesia Settlement and Urban Philanthropy Clusters, Filantropi Indonesia Zakat Clusters for SDGs (Zakat on SDGs), Filantropi Indonesia Food and Nutrition Resilience Cluster, Filantropi Indonesia Educational Cluster, Filantropi Indonesia Environmental and Conservation Clusters, Filantropi Indonesia Art and Culture Cluster. Each Filantropi cluster has a coordinator who is responsible for organizing the cluster.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Filantropi Indonesia and the Global Report Initiative (GRI) recognize that many philanthropic institutions including cluster members are still less aware of the importance of sustainability reporting. It must be realized that sustainability report can also be used to measure its contribution in achieving TPB / SDGs.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">GRI is a pioneer of sustainability reporting. In addition, GRI also provides space for users to be able to add the classifications they want to report. GRI has a reporting standard based on economic, environmental and social aspects. In addition, GRI also uses diverse approaches both in stakeholder aspects and their application in network-related practices. The GRI network has spread in various countries and is utilized by various sectors.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The partnership built between Filantropi Indonesia (FI) and the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) is in order to implement the Corporate Sustainability and Reporting for Competitive Business (CSRCB) program. The aim of this program is to contribute to the process of integrating the Philanthropy and Business sectors into the Global Value Chains (GVCs) / Value Chain through continuous reports. In addition, it is expected that with this platform the philanthropic sector can measure the performance and impact of the TPB / SDGs implementation program that has been implemented.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On June 26<sup>th</sup> -27<sup>th</sup>, Filantropi Indonesia and GRI have successfully held GRI training activities which were attended by 35 participants. For 3 days, Ms. Lany as GRI&#39;s Country Program Manager and Mr. Hendrik facilitated the participants by giving an explanation of what GRI was and its purpose, GRI&#39;s implementation and depiction in the program and also identifying GRI standard indicators that were in accordance with the values or program objectives in their respective organizations.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After the training, the follow-up for each participant was to try to make a training with the GRI standard. Participants can still get continued assistance from Filantropi Indonesia and GRI. Organizations can also apply for continued training if they feel they need further training in their respective organizations.</p>\n', 'b443de82a7b09c1e6dc3864135d6b559.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 07:43:21', '2019-07-05 15:36:45', 5, 'gri-sustainability-reporting-training', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'XEQM7UiBWOLjTvA', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1164, 'Gugus Tugas SEFI', '', 'Pada tanggal 24 Juni 2019, Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan rapat internal terkait peninjauan kembali Standar Etika Filantropi Indonesia (SEFI). Dokumen SEFI berisi kode etik agar mendorong anggota dan pelaku filantropi yang mencerminkan etika yang tinggi sebagai wujud akuntabilitas.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pada tanggal 24 Juni 2019, Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan rapat internal terkait peninjauan kembali Standar Etika Filantropi Indonesia (SEFI). Dokumen SEFI berisi kode etik agar mendorong anggota dan pelaku filantropi yang mencerminkan etika yang tinggi sebagai wujud akuntabilitas. Perwakilan anggota Filantropi Indonesia yang ikut dalam gagasan gugus tugas ini adalah Tomy Hendrajati, Okty Damayanti, Nana Mintarti, Mitra Tobing, dengan diwakili dari pihak Badan Pengurus Filantropi Indonesia, Suzanty Sitorus dan Hamid Abidin selaku Direktur Eksekutif.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Pembahasan diawali dengan diskusi poin per poin dari tiap tajuk atau tema yang tertulis dalam Draft Buku Saku SEFI; adanya pengkajian ulang terhadap kalimat yang tercantum dan usulan penambahan poin yang sesuai. Sebelumnya, Draft Buku Saku SEFI ini telah disahkan pada Rapat Umum Anggota (RUA) Filantropi Indonesia pada tanggal 14 Juni 2013 dan merupakan dokumen berjalan. Revisi yang dilakukan kali ini lebih detil dengan membandingkan pada beberapa kode etik yang dimiliki oleh lembaga-lembaga lainnya.&nbsp; Dalam pertemuan ini juga diputuskan untuk memasukkan revisi ataupun usulan yang terdapat dalam rapat hari itu dalam perumusan draft yang akan di review ulang kembali dengan bantuan secretariat Filantropi Indonesia, kemudian dibentuk SOP atau panduan operasional kode etik, <em>timeline management</em>, serta <em>assessment</em> kode etik lainnya yang dimiliki oleh anggota sebagai acuan.</p>\n', 'f00bd3512010f584f7c8dd0e5c4a4853.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 08:11:19', '2019-07-05 15:41:06', 5, 'gugus-tugas-sefi', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'z8xccQeaiMmgRr5', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1165, 'SEFI Task Force', '', 'On June 24th, 2019, Filantropi Indonesia held an internal meeting related to the review of the Filantropi Indonesia Ethics Standard (SEFI). The SEFI document contains a code of ethics to encourage members and philanthropists who reflect high ethics as a form of accountability.', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On June 24th, 2019, Filantropi Indonesia held an internal meeting related to the review of the Filantropi Indonesia Ethics Standard (SEFI). The SEFI document contains a code of ethics to encourage members and philanthropists who reflect high ethics as a form of accountability. Representatives of Filantropi Indonesia members who took part in this task force were Tomy Hendrajati, Okty Damayanti, Nana Mintarti, Mitra Tobing, and representatives of Filantropi Indonesia Management Board, Suzanty Sitorus and Hamid Abidin as Executive Directors.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The discussion begins with discussion of points from each headline or theme written in the SEFI Draft; the representatives reviewed the sentences listed and also proposed to add the appropriate points. Previously, the SEFI Draft was approved at the Filantropi Indonesia general meeting (RUA) on June 14<sup>th</sup>, 2013 and became a running document. The revisions made this time are more detailed by comparing several codes of ethics from other institutions. In this meeting it was also decided to include the revisions or proposals contained in the meeting in the formulation of the draft which would be reviewed again with the help from the secretariat, then the SOPs or operational guidelines for the code of ethics, management timelines, and assessment of other codes of conduct were formed by members as a reference.</p>\n', 'f00bd3512010f584f7c8dd0e5c4a4853.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-05 08:11:19', '2019-07-05 15:41:06', 5, 'sefi-task-force', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'z8xccQeaiMmgRr5', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1166, '[JOB VACANCY] Communication Officer - Yayasan Danamon Peduli ', '', 'Saat ini Yayasan Danamon Peduli membuka lowongan pekerjaan untuk posisi Communication Officer (Internal dan External Communication). ', '<p><strong><u>Tentang Yayasan Danamon Peduli</u></strong></p>\n\n<p>Yayasan Danamon Peduli (Danamon Peduli) merupakan wujud nyata dari komitmen Bank Danamon, Adira Finance dan Adira Insurance dalam menjalankan tanggung jawab sosial perusahaan secara terfokus dan tepat sasaran. Dengan visi &ldquo;Kami peduli dan membantu jutaan orang mencapai kesejahteraan,&rdquo; Danamon Peduli menerjemahkannya dalam pilar dan program investasi sosial yang berkelanjutan.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Dalam menjalankan tugas dan tanggung jawab sosial perusahaan, Danamon Peduli turut membangun kemitraan, baik bersama pemerintah, swasta maupun masyarakat umum, termasuk dengan internal karyawan. Semua ini untuk memastikan bahwa keberadaan kami senantiasa memberikan manfaat dan dampak yang positif bagi masyarakat Indonesia dan membantu tercapainya tujuan pembangunan global yang berkelanjutan (<em>sustainable development goals</em>).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Saat ini Yayasan Danamon Peduli membuka lowongan pekerjaan untuk posisi&nbsp;<strong>Communication&nbsp;</strong><strong>Officer</strong>&nbsp;dengan kualifikasi yang dibutuhkan sebagai berikut:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>DESKRIPSI PEKERJAAN</strong></p>\n\n<p><u><strong>Internal Communication:</strong></u></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Komunikasi dan koordinasi dengan tim Danamon group&nbsp;untuk semua urusan komunikasi Yayasan&nbsp;Danamon&nbsp;Peduli;</li>\n	<li>Mempersiapkan&nbsp;konten dan&nbsp;desain layout&nbsp;untuk komunikasi internal sesuai kebutuhan Yayasan Danamon Peduli.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>External Communication:</strong></u></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Komunikasi dan koordinasi dengan tim Danamon group untuk komunikasi eksternal;</li>\n	<li>Mengelola data dan konten di website Yayasan Danamon Peduli;</li>\n	<li>Menyusun konten&nbsp;untuk komunikasi eksternal sesuai kebutuhan Yayasan Danamon Peduli;</li>\n	<li>Menyusun&nbsp;konten dan desain layout untuk&nbsp;media placement advertorial Yayasan Danamon Peduli;</li>\n	<li>Paham dalam penggunaan media sosial untuk tujuan komunikasi dan advokasi;</li>\n	<li>Menjadi penghubung komunikasi dan relasi dengan pemangku kepentingan eksternal terkait dengan program kegiatan Yayasan Danamon Peduli.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>Keahlian:</strong></u></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Memiliki pengalaman desain menggunakan&nbsp;aplikasi berbasis teknologi &nbsp;terkini sesuai dengan kebutuhan;</li>\n	<li>Memiliki pengalaman dalam menulis konten&nbsp;dan&nbsp;membuat presentasi dengan&nbsp; multi-media sesuai kebutuhan;</li>\n	<li>Memiliki pengalaman membuat dan mengelola manajemen pengetahuan.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>KUALIFIKASI</strong></u></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Gelar universitas dalam bidang pekerjaan yang relevan (Komunikasi, Hubungan Masyarakat, Hubungan Internasional, Jurnalisme);</li>\n	<li>Minimal&nbsp;5&nbsp;tahun pengalaman bekerja di bidang komunikasi;</li>\n	<li>Memiliki&nbsp;pengalaman dan&nbsp;pengetahuan tentang urusan kemanusiaan;</li>\n	<li>Memiliki pengalaman mengembangkan berbagai bahan komunikasi dalam situasi yang rumit dan sulit;</li>\n	<li>Memahami tentang IT yang relevan dengan bidang pekerjaan;</li>\n	<li>Memiliki keterampilan menulis Bahasa Inggris yang sangat baik termasuk pengalaman yang telah terbukti dalam menyusun konten komunikasi yang menarik untuk berbagai saluran komunikasi;</li>\n	<li>Pernah mengikuti pelatihan: kampanye/advokasi, manajemen web, media sosial atau bidang terkait lainnya (Lebih disukai);</li>\n	<li>Berorientasi pada detail, mampu melakukan banyak tugas, seorang pekerja tim.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Lokasi penugasan:&nbsp;</strong>Jakarta</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tanggal bergabung:</strong>&nbsp;Secepatnya</p>\n\n<p><strong>Supervisi Langsung:</strong>&nbsp;Communication and Knowledge Management Manager</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Kandidat yang tertarik&nbsp;untuk lowongan pekerjaan ini wajib&nbsp;menyerahkan:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Surat lamaran&nbsp;(serta info kompensasi yang diharapkan);</li>\n	<li>Curicullum&nbsp;Vitae;</li>\n	<li>Pelatihan yang pernah diikuti;</li>\n	<li>Daftar referensi (wajib).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Ditujukan ke email:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:hrd@danamonpeduli.or.id\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">hrd@danamonpeduli.or.id</a>&nbsp;dengan&nbsp;<strong><u>subject: Communication&nbsp;</u></strong><strong><u>Officer</u></strong></p>\n', '22fcd1465b810e48dd2d4ade24c91282.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-09 08:29:29', '2019-07-10 08:03:59', 5, '-job-vacancy-communication-officer-yayasan-danamon-peduli-', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'ItaI62alQFnpSIF', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Danamon Peduli', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1167, '[JOB VACANCY] Communication Officer - Yayasan Danamon Peduli ', '', 'The Danamon Peduli Foundation opens job vacancies for the position of Communication Officer (Internal and External Communication).', '<p>About the Danamon Peduli Foundation</p>\n\n<p>Danamon Peduli Foundation (Danamon Peduli) is a tangible manifestation of Bank Danamon, Adira Finance and Adira Insurance&#39;s commitment to carrying out corporate social responsibility in a focused and targeted manner. With the vision of &quot;We care and help millions of people to prosper,&quot; Danamon Peduli translates it into pillars and sustainable social investment programs.</p>\n\n<p>In carrying out its corporate duties and social responsibilities, Danamon Peduli also builds partnerships, both with the government, private sector and the general public, including internal employees. All of this is to ensure that our existence continues to provide positive benefits and impacts for the people of Indonesia and help achieve sustainable development goals.</p>\n\n<p>Currently, Danamon Peduli Foundation opens job openings for Communication Officer positions with the required qualifications as follows:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Internal Communication:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Communication and coordination with the Danamon group team for all communication matters of the Danamon Peduli Foundation;</li>\n	<li>Prepare content and layout design for internal communication according to the needs of the Danamon Peduli Foundation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>External Communication:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Communication and coordination with the Danamon group team for external communication;</li>\n	<li>Manage data and content on the Danamon Peduli Foundation website;</li>\n	<li>Compile content for external communication according to the needs of the Danamon Peduli Foundation;</li>\n	<li>Compile content and layout design for Danamon Peduli&#39;s Foundation advertorial media placement;</li>\n	<li>Understanding in the use of social media for communication and advocacy purposes;</li>\n	<li>Become a liaison of communication and relations with external stakeholders related to the activities of the Danamon Peduli Foundation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Expertise:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Have design experience using the latest technology-based applications as needed;</li>\n	<li>Having experience in writing content and making multi-media presentations as needed;</li>\n	<li>Having experience in creating and managing knowledge management.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>QUALIFICATION</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>University degrees in relevant fields of work (Communication, Public Relations, International Relations, Journalism);</li>\n	<li>Minimum 5 years of experience working in the field of communication;</li>\n	<li>Having experienced and knowledge about humanitarian affairs;</li>\n	<li>Having experience developing various communication materials in complicated and difficult situations;</li>\n	<li>Understand about IT that is relevant to the field of work;</li>\n	<li>Excellent writing skills including proven experience in compiling interesting communication content for various communication channels;</li>\n	<li>Ever attended the training: campaign/advocacy, web management, social media or other related fields (Preferably);</li>\n	<li>Detail-oriented, capable of many tasks, a team worker.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Assignment location: </strong>Jakarta</p>\n\n<p><strong>Join date:</strong> As soon as possible</p>\n\n<p><strong>Direct Supervision: </strong>Communication and Knowledge Management Manager</p>\n\n<p><strong>Candidates who are interested in this job opening must submit:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Cover letter (as well as info on expected compensation);</li>\n	<li>Curriculum Vitae;</li>\n	<li>Training ever attended;</li>\n	<li>Reference list (required).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Intended to email</strong>: hrd@danamonpeduli.or.id with subject:<strong> Communication Officer</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>For the attention and cooperation given, we thank you</p>\n\n<p>.</p>\n\n<p>.</p>\n\n<p>Human Resources Department - Danamon Peduli Foundation</p>\n', '22fcd1465b810e48dd2d4ade24c91282.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-09 08:29:29', '2019-07-10 08:03:59', 5, '-job-vacancy-communication-officer-yayasan-danamon-peduli-', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '0o081X3mVFElsdf', 'ItaI62alQFnpSIF', 'N', '', 'Yayasan Danamon Peduli', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1168, 'PSSF 6: Pelatihan Keterampilan Fasilitasi Forum ', '', 'PSSF (Philanthropy SkillShare Forum) ke-6: Pelatihan Keterampilan Forum ', '<p>Filantropi Indonesia akan menyelenggarakan Philanthropy Skill Share Forum ke-6 berjudul &quot;Pelatihan Keterampilan Fasilitasi Forum&quot;.&nbsp;<br />\nTema ini bertujuan untuk:<br />\n1. Mengenal konsep-konsep kunci dan kompetensi dasar fasilitasi untuk bisa merancang dan menjalankan fasilitasi forum.<br />\n2. Mempersiapkan dan mengeksekusi sesi fasilitasi dan mendapatkan umpan balik bagi pengembangan berikutnya.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nKami percaya bahwa tema tersebut sangat bermanfaat bagi organisasi dalam rangka membekali SDM organisasi dengan ketrampilan fasilitasi forum, baik di lingkungan internal atau eksternal.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\n<strong>Pelatihan akan dilaksanakan pada:</strong></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hari/Tanggal &nbsp; : Rabu - Kamis, 10 - 11 Juli 2019</p>\n\n<p>Waktu &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : 09.00 - 15.00 WIB</p>\n\n<p>Tempat &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Filantropi Indonesia, Jl. Gunung Sahari VI No. 38, Jakarta 10720</p>\n\n<p>Narasumber&nbsp; &nbsp;: Rahmi Yunita (Senior fasilitator, founder Sala Sinau Esensia)</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong><u>Biaya investasi:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Anggota Filantropi Indonesia &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : Rp 375.000/peserta.</li>\n	<li>Non-Anggota Filantropi Indonesia : Rp 750.000/peserta.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Acara terbatas untuk&nbsp;<strong>20 peserta</strong>. Pendaftaran akan ditutup jika kuota terpenuhi.<br />\n<br />\n<strong><u>Pendaftaran:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Mengisi form registrasi di:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF6\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF6</a></li>\n	<li>Membayar biaya training ke Bank BRI 111.901.000.208.307 KCP Tomang atas nama Perhimpunan Filantropi Indonesia.</li>\n	<li>Mengirimkan bukti pembayaran ke email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:dinda@filantropi.or.id\" target=\"_blank\">dinda@filantropi.or.id</a>&nbsp;beserta nama dan organisasi.</li>\n</ol>\n', '2b427210766883f1125553b7c1658221.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-15 01:20:29', '2019-07-15 08:20:29', 5, 'pssf-6-pelatihan-keterampilan-fasilitasi-forum-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'JpdpMAKmzApm8mg', 'N', '', '', '2019-07-10 00:00:00', '2019-07-11 23:59:59'),
(1169, 'PSSF 6: Pelatihan Keterampilan Fasilitasi Forum ', '', '', '', '2b427210766883f1125553b7c1658221.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-15 01:20:29', '2019-07-15 08:20:29', 5, 'pssf-6-pelatihan-keterampilan-fasilitasi-forum-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'JpdpMAKmzApm8mg', 'N', '', '', '2019-07-10 00:00:00', '2019-07-11 23:59:59'),
(1170, 'PSSF 7: GO-PAY Philanthropy Workshop', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia bersama dengan GO-PAY for GOOD akan menyelenggarakan GO-PAY Philanthropy Workshop dengan tema Strategi Marketing Kreatif Pada Era Donasi Digital.', '<p>Filantropi Indonesia bersama dengan GO-PAY for GOOD akan menyelenggarakan&nbsp;<strong>GO-PAY Philanthropy Workshop</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>dengan tema&nbsp;<strong>Strategi Marketing Kreatif Pada Era Donasi Digital&nbsp;</strong>yang akan dilaksanakan pada:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hari/tanggal&nbsp; : Selasa, 16 Juli 2019&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Pukul&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; : 13.00 - 16.00 WIB</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Tempat&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;: Auditorium GO-LEARN, GO-JEK Head Quarter Lt. 7, Pasaraya Blok M, Jl. Iskandarsyah II No. 7, Jakarta 12160</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Kami mengundang lembaga Bapak yang telah memiliki QR Code GO-PAY for GOOD untuk mengikuti pelatihan ini guna memaksimalkan pemanfaatan platform tersebut. Jika Bapak ingin mengikuti pelatihan ini, sila mengisi form pendaftaran di&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF7\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/DAFTARPSSF7</a>&nbsp;dimana satu lembaga dapat diwakilkan oleh 2 perwakilan.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note: Acara ini khusus untuk anggota Filantropi Indonesia yang telah memiliki QR Code GO-PAY</strong></p>\n', '8a22191fc6d73a4bc0cf9f1624b1ce71.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-15 01:23:01', '2019-07-15 08:23:01', 5, 'pssf-7-go-pay-philanthropy-workshop', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'Myii7SfEQ4NNWJ0', 'N', '', '', '2019-07-16 00:00:00', '2019-07-16 23:59:59'),
(1171, 'PSSF 7: GO-PAY Philanthropy Workshop', '', '', '', '8a22191fc6d73a4bc0cf9f1624b1ce71.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-15 01:23:01', '2019-07-15 08:23:01', 5, 'pssf-7-go-pay-philanthropy-workshop', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'Myii7SfEQ4NNWJ0', 'N', '', '', '2019-07-16 00:00:00', '2019-07-16 23:59:59'),
(1172, 'Erna Witoelar Mendapatkan Gelar Doktor Kehormatan dari Griffith University Australia', '', 'Pada Selasa, 23 Juli 2019 lalu, Erna Witoelar, Co-Chair Badan Pengarah Filantropi Indonesia, mendapatkan gelar doktor kehormatan dari Griffith University dalam sebuah upacara resmi yang dilaksanakan di Brisbane, Australia. ', '<p>Pada Selasa, 23 Juli 2019 lalu, Erna Witoelar, Co-Chair Badan Pengarah Filantropi Indonesia, mendapatkan gelar doktor kehormatan dari Griffith University dalam sebuah upacara resmi yang dilaksanakan di Brisbane, Australia. Profesor Carolyn Evans, Wakil Rektor Griffith University, mengatakan dalam pidatonya bahwa Erna Witoelar adalah seorang pelopor internasional dalam bidang pembangunan berkelanjutan dan seorang pejuang masyarakat sipil yang menyampaikan pandangan kritis kepada berbagai komunitas di Kawasan Asia-Pasifik yang menggerakan perubahan global.</p>\n\n<p>Keterlibatan Erna Witoelar di universitas Australia dimulai sejak 13 tahun lalu ketika mempromosikan Piagam Bumi di Brisbane. Beberapa kunjungan kerap dilakukan oleh Erna Witoelar ke Griffith University sebagai Duta Besar Khusus PBB untuk MDGs (Tujuan Pembangunan Milenium) di Asia dan Pasifik kala itu. Menurut catatan konsul Hermanus Dimara dari KJRI Sydney, Erna Witoelar adalah penerima gelar doktor kehormatan pertama dalam tiga tahun terakhir di wilayah New South Wales, Queensland dan Australia Selatan.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'bd26122e601ff4d69cd77631d0aecc2d.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-24 07:08:41', '2019-07-24 14:08:41', 5, 'erna-witoelar-mendapatkan-gelar-doktor-kehormatan-dari-griffith-university-australia', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '9HtChVy49TB9B34', 'N', '', 'Istimewa', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1173, 'Erna Witoelar Received Honorary Doctorate Degree from Griffith University in Australia ', '', 'On July 23, 2019, Erna Witoelar, Co-Chair of Filantropi Indonesia, received Honorary Doctorate Degree from Griffith University in Australia. ', '<p>On July 23, 2019, Erna Witoelar, Co-Chair of Filantropi Indonesia, received Honorary Doctorate Degree from Griffith University in an official event that held in Brisbane, Australia. Professor Carolyn Evans, Vice Chancellor of Griffith University, says&nbsp;that Erna Witoelar&nbsp;is&nbsp;an international pioneer in&nbsp;sustainable development and a civil society fighter who conveys critical views to various communities in the Asia-Pacific Region that drive global change.</p>\n\n<p>Erna Witoelar&#39;s involvement in&nbsp;&nbsp;Australian universities&nbsp;began 13 years ago when promoting the Earth Charter in Brisbane. Several visits were often made by Erna Witoelar to Griffith University as the UN Special Ambassador to the MDGs (Millennium Development Goals) in Asia and the Pacific at that time. According to the consul Hermanus Dimara records from the Consulate General in Sydney, Erna Witoelar was the first recipient of honorary doctorate degree&nbsp;in the last three years in the New South Wales, Queensland and South Australia regions.</p>\n', 'bd26122e601ff4d69cd77631d0aecc2d.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-07-24 07:08:41', '2019-07-24 14:08:41', 5, 'erna-witoelar-received-honorary-doctorate-degree-from-griffith-university-in-australia-', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', '9HtChVy49TB9B34', 'N', '', 'Istimewa', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1174, 'Artikel Suzanty Sitorus yang Berjudul \"Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy\" dimuat pada Website Philanthropy In Focus (WINGS)', '', 'Artikel yang berjudul \"Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy\" menjelaskan tentang beberapa tahun terakhir, trend generasi kedua dan ketiga beberapa yayasan keluarga yang telah berdiri dari perusahaan bisnis memisahkan antara kepentingan yayasan keluarga dan CSR perusahaan serta merekrut orang yang profesional di bidang filantropis untuk menjalankan yayasannya.', '<p>Artikel yang berjudul <a href=\"https://philanthropyinfocus.org/2019/07/31/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" target=\"_self\"><em>&quot;Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy&quot;&nbsp;</em></a>menjelaskan tentang beberapa tahun terakhir, trend generasi kedua dan ketiga beberapa yayasan keluarga yang telah berdiri dari perusahaan bisnis memisahkan antara kepentingan yayasan keluarga dan CSR perusahaan serta merekrut orang yang profesional di bidang filantropis untuk menjalankan yayasannya. Hal ini juga didasarkan kepada program yayasan yang diselaraskan dengan nilai&nbsp;Tujuan Pembangunan Berkelanjutan (SDGs) sehingga memberi kesempatan untuk bekerja pada isu-isu mendasar&nbsp;dan berkolaborasi dengan pemangku kepentingan lainnya.<br />\n<br />\nParagraf diatas menjadi sorotan utama&nbsp;yang dituliskan oleh Suzanty Sitorus,&nbsp;yang juga menjadi salah satu bagian dari Badan Pengurus Filantropi Indonesia. Artikel tersebut&nbsp;telah dimuat dalam website <a href=\"https://philanthropyinfocus.org/\" target=\"_self\"><em>Philanthropy In Focus</em></a> milik WINGS (<em>Worldwide Initiatives for Grantmaker Support</em>) pada 31 Juli 2019 yang lalu. Selain itu, <a href=\"https://www.alliancemagazine.org/blog/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\">Alliance <em>Magazine</em></a>&nbsp;dan&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://www.givingcompass.org/article/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\">Giving Compass</a>&nbsp;</em>kembali menyadur artikel yang terlah diterbitkan. Anda dapat dapat membaca artikel secara lengkapnya di:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://philanthropyinfocus.org/2019/07/31/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\"><em>&quot;Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy&quot; </em>- WINGS</a>.</p>\n', '0bb54815f5b27d37ecc1233de44ef3a9.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-04 04:05:41', '2019-09-04 11:05:41', 5, 'artikel-suzanty-sitorus-yang-berjudul-guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy-dimuat-pada-website-philanthropy-in-focus-wings-', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'ytWyExCDhZd8E8E', 'N', '', 'https://philanthropyinfocus.org/201', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `cd_posts` (`posts_uid`, `posts_title`, `posts_subtitle`, `posts_shortdesc`, `posts_content`, `posts_images`, `posts_link`, `posts_sort`, `posts_status`, `posts_visibility`, `posts_date`, `posts_modified`, `posts_author`, `posts_slug`, `posts_type`, `posts_comments`, `posts_reads`, `posts_lang`, `posts_file`, `posts_meta_title`, `posts_meta_desc`, `posts_tags`, `posts_category`, `posts_lock_code`, `posts_locked`, `posts_parent`, `posts_source`, `posts_start_date`, `posts_end_date`) VALUES
(1175, 'Suzanty Sitorus\'s Article entitled \"Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy\" is Published on the Philanthropy In Focus (WINGS) Website', '', 'The article entitled \"Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy\" describes the past few years, the second and third generation trends of several family foundations that have been established from business companies separating the interests of family foundations and corporate CSR and recruiting people who are professionals in the philanthropic to run their foundations.', '<p>The article entitled <a href=\"http://philanthropyinfocus.org/2019/07/31/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" target=\"_self\">&quot;Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy&quot;</a> describes the past few years, the second and third generation trends of several family foundations that have been established from business companies separating the interests of family foundations and corporate CSR and recruiting people who are professionals in the philanthropic&nbsp;to run their foundations. It is also based on foundation programs that are aligned with the values ??of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) so as to provide opportunities to work on fundamental issues and collaborate with other stakeholders.</p>\n\n<p>The above paragraph is the main highlight written by Suzanty Sitorus, who is also one of the Board&nbsp;Management of Indonesia&nbsp;Philanthropy.&nbsp;The article was posted on the WINGS (Worldwide Initiatives for Grantmaker Support) <a href=\"http://philanthropyinfocus.org/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\">Philanthropy In Focus</a> website on July 31, 2019.&nbsp;In addition, <a href=\"http://www.alliancemagazine.org/blog/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\">Alliance Magazine</a> and <a href=\"http://www.givingcompass.org/article/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\">Giving Compass</a> re-adapt articles that have been published. You can read the full article at: <a href=\"http://philanthropyinfocus.org/2019/07/31/guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy/\" onclick=\"window.open(this.href, \'\', \'resizable=yes,status=yes,location=no,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=yes,dependent=no\'); return false;\">&quot;Guiding Family Foundations for Effective Philanthropy&quot; - WINGS</a>.</p>\n', '0bb54815f5b27d37ecc1233de44ef3a9.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-04 04:05:41', '2019-09-04 11:05:41', 5, 'suzanty-sitorus-s-article-entitled-guiding-family-foundations-for-effective-philanthropy-is-published-on-the-philanthropy-in-focus-wings-website', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'ytWyExCDhZd8E8E', 'N', '', 'https://philanthropyinfocus.org/201', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1176, 'Alliance Magazine September 2019: Human Rights Philanthropy', '', '', '', '1ad5d0703dfbdd3d8ae19fd84dd4c614.png', '', 0, 'N', 'M', '2019-09-04 04:58:14', '2019-09-04 11:59:12', 5, 'alliance-magazine-september-2019-human-rights-philanthropy', 'download', 0, '', 'id', 'Human_Rights_Philanthropy_September-2019.pdf', '', '', '', 'Uej408Ieo348054', 'acKGr5beEnmOyxm', 'Y', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1177, 'Alliance Magazine September 2019: Human Rights Philanthropy', '', '', '', '1ad5d0703dfbdd3d8ae19fd84dd4c614.png', '', 0, 'N', 'M', '2019-09-04 04:58:14', '2019-09-04 11:59:12', 5, 'alliance-magazine-september-2019-human-rights-philanthropy', 'download', 0, '', 'en', 'Human_Rights_Philanthropy_September-2019.pdf', '', '', '', 'Uej408Ieo348054', 'acKGr5beEnmOyxm', 'Y', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1178, 'Kick Off Meeting &quot;PEDOELI INDONESIA&quot;', '', 'Jumat (30/8) lalu, Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan Kick Off Meeting bersama berbagai platform crowdfunding yang ada di Indonesia. Kick Off Meeting ini merupakan bagian dari acara sosialisasi \"PEDOELI INDONESIA\" (Pekan Donasi Online Indonesia), sebuah program kampanye dan aksi penggalangan donasi online nasional yang melibatkan berbagai lembaga filantropi, perusahaan, dan publik untuk membantu mengatasi masalah sosial di Indonesia.', '<p>Jumat (30/8) lalu, Filantropi Indonesia mengadakan <em>Kick Off Meeting</em> bersama berbagai platform crowdfunding yang ada di Indonesia. <em>Kick Off Meeting</em> ini merupakan bagian dari acara sosialisasi &quot;<strong>PEDOELI INDONESIA</strong>&quot;&nbsp;(<em>Pekan Donasi Online Indonesia</em>), sebuah program kampanye dan aksi penggalangan donasi online nasional yang melibatkan berbagai lembaga filantropi, perusahaan, dan publik untuk membantu mengatasi masalah sosial di Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p>Dari 69 organisasi, ada 13 organisasi anggota Filantropi Indonesia yang mempunyai platform <em>crowdfunding</em>, yaitu <strong>Sharing Happiness, Bawa Berkah, Solusi Peduli, Bee Happy, Peduli Sehat Gotong Royong, LAZ Harfa, Badan Wakaf AlQuran, BAZNAS, Meraih Mimpi &ndash; Wahana Visi Indonesia, LazisMU, NU Care, Insan Bumi Mandiri, dan Cepat Tanggap</strong>. Melalui program PEDOELI INDONESIA, Filantropi Indonesia ingin mengajak para anggotanya untuk bersinergi dan berkolaborasi dalam meningkatkan keterlibatan masyarakat, khususnya kaum muda, dalam kegiatan filantropi dan inisiatif sosial melalui pemanfaatan platform digital.</p>\n\n<p>Banyak gagasan dan umpan balik yang diterima Filantropi Indonesia dalam rapat perdana ini, salah satunya adalah pembuatan &lsquo;<em>landing page</em>&rsquo; bersama yang dapat memudahkan organisasi peserta PEDOELI INDONESIA dan calon donatur untuk mendapatkan informasi tentang program yang dapat disumbang.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Program PEDOELI INDONESIA ini juga mendapatkan dukungan dari GO-PAY, sebagai salah satu <em>provider</em> penyedia uang digital di Indonesia. Hal ini sesuai dengan komitmen GO-PAY dan Filantropi Indonesia dalam kerangka kemitraan strategis GO-PAY FOR GOOD untuk mendukung peningkatan kapasitas anggota Filantropi Indonesia.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Selanjutnya, setelah <em>Kick Off Meeting</em> bersama 13 crowdfunding anggota Filantropi Indonesia, akan berlangsung pertemuan bersama anggota Filantropi Indonesia dalam&nbsp;<em>partnership gathering</em>, untuk menjaring dukungan yang lebih luas dalam pelaksanaan <strong>NEXT GENEROUSion FEST&nbsp;&ndash; Festival Filantrop Muda 2019</strong>, sebuah festival yang bertujuan mempromosikan berbagai kegiatan filantropi dan inisiatif sosial kaum muda sekaligus menginspirasi dan mendorong mereka untuk lebih peduli dan terlibat dalam berbagai kegiatan sosial.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>PantauInfo detail mengenai NEXT GENEROUSion FEST&nbsp;&ndash; Festival Filantrop Muda 2019 dan PEDOELI INDONESIA</strong> <strong>dapat dilihat di platform sosial media Instagram</strong> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nextgenerousionfest/\" target=\"_blank\">@nextgenerousionfest</a>.</p>\n', '1eac5f917c49a95275e5edc4b9bafe59.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:03:13', '2019-09-05 15:03:13', 5, 'kick-off-meeting-pedoeli-indonesia-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'AqxQZfrQS1U2kqM', 'N', '', '', '2019-08-30 00:00:00', '2019-08-30 23:59:59'),
(1179, 'Kick Off Meeting &quot;PEDOELI INDONESIA&quot;', '', 'Last Friday (8/30), Indonesian Philanthropy Association held a Kick-Off Meeting with various crowdfunding platforms in Indonesia. This Kick-Off Meeting is part of the socialization event \"PEDOELI INDONESIA\" (Indonesian Online Donation Week), a national online campaign and donation drive program involving various philanthropic institutions, companies and the public to help overcome social problems in Indonesia.', '<p>Last Friday (8/30), Indonesian Philanthropy Association held a Kick-Off Meeting with various crowdfunding platforms in Indonesia. This Kick-Off Meeting is part of the socialization event &quot;PEDOELI INDONESIA&quot; (Indonesian Online Donation Week), a national online campaign and donation drive program involving various philanthropic institutions, companies and the public to help overcome social problems in Indonesia.</p>\n\n<p>Out of 69 organizations, there are 13 Indonesian Philanthropy Association&#39;s member organizations that have crowdfunding platforms, namely&nbsp;<strong>Sharing Happiness, Bawa Berkah, Solusi Peduli, Bee Happy, Peduli Sehat Gotong Royong, LAZ Harfa, Badan Wakaf AlQuran, BAZNAS, Meraih Mimpi &ndash; Wahana Visi Indonesia, LazisMU, NU Care, Insan Bumi Mandiri, and&nbsp;Cepat Tanggap</strong>. Through the PEDOELI INDONESIA program, Indonesian Philanthropy Association wants to invite its members to work together and collaborate in increasing community involvement, especially young people, in philanthropic activities and social initiatives through the use of digital platforms.</p>\n\n<p>Many ideas and feedback were received by Indonesian Philanthropy Association in this inaugural meeting, one of which was the creation of a joint &#39;landing page&#39; that could facilitate the organizations of PEDOELI INDONESIA participants and potential donors to obtain information about programs that could be contributed.</p>\n\n<p>The INDONESIA PEDOELI program also received support from GO-PAY, as one of the providers of digital money providers in Indonesia. This is in line with the commitment of GO-PAY and Indonesian Philanthropy Association within the framework of the GO-PAY FOR GOOD strategic partnership to support capacity building for Indonesian Philanthropy Association members.</p>\n\n<p>Furthermore, after the Kick-Off Meeting with 13 crowdfunding members of the Indonesian Philanthropy Association, a meeting will take place with other members in&nbsp;a partnership gathering, to reach&nbsp;support in the implementation of the <strong>NEXT GENEROUSion FEST -&nbsp;Young Philanthropy Festival 2019</strong>, a festival aimed at promoting various philanthropic activities and social initiatives of young people at the same time inspire and encourage them to be more concerned and involved in various social activities.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Check for&nbsp;detail&nbsp;information about NEXT GENEROUSion FEST -&nbsp;Young Philanthropy Festival 2019 and PEDOELI INDONESIA can be seen on the Instagram</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nextgenerousionfest/\" target=\"_blank\">@nextgenerousionfest</a>.</p>\n', '1eac5f917c49a95275e5edc4b9bafe59.jpeg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:03:13', '2019-09-05 15:03:13', 5, 'kick-off-meeting-pedoeli-indonesia-', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'AqxQZfrQS1U2kqM', 'N', '', '', '2019-08-30 00:00:00', '2019-08-30 23:59:59'),
(1180, 'Perkuat Database dan Transparasi, Filantropi Indonesia Jalin Kemitraan dengan Filantropi Cina', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia (FI) menjalin kemitraan dengan beberapa asosiasi dan lembaga filantropi di Cina untuk pengembangan real time database dan indeks transparansi lembaga filantropi. Dua instrumen tersebut dinilai sebagai perangkat modern dalam memperkuat transparansi dan akuntabilitas filantropi di berbagai negara, termasuk di Cina. Karena itu, Filantropi Indonesia bersama dengan BAZNAS (Badan Amil Zakat Nasional) dengan dukungan dari Ford Foundation melakukan kunjungan ke Cina pada 13 – 16 Agustus 2019 dan mengkaji pengembangan real time database dan Foundation Transparancy Index (FTI) di China Foundation Center (CFC).', '<p>Filantropi Indonesia (FI) menjalin kemitraan dengan beberapa asosiasi dan lembaga filantropi di Cina untuk pengembangan <em>real-time database</em> dan indeks transparansi lembaga filantropi. Dua instrumen tersebut dinilai sebagai perangkat modern dalam memperkuat transparansi dan akuntabilitas filantropi di berbagai negara, termasuk di Cina. Karena itu, <strong>Filantropi Indonesia bersama dengan BAZNAS (Badan Amil Zakat Nasional) dengan dukungan dari Ford Foundation melakukan kunjungan ke Cina pada 13-16 Agustus 2019 dan mengkaji pengembangan <em>real-time database</em> dan <em>Foundation Transparancy Index</em> (FTI) di China Foundation Center (CFC)</strong>. <em>Foundation Transparancy Index</em> sudah diakui dan menjadi rujukan bagi lembaga-lembaga filantropi Cina dan filantropi global sebagai salah satu solusi inovatif dan standar baru dalam mendorong dan meningkatkan transparansi lembaga-lembaga filantropi.</p>\n\n<p>Hamid Abidin, Direktur Eksekutif Filantropi Indonesia, menjelaskan bahwa FTI merupakan sistem database lembaga filantropi yang dibangun untuk memberikan layanan informasi berbasis online secara <em>real-time</em> kepada publik mengenai lembaga filantropi di Cina berikut program dan laporan keuangannya. CFC sebagai pengelola FTI mengumpulkan informasi tersebut dari laporan yayasan yang disampaikan di situs organisasinya dan laporan yang disampaikan kepada pemerintah. Dari informasi-informasi inilah, FTI kemudian melakukan pemeringkatan berdasarkan indikator yang sudah ditetapkan untuk menentukan posisi dan peringkat yayasan tersebut. FTI memiliki 40 indikator transparansi yang dikelompokkan dalam 4 katagori: informasi dasar organisasi, informasi program/proyek, informasi keuangan dan informasi donor. Posisi dan peringkat yayasan di FTI bersifat dinamis bergantung pada seberapa lengkap data yang mereka sampaikan ke publik.</p>\n\n<p>Selain belajar tentang pengembangan data base dan FTI di CFC, Filantropi Indonesia juga berkunjung ke beberapa asosiasi dan lembaga filantropi di Cina untuk berbagi informasi dan menjalin kemitraan. <strong>Beberapa lembaga yang dikunjungi adalah CCA (China Charity Alliance), China Global Filantropi Institute, Tanoto Foundation Beijing, dan Ford Foundation Cina</strong>. Melalui kunjungan ini, Filantropi Indonesia&nbsp;berbagi sekaligus menyerap banyak informasi dan inspirasi yang diharapkan bisa jadi rujukan dalam pengembangan filantropi di Indonesia. &ldquo;Indonesia dan Cina memiliki banyak kesamaan dalam hal kebijakan dan kultur filantropi sehingga ada banyak gagasan dan inisiatif yang bisa diadaptasi, tentu melalui penyesuaian dengan kultur dan konteks filantropi Indonesia,&rdquo; kata Hamid.</p>\n\n<p>Cina dikenal sebagai salah satu negara yang kegiatan filantropinya berkembang sangat pesat dalam sepuluh tahun terakhir. Di negara tirai bambu yang dikenal sangat tertutup ini, sektor filantropi baru tumbuh pada tahun 2008 yang dipicu oleh terjadinya gempa bumi dahsyat di wilayah Wenchuan. Bencana nasional itu dinilai sebagai momentum kebangkitan filantropi Cina yang menggerakkan ribuan inisiatif penggalangan dan penyaluran sumbangan oleh berbagai yayasan, sebuah fenomena yang belum ada sebelumnya. Perkembangan Filantropi Cina mencapai puncaknya pada tahun 2016 seiring dengan diterbitkannya <em>China Charity Law</em> sebagai regulasi yang mendorong dan memfasilitasi perkembangan filantropi di Cina. Sejak regulasi tersebut dirilis, pertumbuhan lembaga filantropi mengalami kenaikan yang fantastis dengan rata rata pertumbuhan 64,9% per tahun. Sampai tahun 2018 di Cina sudah berdiri lebih dari 800.000 organisasi sosial dan 7.333 diantaranya merupakan yayasan amal/filantropi. Total aset organisasi filantropi di Tiongkok diperkirakan mencapai RMB 60,4 Milyar dengan perolehan donasi RMB 33,7 M per tahun dan penyaluran hibah mencapai RMB 25,6 Milyar per tahun. Kini beberapa lembaga filantropi Cina sudah bermetamorfosis menjadi yayasan filantropi global yang tidak hanya memberikan dukungan hibah dan layanan sosial untuk warga Cina, tapi masyarakat di belahan bumi lainnya.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Perkembangan filantropi yang cukup fantastis di Cina bisa jadi inspirasi, model dan <em>bench marking</em> dalam pengembangan filantropi di Indonesia melalui pengembangan regulasi yang kondusif dan instrumen transparansi inovatif&rdquo; kata Hamid.</p>\n', 'cfd2bae39e65d6d1be3ab33cc7172da4.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:21:18', '2019-09-05 15:21:18', 5, 'perkuat-database-dan-transparasi-filantropi-indonesia-jalin-kemitraan-dengan-filantropi-cina', 'news', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'YnWjw9sliV9RIQ2', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1181, 'Strengthening Databases and Transparency, Indonesian Philanthropy Association Establishes Partnership with Chinese Philanthropy', '', 'Indonesian Philanthropy Association (FI) has formed partnerships with several philanthropic associations and institutions in China for the development of a real-time database and transparency index for philanthropic institutions. The two instruments are considered as modern tools in strengthening the transparency and accountability of philanthropy in various countries, including in China. Therefore, Indonesian Philanthropy Association together with BAZNAS (National Amil Zakat Agency) with support from the Ford Foundation visited China on August 13-16, 2019 and examined the development of the real-time database and Foundation Transparency Index (FTI) at the China Foundation Center (CFC).', '<p>Indonesian Philanthropy Association (FI) has formed partnerships with several philanthropic associations and institutions in China for the development of a real-time database and transparency index for philanthropic institutions. The two instruments are considered as modern tools in strengthening the transparency and accountability of philanthropy in various countries, including in China. Therefore, Indonesian Philanthropy Association together with BAZNAS (National Amil Zakat Agency) with support from the Ford Foundation visited China on August 13-16, 2019 and examined the development of the real-time database and Foundation Transparency Index (FTI) at the China Foundation Center (CFC). The Foundation Transparency Index has been recognized and is a reference for Chinese philanthropic institutions and global philanthropy as one of the innovative solutions and new standards in encouraging and increasing the transparency of philanthropic institutions.</p>\n\n<p>Hamid Abidin, Executive Director of FI, explained that FTI is a database system of philanthropic institutions that were built to provide real-time, online-based information services to the public about philanthropic institutions in China and their financial statements and programs. CFC as the manager of FTI collects this information from the foundation&#39;s report submitted on the organization&#39;s website and the report submitted to the government. From this information, FTI then ranks based on indicators that have been determined to determine the position and rank of the foundation. FTI has 40 transparency indicators that are grouped into 4 categories: basic organizational information, program/project information, financial information, and donor information. The position and ranking of foundations in FTI are dynamic depending on how complete the data they are conveying to the public.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to learning about developing a database and FTI at CFC, FI also visited several associations and philanthropic institutions in China to share information and establish partnerships. Some of the institutions visited were CCA (China Charity Alliance), China Global Philanthropy Institute, Beijing Tanoto Foundation, and Ford Foundation of China. Through this visit, FI shared and received&nbsp;a lot of information and inspiration that was hoped to be a reference in developing philanthropy in Indonesia. &quot;Indonesia and China have many similarities in terms of philanthropic policy and culture so that there are many ideas and initiatives that can be adapted, of course through adjustments to the culture and context of Indonesian philanthropy,&quot; Hamid said.</p>\n\n<p>China is known as one of the countries whose philanthropic activities have developed very rapidly in the last ten years. In this bamboo curtain country which is known to be very closed, the philanthropic sector only grew in 2008 triggered by a devastating earthquake in the Wenchuan region. The national disaster was considered as the momentum of the rise of Chinese philanthropy that has driven thousands of initiatives to raise and distribute donations by various foundations, a phenomenon that has not existed before. The development of Chinese Philanthropy reached its peak in 2016 along with the issuance of China Charity Law as a regulation that encourages and facilitates the development of philanthropy in China. Since the regulation was released, the growth of philanthropic institutions has increased fantastically with an average growth of 64.9% per year. Until 2018 in China there were already more than 800,000 social organizations and 7,333 of them were charitable/philanthropic foundations. The total assets of philanthropic organizations in China are estimated at RMB 60.4 billion with the acquisition of RMB 33.7 billion per year and the distribution of grants reaching RMB 25.6 billion per year. Now some Chinese philanthropic institutions have metamorphosed into a global philanthropic foundation that not only provides grant support and social services for Chinese citizens but people in other parts of the world.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;The development of philanthropy which is quite fantastic in China can be an inspiration, model and benchmarking in developing philanthropy in Indonesia through the development of conducive regulations and innovative transparency instruments,&quot; Hamid said.</p>\n', 'cfd2bae39e65d6d1be3ab33cc7172da4.jpg', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:21:18', '2019-09-05 15:21:18', 5, 'strengthening-databases-and-transparency-indonesian-philanthropy-association-establishes-partnership-with-chinese-philanthropy', 'news', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', 'heQTxv0tauYmEjY', 'YnWjw9sliV9RIQ2', 'N', '', 'Internal', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1182, 'NEXT GENEROUSion FEST ', '', 'Festival Filantrop Muda merupakan sebuah festival yang bertujuan mempromosikan berbagai kegiatan filantropi dan inisiatif sosial kaum muda sekaligus menginspirasi dan mendorong mereka untuk lebih peduli dan terlibat dalam berbagai kegiatan sosial.', '<p><strong>Festival Filantrop Muda</strong> merupakan sebuah festival yang bertujuan mempromosikan berbagai kegiatan filantropi dan inisiatif sosial kaum muda sekaligus menginspirasi dan mendorong mereka untuk lebih peduli dan terlibat dalam berbagai kegiatan sosial. Acara ini terdiri dari berbagai aktivitas, seperti: <em>Selasar Filantrop Muda (pameran/marketplace), Panggung Inspirasi Filantropi, Bedah Aksi dan Solusi, Digital Fundraising Campaign, Pojok Donasi, dan Pemberian Penghargaan (awards) untuk Filantrop Muda Indonesia</em>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>&quot;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/NGF-2019\" target=\"_self\">NEXT GENEROUSion FEST</a>&quot;</strong>&nbsp;dengan tema &ldquo;<em><u>Muda</u>, <u>Peduli</u>, <u>Memberi Solusi</u></em>&rdquo; ini <strong>akan diselenggarakan pada Sabtu dan Minggu, 2&ndash;3 November 2019 di Epiwalk Epicentrum Kuningan Jakarta</strong>. Festival ini akan diikuti oleh komunitas filantropi anak muda, yayasan/organisasi filantropi, organisasi nirlaba, perusahaan, serta kementerian/komisi/badan negara yang mendukung inisiatif sosial anak muda. Festival ini menargetkan 10.000 pengunjung/partisipan dari kalangan pelajar (SMP/SMA), mahasiswa, dan profesional muda, dan masyarakat umum.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Pantau terus dan follow sosial media&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nextgenerousionfest/\" target=\"_blank\">NEXT GENEROUSion FEST</a> di Instagram untuk info terbarunya!</strong></p>\n', '0f8f02268d1dd296aefa60b203ca3398.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:47:12', '2019-09-05 15:59:31', 5, 'next-generousion-fest-', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'wUSxLJRAkAtOhsd', 'N', '', '', '2019-11-02 00:00:00', '2019-11-03 23:59:59'),
(1183, 'NEXT GENEROUSion FEST', '', 'Festival Filantrop Muda is a festival that aims to promote various philanthropic activities and social initiatives of young people while simultaneously inspiring and encouraging them to be more concerned and involved in various social activities.', '<p><strong>Festival Filantrop Muda</strong> is a festival that aims to promote various philanthropic activities and social initiatives of young people while simultaneously inspiring and encouraging them to be more concerned and involved in various social activities. This program consists of various activities, such as <em>Selasar Muda Philanthropy (exhibition/marketplace), Philanthropic Inspiration Stage, Surgery for Action and Solutions, Digital Fundraising Campaign, Donation Corner, and Awarding for Young Indonesian Philanthropists</em>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>&quot;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/NGF-2019\" target=\"_blank\">NEXT GENEROUSion FEST</a></strong>&quot; with the theme &quot;<em><u>Young</u></em>, <u><em>Caring</em></u>, <em><u>Providing Solutions</u></em>&quot; <strong>will be held on Saturday and Sunday, November 2-3 - 2019 at Epiwalk Epicentrum Kuningan Jakarta</strong>. This festival will be participated by the philanthropic community of young people, philanthropic foundations/organizations, non-profit organizations, companies, and ministries/commissions/state agencies that support youth social initiatives. The festival targets 10,000 visitors/participants from among students (junior / senior high school), students, and young professionals, and the general public.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Stay tuned and follow social media <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nextgenerousionfest/\" target=\"_blank\">NEXT GENERATion FEST</a> on Instagram for the latest info!</strong></p>\n', '0f8f02268d1dd296aefa60b203ca3398.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:47:12', '2019-09-05 15:59:31', 5, 'next-generousion-fest', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'wUSxLJRAkAtOhsd', 'N', '', '', '2019-11-02 00:00:00', '2019-11-03 23:59:59'),
(1184, 'NEXT GENEROUSion FEST', '', 'Festival Filantrop Muda merupakan sebuah festival yang bertujuan mempromosikan berbagai kegiatan filantropi dan inisiatif sosial kaum muda sekaligus menginspirasi dan mendorong mereka untuk lebih peduli dan terlibat dalam berbagai kegiatan sosial', '', 'bd38082c5101cf658e463dda94ea7f97.png', 'http://filantropi.or.id/acara/d/next-generousion-fest-', 9, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:54:28', '2019-09-05 15:54:28', 5, '', 'slider', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'gDLlt4TupSKEhEo', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1185, 'NEXT GENEROUSion FEST', '', 'Festival Filantrop Muda is a festival that aims to promote various philanthropic activities and social initiatives of young people while simultaneously inspiring and encouraging them to be more concerned and involved in various social activities.', '', 'bd38082c5101cf658e463dda94ea7f97.png', 'http://filantropi.or.id/acara/d/next-generousion-fest-', 9, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 08:54:28', '2019-09-05 15:54:28', 5, '', 'slider', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'gDLlt4TupSKEhEo', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1186, 'Klaster Filantropi', 'Klaster Filantropi', 'Berbagai Klaster Filantropi yang sudah terbentuk sampai dengan bulan Juli 2019', '<p>Tujuan dari pembentukan Klaster Filantropi ini adalah agar dapat secara intensif mendorong kemitraan antarorganisasi filantropi dan fokus dalam mencari solusi bersama terhadap pemecahan suatu isu.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Kami mengundang organisasi Anda untuk terlibat dan menjadi bagian dari Klaster Filantropi ini sesuai bidang yang diminati (<em>boleh lebih dari satu</em>).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Klaster Lingkungan Hidup dan Konservasi&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Klaster Ketahanan Pangan dan Gizi</li>\n	<li>Klaster Pendidikan</li>\n	<li>Klaster Kesenian dan Kebudayaan</li>\n	<li>Klaster Zakat on SDGs</li>\n	<li>Klaster Pemukiman dan Perkotaan</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Perlu diketahui bahwa:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Masing-masing dari Klaster Filantropi dikoordinasi oleh satu organisasi yang ditunjuk berdasarkan kesepakatan bersama oleh anggota Klaster.</li>\n	<li>Masing-masing dari Klaster Filantropi mempunyai kesepakatan bersama (charta) yang mengatur tentang hak dan kewajiban setiap anggota Klaster dan program yang akan dijalankan.</li>\n	<li>Masing-masing dari Klaster mempunyai agenda pertemuan bulanan untuk membahas segala hal yang berkaitan dengan klaster.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OkIfYP5fggSIuXV_8Wc0l4KPKzdc66UEJIsuLVnnLHI/viewform?edit_requested=true\" target=\"_blank\">Apakah lembaga Anda sudah tergabung?</a></p>\n', '', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 10:20:50', '2019-09-05 17:20:50', 5, 'klaster-filantropi', 'pages', 0, '', 'id', 'statis.php', '', '', '', 'static', '5DrEE6fv5Fkd5wp', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1187, 'Cluster of Filantropi', 'Cluster of Filantropi', 'Various Cluster of Filantropi that have been formed until July 2019', '<p>The purpose of forming this Cluster of Filantropi&nbsp;is to be able to intensively encourage partnerships between philanthropic organizations and focus on finding joint solutions to solving an issue.</p>\n\n<p>We invite your organization to get involved and become part of this Cluster of Filantropi according to the field of interest (<em>maybe more than one</em>).</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Environmental and Conservation</li>\n	<li>Food Security and Nutrition</li>\n	<li>Education</li>\n	<li>Art and Culture</li>\n	<li>Zakat&nbsp;on SDGs</li>\n	<li>Settlement and Urban</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Need to know that:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Each of the Cluster of Filantropi is coordinated by an organization appointed based on mutual agreement by the members.</li>\n	<li>Each of the Cluster of Filantropi&nbsp;has a mutual agreement (charta) governing the rights and obligations of each member and the program to be carried out.</li>\n	<li>Each of the Cluster of Filantropi has a monthly meeting agenda to discuss all matters relating to the cluster.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OkIfYP5fggSIuXV_8Wc0l4KPKzdc66UEJIsuLVnnLHI/viewform?edit_requested=true\" target=\"_blank\">Is your institution have to joined?</a></p>\n', '', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 10:20:50', '2019-09-05 17:20:50', 5, 'cluster-of-filantropi', 'pages', 0, '', 'en', 'statis.php', '', '', '', 'static', '5DrEE6fv5Fkd5wp', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1188, 'Klaster Filantropi', '', 'Berbagai Klaster Filantropi yang sudah terbentuk sampai dengan bulan Juli 2019', '<p>Tujuan dari pembentukan Klaster Filantropi ini adalah agar dapat secara intensif mendorong kemitraan antarorganisasi filantropi dan fokus dalam mencari solusi bersama terhadap pemecahan suatu isu.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Kami mengundang organisasi Anda untuk terlibat dan menjadi bagian dari Klaster Filantropi ini sesuai bidang yang diminati (<em>boleh lebih dari satu</em>).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Klaster Lingkungan Hidup dan Konservasi&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Klaster Ketahanan Pangan dan Gizi</li>\n	<li>Klaster Pendidikan</li>\n	<li>Klaster Kesenian dan Kebudayaan</li>\n	<li>Klaster Zakat on SDGs</li>\n	<li>Klaster Pemukiman dan Perkotaan</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Perlu diketahui bahwa:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Masing-masing dari Klaster Filantropi dikoordinasi oleh satu organisasi yang ditunjuk berdasarkan kesepakatan bersama oleh anggota Klaster.</li>\n	<li>Masing-masing dari Klaster Filantropi mempunyai kesepakatan bersama (charta) yang mengatur tentang hak dan kewajiban setiap anggota Klaster dan program yang akan dijalankan.</li>\n	<li>Masing-masing dari Klaster mempunyai agenda pertemuan bulanan untuk membahas segala hal yang berkaitan dengan klaster.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OkIfYP5fggSIuXV_8Wc0l4KPKzdc66UEJIsuLVnnLHI/viewform?edit_requested=true\" target=\"_blank\">Apakah lembaga Anda sudah tergabung?</a></p>\n', 'eae472cefb215d609f87404bb3775b88.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 10:24:21', '2019-09-05 17:24:21', 5, 'klaster-filantropi', 'about', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'JOsmt9tAfgexI0Z', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1189, 'Cluster of Filantropi', '', 'Various Cluster of Filantropi that have been formed until July 2019', '<p>The purpose of forming this Cluster of Filantropi&nbsp;is to be able to intensively encourage partnerships between philanthropic organizations and focus on finding joint solutions to solving an issue.</p>\n\n<p>We invite your organization to get involved and become part of this Cluster of Filantropi according to the field of interest (<em>maybe more than one</em>).</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Environmental and Conservation</li>\n	<li>Food Security and Nutrition</li>\n	<li>Education</li>\n	<li>Art and Culture</li>\n	<li>Zakat&nbsp;on SDGs</li>\n	<li>Settlement and Urban</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Need to know that:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Each of the Cluster of Filantropi is coordinated by an organization appointed based on mutual agreement by the members.</li>\n	<li>Each of the Cluster of Filantropi&nbsp;has a mutual agreement (charta) governing the rights and obligations of each member and the program to be carried out.</li>\n	<li>Each of the Cluster of Filantropi has a monthly meeting agenda to discuss all matters relating to the cluster.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OkIfYP5fggSIuXV_8Wc0l4KPKzdc66UEJIsuLVnnLHI/viewform?edit_requested=true\" target=\"_blank\">Is your institution have to joined?</a></p>\n', 'eae472cefb215d609f87404bb3775b88.png', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 10:24:21', '2019-09-05 17:24:21', 5, 'cluster-of-filantropi', 'about', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'JOsmt9tAfgexI0Z', 'N', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1192, 'Study Group: Pemanfaatan Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) untuk Sustainability Report Bagi Sektor Filantropi dalam Pencapaian TPB/SDGs', '', 'Filantropi Indonesia dan Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) telah mengadakan study group \"Pemanfaatan Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) untuk Sustainability Report Bagi Sektor Filantropi dalam Pencapaian TPB/SDGs\" sebagai kelanjutan pelatihan sebelumnya pada tanggal 26-27 Juni 2019. Para peserta yang sudah mengirimkan laporan organisasinya yang disesuaikan dengan beberapa indikator GRI yang telah ditentukan, kembali adanya penyesuaian indikator lebih detail. Study group ini dipimpin oleh Ibu Lany Harijanti', '<p>Filantropi Indonesia dan <em>Global Reporting Initiative</em>&nbsp;(GRI) telah mengadakan <em>study group</em>&nbsp;&quot;<em>Pemanfaatan Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) untuk Sustainability Report Bagi Sektor Filantropi dalam Pencapaian TPB/SDGs</em>&quot; sebagai kelanjutan pelatihan sebelumnya pada tanggal 26-27&nbsp;Juni&nbsp;2019. Para peserta yang sudah mengirimkan laporan organisasinya yang disesuaikan dengan beberapa indikator GRI yang telah ditentukan, kembali adanya penyesuaian indikator lebih detail. <em>Study group</em> ini dipimpin oleh Ibu Lany Harijanti</p>\n\n<p>Semenjak tahun 2018, Filantropi Indonesia&nbsp;dan GRI&nbsp;telah berkolaborasi untuk melakukan rangkaian pelatihan <em>Sustainability Reporting</em> (SR) bagi lembaga filantropi. Tujuan dari aktivitas tersebut adalah agar lembaga filantropi dapat menghasilkan laporan yang tidak hanya dapat menunjukkan dampak tapi juga transparansi dan akutanbilitas.</p>\n\n<p>Pada bulan Juni yang lalu, telah diselenggarakan pelatihan penyusunan SR GRI yang diikuti peserta dari anggota Filantropi Indonesia. Selama pelatihan tersebut, semua peserta telah membuat matriks keselarasan antara GRI dengan SDGs untuk organisasinya. Pelatihan tersebut belum selesai, karena masih terdapat kriteria pelaporan yang belum dijabarkan. Menindaklanjuti pelatihan sebelumnya, maka dibuatlah <em>study group</em> tersebut. Peserta yang hadir didorong agar mulai bisa untuk menarasikan standar GRI ke dalam laporan tahunan organisasinya. Narasi laporan tahunan akan lebih menarik jika menonjolkan tampilan data atau angka. Telah disepakati bahwa <em>study group</em> SR GRI akan diadakan secara rutin setiap dua minggu sekali. FI dan GRI membuka kesempatan bagi seluruh anggota FI yang ingin bergabung untuk belajar penyusunan SR GRI.</p>\n', '0948932cb0804461b9cbf0da26d43a9b.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 10:55:52', '2019-09-06 10:44:36', 5, 'study-group-pemanfaatan-global-reporting-initiative-gri-untuk-sustainability-report-bagi-sektor-filantropi-dalam-pencapaian-tpb-sdgs', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'KXQpyJycHObrwOn', 'N', '', '', '2019-08-23 00:00:00', '2019-08-23 23:59:59'),
(1193, 'Study Group: Utilization of the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) for Sustainability Reports for the Philanthropy Sector in Achieving TPB/SDGs', '', 'Indonesian Philanthropy Association (FI) and the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) have held a study group \"Utilizing the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) for Sustainability Reports for the Philanthropic Sector in Achieving TPB / SDGs\" as a continuation of previous training on 26-27 June 2019', '<p>Indonesian Philanthropy Association (FI) and the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) have held a study&nbsp;group &quot;<em>Utilizing the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) for Sustainability Reports for the Philanthropic Sector in Achieving TPB / SDGs</em>&quot; as a continuation of previous training on 26-27 June 2019. Participants who have sent the organization&#39;s report adjusted to several GRI indicators that have been determined, re-adjustment of indicators in more detail. The study group is led by Ms. Lany Harijanti</p>\n\n<p>Since 2018, FI and GRI have collaborated to conduct a series of Sustainability Reporting (SR) training for philanthropic institutions. The aim of the activity is for philanthropic institutions to produce reports that can not only show impact but also transparency and accountability.</p>\n\n<p>Last June, the training of&nbsp;SR GRI preparation was held, which was attended by participants from FI members. During the training, all participants created a matrix of alignment between GRI and SDGs for the organization. The training has not yet been completed, because there are still reporting criteria that have not yet been spelled out. Following up on the previous training, a study group was created. Participants in attendance were encouraged to begin to be able to narrate GRI standards in their organization&#39;s annual reports. The narrative of an annual report will be more interesting if it highlights the display of data or numbers. It has been agreed that the SR GRI study group will be held routinely every two weeks. FI and GRI open opportunities for all FI members who want to join to learn the preparation of SR GRI.</p>\n', '0948932cb0804461b9cbf0da26d43a9b.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 10:55:52', '2019-09-06 10:44:36', 5, 'study-group-utilization-of-the-global-reporting-initiative-gri-for-sustainability-reports-for-the-philanthropy-sector-in-achieving-tpb-sdgs', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'KXQpyJycHObrwOn', 'N', '', '', '2019-08-23 00:00:00', '2019-08-23 23:59:59'),
(1194, 'Pertemuan Awal Pembentukan Klaster Filantropi Kesehatan: Peran Aktif Filantropi untuk Pembangunan Kesehatan di Indonesia', '', 'Mengingat bahwa untuk bidang kesehatan, setiap tahunnya pemerintah hanya menganggarkan 5 persen dari APBN, maka dibutuhkan alternatif sumber daya untuk pembangunan kesehatan nasional, salah satunya membangun kemitraan harus menjadi poin penting. Atas dasar tersebut, Filantropi Indonesia bersama Filantropi Kesehatan dari Pusat Kebijakan dan Manajemen Kesehatan FKKMK UGM menggagas kegiatan “Pertemuan Awal Pembentukan Klaster Filantropi Kesehatan: Peran Aktif Filantropi untuk Pembangunan Kesehatan di Indonesia” pada 26 Agustus 2019, sebagai salah satu penjajakan dan perkenalan Klaster Filantropi Kesehatan', '<p>Pencapaian keseluruhan SDGs termasuk kesehatan membutuhkan sumber daya besar. Mengingat bahwa untuk bidang kesehatan, setiap tahunnya pemerintah hanya menganggarkan 5 persen dari APBN, maka dibutuhkan alternatif sumber daya untuk pembangunan kesehatan nasional, salah satunya membangun kemitraan harus menjadi poin penting. Atas dasar tersebut, Filantropi Indonesia bersama Filantropi Kesehatan dari Pusat Kebijakan dan Manajemen Kesehatan FKKMK UGM menggagas kegiatan &ldquo;<em>Pertemuan Awal Pembentukan Klaster Filantropi Kesehatan: Peran Aktif Filantropi untuk Pembangunan Kesehatan di Indonesia</em>&rdquo; pada 26 Agustus 2019, sebagai salah satu penjajakan dan perkenalan Klaster Filantropi Kesehatan.</p>\n\n<p>Agenda kegiatan termasuk pemaparan hasil riset dari Filantropi Kesehatan, pemetaan kebutuhan klaster berdasarkan pengalaman dan kepentingan tiap peserta yang memiliki program kerja terkait dengan kesehatan serta diskusi strategi filantropi di bidang kesehatan. Pemaparan presentasi oleh Prof. dr. Laksono Trisnantoro, MSc, PhD. selaku Director of Health Policy and Management, FKKMK UGM, menuturkan berdasarkan riset Filantropi Kesehatan yang telah dilakukan hingga tahun 2017, bahwa adanya sejumlah masalah pada pembayaran rumah sakit, dikarenakan <em>cash flow</em> BPJS yang tidak lancar. &ldquo;Pendanaan kesehatan bisa bersumber dari filantropi sehingga dapat membantu langsung pasien dan meringankan biaya investasi rumah sakit sebagai pelengkap dana BPJS dan pemerintah&rdquo;, ujar Prof. Laksono. Sumber dana filantropisme yang berasal dari masyarakat juga terimplementasi dalam kegiatan <em>crowdfunding</em>, dimana telah berkembang di Indonesia oleh beberapa lembaga.</p>\n\n<p>Dilanjutkan dengan pemetaan kebutuhan Klaster Filantropi Kesehatan dari lembaga anggota Filantropi Indonesia yang hadir saat itu, seperti Rumah Zakat, GPDLI, Yayasan Cipta, BAZNAS, Dompet Dhuafa, LAZ Harfa Banten, Peduli Sehat, STF UIN Jakarta, NU Care dan LAZISMU. Adapun kategori pemetaan kebutuhan yang diidentifikasi dan sebagai <em>sharing knowledge</em> antar organisasi yaitu di bidang Peningkatan Kapasitas, Manajemen Pengetahuan dan Advokasi. Masing-masing lembaga diminta untuk memberikan ketertarikan dan kemampuan yang dimiliki sehingga dapat berbagi bahkan menjadi contoh pembelajaran.</p>\n\n<p>Kemudian, diskusi strategi yang dilakukan dalam mendorong kolaborasi antara lembaga filantropi juga dibahas oleh Prof. Laksono melalui pengembangan website software khusus filantropi kesehatan yakni <a href=\"http://www.filantropikesehatan.net\">www.filantropikesehatan.net</a>. &quot;Tak lain, harapannya agar filantropi kesehatan Indonesia dapat seperti Association for Health Philanthropy&quot;, tutup Prof. Laksono.</p>\n', '032dabb7244353c567fc1781ad10f633.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 11:58:16', '2019-09-06 12:21:48', 5, 'pertemuan-awal-pembentukan-klaster-filantropi-kesehatan-peran-aktif-filantropi-untuk-pembangunan-kesehatan-di-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'id', '', '', '', '', '', 'RWfMNEw0OZHD6VV', 'N', '', '', '2019-08-26 00:00:00', '2019-08-26 23:59:59'),
(1195, 'Initial Meeting on the Establishment of the Health Philanthropy Cluster: The Active Role of Philanthropy for Health Development in Indonesia', '', 'Considering that for the health sector, each year the government only allocates 5 percent of the APBN, alternative resources for national health development are needed, one of which is building partnerships must be an important point. On that basis, Indonesian Philanthropy together with Health Philanthropy from the Center for Health Policy and Management, Faculty of Medicine, Public Health and Nursing, Gadjah Mada University (FKKMK UGM) initiated the activity \"Initial Meeting of Health Philanthropy Clusters Formation: The Active Role of Philanthropy for Health Development in Indonesia\" on August 26, 2019, as one of the explorations and introductions of the Health Philanthropy Cluster', '<p>The overall achievement of SDGs including health requires huge resources. Considering that for the health sector, each year the government only allocates 5 percent of the APBN, alternative resources for national health development are needed, one of which is building partnerships must be an important point. On this basis, Indonesian Philanthropy Association together with Health Philanthropy from the Center for Health Policy and Management,&nbsp;Faculty of Medicine, Public Health and Nursing, Gadjah Mada University (FKKMK UGM)&nbsp;initiated the activity &quot;<em>Initial Meeting of the Establishment of Health Philanthropy Clusters: The Active Role of Philanthropy for Health Development in Indonesia</em>&quot; on August 26, 2019, as one of the explorations and introductions of the Health Philanthropy Cluster.</p>\n\n<p>The agenda of activities include the presentation of research results from Health Philanthropy, mapping of cluster needs based on the experience and interests of each participant who has a work program related to health and discussion of philanthropic strategies in the health sector. Presentation of the presentation by Prof. dr. Laksono Trisnantoro, MSc, Ph.D. as Director of Health Policy and Management,&nbsp;FKKMK UGM, said based on Health Philanthropy research that had been conducted until 2017, that there were a number of problems with hospital payments, due to BPJS cash flow that was not paid. &quot;Health funding can come from philanthropy so that it can directly help patients and reduce hospital investment costs as a complement to BPJS and government funds,&quot; said Prof. Laksono Sources of philanthropic funding from the community are also implemented in crowdfunding activities, which have been developed in Indonesia by several institutions.</p>\n\n<p>Followed by mapping the needs of the Health Philanthropy Cluster from Indonesian Philanthropy member institutions present at the time, such as Rumah Zakat, GPDLI, Yayasan Cipta, BAZNAS, Dompet Dhuafa, LAZ Harfa Banten, Peduli Sehat, STF UIN Jakarta, NU Care, and LAZISMU. The category of mapping needs is identified and as knowledge sharing between organizations in the fields of Capacity Building, Knowledge Management and Advocacy. Each institution is asked to provide their interests and abilities so they can share and even become examples of learning.</p>\n\n<p>Then, the strategy discussion carried out in encouraging collaboration between philanthropic institutions was also discussed by Prof. Laksono through the development of a special philanthropic health software website, www.filantropikesehatan.net. He hopes that Indonesian health philanthropy can be like the Association for Health Philanthropy.</p>\n', '032dabb7244353c567fc1781ad10f633.JPG', '', 0, 'Y', 'P', '2019-09-05 11:58:16', '2019-09-06 12:21:48', 5, 'initial-meeting-on-the-establishment-of-the-health-philanthropy-cluster-the-active-role-of-philanthropy-for-health-development-in-indonesia', 'events', 0, '', 'en', '', '', '', '', '', 'RWfMNEw0OZHD6VV', 'N', '', '', '2019-08-26 00:00:00', '2019-08-26 23:59:59');
